name: Everyday Beast Rosemary Grilled Chicken Thighs
description: This healthy chicken recipe simplifies meal prep and keeps you on track to reach your fitness goals. If you're following a low-carb diet to lose weight, or you're looking for more protein to help you build muscle, this is the recipe for you.
recipeIngredient: ['grilled chicken thighs - 5 lb', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'rosemary - 2 oz', 'lemon juice - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and let chicken marinate for 30-60 minutes.
2. Heat two pans on the stove on medium-high heat. Split the butter between the two pans and melt.

name: Everyday Beast Quick Chicken, Bacon, and Collard Green Sauté
description: Fitness success is 80 percent nutrition, which is why this keto-friendly dish uses leftover chicken to make prepping a healthy, delicious meal as quick and easy as possible.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken thighs, slice (boneless and skinless) - 6 oz', 'mushrooms, sliced - 2 cup', 'poblano pepper - 1 cup', 'bacon - 2 slice', 'collard greens - 4 cup, chopped']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a pan on medium heat. Once warm, add bacon. Once the bacon fat renders, add the mushrooms.
2. Once the mushrooms have browned on each side, add the chopped poblano peppers to the pan and cook until peppers soften and begin to brown.
3. Add the chicken thighs to the pan and cook until warmed through.
4. Add the collard greens and cook just until they begin to wilt, 1-2 minutes.
5. Remove sauté from heat and serve.

name: Everyday Beast Grilled Chicken Thighs and Broccoli Saute with Cheddar Mushroom Bake
description: Fitness success is 80 percent nutrition, which is why this keto-friendly dish uses leftover chicken to make prepping a healthy, delicious meal and low-carb side dish as quick and easy as possible.
recipeIngredient: ['grilled chicken thighs - 6 oz', 'broccoli, chopped - 2 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 3 cup', 'unsalted butter - 2 tbsp', 'white cheddar - 2 oz', 'green onion, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the broiler on high.
2. Heat two pans on the stove on medium-high heat. Split the butter between the two pans and melt.
3. Add broccoli to one pan and mushrooms to the other. Cook on medium-high heat, stirring the contents of each pan to ensure even cooking. q
4. Once cooked through, remove mushrooms from heat and transfer to an oven-proof baking dish. Top with cheese and season with salt and pepper. Place in the broiler for 3-5 minutes until cheese on top is melted.
5. While mushrooms are broiling, add cooked chicken thighs to the broccoli, cooking for 3-5 minutes and stirring until heated through. Remove from heat and season with salt and pepper. Serve topped with 1/2 of chopped green onion.
6. Once mushrooms are done, remove from oven and serve topped with remaining half of chopped green onions.

name: Pizza Stuffed Chicken Breast
description: Who doesn't love pizza? But, when your goals say you can't have pizza, you've got to think of something that combines the same awesome flavors in a macro-friendly way.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast, pounded out to 1/4-inch - 3 piece', 'marinara sauce - ½ cup', 'pepperoni - 3 oz', 'black olives, sliced - 3 tbsp', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 3 oz', 'fresh basil leaves - ½ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Butterfly the chicken breast by slicing right down the middle, taking care not to cut all the way through.
2. Place the butterflied breasts between two sheets of parchment paper and hammer the chicken to about a 1/4-inch thickness.
3. Season both sides of the breast with salt and pepper. Spread marinara sauce on one side of the chicken (see Rob's marinara sauce recipe to make your own).
4. Add pepperoni, chopped spinach, olives, and 1 ounce of mozzarella to one side. Sprinkle with chopped basil, then fold other side over. Use toothpicks to hold the two sides together. Top with additional marinara sauce, and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
5. Place chicken breasts in a baking dish and bake for 30-40 minutes at 375 degrees F until chicken is cooked through. Remove the toothpicks before serving.

name: Core Camper Protein Balls
description: You may have tried protein balls before, but these are the ones you'll keep coming back to. Just mix, chill, and enjoy!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¾ cup(s)', 'sugar-free dark chocolate chips - ½ cup', 'raw oats - 2 cup', 'natural creamy peanut butter - 1 cup', 'honey - ¼ cup', 'ground flaxseed - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix together.
2. Form into about 12 golf-ball sized protein balls and place on a plate.
3. Refrigerate until cool, and enjoy!

name: Buddha Bowl
description: Buddha bowls are all the rage, which means they're also very expensive. This version can be made on the cheap, but neither you or your family will have anything but rave reviews!
recipeIngredient: ['kale - ¼ cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'quinoa - ¼ cup', 'low-sodium black beans - ½ cup', 'chickpeas - ½ cup', 'corn kernels - ½ cup kernels', 'salsa - ½ cup', 'avocado - 1']
recipeInstructions:
1. Steam kale and quinoa for about 4 minutes, or follow direction if you buy them together in a steamable bag. Place in a large soup bowl.
2. Add the rest of the ingredients, one at a time, in their own small sections of the bowl or plate. Dump sliced or chunked avocado on top and enjoy!

name: Core Camper Detox Tea
description: Looking for the perfect way to get your water and a whole lot more? Make up a jug of this delicious tea and drink it as often as you want!
recipeIngredient: ['water - 2 gallon', 'ginger root - 6 slices (1" dia)', 'lemon, quartered and thinly sliced - 2', 'roasted dandelion root tea - 2 bag', 'stalk celery - 2 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put water in a large, clean jug with a wide mouth.
2. Slice lemons in fourths and squeeze into water. Put the ginger, tea bags, and celery in the water as well.
3. Put lid on the jug, shake it, and refrigerate for at least an hour before drinking.
4. Try to drink a jug a day for 7 days straight!

name: Ice Cube Tray Snack
description: Looking for a way to get your kids excited about healthy snacks? Get some ice cube trays at the dollar store and give them this delicious lineup!
recipeIngredient: ['grapes - 1 cup', 'low-fat cheddar cheese - ¼ cup, diced', 'turkey breast, white meat - 2 oz', 'strawberries - 2 whole', 'almonds - ¼ cup whole kernels']
recipeInstructions: 1. Arrange all ingredients in individual compartments of the ice cube tray. Serve to your kids, or enjoy it yourself!

name: 100-Calorie Popcorn
description: Popcorn is about as simple and guilt-free a snack as there is, if you make it yourself. Cook up a bag in the microwave and dig in any time!
recipeIngredient: ['100-calorie popcorn - 1 serving']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pour the kernels in a brown paper lunch bag and roll the top so it is loosely closed.
2. Cook on high in the microwave for 90 seconds. Enjoy!

name: Core Camper High-Protein Peanut Butter Cookies
description: Not all protein cookies live up to the billing. These give unbelievable taste plus 9 grams of protein apiece, and can be made in no time flat!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'egg whites - ¼ cup', 'sugar-free dark chocolate chips - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 1 cup', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'organic cane palm sugar - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Add all ingredients except the chocolate chips to a large mixing bowl and stir together for about 30 seconds, until blended.
3. Add dark chocolate chips and continue stirring.
4. Make 12 spoonful-sized balls and put them on a lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten each cookie with a fork.
5. Bake for 10-12 minutes, let cool, and enjoy!

name: Everyday Beast Ribeye
description: You want to eat a good meal, something that you created yourself that tastes good. That's what this ribeye is going to do for you. This dish is so flavorful it's going to fill up your kitchen with aromas you can only dream of.
recipeIngredient: ['ribeye steak - 290 g', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'cream cheese - 1 tbsp', 'heavy whipping cream - 6 tbsp', 'swiss chard - 2 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'parmesan cheese, grated - ¼ cup', 'salt pork - ½ oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Let the ribeye sit out for 10-20 minutes to come to room temperature so when it hits the hot pan it starts cooking right away. Preheat a pan on medium-high heat.
2. Bring water to a boil in your steamer. Place another pan on medium heat and add the chopped bacon to cook and render the fat.
3. Rub olive oil on both sides of the ribeye and season with salt and pepper.
4. Place seasoned ribeye in the preheated pan—you should hear a sizzle when the meat hits the hot surface. Cook for 3-5 minutes on each side to desired doneness. Once cooked, remove the pan from heat and allow the ribeye to rest for about 10 minutes.
5. Once the water is boiling, place swiss chard in steamer basket. Cook 1-2 minutes until softened, then remove from heat and drain.
6. Add mushrooms to the bacon to cook. Once the mushrooms have browned on both sides, add the whipping cream and simmer for a minute before adding the cream cheese. Finally, add the Parmesan cheese and stir to combine as the cheese melts, seasoning with salt and pepper. Once sauce comes together, remove from heat
7. Divide the ribeye and swiss chard between two plates and drizzle with homemade bacon alfredo sauce.

name: Antipasto Salad And Stuffed Mushrooms
description: In Italian, antipasto literally means "before the meal." This recipe, served with a side of tasty stuffed mushrooms, is hearty enough to replace the meal!
recipeIngredient: ['artichoke hearts, cut into quarters - 2', 'arugula, raw - 1 cup', 'mini bell peppers, chopped - 2', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'kalamata olives (pitted) - 1 tbsp', 'chicken breast - 3 oz', 'balsamic vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'mozzarella string cheese - 1 piece', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'crimini mushrooms - 4', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 2 strip', 'Italian seasoning - ¼ tsp', 'garlic salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for salad: In Italian, antipasto literally means "before the meal." This recipe, served with a side of tasty stuffed mushrooms, is hearty enough to replace the meal!
2. Directions for mushrooms: Preheat oven to 350.
3. Remove the stems from the Cremini mushrooms and fill each mushroom with approximately 1/2 tablespoon of yogurt.
4. Wrap each mushroom with a half slice of turkey bacon and secure with a toothpick.
5. Top each mushroom with a dash of Italian seasoning and garlic salt, bake for 10-12 minutes.
6. Serve immediately with antipasto salad.

name: Pizza Rustica
description: I am very excited to share this recipe because it is not only diet-friendly, but it tastes great! I worked very hard to find the perfect crust -- delizioso!
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - ¾ cup', 'water - 1 cup', 'baking soda - 1 tsp', 'granulated Stevia - 1 tbsp', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'ricotta cheese (skim-milk) - ¼ cup', 'mozzarella cheese - 2 tbsp', 'lean ground beef - 4 oz', 'arugula, raw - ¼ cup', 'prosciutto - 2 slice', 'marinara sauce - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for crust: Preheat oven to 400.
2. Bring 1 cup water to boil. Add the grounded steel cut oats and sugar substitute.
3. Reduce heat and cook for 10 minutes, or until the mixture thickens.
4. Remove from heat and allow to cool for 5 minutes.
5. Stir in the baking soda and egg white and flatten onto pre-sprayed pizza pan.
6. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until the crust is lightly browned.
7. Directions for the pizza: Brown the ground beef/turkey in a pan over medium-high heat and set aside.
8. Mix the ricotta and marinara in a small bowl.
9. Top pizza crust with sauce and ricotta mixture, ground meat, arugula, prosciutto, mozzarella and bell peppers.
10. Return to oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
11. Note: The toppings can be modified to fit your dietary needs, but these are my favorite.

name: Chocolate Hazelnut Gelato
description: This recipe is amazing because it converts cottage cheese into a sinfully delightful Italian treat!
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cottage cheese - 1 cup', 'Torani Sugar-Free Hazelnut Syrup - 3 tbsp', 'sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - 1 tbsp', 'chocolate almond milk - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients together until smooth (at least 2-3 minutes)
2. Pour into mini muffin pans.
3. Freeze for one hour.
4. Optional garnish: Chopped chocolate covered almonds.

name: Mini Italian Frittatas
description: This savory breakfast was inspired by Giada de Laurentiis. It is a quick and delicious start to the day!
recipeIngredient: ['egg beaters - 1 cup', 'asparagus - ½ cup', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 4 oz', 'parsley, dried - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a sauce pan, saute asparagus and turkey bacon.
2. Stir together with egg beaters and parsley.
3. Pour mixture into a mini muffin pan and bake at 375 for 8-10 minutes.

name: "Souped Up" Chicken Noodle Soup
description: This variation of the classic favorite is loaded with antioxidants, nutrient-dense, and designed to support your body-composition goals. If you're building muscle, double up the pasta serving for more carbs. If you're on a strict low-carb diet, prepare it without pasta for a leaner option that works with individual goals.
recipeIngredient: ['low-sodium chicken stock - 8 cup', 'water - 4 cup', 'onions - 2 large', 'carrots - 2 large (7-1/4" to 8-/1/2" long)', 'celery, raw - 2 stalk, large (11"-12" long)', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'chicken breast - 3 piece', 'egg noodles - 2 cup', 'cabbage - 1 cup, shredded']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring broth and water to a simmer over medium-high heat in a large pot. Next, add onions, carrots, celery and thyme and continue to simmer for 30 minutes.
2. Add egg noodles with chicken and pasta and simmer uncovered for 8-10 minutes.

name: Pumpkin Hummus
description: Although no single nutrient in pumpkin is a magical performance-boosting bullet, this glorious gourd does contain a synergistic combination of good-for-you gains. You'd be foolish to skimp on such a good source of fiber, B vitamins, vitamin A, and the antioxidant selenium!
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 2 can drained', 'pumpkin, canned - 2 cup', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'tahini paste - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all of the ingredients in a blender or food processor, and blend for 30-60 seconds.
2. Add a small amount of water as necessary to thin to your desired consistency.
3. Serve the hummus as a dip with fresh veggies and pretzels, spread it on sandwiches, or eat it with a spoon!

name: BBQ Chicken Flatbread
description: This recipe is a great choice for the big game, but is also one of my favorites for a stay-at-home Friday night treat. It's simple, quick, and oh-so-good. You'll never have to order a barbecue chicken pizza again!
recipeIngredient: ['Flat Out sandwich wraps - 2 flatbread', 'chicken breast, cut into 1/2-inch strips - 6 oz', 'Walden Farms BBQ Sauce - 4 tbsp', 'arugula, raw - 1 cup', 'red onion, sliced - ½', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 2 oz', 'cilantro - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
2. Place flatbreads on baking sheet and spray with olive oil spray.
3. Spread 2 tbsp BBQ sauce on each flatbread.
4. Layer arugula, caramelized onion, chicken and shredded cheese on each.
5. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until edges are slightly brown.
6. Top with chopped cilantro and enjoy!

name: Sesame Soy Kale Chips
description: Kale is a superfood! I love it in salads, stir fries, green juices and protein smoothies. This recipe makes kale irresistible to even the toughest veggie critic. The chips are crisp, light, and full of flavor. Even better, you won't have to worry if you accidentally devour the whole plate!
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - 3 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'sesame seeds - ½ tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
2. Using your hands, toss kale so every piece is fully coated with olive oil.
3. Lay kale in a single layer on a baking sheet.
4. Bake for 15-20 minutes until lightly crispy.

name: Slow-Cooker Stew
description: If you're on a high-fat diet, the slow cooker is one of your best friends! It can make almost any cut of meat taste good, including those tough cuts of beef like chuck and top round. Here's a super-easy recipe for you to try!
recipeIngredient: ['beef, chuck for stew, cut into cubes - 16 oz', 'bay leaf - 1', 'carrot, chopped - 3', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 3', 'onion, chopped - 1', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'beef stock - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Once everything's in the pot, turn it on low and let it cook for 8-10 hours. If you're in a bit of a hurry, you can probably have everything cooked on high in about 4 hours.

name: Egg-Salad-Filled Endive Cups
description: These yummy snacks are the perfect low-carb finger food! They're full of healthy fats, protein, and delicious creamy flavor!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites, hardboiled - 6', 'endive - 1 head', 'avocado - 1', 'hot sauce - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'paprika - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, combine egg whites, avocado, hot sauce, and salt and pepper.
2. Mash together with a fork.
3. Fill endive cups with egg salad filling.
4. Sprinkle paprika on top and enjoy!

name: Baked Yam Fries
description: Everyone loves fries! Add them to your Super Bowl menu or implement them into your everyday lean diet. For new flavors, try experimenting with herbs and spices like rosemary and garlic, cayenne pepper and paprika, or even cinnamon and Stevia for a sweet treat!
recipeIngredient: ['yams, sliced into strips - 1 cup, cubes', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
2. Wash, peel and slice yam into strips.
3. In a large Ziplock bag, add yam fries, coconut oil, and any other spices.
4. Shake until all fries are coated evenly.
5. Lay fries on baking sheet in a single layer.
6. Bake for 15 minutes, or until edges are slightly brown.

name: Pumpkin Protein Pancakes
description: Looking for your own, tasty protein-pancake recipe? Check out the recipe below for a treat that's sure to please. Looking for an additional boost in muscle-building calories? Try making two medium-sized pancakes and stuffing them with peanut butter and banana!
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, French Vanilla Creme - 1 scoop', 'pumpkin puree - 2 tbsp', 'almond flour - 2 tbsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'baking powder - ¼ tbsp', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - ¼ tsp', 'granulated Stevia -  to taste']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend all ingredients, and cook as you would a traditional pancake!

name: Creamy Chocolate Super Soy Smoothie
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['unsweetened soy milk - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'banana - ½ medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'avocado - ¼', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'granulated Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Dark Chocolate Hemp Heaven
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['hemp milk - ½ cup', 'pea protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'banana - 1', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Banana Almond Cream Shake (Vegetarian-Friendly)
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice protein powder, vanilla - ½ scoop', 'pea protein powder - ½ scoop(s)', 'banana - 1', 'almond milk - 1 cup', 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Cinnamon Cashew Delight
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'cashews, chopped - ½ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'water - 1 cup', 'cashew milk - 1 cup', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Strawberry Banana G.O.A.T.
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['goat milk - 1 cup', 'unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'banana - 1', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Omega-3 Balsamic Vinaigrette
description: Whether on a spoon or in your morning coffee or smoothie, liquid omega-3s are sure to go down smoothly. They can even be added to savory treats like this simple salad dressing.
recipeIngredient: ['extra virgin olive oil - 6 tbsp', 'liquid omegas - 2 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ cup', 'red wine vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, whisk the ingredients together.
2. Enjoy atop your favorite salad!

name: Coconut Protein Pina Colada
description: Ol' Bessie the cow was once queen of the dairy aisle, but today she's got plenty of company. When your smoothie screams for a splash of creamy goodness, you've got options. No matter the reason you're avoiding dairy, there's a milk for you.
recipeIngredient: ['pineapple, raw - ½ cup', 'banana, frozen - ½', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'unsweetened coconut milk - ½ cup', 'ice - ¼ cup', 'water - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Add all ingredients to a blender, mix, and serve.

name: Ground Turkey And Sweet Potato Hash
description: Too often, people lock into the mindset that they can only have "breakfast foods" upon waking, but having egg whites every morning, month after month, would become boring. Don't be afraid to include other lean proteins and whole-grain carbohydrates.
recipeIngredient: ['93% lean ground turkey - 5 oz', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 1', 'green bell pepper - ½ medium (approx 2-3/4" long, 2-1/2" dia)', 'onion, chopped - ¼', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'garlic powder - ¼ tsp', 'red pepper - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Poke holes in sweet potato with a fork. Microwave for 5 minutes.
2. Dice bell pepper, onion, and garlic. Store remainder in fridge for a future meal.
3. Cook ground turkey in a separate skillet. This dish works if you already have turkey cooked ahead of time too.
4. Using a nonstick frying pan, begin to sauté vegetables on medium-high heat.
5. Add salt, garlic powder, and red pepper to taste.
6. Once sweet potato is finished cooking, allow to cool for 2 minutes before handling.
7. Upon cooling, dice sweet potato into small cubes. Add to frying pan.
8. Continue to sauté ingredients until vegetables are tender.
9. Incorporate ground turkey and mix until thoroughly heated.
10. Transfer ingredients to plate, top with salsa, and enjoy!

name: Breakfast Club Sandwich
description: Too often, people lock into the mindset that they can only have "breakfast foods" upon waking, but having egg whites every morning, month after month, would become boring. Don't be afraid to include other lean proteins and whole-grain carbohydrates.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-grain bread - 2 slice regular', 'low-fat deli turkey - 4 oz (1 serving)', 'pepper jack cheese - 1 oz (slice)', 'avocado - ½', 'tomatoes - 1 slice, medium (1/4" thick)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Layer turkey slices atop bread, splitting slices evenly between each piece.
2. Layer one piece of bread with pepper jack cheese.
3. Place in toaster oven and cook to desired texture and doneness.
4. Top with avocado and tomato. Complete sandwich, cut in half, and enjoy!

name: Parmesan-Crusted Baked Cod
description: Serve up a fresh flavor your family is sure to love with this easy-to-make recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['cod atlantic - 16 oz', 'whole-wheat flour - ¼ cup', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'egg - 1', 'egg whites - 2', 'whole-wheat panko bread crumbs - ⅔ cup', 'parmesan cheese, grated - ¼ cup', 'oregano - ½ tsp, ground', 'basil, dried - ½ tsp, ground', 'thyme - ¼ tsp, ground', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with foil, and place a wire cooling rack on top of it. Place the prepared baking sheet in the oven to preheat.
2. Pat the fillets dry with a paper towel and season them with salt and black pepper.
3. In a shallow dish, stir together the flour, salt, and black pepper.
4. In a second shallow dish, whisk together the egg and egg whites.
5. In a third shallow dish, stir together the panko, parmesan cheese, dried oregano, basil, and thyme.
6. Dredge each fillet in the flour, shaking off any excess. Dip the fillet in the egg wash, allowing the excess to drip off.
7. Gently press the fillet into the breadcrumbs.
8. Spray the tops generously with cooking spray.
9. Carefully remove the preheated baking sheet, and place each fillet sprayed-side down on the cooling rack. Spray the other side with cooking spray.
10. Bake for 16-18 minutes, or until just cooked through.
11. Pro tip: Use a meat thermometer to make sure your fish has reached an internal temperature of 145 degrees F before plating, to guarantee that it's done.

name: PB & Berry Protein Oats
description: These make-ahead gussied-up oats are ready to help you recover the minute your workout comes to a halt. Soaking the oats removes the need to cook them, making this recipe a great option for transporting with you if you're going to be away from the kitchen after exercise and you don't want to delay refueling. The recipe can also be easily altered if you're dairy-free, gluten-free, vegan, or vegetarian.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'chia seeds - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'low-fat milk - ⅔ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'raspberries - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a wide-mouth half-pint glass jar, layer in oats, protein powder, chia seeds, and cinnamon.
2. Stir in milk and vanilla if using.
3. Top with peanut butter and raspberries.
4. Seal shut and chill for two or more hours or up to three days.

name: Firehouse Chili
description: If you're in the mood for something spicy yet packed with protein, check out this healthy variation on a firehouse classic!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1½ lb', 'onions - 1 cup, chopped', 'green bell pepper, chopped - 1', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'turmeric - 1 tsp', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'low-sodium black beans - 15 oz', 'diced tomatoes - 15 oz', 'low-sodium beef broth - 1 can 14.5 oz', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a pan, cook the buffalo, green pepper, onions, garlic for 5-6 minutes, or until just before meat is completely browned.
2. Transfer everything in a big casserole dish.
3. Add chili powder, turmeric, oregano, beans, tomatoes, broth, salt and pepper.
4. Bring to a boil.
5. Reduce heat and stir for 20 minutes until chili reaches wanted thickness.

name: White Chocolate Almond Protein Bars
description: Don't waste time in the grocery store aisle deciding between chewy and crunchy granola bars. Bake up some protein-infused bars in your own kitchen!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'coconut flour - 2 tbsp', 'almonds, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'ground almonds - 3 tbsp', 'vanilla pods - ½ tsp', 'white chocolate, melted - 2 oz', 'dark chocolate - 1 square']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together all of your filling ingredients. Mix until you get a dough that's the right consistency—you should be able to mold it with your hands. If your mixture is too wet to allow you to mold it, add a bit more ground almonds until it becomes more solid.
2. Shape four small bars (or rectangles) out of your mix. Place them on a tray lined with baking paper.
3. Melt the white chocolate in a bain marie (a glass bowl on top of a pot of boiling water). If your chocolate is sticking too much and isn't melting properly, add a tiny bit of coconut oil to help it along.
4. Once your chocolate has melted, pour some of it on top of the bars. Then turn them around and pour more of the chocolate on the other side.
5. To decorate the bars, you can add a few layers of melted dark chocolate and more chopped nuts. Use your imagination. You can make some zebra-striped bars like I did, or let your imagination run wild.

name: Dr. Sara Solomon's Protein Fudge
description: Even the healthiest eaters need a tantalizing treat now and then. These little fudge cheats provide the best of both worlds—taste and nutrition. Try them today!
recipeIngredient: ['coconut butter - 4 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 4 tbsp', 'peanut butter whey protein - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place 4 tbsp of coconut butter in a Magic Bullet.
2. Microwave for 20 seconds to melt the butter.
3. Add 4 tbsp almond milk to Magic Bullet.
4. Add 1 scoop protein powder to Magic Bullet.
5. Blend mixture in Magic Bullet until well combined.
6. Pour mixture into a plastic-lined Tupperware container, distribute evenly.
7. Place container in the freezer for about 5-10 minutes.
8. Check fudge for hardness.
9. Remove fudge from container by pulling up on the plastic lining.
10. Take fudge out of lining and place on plate.
11. Cut block into one-inch squares.
12. Stuff your face.
13. Note: The catch to this recipe is that it will melt if you leave it out on the counter. So make sure you put whatever you don't eat back into the fridge!

name: Fully Loaded Sweet Potato Salad
description: Being from Texas, me showing up to a picnic or cookout without some form of potato salad is like showing up to the gym without headphones—it's a necessary tool to get you in the proper mood. Here's my #FitMenCook take on a Southern classic that will leave your taste buds screaming and your muscles pumped. Seriously: You'll grow after eating this.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato, cut into cubes - 450 g', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 3 strip', '2% greek yogurt, plain - ¾ cup', 'low-sodium black beans - ½ cup', 'kale - ⅓ cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'corn - ½ cup', 'green onion, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'goat cheese - 1 oz', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 1 oz', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 350F.
2. Cut sweet potatoes into small quarter-sized chunks and place on a baking sheet. Lightly spray with coconut oil and sprinkle with sea salt and pepper.
3. Bake in the oven for about 25 minutes or until the chunks are soft, yet slightly firm. Remove and allow to cool for about 10 minutes on a rack.
4. Cook turkey bacon in a skillet and then cut it into small pieces.
5. In a large bowl, add all of the ingredients listed. Mix everything together using a spatula, and serve immediately. This dish can be served warm or cold.

name: Chocolate Protein Cheesecake Popsicles
description: If there's any room left for dessert—and, believe me, you'll want there to be—whip out these chocolate cheesecake pops. You really can't go wrong with cheesecake, especially when it contains protein and chocolate. These frozen treats are perfect to help you beat the heat and cool down from working on the grill. Sit back and enjoy!
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'fat-free cream cheese - 8 oz', 'almond milk - ⅓ cup', '2% greek yogurt, plain - ⅓ cup', 'graham crackers, crushed - ¼ cup', 'ground flaxseed - ¼ cup', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, add graham cracker crumbs, milled flax seed, and coconut oil. Mix well until it begins to stick together. Set aside.
2. In a food processor or blender, mix protein powder, cream cheese, almond milk, and Greek yogurt.
3. Pour the cheesecake mixture into the individual Dixie cups, leaving about 3/4 of an inch at the top for the crust.
4. Pack the graham cracker crumbs onto the top of the Dixie cups and pat down so it sticks to the cheesecake batter and is compact.
5. Slide a Popsicle stick through the middle of the Dixie cup.
6. Freeze cups for at least 5 hours. For better results, freeze overnight before your picnic.
7. Enjoy!

name: Amino Vitamin Water
description:
When the outside temperature starts to creep into triple-digits, hydration is paramount. Make sure you have something to quench your thirst and wash down your four-course meal!

Kick classic water up a notch by adding your favorite aminos and fresh fruit into the mix. You'll stay hydrated while feeding your muscles with natural vitamins, minerals, and amino acids.
recipeIngredient: ['BCAA powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'mint leaves, chopped - 1 cup', 'blood orange - 3', 'blueberries - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add room-temperature water to a large Mason jar or glass container. Remember to leave enough room to add fruit.
2. Mix in your favorite BCAA powder until it's completely dissolved. If your BCAA powder tends to be sweet, add just 1 scoop so you don't overpower the fresh, natural flavors of the fruit.
3. Slice blood oranges into horizontal pieces and add to the jar. Add in fresh blueberries and, finally, the mint. Stir with a wooden spoon.
4. Let the water sit for at least 30 minutes so it becomes infused, then add ice to the jar.
5. Serve immediately! While you can eat the fruit, I don't recommend eating it after more than 24 hours or if the water jug becomes too warm.

name: Spicy Tex-Mex Lime Chicken Kabobs
description: Add a little Tex-Mex flair to the barbecue with this easy chicken kabob recipe that's sure to impress. Just make sure you have enough on hand—these highly addictive skewers are sure to leave your guests coming back for more.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast, cut into 1-inch pieces - 30 oz', 'red hot sauce - 3 tbsp', 'cumin - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - ½ tbsp, ground', 'cayenne powder - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice raw chicken breasts horizontally into 2-3 oz pieces.
2. In a sealable bag, add chicken breast and seasonings. Release the air from the bag, re-seal, and shake, ensuring all the chicken pieces are thoroughly covered in the sauce. Marinate in the refrigerator for at least two hours (or overnight, if desired).
3. Place wooden skewers in water for at least 30 minutes. This will prevent them from burning in case you're cooking the chicken on the grill or in the oven.
4. Remove the chicken pieces from the bag and skewer them with the wooden sticks.
5. For cooking on a stovetop grill or with a skillet, set the fire on medium heat and lightly spray your pan with coconut oil. Wait for the pan to heat before adding the chicken skewers.
6. Add the chicken skewers to the pan and cook, rotating them so all sides are cooked evenly with noticeable grill marks. Don't cover them while they cook.
7. Remove the cooked skewers from the grill. Sprinkle with lime juice and freshly chopped cilantro. Serve immediately.

name: Arugula, Watermelon, Feta And Kind Bar Salad
description:
Every good meal should be kicked off with salad. Salad brings color and nutrients to the table and whets your palate for dishes to come. With that said, salads don't have to be wimpy! This power-packed salad is good enough to be a standalone dish.

One of my new favorite ways to spice up salads is to add crushed KIND Strong & Kind bars to the mix. The all-natural ingredients and whole nuts and grains make for a fantastic topping, and the bars are an easy ingredient to boost the content of healthy fats and protein, like croutons with added nutritional value.

Plus, funky flavors like honey mustard create a flavor explosion in your mouth. Toss them with fresh summer fruit like watermelon, add some feta cheese, and you create a salad that's sure to be a hit!
recipeIngredient: ['arugula, raw - 5 cup', 'KIND Strong & Kind Bars - 3 bar', 'watermelon - 3 cup, diced', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Break your favorite Strong & Kind bar into pieces. You can do this one of two ways: get them cold in the fridge, slip them into a Ziploc bag, and hammer them, or simply break the bar into pieces using your hands. Set your "croutons" aside.
2. Dice watermelon into cube-sized pieces.
3. Pack for a picnic: Place the individual ingredients in separate compartments and assemble each salad individually to avoid making the arugula soggy.

name: Big Blue
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'frozen blueberries - 2 cup', 'avocado - 1', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'banana, frozen - 1', 'milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add liquids to the blender.
2. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Tropical Protein Paradise
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1½ cup', 'nonfat milk - 1 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'banana, frozen - 2', 'frozen pineapple - 1 cup', 'extra virgin coconut oil - ½ tbsp', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add oats to blender and blend until powdered.
2. Add liquids to the blender and blend until incorporated.
3. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Creamy Chocolado
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 1', 'chocolate protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'banana, frozen - 2', '2% greek yogurt, plain - ½ cup', 'milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add liquids to the blender.
2. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Sweet Orange Dream
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'carrots, shredded - ½ cup', 'frozen pineapple - 2 cup', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 cup', 'nonfat milk - 1 cup', 'banana, frozen - 1', 'honey - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add liquids to the blender.
2. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Beastly Berry Blast
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1½ cup', 'nonfat milk - 1 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'strawberries, frozen - 1 cup', 'frozen blueberries - 1 cup', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add oats to blender and blend until powdered.
2. Add liquids to the blender and blend until incorporated.
3. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Choconut Peanut Butter Dream
description: Leave your smaller, former self behind with hard training and this simple, delicious shake!
recipeIngredient: ['2% greek yogurt, plain - ½ cup', 'milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'chocolate protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'banana, frozen - 2', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add liquids to the blender.
2. Add remaining ingredients and blend on high for 30-60 seconds.

name: Protein Pow Protein Pancakes
description: Protein Pow pancake recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 1 scoop', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'pea protein powder - ⅛ cup(s)', 'coconut, flaked - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'baking soda - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients together.
2. Spray a nonstick pan with coconut flour, PAM, or low-calorie spray.
3. Turn your heat to medium/high.
4. Once the pan is sizzling hot, pour your batter on it. Then turn the heat back to medium/low to make sure the pancakes cook through without burning.
5. Flip once bubbles start to appear on the pancake's surface, flip again, and then boom: ready!

name: Two-Ingredient Pancakes
description: A fantastic protein pancake recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 2 large', 'banana - 1 medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'egg - 1 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mash the banana and crack the eggs in it, stirring until the mixture becomes somewhat homogenized.
2. Heat a greased griddle or frying pan on medium heat and pour about a 2.5-inch wide puddle of batter.
3. Delicately flip the pancake after about 25 seconds or when it browns. The recipe makes 3-4 small pancakes.

name: Baked Kale With Peanut Green Tea Dressing
description: Vegetarian bodybuilders can find a wide variety of protein sources and green leafy vegetables at the farmer's market. Kale makes an absolutely mouth-watering treat when it's baked and topped with a delicious dressing. Stop chomping your Caesar salad; try this sweet and savory recipe instead!
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - 4 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'green tea - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for kale: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Spread kale on greased cookie sheet.
3. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
4. Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until slightly crispy.
5. Remove from cookie sheet and top with dressing.
6. Directions for dressing: Combine yogurt, peanut butter and green tea in a blender.
7. Mix until well combined.
8. Pour mixture in small bowl and chill until serving time.

name: Sweet 'n Spicy Gazpacho With Shrimp
description: Enjoy fresh ingredients in a soup. This festive and healthy gazpacho recipe is a refreshing summer treat!
recipeIngredient: ['diced tomatoes - 1', 'cucumber, chopped - 1', 'red wine vinegar - ¼ cup', 'water - ¼ cup', 'apple, diced - ½', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'red chili flakes - 1 tsp', 'shrimp - 3 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all the ingredients, except the shrimp, in a blender and puree until smooth.
2. Top the mixture with shrimp and serve immediately.

name: Kefir Pancakes
description: A great protein pancake recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['all-purpose flour - 1 cup', 'oat flour - 1 cup', 'baking soda - 1½ tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'low-fat Kefir, plain - 2 cup', 'skim milk - 1 cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'Peanut butter, smooth, reduced fat - 3 tablespoon', 'blueberries - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, mix flour, oat flour, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine together the kefir, milk, vanilla extract and eggs; beat until well-blended. Next, add the dry mixture to the wet mixture until a moist batter has formed.
2. Pre-heat a skillet on medium heat and spray with non-stick cooking spray. Drop the batter onto the skillet by large tablespoon and cook for 1-2 minutes before flipping and cooking for another minute or two on the second side. Continue until all pancakes are completed.
3. Place the natural peanut butter in the microwave for 20-30 seconds to soften and then drizzle over pancakes; top pancakes with the fresh berries.

name: Basic Protein Pancakes
description: It's time to take back breakfast with this healthy protein pancake recipes
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ¼ cup', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ¼ cup', 'banana or vanilla protein powder - ½ scoop(s)', 'egg whites - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all the ingredients until a batter forms. Pour over a hot griddle.
2. Flip when the edges start browning.
3. Serve with a tablespoon of natural peanut butter and top with almonds.

name: Blueberry Pancakes
description: A blueberry with protein pancake recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6 large', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'table salt - 1 dash', 'granulated Stevia - 2 tsp', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put egg whites, oats, baking powder, almond milk, salt, and Stevia in the blender.
2. Blend for 30 seconds on med-high speed.
3. Spray a pan with non-stick cooking spray, pour batter on pan, and add half the blueberries.
4. Cook like a regular pancake.
5. For topping, add applesauce and cinnamon.

name: Fitmencook Lean Pro8, Blueberry Pancakes
description: Here's a great pancake recipe packed with extra protein!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - ½ cup', 'banana - ½ small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'Lean Pro 8 protein - 1 scoop', 'oatmeal, cooked - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mash the banana and crack the eggs in it, stirring until the mixture becomes somewhat homogenized.
2. Heat a greased griddle or frying pan on medium heat and pour about a 2.5-inch wide puddle of batter.
3. Delicately flip the pancake after about 25 seconds or when it browns. The recipe makes 3-4 small pancakes.

name: Strawberry Salsa
description: Grab fresh ingredients for homemade salsa. Add fruit, like strawberries, to jazz up that everyday chicken dish!
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries, sliced - 2 cup', 'onion, diced - 1 cup, chopped', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'diced tomatoes - 1', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'garlic, minced - 2 tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tbsp', 'granulated Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'water - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl, stir.
2. Cover and chill until serving time.

name: Sweet Potato Deviled Eggs
description: From the White Batus to the Purple Japanese, sweet potato varieties are abundant at farmer's markets. Discover your favorite and try this amazing, fat-free deviled egg recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['hard-boiled egg - 4', 'sweet potato, mashed - ¼ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'cinnamon - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise and discard the yolks.
2. Combine the sweet potato and Greek yogurt in a small bowl and mix well.
3. Spoon the sweet potato filling into egg whites.
4. Sprinkle tops with cinnamon.
5. Cover and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

name: Beet Pancakes
description: Beets are one of nature's super foods; they're rich in fiber, antioxidants and folic acids. Try some fresh beets in your pancakes for some fun flavor and color!
recipeIngredient: ['beets, cut into cubes - ½ cup', 'oat bran - ¼ cup', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'egg whites - 3', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all the ingredients into a blender and puree until well mixed.
2. Pour the mixture onto a greased griddle or pan over medium heat until bubbles form on the surface, then turn over and cook until dark golden brown.
3. Serve with sugar-free syrup.

name: Key Lime Pie Post JYM Delight
description: This shake uses a coconut-almond milk combination for taste and texture, but feel free to use regular milk if it's more convenient. The addition of spinach is unique and also adds a good boost of micronutrients.
recipeIngredient: ['Post JYM, Natural Lemon Lime - 1 scoop', 'water - ¼ cup', 'Pro JYM, Tahitian Vanilla Bean - 1 scoop', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'angel food cake - 1 slice', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'unsweetened coconut almond milk blend - 1 cup', 'ice - 1 cup', 'baby spinach - 20 g']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine all ingredients into a blender, blend until smooth, and top with a dollop of whipped cream.

name: Rainbow Post JYM Fruity Fusion
description: Post-workout is the one time of day that eating Froot Loops will actually help you, as the sugar will help raise insulin in the body and drive more protein into the muscle. The marshmallow fluff (one of my favorites) adds great flavor and texture to the shake.
recipeIngredient: ['Post JYM, Rainbow Sherbet - 1 scoop', 'Pro JYM, Tahitian Vanilla Bean - 1 scoop', 'water - ¼ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'froot loops cereal - 30 g', 'marshmallow fluff - 2 tbsp', 'ice - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine all ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth. Enjoy with an Ice Cream Pro JYM Doughnut.

name: Cherry Lemonade Post JYM Blast
description: After a hard training session is one of the few times you can get away with having some juice (cherry, in this case) and not have to worry about the sugar content. That said, the carbs in this recipe are a little high, so if you're in a get-lean phase, you can cut the amount of juice and lemon ice in half.
recipeIngredient: ['Post JYM, Lemonade - 1 scoop', 'Pro JYM, Tahitian Vanilla Bean - 1 scoop', 'water - ¼ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 150 g', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ½ cup', 'frozen Italian Lemon Ice - 6 oz', 'concentrated cherry juice - 2 oz', 'ice - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine all ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth.

name: Tropical Post JYM Paradise
description: In this post-workout shake, your carbs are coming mostly from fruit (cantaloupe), complemented by fruit-flavored Post JYM (Mandarin Orange) and Pro JYM (Banana Cream Pie). I normally wouldn't recommend taking in fat post-workout because it could slow down absorption of nutrients, but the coconut here adds only a modest amount of fat.
recipeIngredient: ['Post JYM, Mandarin Orange - 1 g', 'Pro JYM, Banana Cream Pie - 1 scoop', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'unsweetened coconut almond milk blend - ¾ cup', 'cantaloupe - 400 g', 'water - ¼ cup', 'ice - 1 cup', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 8 g']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine all ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth.

name: Muscle Milk Frozen Cheesecake Cups
description: No need to head to the Factory. Save calories and cash by making your own cheesecake cups with minimal prep work! This recipe makes six cheesecake cups.
recipeIngredient: ['jello sugar-free cheesecake mix - 6 oz', 'granulated Stevia - 4 tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup', 'Muscle Milk Complete Whey, Graham Cracker - 2 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients until batter reaches a thick consistency.
2. Place cupcake wrappers into cupcake baking tray and pour batter about half way in each.
3. Freeze for 1-2 hours.
4. Top with peanut butter or almond butter. Enjoy!

name: The College Boy
description: I call this the "College Boy" because of its simple preparation. No chopping, dicing, slicing, or any real work is needed. You need only be able to use a can opener and get the top off the jar, and several hours later you will end up with some high-quality belly stuffing.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 4 piece', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 16 oz can', 'corn - 1 15 oz can', 'cream cheese - 8 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place chicken breasts in the Crock-Pot. They can still be frozen if that is your style.
2. Drain cans of black beans and corn and add them into the cauldron.
3. Top it with your salsa, stir it up, and let it go!
4. Slow cook for 7-8 hours on low, or 4-5 hours on high.
5. Save cream cheese until the food is nearly done; let it melt on top prior to serving.

name: Red Velvet Protein Pudding
description: For added muscle-building power—and a new take on dessert—opt for protein pudding. This rich recipe can fit into your macros and works as a finish to a dinner party. Your friends will never know the difference!
recipeIngredient: ['Muscle Milk protein powder, Red Velvet Cake - 1 scoop', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'dark chocolate - 1 square', 'olive oil - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, combine protein powder and liquid egg whites.
2. Whisk well with a fork until ingredients are slightly runny. Add a splash of water, if needed. Set aside.
3. In a separate dish, melt dark chocolate squares in the microwave for 90 seconds or until fully melted. Do not overcook.
4. Remove chocolate from the microwave and add olive oil. Whip with a fork and drizzle over pudding.
5. Chill and enjoy!

name: Favorite Morning Smoothie
description: Sometimes, nothing starts a day off better than a fruit-filled smoothie. Add a protein base and blend for a delicious, nutritious, muscle-making shake!
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries, frozen - 3', 'frozen blueberries - ½ cup', 'banana - 1', 'coconut milk - 8 oz', 'low-sugar granola - ¾ cup', 'Muscle Milk Complete Whey, Graham Cracker - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients together.
2. Drink!

name: Oatmeal Banana Nut Protein Cookie
description: If you thought about tossing out your overripe bananas, think again. Make the most of that dose of potassium by adding it to protein-cookie batter! Customize your cookie with anything from almond slivers to chocolate chips and raisins. Eat these warm or refrigerate for a delicious, chilled treat.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, mashed - 2', 'quick oats - 1 cup', 'sea salt - ⅛ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'Muscle Milk protein powder, Vanilla Creme - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 F.
2. Lightly spray a cookie sheet with olive or coconut oil. Evenly distribute the spray with a napkin or paper towel.
3. In a large bowl, mash bananas until creamy. Add oats, protein, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, and any additional ingredients of your choice. Mix well.
4. Plop mounded spoonfuls of the mixture onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle with almond slivers.
5. Bake for 15 minutes.
6. Eat and enjoy!

name: Muscle Milk Protein Brownies
description: This recipe began as a challenge: Try to create something exceptional with limited ingredients. I wanted to capture the best "health benefits" a brownie could bring while still giving the bakery a run for its money. I've tried many variations and protein flavors, but never achieved the richness and texture a true brownie brings.
recipeIngredient: ['Muscle Milk protein powder, Natural Chocolate - 1 scoop', 'Muscle Milk Complete Whey, Cocoa Bean - ½ scoop', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'water - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - ⅛ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a microwave safe bowl.
2. Stir in small amounts of water until you reach a brownie-batter consistency.
3. Microwave for one minute, check and stir, then microwave again for 30 seconds to 1 minute. Microwaves vary, so be careful not to overcook. You want a brownie texture—soft and gooey!

name: Everyday Beast Roasted Tomato Marinara Sauce
description: This quick and easy roasted tomato marinara sauce gives you the confidence of knowing exactly what you're putting in your body. From fats and carbs to sodium and added sugars, this recipe gives you 100 percent control over your diet.
recipeIngredient: ['fresh basil - 1 cup leaves, whole', 'plum tomato, finely chopped - 12 whole', 'garlic, minced - 8 clove', 'olive oil - 4 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise.
3. Place cut tomatoes in a large roasting pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Add smashed garlic cloves. Toss to coat.

name: Chipotle Tomato Jam
description: Chipotle peppers are smoked and dried red jalapeños. They are often packed with a flavorful tomato sauce called adobo that brings a smoky heat to recipes. This punchy chipotle-infused tomato sauce makes an exciting topping for chicken, eggs, tacos, and burgers.
recipeIngredient: ['tomatoes - 6', 'sugar - 2 tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce - 2', 'Worcestershire sauce - 1 tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a sharp knife, slice a shallow X into the bottom of each tomato. Fill a medium-sized saucepan about halfway with water and bring to a boil. Drop tomatoes into the boiling water for 1 minute, then remove with a slotted spoon. When cool enough to handle, peel back the skin from the tomatoes, slice each in half, scoop out the seeds, and finely chop.
2. Mix together tomatoes and sugar in the saucepan. Let stand for 10 minutes. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often. Stir in apple cider vinegar, chipotle chili pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and black pepper. Simmer until thickened, about 10 minutes.

name: Mayan Chocolate Fudge Smoothie
description: A touch of cayenne gives this smoothie some surprising kick, while avocado makes each mouthful deliciously thick. The drink has a winning mix of protein, carbs, and fats to help your body mend after a spirited workout.
recipeIngredient: ['skim milk - 1 cup', 'avocado - ½', 'chocolate protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'cayenne powder - ⅛ tsp', 'banana, frozen - 1']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender container in the order listed and blend until smooth. If the mixture is too thick, blend in additional milk.

name: Asparagus Gazpacho
description: Spring's quintessential vegetable is a great stand-in for tomatoes in this version of the iconic cold Spanish soup. Blending in jalapeño adds a kick to each spoonful. Serve for lunch or dinner, and consider making the gazpacho a day or two in advance, as the flavors only get better when left lingering in the fridge. Garnish options include pumpkin seeds, feta, chopped chives, and shaved parmesan.
recipeIngredient: ['asparagus, woody ends trimmed - 1 bunch', 'low-sodium vegetable broth - ½ cup', 'green bell pepper, chopped - 1', 'cucumber, chopped - ½', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 2', 'scallions, sliced - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add asparagus and blanch for 1 minute or until bright green and slightly tender. Drain and transfer asparagus to a bowl of ice water to cool. Drain asparagus when thoroughly cooled.
2. Place broth or water, asparagus, green pepper, cucumber, basil, jalapeño, scallions, garlic, lemon zest, white wine vinegar, salt, cumin, and black pepper in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. With the blender on low, slowly add the olive oil. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
3. Garnish options include pumpkin seeds, feta, chopped chives, and shaved parmesan.

name: Everyday Beast Grilled Salmon Burger
description: This quick and easy pre-workout salmon burger has everything you need to grow: 35 grams of protein, healthy Omega-3 fats, and complex carbs. No matter what your goal is, you need all three to build, recover, and repair.
recipeIngredient: ['wild salmon - 16 oz', 'whole-wheat panko bread crumbs - ½ cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 30 g', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 3 serving']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the grill or warm a grill pan on medium-high heat on the stove.
2. Place the salmon in a food processor and pulse to chop to a consistency of ground chicken or ground beef. Do not blend the salmon or it will end up as a paste.
3. Scoop the salmon into a large bowl and add the panko bread crumbs, grated parmesan, and olive oil. Mix to combine.
4. Divide the mixture into three even portions and form into patties. Season with salt and pepper and place on grill. Cook 3-4 minutes per side, making sure the salmon is golden brown before you flip it over.
5. To make the burgers, open a multigrain bun and layer the bottom half with Dijon mustard, arugula, cooked salmon patty, onion, and tomato. Top with additional arugula and mustard before covering with top half of bun.

name: Cranberry-Almond Oatmeal
description: Harness the power of proper nutrition to build muscle without gaining fat. The Macro Manager shows you how.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'dried cranberries - 3 tbsp', 'almonds - 4 tbsp', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'water - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine water, oats, and cranberries in a bowl.
2. Microwave for 1-2 minutes.
3. Stir and let sit for 1 minute.
4. Mix in protein powder and almonds.

name: Flank Steak With Mushrooms And Onions
description: Harness the power of proper nutrition to build muscle without gaining fat. The Macro Manager shows you how.
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 8 oz', 'onion, chopped - 1', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1½ cup', 'extra virgin olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'blue cheese - 2 tbsp', 'soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - 2 tsp, ground', 'garlic powder - 2 tsp', 'table salt - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place onions, mushrooms, soy sauce, and olive oil in a non-stick pan over a medium heat, stirring occasionally.
2. Cook until the onions caramelize and the mushrooms soften and become a deeper brown - approximately 20 minutes. The volume of the onions and mushrooms will greatly reduce as they cook.
3. While the mushrooms and onions are cooking, rub steak with garlic powder, salt, and pepper on both sides.
4. Heat a frying pan over medium/high heat. Once pan is hot, place the steak on the pan for four minutes, then flip and cook for another three minutes. Depending on the thickness of the flank steak, this cooking method will produce a medium cooked steak.
5. Once you remove the steak from the pan, let it sit for at least five minutes before cutting and eating.
6. Finish the dish by pouring the onion/mushroom mixture over the steak and topping with blue cheese.

name: Everyday Beast Avocado Smoothie
description: Healthy fats, carbs, and lean proteins combine in one nutrient-packed smoothie to refuel your post-workout gains and help your body recover fast!
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 60 g', 'honey - ½ tbsp', 'banana - ½ cup, sliced', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 4 oz', "Nature's Best Isopure Whey Protein Isolate - 1 scoop", 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.

name: Mocha Pops
description: It's time to take your java out of the mug and into a popsicle mold. Naturally sweetened with dates, these ice pops taste like a fancy coffee drink but with way more nutritional credibility.
recipeIngredient: ['coffee, brewed - 1¼ cup', 'chopped dates - ⅓ cup', 'plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 3 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place hot coffee and dates in a blender and let sit for 30 minutes. Add yogurt, protein powder, cocoa powder, vanilla, and cinnamon to blender container and blend until smooth.
2. Evenly distribute mixture into popsicle molds, filling each about three-quarters full. Insert sticks and freeze for about 8 hours.
3. To unmold popsicles, run the mold under warm water for a few seconds, being careful not to thaw the pops.

name: Green Mango Pops
description: You'll be hard pressed to find frosty pops with more nutritional heft than these. Hemp seeds add a dose of plant-based protein and essential omega fats, while the mild-tasting baby spinach adds a dose of antioxidants. Use a plant-based protein powder if you want to keep these pops vegan or dairy free. Pineapple could also stand in for mango, and the mint can be replaced with fresh basil.
recipeIngredient: ['unsweetened coconut milk - ¾ cup', 'frozen mango pieces - 1½ cup', 'baby spinach - 1½ cup', 'mint leaves, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'hemp seeds - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, powdered - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
2. Evenly distribute mixture into popsicle molds, filling each about three-quarters full. Insert sticks and freeze for about 8 hours.
3. To unmold a popsicle, run the mold under warm water for a few seconds, being careful not to thaw the pops.

name: Blueberry Cheesecake Pops
description: After a sweltering summer workout, these pops are just what you need to cool off inside and out, while simultaneously kick-starting the recovery process. The protein-packed trio of cottage cheese, antioxidant-rich blueberries, and almond butter gives you the nutrients your body needs to take the heat.
recipeIngredient: ['skim milk - ½ cup', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 1 cup', 'frozen blueberries - 1½ cup', 'natural almond butter - ¼ cup', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 2 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 2 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
2. Evenly distribute mixture into popsicle molds, filling each about three-quarters full. Insert sticks and freeze for about 8 hours.
3. To unmold a popsicle, run the mold under warm water for a few seconds, being careful not to thaw the pops.

name: Banana Maple Cookies
description: This simple, reduced-carb recipe is a quick and diet-friendly treat that satisfies your cookie cravings without increasing your waistline. Made from natural, healthy ingredients that are high in fiber and lower in carbs, these cookies are a delicious post-workout treat or a great high-energy snack on the go.
recipeIngredient: ['coconut flour - ½ cup', 'banana - ½ cup, mashed', 'maple syrup - ¼ cup', 'natural almond butter - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine the coconut flour and banana in a medium mixing bowl.
3. In a small bowl, combine the syrup and almond butter and melt in the microwave.
4. Mix the liquid ingredients into the coconut flour and banana mixture.
5. Form the mixture into balls and place on a lined cookie sheet.
6. Press the balls flat and bake for 10-12 minutes until golden.

name: Coconut Pancakes
description: Coconut flour is a great low-carb baking option, perfect for this delicious twist on a breakfast favorite. This quick and easy breakfast a great go-to when you're in a cutting phase. For those times you're not as strict on your macros, you can add chopped nuts, frozen blueberries, or even chocolate chips.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 3', 'coconut flour - 2 oz', 'coconut milk - 3 oz', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'baking powder - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Separate egg, being careful not to get any yolk in the egg white. Set aside egg white.
2. Combine egg yolk, oil, and coconut milk in a bowl.
3. In a separate bowl, mix together dry ingredients, then add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture.
4. Whip the egg white with a pinch of salt until stiff peaks form.
5. Gently fold the egg white into the batter.
6. Cook the pancakes in a pan or griddle on medium-high heat.
7. Serve with fresh fruit and a small spoonful of sour cream.

name: Kamut Breakfast Bowl
description: If you're looking for a new take on morning oatmeal, kamut is a high-protein grain known for its rich, nutty flavor that blends well with both sweet or savory dishes. Save time by cooking this ancient cereal grain ahead of time, and spice it up with any of your favorite macro-friendly toppings.
recipeIngredient: ['kamut, uncooked - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'low fat yogurt - ¼ cup (8 fl oz)', 'almonds, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pulse the kamut in a food processor a few times to break up the grains and make them easier to cook.
2. Simmer the kamut in 2 cups of water for about 45 minutes or until tender.
3. Let cool and serve with yogurt, blueberries, and almonds.

name: Spaghetti with Cashew Cream, Peas, and Spinach
description: What better choice for a high-carb meal than the undisputed king of carbs, pasta. Tossed in a rich cashew-cream sauce, this delicious, fresh meal is completely vegan, but you can substitute your favorite cream-based sauce if you prefer.
recipeIngredient: ['spaghetti, dry - 4 oz', 'cashews, chopped - 1 cup', 'water - 1½ cup', 'nutritional yeast - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'peas - ½ cup', 'spinach - 6 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend the soaked cashews with water, nutritional yeast, and lemon. Season to taste with salt.
2. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the pasta to the water and stir occasionally to prevent noodles from sticking together. Cook for 8-12 minutes, until desired tenderness is reached.
3. Drain the cooked pasta, but reserve a little bit of the pasta water.
4. Toss the hot cooked pasta in a mixing bowl with the peas, spinach, and cashew cream. If it looks a little too thick, add some pasta water to achieve desired consistency.

name: Grilled Halibut with Minted Peas and Freekeh
description: Freekeh is high in both protein and fiber, making it a great rice alternative when you're trying to reduce your body fat. Halibut a very lean protein that pairs well with the strong flavors of chopped mint and the metabolism-boosting spices in the garam masala. For a low-carb option, simply omit the freekeh and pair the seared halibut with a bed of fresh greens.
recipeIngredient: ['halibut - 8 oz', 'peas - ¾ cup', 'mint leaves, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'freekeh, cooked - ¾ cup', 'shallots - 1 tbsp chopped', 'Garam Masala - 2 tsp', 'water - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. In a saucepan on low heat, sweat the shallot with the garam masala. Add the freekeh and water and cook until the liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes. Cover, remove from heat, and let sit for 5-10 minutes.
3. While freekeh is cooking, season the halibut with salt as you heat an oven-proof pan on high heat. Gently place the halibut in preheated pan with a little bit of oil. Let the fish sear on high for 3-4 minutes, then move the pan to the oven.
4. Finish halibut in oven for another 4-5 minutes.
5. In a shallow pan of water, add the peas and cook 2-3 minutes. Finish with chopped mint and salt to taste.
6. Serve the peas over the freekeh, and top with seared halibut.

name: Marinated Chicken with Cauliflower Rice
description: This deliciously seasoned dish is a twist on the classic chicken and rice meal. Cauliflower rice helps keep the carb load to a minimum, and fresh cilantro and serrano pepper add freshness and heat to your tasty homemade peanut sauce.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken thighs, slice (boneless and skinless) - 4 oz', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'coriander - ½ tsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'coconut milk - 4 oz', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'serrano chili - ½ pepper', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'cauliflower, chopped - 4 oz', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'peanuts, chopped - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine Chicken Thighs, with seasonings and olive oil, and let marinate for at least an hour.
2. Cook marinated chicken thighs either on the grill or in the oven. Once cooked, set aside to cool slightly before serving.
3. In a small saucepan, whisk together coconut milk, garlic, chili, soy sauce, and peanut butter.
4. Bring to a simmer and allow to reduce slightly. Add cilantro just before serving.
5. Heat the cauliflower rice through in a large skillet with a little olive oil. Cook for 3-5 minutes until the cauliflower is tender, then remove from heat. Add the spinach, letting it wilt.
6. Slice chicken and serve with cauliflower mixture and sauce. Top with chopped peanuts.

name: Root Vegetable Salad with Parsnip Puree
description:
If you're trying to stick to a whole-food or plant-based diet, this is the perfect high-carb meal for you. Root vegetables like beets, carrots, and potatoes are full of vitamins and minerals you don't find in breads, pastas, and other refined carbohydrates. 

Enjoy these root veggies with the fresh parsnip puree, or mix things up by using your favorite dressing or marinade instead. You can enjoy this vegetarian meal on its own, or pair with grilled steak or baked chicken for a savory and satisfying meal.
recipeIngredient: ['beets, cut into cubes - 1 beet (2" dia)', 'carrot, chopped - 1 medium', 'chives - ¼ cup', 'parsnips, cut into cubes - 1', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'pumpkin seeds - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring a pot of water to a boil and lightly salt.
2. Cook the beets, carrots, and potatoes in salted water until slightly tender, about 20 minutes. Let cool.
3. Combine the parsnip, lime juice, honey, and olive oil in a food processor or blender, and mix until very smooth.
4. Toss the cooked vegetables and chives with the parsnip puree. Top with pumpkin seeds and serve.

name: Grilled Kale Caesar with Chicken
description: This recipe takes only minutes to prepare and is a great way to jazz up your basic Caesar salad. To save time, grill or roast batches of chicken ahead of time to use in this salad, and make a larger batch of the dressing so you can whip up this healthy and delicious salad any time you want.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 5 oz', 'kale - 4 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'anchovy - 2 fillet', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the broiler.
2. Combine the garlic, anchovy, lemon juice, mayonnaise, and black pepper.
3. Massage the kale with a little olive oil and salt, and put under the broiler for a few minutes, to wilt and char just slightly.
4. Chop up the cooked chicken breast into small pieces. Toss with kale and dressing.

name: Roasted Chicken With Zoodles and Spicy Tomato Sauce
description: Zucchini noodles or "zoodles" are a low-carb, low-calorie alternative to pasta and a great side dish on their own. Chicken thighs have more fat and therefore more flavor than chicken breasts, but either works for this recipe. You can use canned crushed tomatoes for the sauce, and many stores now sell pre-spiralized zoodles so you can whip up this light and healthy meal in no time.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken thighs, slice (boneless and skinless) - 8 oz', 'zucchini, sliced into noodles - ¾ cup', 'tomatoes, crushed, canned - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper, and sear in a skillet on medium-high heat.
2. Cook on each side for 5-6 minutes depending on size. Once cooked through, remove from heat and set aside to cool.
3. While chicken is cooking, heat olive oil in a saucepan on low to medium heat and add the garlic and crushed red pepper. Once the garlic begins to brown slightly, add the crushed tomatoes. Bring to a simmer, then remove from heat and add chopped basil.
4. Heat zucchini noodles in a sauté pan with just a little bit of water, cooking for 3-4 minutes until tender. Drain zoodles and serve with tomato sauce and chicken thighs.

name: Cauliflower Hash With Eggs
description: Poaching eggs is easier than you think and a great way to cook eggs without adding fat. Using cauliflower for the hash instead of potatoes keeps the carbs down for this quick and easy low-carb breakfast. Served over a bed of vitamin-rich kale, this delicious hash takes minutes to prepare and gives you the protein and nutrients you need to start your day.
recipeIngredient: ['onion, diced - ½ medium (2-1/2" dia)', 'cauliflower - 1 cup chopped (1/2" pieces)', 'kale, diced - 1 cup', 'egg - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Sweat the onion gently in a pan on low heat for about 2 minutes.
2. Add the cauliflower and cook another 2 minutes, then add the kale and continue cooking until kale brightens and softens, about 2 minutes. Season to taste with salt.
3. Bring a small saucepan of water to a slow boil. Add 1 tablespoon of vinegar. Crack the eggs gently into the water to poach, cooking for 2 minutes. Make sure the water does not boil too hard.
4. Use a slotted spoon to retrieve the eggs and serve over the cauliflower and kale hash.

name: Tempeh Lettuce Wraps with Radishes
description: A close relative of tofu, tempeh is a fermented soy product that is often used as a meat replacement. In this recipe, it takes the place of chicken in these fresh lettuce wraps. Radishes and ginger add a zing to this restaurant classic, and water chestnuts add crunch without adding calories.
recipeIngredient: ['tempeh, sliced - 6 oz', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'soy sauce - 1 tsp', 'rice vinegar - 1 tsp', 'butter leaf lettuce - 1 head (5" dia)', 'radishes, thinly sliced - 2 small', 'water chestnut, sliced - 3', 'cilantro - 2 tbsp', 'shallots - 1 tbsp chopped', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'ginger, minced - 2 tsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the tempeh with the ginger, soy, and vinegar and let marinate for 30-45 minutes.
2. Mix the cilantro, ginger, and olive oil, and toss with sliced radish, water chestnut, and shallot until coated.
3. Using the butter leaves as cups, fill with the radish mixture and top with tempeh.

name: Salmon Cake with Roasted Asparagus
description: Since fish fillets don't always come in perfectly pre-measured packages, this is a great recipe to use up your leftover cooked salmon. Using almond flour helps keep these salmon cakes low-carb, and the grilled asparagus and avocado lime puree add light, fresh flavors to round out this quick and satisfying meal.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon, smoked - 5 oz', 'egg - 1', 'almond flour - 2 tbsp', 'chives - 1 tbsp chopped', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 2 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 dash', 'asparagus - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'avocado - 1', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Prepare the asparagus by snapping off the woody base of the stalks. Toss the asparagus spears with olive oil, and a little salt.
3. Roast asparagus for 8-10 minutes depending on size and desired doneness.
4. Skin the avocado and remove the seed. Mash the flesh with lime juice and a little salt, mix in mayonnaise, and set aside.
5. Combine the salmon with the egg white, almond flour, spices, and lemon zest. Season to taste with salt and form into a cake. Cook in a hot skillet with a little oil.
6. Cook salmon cakes for 3-4 minutes per side, serve with roasted asparagus and the avocado lime puree.

name: Spinach, Bacon and Avocado Salad
description: Substituting turkey bacon for its pork cousin helps lower the saturated fat and overall calories of this quick and easy salad. Other than salt and pepper for seasoning, this quick, fresh lunch has only four ingredients, making it an easy throw-together meal on busy days.
recipeIngredient: ['turkey bacon - 3 oz', 'spinach - 4 cup', 'avocado - 1', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
