description: Guiltlessly enjoy pizza for breakfast. This version is full of fiber; vitamins C, B-6 and K, calcium, phosphorous, and selenium. It also has a great balance of carbs, proteins, and fats to help you start the day right.
recipeIngredient: ['Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - 1 pita, small  (4" dia)', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 3', 'mushrooms, sliced - ¼ cup', 'onion, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - ¼ cup', 'green onion, sliced - 1', 'turkey bacon - 2 strip', 'olive oil - ½ tbsp', 'mushroom - 1 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Whisk eggs and add diced vegetables.
2. Bend edges of the pita to create a bowl.
3. Brush both sides with olive oil and place on the grill, dome side down.
4. Cook for 30-60 seconds or until golden and then flip.
5. Pour egg mixture into the pita.
6. Cook for 1-2 minutes or until eggs are nearly cooked.
7. Add chopped turkey bacon slices, cheese, and green onion.
8. Cook until cheese is melted and eat up!

name: Tilapia Veracruz
description: Try this delicious fish and salsa combo, and others from the Bodybuilding.com recipe section. Enjoy!
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 6 oz', 'lime juice - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'sea salt - ¼ tsp', 'tomatoes - 1 cup, chopped or sliced', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'green olives, sliced - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'sea salt - ¼ tsp', 'hot sauce - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat broiler. Rinse fish well and pat dry.
2. Spray both sides of fish lightly with cooking spray then sprinkle with lime juice, cumin, pepper and salt.
3. Place fish on pre-sprayed broiler pan then broil 4-5 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
4. Most tilapia is quite thin and may need less time and often does not need to be turned over or it will fall apart. Use a slotted spatula when carefully turning if needed. Be careful not to overcook this delicate fish or it will become dry.)
5. In a medium bowl mix together all ingredients for salsa, toss gently and chill.
6. Serve fish over Spanish rice and black beans topped with salsa and fresh limes.
7. Time saver tip: To cut down on cooking time substitute your favorite salsa for making it from scratch but be sure to add fresh cilantro for that fresh garden flavor.

name: Ghost Brownies
description: Kick your regular protein brownie recipe up a notch with these ghostly additions! Not only do the brownies and sauce taste amazing, but the presentation is just too cute. I guarantee that if you bring a plate of these to a party, you'll get nothing but compliments. Their awesome nutrition facts just make them even better!
recipeIngredient: ['Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - ½ cup', 'baking soda - ¼ tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 oz', 'egg - 1 whole', 'BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - ½ scoop', 'banana - 1 cup, mashed']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven 350 degrees F.
2. In a bowl, blend egg, 2 tbsp syrup, black beans, protein, and baking soda with a small blender or hand mixer.
3. Pour batter into a greased 4x6 baking pan.
4. Top with 1 tbsp dark chocolate chips.
5. Bake 18-25 minutes. After cooling, cut into 6 brownies.
6. In a bowl, combine yogurt and syrup to make a sauce.
7. Coat banana pieces in sauce, then fix two chocolate chips on each banana piece for eyes. You now have ghosts.
8. Place a ghost on top of each brownie, and drizzle with any remaining sauce. If desired, secure banana pieces to brownies with toothpicks.

name: Jack O'Lantern Ice Cream
description: OMG, this is seriously cute. The ice cream has a delicate flavor and looks fantastic in a little orange jack-o'-lantern. The recipe is really easy to double, triple, or even quadruple if you want to make more.
recipeIngredient: ['BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - ½ scoop', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'orange - 1 fruit (2-7/8" dia)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice the top off an orange. Use a knife to slice around the inside of the orange peel, then scoop out the insides with a spoon.
2. Blend orange flesh, almond milk, Greek yogurt, protein, and syrup together.
3. Pour into an ice cream maker.
4. Let freeze and churn for 15-20 minutes.
5. While waiting, carve a face into the orange peel.
6. Place finished ice cream inside empty orange peel.

name: Grilled Banana French Toast
description: French toast is a classic breakfast favorite, but it's not really part of a healthy nutrition plan. With the right substitutions however, you can re-introduce it into your fit diet! Since this is a carb-heavy meal, try adding a few slices of turkey bacon or a protein shake for more balanced nutrition.
recipeIngredient: ['ezekiel bread - 4 slice', 'egg - 2', 'egg whites - 2', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'banana - 2', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Whisk eggs, egg whites, skim milk, cinnamon, and vanilla.
2. Submerse both bread slices in egg mixture; place on the grill.
3. Cook for 3-5 minutes, flip, and cook other side until desired crispiness is reached.
4. Place sliced bananas on the grill. Cook for 1-2 minutes per side.
5. Top French toast with banana slices. If you'd like additional toppings, try natural peanut butter and/or sugar-free maple syrup.

name: Confetti Cake Protein Cookies
description: Getting a protein cookie to turn out well can be difficult. Having it taste good while simultaneously meeting your macros is no easy task, but this is by far the best recipe I've made. Again, the prep time is a breeze, as is the minimal cook time—5 and 9 minutes, respectively. This means you can enjoy these cookies almost immediately!
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas - 1 cup', 'MusclePharm Combat Powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'powdered Stevia - ½ cup', 'coconut flour - ¼ cup', 'egg - 1 whole', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'milk (2% fat) - 2 tbsp', 'cake sprinkles - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'coconut sugar - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Drain garbanzo beans and rinse well. Add garbanzo beans, egg, applesauce, milk, and vanilla extract to food processor. Process until smooth.
3. Add Stevia, coconut sugar, protein powder, and coconut flour, and process again. Lastly, add sprinkles, and pulse a few times to incorporate.
4. Scoop cookies onto cookie sheet about 1/4 cup at a time. There should be enough batter to make 10 cookies.
5. Bake for 8-10 minutes. Cook longer if you like them more done, but cooking less gives more of a moist cake texture instead of drying the cookies out.

name: Ham-And-Cheese Breakfast Griller
description: Simple and delicious, a ham-and-cheese griller offers a great source of protein and calcium. Add Popeye's favorite veggie to enjoy an exhaustive list of vitamins and minerals like A, K, potassium, and iron. You'll be out the door quickly with a smile on your face, since you didn't force yourself through another bowl of bland oats.
recipeIngredient: ['ezekiel bread - 2 slice', 'ham, low sodium - 2 oz', 'low-fat cheddar cheese - 1 oz', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 2 tbsp', 'mustard - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brush one side of each piece of bread with a tablespoon of fat-free mayonnaise.
2. Place bread and ham separately on the grill.
3. Flip ham after 1-2 minutes, or until slightly crispy.
4. Transfer ham slices, cheddar cheese, and spinach to one slice of bread. Then cover with second piece.
5. Cook for 30-60 seconds or until cheese begins to melt, then flip. Cook for 30 more seconds to seal sandwich.
6. Add mustard for additional flavor.

name: Chocolate Dessert
description: Oh yes, you can still have dessert! Instead of reaching for a cookie, try this recipe. It's sweet and creamy, but has less sugar and more nutrition for you and your baby!
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 2 fruit, without skin and seed', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'agave syrup - 1 tbsp', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Mix all ingredients into blender and enjoy.

name: Grilled Parfait
description: Finally, a parfait that tastes as great as it looks! Skip the frozen berries and mushy granola and grill up something fresh. The colorful fruit means a delicious dose of fiber and antioxidants. Add some almonds and you'll also get healthy fats and protein.
recipeIngredient: ['pineapple - 4 slice (3-1/2" dia x 3/4" thick)', 'orange - 1', 'grapefruit - 1', 'apples - 1', 'light margarine - 1 tbsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 3 cup', 'almonds, slivered - 2 tbsp', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice the orange, grapefruit, and apple.
2. Melt the margarine in the microwave and combine with cinnamon. Brush mixture over the fruit slices.
3. Put fruit on a skewer and place on grill. Grill the fruit for 3-4 minutes per side, or until grill marks form.
4. Remove from grill and cut into small, bite-sized pieces.
5. Layer fruit with Greek yogurt and top with a sprinkle of almonds and dried coconut.

name: Cajun Spiced Salmon
description: This recipe is family and figure friendly. Even the most skeptical fish eaters won't turn their nose up at this dish. Salmon is packed with protein, healthy fats, and is basically carb-free. Try this recipe with organic brown rice or quinoa and vegetables.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 4 fillet', 'cumin - 1 tbsp', 'coriander - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 2 tbsp', 'pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, ground', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all the spices together in a bowl. If needed, add extra sea salt.
2. Rub the mix on both sides of salmon filets. Cover filets with plastic wrap and let stand for 30 minutes, or until salmon reaches room temperature.
3. When salmon is ready to cook, heat a frying pan on high heat.
4. Melt coconut oil.
5. Place the salmon filets in hot pan and cook for 2-3 minutes on one side.
6. After 2-3 minutes, flip and cook for another 2-3 minutes.
7. Remove from pan and eat!

name: Stuffed Baked Apples
description: A healthy baked apple breakfast sounds too good to be true. Yet this sweet treat has it all: protein, carbs, and fiber. The cinnamon also helps keep your blood sugar levels stable.
recipeIngredient: ['apples - 3 medium (3" dia)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - 3 tbsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the cinnamon and brown sugar.
2. Place the cored apple in the mixture. Coat the apple, inside and out, and place on the grill.
3. Cook for 3-4 minutes or until tender.
4. Mix the Greek yogurt, protein powder, rolled oats, and walnuts until well mixed.
5. Fill the baked apple with the mixture.
6. Cover and cook for 1-2 minutes or until yogurt is heated.

name: Watermelon Cherry Re-Jello
description: For the times you don't feel like sipping on aminos, or simply want something a little more substantial in your stomach, this refreshing Jell-O snack is king! It's the perfect combination of palate-pleasing, muscle-building fuel, and it's easy to customize to meet your flavor preference.
recipeIngredient: ['rsp nutrition regen bcaa - 1 scoop', 'water - 2 cup', 'jello - 1 serving', 'water - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add two cups of boiling water to a large bowl. Mix in a Jell-O packet, and gently stir until it's completely mixed.
2. Add 3 scoops of Watermelon ReGen to a shaker with two cups of cold water.
3. Once the ReGen is dissolved, add it to the hot Jell-O liquid.
4. Gently stir the mixture and portion into six small cups or bowls.

name: Sweet Lime Sesame Shrimp
description: Add a tangy taste to your protein with this muscle-building seafood favorite.
recipeIngredient: ['honey - ¼ cup', 'sriracha - 2 tbsp', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'arrowroot starch - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - ½ tbsp', 'red bell pepper - ⅓ cup, chopped', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 oz', 'jumbo shrimp - ¾ lb', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix honey, sriracha, fresh lime juice, and arrowroot, in a bowl.
2. Spray skillet with olive oil and toss in garlic and red bell pepper. Sauté until edges are brown.
3. Add shrimp to skillet, and cook until shrimp is nearly done.
4. Reduce the heat and add in the sauce from the bowl.
5. Simmer the sauce with shrimp, and mix together.
6. Finish with sesame oil, dish up, and garnish with cilantro.

name: Protein Acai Bowl
description: Add some fresh fruit to your diet with this acai bowl that's sure to curb cravings and spice up ordinary yogurt.
recipeIngredient: ['frozen acai berry pulp - 1 pack', 'banana - ½', 'strawberries, frozen - ⅓ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth.
2. Garnish with favorite toppings. Optional toppings include: 
Fresh blueberries, 1/4 cup
Fresh kiwi chunks, 1 kiwi
Shaved almonds, 1 tsp
Shredded coconut, 1 tbsp

name: Dairy-Free Chicken Zasta
description: Looking for lean gains? This zucchini-inspired pasta will leave you feeling full and satisfied.
recipeIngredient: ['zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'arrowroot starch - 2 tbsp', 'chicken breast - ¾ lb', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'garlic, minced - ⅓ tbsp', 'red onion, diced - ⅓ cup', 'rosemary - 1 tbsp', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, ground', 'coconut cream - 1 cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 2 tbsp', 'parsley, dried - 1 tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'sea salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut off zucchini ends, and spiralize into a bowl.
2. Add a few tablespoons to arrowroot and stir.
3. Spray nonstick skillet with olive oil and slice chicken into cubes.
4. Season chicken with sea salt and ground pepper. Sauté for about 8 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Place chicken in a bowl.
5. Spray nonstick skillet with olive oil. Add garlic, onion, rosemary, oregano, and sauté until onion browns. Add coconut cream to skillet with onions and bring to simmer.
6. After about 2 minutes, add the arrowroot and water mixture and stir. Add chicken broth to simmering skillet followed by the zucchini pasta.
7. Toss the pasta to coat with creamy sauce. Add the cooked chicken to the pasta and sauce.
8. Garnish with parsley and season to taste with sea salt and pepper.

name: Gainzerito
description: Move over, Chipotle. Get your burrito fix and meet your macros with this Gainzerito.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 6 oz', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'safflower mayonnaise - 1 tbsp', 'sriracha - 1 tsp', 'dijon mustard - ½ tbsp', 'whole-wheat tortilla (10-inch) - 1', 'lettuce - 1 leaf', 'tomato, diced - 1', 'red onion, diced - 1', 'low-fat cheddar cheese - ¼ cup, shredded', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook ground beef and season in the pan with garlic, sea salt, and ground pepper.
2. Mix mayo, sriracha, and Dijon mustard in small bowl.
3. Spread mayo sauce on tortilla. Add lettuce, tomato, onion, beef, and cheese.
4. Fold and wrap burrito.

name: Stuffed French Toast With Protein Cream
description: Morning, noon, or night enjoy this calorie-conscious treat that will satisfy your sweet tooth without sabotaging your goals.
recipeIngredient: ['rye bread - 5 slice, thick', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2', 'almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'fat-free cream cheese - 5 oz', 'whey protein powder isolate - ½ scoop', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Whisk together eggs and almond milk in a bowl. Set aside.
2. Mix together filling ingredients.
3. Make slight incision on pieces of bread to form a pocket (like pita bread).
4. Add sliced strawberries (and/or blueberries) and some of the protein cheese mixture.
5. Dip both sides of stuffed bread in egg mixture.
6. Spray skillet. Let it get hot. Add French toast. Garnish with cinnamon and sugar-free maple syrup (optional).

name: Thyme-Less Gains Burger
description: An herb-filled burger topped with sugar-coated bacon. Sounds like gains to me!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1 lb', 'fresh thyme - 1½ tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'challah bread - 1 roll', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'reduced-fat cheddar cheese - 1 slice', 'avocado - 1 tbsp', 'bacon - 4 slice', 'coconut sugar - 1 tbsp', 'lettuce - 2 leaf', 'tomatoes - 2 slice, medium (1/4" thick)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place bacon on parchment paper and sprinkle with coconut sugar. Bake for 10 min. at 350 degrees F.
2. Add thyme, smoked paprika, garlic, sea salt, and pepper to ground beef. Mix.
3. Mold into patties.
4. Spray skillet with non-stick olive oil, then cook patties.
5. Add cheese and cover with lid until melted.
6. Toast buns in pan. Then, build burgers by adding toppings. Serve.

name: Crunchy Chicken Chalupa
description: Kiss fast food goodbye and make taco time fit your macros with this chicken-based take on the original.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'whole-wheat panko bread crumbs - ⅓ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'egg - 1', 'coconut flour - ¼ cup', 'lettuce shredded - 1 cup', 'pico de gallo - 1 tbsp', 'avocado - ¼ cup, pureed', 'low-fat cheddar cheese - ½ cup, shredded']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 420 degrees F.
2. Mix panko and seasonings.
3. Butterfly the chicken breast. Hammer it thin with a mallet, if needed. Dust with coconut flour.
4. Beat an egg in a small bowl. Dip the chicken breast in egg, then seasoned panko.
5. Spray a skillet with oil and allow it to get hot. Add the chicken breast and sear both sides (about 2-3 minutes).
6. Place the skillet and chicken breast in the oven for an additional 5-8 minutes.
7. Allow to cool, then add chicken to taco holder and garnish.

name: Crunchy Parmesan Green Bean Fries
description: French fries are often a welcomed guilty pleasure, but the traditional potato kind come drenched in oil and loaded with salt. Get in your veggies and satisfy your craving with green bean fries!
recipeIngredient: ['green beans - 2 cup', 'egg - 1', 'egg whites - 1', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 cup', 'whole-wheat panko bread crumbs - ⅔ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Beat eggs. Mix panko, parmesan, and seasonings together.
3. Dip green beans in egg wash, then in parmesan mix. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or on a rack.
4. Bake in oven for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
5. Enjoy with your favorite dipping sauce (BBQ sauce or Dijon or Greek yogurt-based ranch dressing).

name: Gainz Lover's Nachos
description: Skip greasy, fried nachos in favor of complex carbs with these sweet-potato, protein-topped nachos.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 3 whole', 'red onion, diced - ⅓ cup', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'chili powder - 2 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'low-sodium tomato sauce - ½ cup', 'avocado - 2½ oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2½ oz', 'low-fat cheddar cheese - 1 oz', 'green onion, chopped - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice sweet potato into wedges, and spray potato wedges with olive oil.
2. Season wedges with sea salt and pepper to taste.
3. Sauté seasoned wedges for 5 minutes until outsides are brown.
4. Bake sautéed potatoes at 400 F for 20 minutes.
5. Sauté onions with olive oil, and add turkey to the skillet.
6. Season turkey with chili powder, garlic powder, sea salt, and pepper. Add no-salt tomato sauce.
7. Remove the potatoes from the oven, and top them off with the meat sauce.
8. Garnish with avocado, Greek yogurt, green onions and cheese.

name: Smokin' Jalapeno Popper Burger
description: Add some kick to a protein-packed burger with this spicy take on a classic favorite.
recipeIngredient: ['jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', '2% greek yogurt, plain - 1 tbsp', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - ⅛ cup', 'goat cheese - 1 oz', 'lean ground beef - 6 oz', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'cumin - ½ tbsp', 'portabella mushroom caps - 2 piece whole', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'brown mustard - 1 tbsp', 'lettuce - 2 leaf', 'tomatoes - 2 slice, thick/large (1/2" thick)', 'turkey bacon - 2 strip']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice jalapeno in half, remove seeds, and chop.
2. Mix Greek yogurt, mozzarella, goat cheese, and chopped jalapeno together. Place in freezer.
3. Mix meat, garlic, cumin, sea salt, and ground pepper. Form patty with seasoned meat mixture and make a hole in the center using your thumb.
4. Add the filling from the freezer into the hole. Fold over the sides of the meat to cover the hole.
5. Place burger patty in skillet, brown both sides, cover, and cook to your desired readiness.
6. Add mustard, lettuce, tomato, burger patty, and turkey bacon to bun or Portobello mushroom cap.

name: Gainz Breakfast Bowl
description: Power your training sessions—and get huge—with this morning power bowl.
recipeIngredient: ['fingerling potatoes - 6 whole', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'rosemary -  to taste', 'egg - 5 whole', 'goat cheese - 2 oz', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'green onion, chopped - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut potatoes. Spray nonstick skillet with olive oil and add potatoes, garlic powder, pepper, and sea salt.
2. Sear potatoes until edges are brown, then bake in oven for 20 minutes at 420 F.
3. Chop rosemary, crack 2 whole eggs, and add 3 egg whites to a bowl and beat.
4. Season eggs with pepper and rosemary.
5. Cook eggs in skillet, and add goat cheese.
6. Place cooked eggs in bowl, add potatoes, then top with tomatoes, green onion, sea salt, and pepper.

name: BBQ Bison Pineapple Pizza
description: Add some protein to your meal with 'za so good it'll taste like a cheat-day treat.
recipeIngredient: ['bison, ground - 6 oz', 'cumin - ½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'whole-wheat naan bread - 1 piece', 'low-sodium barbecue sauce - 2 tbsp', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'pineapple - ½ cup, chunks', 'red onion, diced - ⅓ cup', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - ¼ cup', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray nonstick skillet with olive oil. Add bison, cumin, cayenne, paprika, and pepper. Cook until brown.
2. Place wheat naan bread on baking sheet with cooling rack.
3. Spread barbecue sauce on the naan and add spinach, bison, pineapple, onion, and mozzarella.
4. Bake pizza in oven at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
5. Slice and enjoy.

name: Black Bean Bacon Dip
description: Add some extra protein to your bean dip with this FitMenCook-approved recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['bacon - 2 slice', 'low-sodium black beans - 15 oz', 'natural almond butter - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook bacon until crispy.
2. Let bacon cool, and then chop it up.
3. Use a food processor to blend black beans, almond butter, olive oil, garlic, cumin, chili powder, salt, pepper, cilantro, and lime.
4. Place mix into a bowl, and top with bacon.

name: Protein Chocolate Lava Cakes
description: Nothing says love like chocolate cake. Show your swole-mate how you really feel on Valentine's Day with this protein lava cake recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['Animal chocolate whey - 2 scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 3 tbsp', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'lite coconut  milk - ¼ cup', 'coconut sugar - 2 tbsp', 'gluten-free oats - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a handheld blender or food processor, blend all ingredients together until you get a creamy batter.
2. Pour the mix into two silicone baking pods or regular souffle dishes. Just bear in mind that, if you're using souffle dishes, you'll have to butter them so the mix doesn't stick.
3. Bake at 356 F (180 C) for no more than 4 minutes. You want the top to be cooked but the center to be gooey, so check on you cakes after 3 minutes and assess accordingly.
4. As soon as they're ready, carefully remove them from the mold and turn them upside down on a plate.
5. Top with strawberries, cream, MCT powder, or just enjoy them solo!

name: Sweet Potato Oatmeal Muffins with Blueberry Sauce
description:
Bake up a batch of these in advance and you'll have a week's worth of a pre-portioned breakfast meals that'll help you bolt out the door in the morning. 

If you want to use rolled oats, simply delete the step where you soak the steel-cut oats and increase the amount of oats to 1-1/2 cups. You can also replace the sweet potato with canned pumpkin puree.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - 1 cup', 'oat bran - ½ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1½ tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'egg - 2', 'sweet potato puree - 1 cup', 'milk (2% fat) - ¾ cup', 'maple syrup - 4 tbsp', 'blueberries - 2 cup', 'water - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cornstarch - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, cover steel-cut oats with water and soak overnight or for at least 2 hours.
2. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Drain oats and add to a large bowl along with oat bran, walnuts, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, and salt.
3. In a separate bowl, lightly beat eggs and mix with sweet potato, milk, and 2 tablespoons of maple syrup. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir to combine.
4. Divide oat mixture among 12 standard-sized paper-lined or greased muffin cups. Bake for 20 minutes, or until muffins are set. Let cool for a few minutes before unmolding.
5. To make the blueberry sauce, place blueberries, water, 2 tablespoons maple syrup, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, and vanilla in a medium sized saucepan. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water, stir into blueberry mixture and heat 1 minute, or until thickened.
6. Serve warmed muffins topped with warmed blueberry sauce.

name: Low-Carb Almond Butter Fudge (Keto Fat Bombs)
description: When you're looking to get in your daily dose of healthy fats, you can't go wrong with fudge. Whip up this dessert for some Keto gains.
recipeIngredient: ['natural almond butter - 1 cup', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 cup', 'powdered Stevia - 2 g', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'cacao nibs - 2 tbsp', 'baking chocolate, unsweetened - ⅓ oz square bakers']
recipeInstructions:
1. Line a small baking dish with parchment paper.
2. Melt the coconut oil and almond butter so they can easily be mixed together. Add to a mini-food processor along with stevia and vanilla. Pulse blend until thoroughly mixed.
3. Pour into the baking dish, and smooth out with a spatula.
4. Add cacao nibs to the top.
5. Freeze for 30 minutes, then place in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
6. Cut into thick cubes and enjoy. Keep refrigerated.
7. Note: Looking to add an extra special touch? Dip each cube halfway into melted unsweetened baking chocolate (optional). Then place on a baking sheet or large plate. Store the dipped cubes in the fridge. Chocolate should harden upon contact.

name: Pea Guacamole
description: Consume an extra dose of vitamins and added protein with this pea-and-egg rich guacamole.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 4', 'peas - 1⅓ cup', 'red onion, diced - ⅔ cup', 'tomatoes - 1 cup, chopped or sliced', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - ⅓ cup', 'hard-boiled egg - 4', 'lime juice - 4 tbsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'cumin - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut avocados in half, remove the pits, and place avocado meat in a bowl.
2. Puree peas in food processor.
3. Mash avocados with a fork, and mix in pea puree.
4. Mix in red onion, diced tomato, diced jalapeno, cumin, salt, pepper, and fresh-squeezed lime juice.
5. Add cilantro and chopped egg whites. Mix well.
6. Serve with celery, bell peppers, or corn chips.

name: Black Bean Brownies
description: Have your dessert and enjoy your gains too with these protein-rich brownies.
recipeIngredient: ['black beans, drained and rinsed - 1½ 15 oz can', 'raw cacao powder - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 4 tbsp', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'almond milk - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'dark chocolate - 8 square', 'walnuts, chopped - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add drained black beans, cacao, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, stevia, coconut oil, almond milk, and vanilla extract to food processor. Blend into a smooth, consistent batter.
2. Dump the batter into a bowl, then mix in chocolate chunks and add walnuts.
3. Spray a baking dish with nonstick spray and add batter.
4. Top with walnuts and bake at 350 F for 25 minutes.

name: Garlic Parmesan Wings
description: Cut back on fat and keep all the flavor with these finger-food favorites.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'chives - 1 tsp chopped', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 tsp', 'oat flour - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Trim fat from the wings. Season chicken with pepper.
2. Lay wings flat on a baking sheet with cooling rack and dust wings with oat flour.
3. Spray coated wings with olive oil and bake wings at 420 F for 25 minutes.
4. To make the sauce, sauté coconut oil, garlic, chives and ground pepper for 5 minutes.
5. Placed cooked wings in bowl and toss with sautéed sauce, parmesan, and sea salt.

name: Homemade Kale Chips
description: Another low cal snack! Low calories and a fraction of the badness of any other chips.
recipeIngredient: ['kale - 2 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'table salt - 2 tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Remove stems from washed Kale and tear into small pieces. Toss with oil and salt and place on baking sheet. Bake at 375F for 10-12 minutes.

name: Golden Milk Oatmeal
description: Inspired by turmeric-flavored "golden milk", these photogenic no-cook overnight oats are jazzed up with an exciting spice mixture and tangy kefir, a fermented milk filled with lots of gut-friendly probiotics. Yum!
recipeIngredient: ['honey - 1 tbsp', 'turmeric - 1 tsp', 'ground ginger - ¼ tsp', 'cardamom - ¼ tsp, ground', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'table salt - ⅛ tsp', 'low-fat Kefir, plain - 1½ cup', 'rolled oats - 1⅓ cup', 'ground flaxseed - ¼ cup', 'mango - 1 cup', 'coconut flakes - 2 tbsp', 'pistachio nuts - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, combine the honey, turmeric, ginger, cardamom, cinnamon, and salt. Add 2 tablespoons of boiled water and stir to dissolve honey and spices together. Stir in kefir.
2. Place 2/3 cup of oats and 2 tablespoons of flax in each of two wide-mouth pint jars or cereal bowls. Add half the kefir mixture to each jar or bowl and stir until all the oats are moist. Top with mango, coconut, and pistachios. Seal jar shut or cover bowl and chill overnight. The oats can be chilled for up to 4 days.

name: Protein Jell-O
description: Mass-maintaining BCAAs are an essential supplement for any bodybuilding aficionado, but chugging them down can get old, fast. Learn how to turn that powder into a tasty treat worth savoring.
recipeIngredient: ['BCAA powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'green tea - 1 cup', 'water - 1 cup', 'jello - 1 serving']
recipeInstructions:
1. Make a big cup of tea with a pint (568ml) of almost-boiling water.
2. After a minute, remove the tea bag. Whisk the tea with the gelatin and BCAAs. I use Dymatize Nutrition Elite Recoup, grape flavor. I love the flavor and it contains higher amounts of B-vitamins than other BCAA powders out there.
3. Whisk it until everything is well dissolved.
4. Divide the mixture into four glasses, bowls, or ramekins.
5. Leave it to set in the fridge overnight and...kaPOW! Done.

name: Mozzarella Chicken Meatballs
description: Looking to take mom's meatball recipe to the next level? Up the ante with this cheese-filled, flavor-packed take on the original.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free mozzarella cheese - 12 oz', 'ground chicken - 2 lb', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, ground', 'marinara sauce - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Chop mozzarella sticks into quarters.
2. Place chicken, basil, garlic powder, oregano, and green onions in bowl and mix together.
3. Spray hands with olive oil, take a piece of mozzarella, and form meatballs around the cheese.
4. Place meatballs in a muffin pan. Bake for 5 minutes at 420 degrees F.
5. Bring marinara to a simmer in a skillet. Add meatballs to the sauce and cook for about 5 minutes.
6. Garnish with chives, and season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Greek Yogurt Parfait
description: This is great for entertaining while still serving a healthy treat that gets high presentation scores. Be sure to serve it in a clear glass—to impress. Greek Yogurt has no fat, making it onto my list of favorite treats.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 3 oz', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'lemon zest - ½ tsp', 'blackberries - ½ cup', 'raspberries - ½ cup', 'mint leaves - 4 tsp', 'granola - ¼ cup', 'frozen papayas - ¼ cup 1" pieces']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine half of yogurt to honey and zest (with lemon juice) and chopped mint.
2. Make mixture by adding to bowl of fruit to coat.
3. In glass, spoon in a layer of fruit, then a layer of plain yogurt, followed by a layer of fruit and yogurt mixture.
4. Finish with granola and mint to garnish.

name: Tex-Mex Turkey Burgers
description: The fantasy isn't just how good and healthy these meals are for your body; it's how your body will look after you start eating this way!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'salsa - 2 tbsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'egg - 1 whole', 'onions -  slice, large (1/4" thick)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix ingredients together and shape into patties.
2. Panfry or grill.
3. Bun is optional, if you must have the bread try Ezekiel buns. If you brown the turkey in a pan, you can serve as a taco with corn OR Ezekiel tortilla for another great option.

name: Roasted Almond Bark
description: Add some protein to your chocolate with this easily customizable recipe for almond bar that's FitMenCook approved.
recipeIngredient: ['almonds - 4 oz', 'dark chocolate - 6 oz', 'dried cranberries - ¼ cup', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'sea salt - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place almonds on cookie sheet sprayed with olive oil. Roast in oven for 20 minutes at 350 degrees F.
2. Let almonds cool, and crush them.
3. Melt dark chocolate in microwave at 45-second intervals until smooth.
4. Add crushed almonds to melted chocolate.
5. Spread mixture on parchment paper placed on a baking sheet.
6. Top with cranberries, sea salt, and red pepper to taste.
7. Put tray in freezer for 45 minutes.
8. Break apart into bark pieces, and eat!

name: Dark Chocolate and Oat Protein Truffles
description: Protein chocolates are fantastic because they're high in antioxidants, rich in fiber, and completely sugar-free. Also, did I mention they're delicious? Giving your loved one homemade protein chocolates in a homemade box is a great way to show him or her how much you care! I guarantee you'll be well rewarded for your hard work (wink)!
recipeIngredient: ['chopped dates - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'water - ¼ cup', 'raw oats - ⅛ cup', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'chocolate squares - 3 oz square bakers']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together mulberries, protein powder, water, oats, and coconut flour and roll into 8 balls.
2. Dip each ball into melted chocolate until completely covered.
3. Top each truffle with cocoa or coconut and put them in the freezer for 30 minutes.
4. When the chocolate hardens, you're done!

name: A Protein Milkshake
description: For those of you who are bulking and require significant amounts of calories and aren't as worried about fat content, this recipe is perfect.
recipeIngredient: ['whey protein powder isolate - 1 scoop', 'milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'vanilla ice cream - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Protein Peanut Butter Ball
description: Instead of resorting to unhealthy items, why not try and find something that you can substitute your shake with... Here are a few recipes using protein powder that are easy to make.
recipeIngredient: ['natural peanut butter - ¾ cup', 'honey - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'raw oats - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and form into small 1" balls
2. Place in the fridge for a few hours and then enjoy.

name: Protein Powder Parfait
description: Instead of resorting to unhealthy items, why not try and find something that you can substitute your shake with... Here are a few recipes using protein powder that are easy to make.
recipeIngredient: ['mixed berries - 2 cup', 'whey protein powder isolate - 1 scoop', 'yogurt, fat-free - 2 cup (8 fl oz)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix protein powder in with yogurt or pudding.
2. Layer fruit and pudding/yogurt in a tall parfait glass.
3. Top with chocolate shavings or a dab of fat free cool whip.

name: Chocolate Protein-Filled Dark Chocolate Cups
description: If you're looking for the perfect Valentine's Day gift to surprise your fit sweetie, here it is. Make your own protein chocolates and display them in a box of your own design! Awww.
recipeIngredient: ['hemp protein - ⅛ cup', 'chocolate squares - 4 oz square bakers', 'Animal chocolate whey - ⅛ scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'hemp seeds - 1 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'milk (2% fat) - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Melt two squares of chocolate.
2. Once melted, divide the chocolate into 4 paper cupcake-tin liners. Use the chocolate to coat bottom and walls of the liners.
3. Put liners in freezer for 20 minutes.
4. For filling, mix together protein powders, cocoa powder, hemp seeds, coconut flour, and milk.
5. Remove liners from freezer and fill them with protein filling.
6. Melt the other two squares of chocolate and pour the melted chocolate on top of the filling.
7. Put chocolates back into freezer for 20 minutes.

name: Peach Cinnamon Protein Shake
description: Pour the flavors of fall into a jar with this delicious combination of cinnamon and peach. With a profile that's similar to that of a dessert-style crisp, it's no wonder that this sweet duo ranks among the favorite shakes of Myprotein athlete Chris Lavado. "This recipe is a welcome break from the classic chocolate, vanilla, and strawberry flavors. Plus, the combination of protein-rich yogurt and micronutrient-rich spinach, coupled with the fast-acting carbs from fruit and cereal, provides that great pre-gym morning energy."
recipeIngredient: ['Myprotein impact whey protein - 2 scoop', 'milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'peach, sliced - ½ medium (2-2/3" dia)', '2% greek yogurt, plain - 1 cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'whole wheat cereal - ¾ cup', 'creatine powder - 1 scoop', 'ice - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Tomato Basil Omelet
description: IFBB Bikini pro Nicole Moneer eats clean all year so she never has to diet hard before a show. Try this easy, delicious, and nutritious meal!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 3 whole', 'cherry tomatoes - 10', 'fresh basil leaves - ⅛ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'kelp - ¼ tbsp (1/8 cup)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Coat skillet in palm oil.
2. In a mixing bowl, whisk 3 whole eggs with salt, pepper, basil, and kelp.
3. Slice 10 cherry tomatoes.
4. Add everything to a skillet.
5. Cook on medium heat to desired doneness.
6. Note: Sometimes I add onions and organic, antibiotic- and hormone-free pork sausage. If you add the sausage, brown it in a separate pan before adding it to the omelet.

name: Fried Avocado Tacos
description: Can you think of anything more mouthwatering than the words "fried avocado tacos?" Neither can we, which is why this is one recipe you don't want to miss.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 2', 'egg whites - 2', 'whole-wheat flour - ¼ cup', 'whole-wheat panko bread crumbs - ⅔ cup', '2% greek yogurt, plain - ⅔ cup', 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce - 2 oz', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'whole-wheat tortilla (10-inch) - 4 whole', 'pico de gallo - 4 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Remove the pits from the avocados. Slice each avocado into even wedges, about four slices per each half for a total of eight slices per avocado.
3. Pour flour onto a plate or shallow dish. Pour panko bread crumbs on a separate plate or shallow dish. Whisk the egg white slightly in another bowl.
4. Dip the avocado slices in the flour, then the egg white, then the panko, before placing them on a baking tray lined with parchment paper (or use a baking rack for more even-sided baking). Lightly spray avocado fries with olive oil before baking to help crust brown and get crispy.
5. Bake for 20 minutes until golden brown. Check them halfway through baking and flip, if needed, to get an even golden brown and crispy result. Remove fries when done and season immediately with sea salt and pepper.
6. Place Greek yogurt, chipotle peppers, lime juice, and cilantro in a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside in the fridge.
7. For a thinner sauce, add a tablespoon or two of water while blending.
8. To assemble the tacos, place a whole-wheat tortilla in a taco stand and layer shredded purple cabbage, a dollop of chipotle sauce, 3-4 baked avocado fries, pico de gallo, and cilantro to taste.

name: Pork, Pear, And Greens
description: IFBB Bikini pro Nicole Moneer eats clean all year so she never has to diet hard before a show. Try this easy, delicious, and nutritious meal!
recipeIngredient: ['ground pork, antibiotic- and hormone-free - 6 oz', 'kale - 1 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'pear, sliced - 1', 'pumpkin seed oil - 1 tsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tsp', 'Himalayan rock salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Tear up kale in a big bowl. Skin and chop pear.
2. Mix kale with oil and vinegar in a big bowl and shake.
3. Let sit for an hour or more. The kale won't get soggy, I promise!
4. Brown pork in a skillet, about 10-12 minutes.
5. Top kale with fresh pork.

name: PB and J Smoothie
description: When it comes to classic combos, nothing tops the list quite like a PB&J—just ask Myprotein athlete Owen Harrison. Take that childhood favorite to the next level and ditch the Wonder Bread with this drinkable version. The combination of healthy fats and complex carbs in the form of oats will leave you feeling satisfied and satiated for the day ahead. The best part? No crust!
recipeIngredient: ['natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'plain instant oats - ¼ cup', 'nonfat milk - 8 fl oz', 'Greens Freak - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Fruit Funk Smoothie
description: Bypass the tap and add some flair to your shake with coconut water. This favorite of fitness athlete Lewis Harrison is not only more flavourful than an H2O-based shake, but is also richer in potassium—an electrolyte that helps to maintain fluid balance in the body and is key to the rehydration process. Coconut water contains 470 milligrams of potassium per 8 ounces, or more than an average-sized banana. This makes it the perfect finish to that hardcore sweat session.
recipeIngredient: ['Myprotein impact whey protein - 2 scoop', 'frozen mixed berries - 1 cup', 'coconut water, unsweetened - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Banana Nut Shake
description: In a rush and looking for something quick to fuel your day? This morning shake might be just what the doctor ordered. "It's a great all-around shake that includes a good balance of proteins and fats," says fitness model Kirk Miller.
recipeIngredient: ['my protein impact whey vanilla - 1½ scoop', 'banana - 1 large (8" to 8-7/8" long)', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'water - 16 fl oz']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Chocolate Banana Smoothie
description: "I usually like to drink this in the morning within 30-60 minutes of working out," Myprotein athlete Charissa Littlejohn says of her chocolate-banana drink. "The protein is great for recovery, the oats digest slowly so you receive a steady release of sugar into the bloodstream, and the banana is a fast-acting carb that replenishes glycogen and helps your body recover faster." Add a dollop of nut butter for that extra creaminess and a serving of healthy fats!
recipeIngredient: ['Myprotein impact whey protein - 1 scoop', 'almond milk - 1 cup', 'ice - 1 cup', 'almonds - 1 tbsp', 'banana - ½ medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'raw oats - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: High-Protein, High-Fiber, Low-Fat Egg White Pancakes
description: Bored of your current menu? Check out these great bodybuilding recipes! Taste tested and bodybuilder approved.
recipeIngredient: ['cornmeal, whole-grain, yellow - ½ cup', 'whole-wheat flour - ½ cup', 'all-purpose flour - ½ cup', 'skim milk - 1½ cup', 'egg whites - 3', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together the cornmeal, whole-wheat flour and white flour. Blend in the skim milk and allow the batter to stand for 5 minutes.
2. Whip the egg whites until they stand in peaks. Then fold them into the batter.
3. Spoon the batter onto a preheated non-stick skillet and cook until bubbles form on the pancake or the edges turn brown, then flip the pancake over and cook for 1 minute more.
4. Top each with a dollop of non-fat plain yogurt.

name: Watermelon Cooler
description: This simple, refreshing shake is a favorite of nutritionist and trainer Abby Pell. "It's a perfect hit of pure protein and simple, natural sugar," she says. "It's ideal for quenching your thirst after a hot summer workout."
recipeIngredient: ['Myprotein impact whey protein - 1 scoop', 'ice - ½ cup', 'watermelon - ¼ melon (15" long x 7-1/2" dia)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Orange And Vanilla Protein Cupcakes
description: You know what's great? A protein muffin. Know what's even better? A protein cupcake! The proof is in the frosting. Learn how to make it here.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin puree - ½ cup', 'egg whites - 1 cup', 'quinoa flakes - ½ cup', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'baking powder - 2 tsp', 'orange zest - 2 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'casein protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'casein protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'skim milk - 5 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for cupcakes: Preheat oven to 360 degrees F (180 C).
2. Blend all of the above ingredients together.
3. Pour batter into six muffin cups.
4. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
5. Once done, remove cupcakes from oven and allow to cool.
6. Directions for frosting: In a bowl, stir together protein powder and yogurt.
7. Stir in one tablespoon of milk at a time until you get a frosting-like mixture. It should be creamy and not overly runny. Feel free to add more casein if you want thicker frosting, or more yogurt if you want it creamier.
8. When casein mixture is ready, use it to frost your cooled muffins! You can use a knife, or put the frosting in a Ziploc bag, cut off a corner, and squeeze the frosting onto your cupcakes. If you have a piping nozzle, you can use that as well!
9. Note: If you want to use whey instead of casein, use 1/4 cup of whey and ditch the milk—you won't need it. Once frosted, store the cupcakes in the fridge. You'll notice as the casein cools, it hardens and creates a creamy shell of deliciousness!

name: Banoffee Breakfast Bang
description: Ditch the morning Starbucks run and the lure of a Frappuccino, and indulge in this caffeinated protein drink instead. It's a favorite of bodybuilder and all-around king of aesthetics Simeon Panda. The combination of complex and quick-digesting carbs, as well as the caffeine jolt, make it a perfect pre-workout meal.
recipeIngredient: ['Myprotein impact whey protein - 1 scoop', 'banana, frozen - 1 medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'plain instant oats - ¼ cup', 'instant coffee - 1 tsp', 'milk (2% fat) - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Peppermint Bark
description: Those candy canes you've got hanging on the tree are for more than just decoration. Put them to good use with this protein-packed take on peppermint bark! The sweet, minty combination of this seasonal dessert is sure to be a hit.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'peppermint extract - ⅛ tsp', 'water - 1 tbsp', 'candy cane - 1 piece', 'cake sprinkles - ⅛ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
2. Place a layer of plastic wrap over a plate.
3. Pour the mixture onto the plastic wrap in an even later (it doesn't have to be perfect).
4. Top with 1/4 of a smashed candy cane (use a hammer) and 1/8 tsp of red and green edible sprinkles.
5. Place in the freezer for 30-60 minutes or until hard.
6. Break bark into pieces and serve immediately. Store leftovers in the freezer.

name: Sesame Tahini Shrimp And Zucchini Linguine Pasta Salad
description: One of my mottos: "No boring food. Ever." That's especially true for salads. Spruce up that lowly bed of lettuce with good-for-you protein and fresh, raw veggies. In the right amount they can be satisfying, filling, and supply your body with the needed vitamins, antioxidants, and enzymes to aid in digestion, heart function, and overall health.
recipeIngredient: ['shrimp - 6 oz', 'zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'red bell pepper - 1½ cup, sliced', 'tahini paste - 1 tbsp', 'sesame seeds - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut zucchini using a Julienne shredder in order to make the raw linguine.
2. Slice veggies for pasta.
3. In a bowl, mix tahini, sesame oil and Bragg's Liquid Aminos.
4. Place all ingredients into a large bowl, including cooked shrimp. Pour the Tahini sauce you made over the meal. Toss it to make sure all sides are covered in the sauce.
5. Sprinkle sesame seeds on top. And then devour!

name: Confetti Chocolate Chunk Protein Blondies
description: One quick glance at these confetti chocolate-chunk protein blondies will have you salivating. The good news is that they taste even better than they look! Using the natural sweetener Stevia allowed me to match that great cheat-meal taste at only a fraction of the macros. Healthy snacking can be fun too!
recipeIngredient: ['all-purpose flour - 1 cup', 'MusclePharm Combat Powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'powdered Stevia - ⅓ cup', 'cinnamon - ¾ tbsp', 'baking powder - ¼ tsp', 'table salt - ⅛ tsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'agave syrup - 3 tbsp', 'dark chocolate chips - ⅓ cup', 'cake sprinkles - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 F. In a large bowl, mix whole-wheat flour, protein powder, Stevia, cinnamon, baking powder, and salt.
2. In another large bowl, add egg, almond milk, Greek yogurt, and agave syrup.
3. Microwave coconut oil in a separate small bowl. Let coconut oil cool slightly, then add to wet ingredients. Whisk together all wet ingredients.
4. Add half of the dry ingredients to the wet. Gently fold together.
5. Add remaining dry ingredients, and gently mix again until combined. Be careful not to overmix.
6. Add chocolate chunks and sprinkles to batter. Fold in chocolate chunks and sprinkles. Pour batter into a 6x8 baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray or greased with coconut oil.
7. Bake for about 24 minutes or until a knife comes out clean. Let cool and slice into 8 blondie bars.

name: Mustard Roasted Chicken
description: Bored of your current menu? Check out these great bodybuilding recipes! Taste tested and bodybuilder approved.
recipeIngredient: ['dijon mustard - 4 oz', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 tbsp', 'chicken breast - 4 lb', 'paprika - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 425°F.
2. Combine mustard and parsley in a bowl.
3. Arrange chicken breasts, skin-side up, in a shallow baking pan.
4. Brush with mustard mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
5. Bake 30 minutes, or until cooked throughout.

name: Turkey Meatloaf With Spinach And Whole Wheat Pearl
description: Time to dust off your muffin pan! Steer clear of sugary carbs and use your baking tray for good with this easy meal you'll prep in virtually no time at all. Add your own swag and flavor with optional seasonings like olive tapenade and fruit.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 5 oz', 'red onion, diced - ¾ cup', 'marinara sauce - ⅓ cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'parsley, dried - 1 tsp', 'basil, dried - 1 tsp, ground', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'coriander - 1 dash', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'couscous, whole-grain - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 405°F.
2. Season ground turkey with your choice of seasonings. Add in your choice of diced veggies.
3. Lightly spray your muffin pan with coconut oil. Place the ground turkey inside of the muffin holders. Depending on how big your muffin pan is and your singular serving, you may have to use 2 muffin holders for each serving.
4. Top each serving with 1 tbsp marinara sauce.
5. Bake in the oven for about 8-10 minutes. If you use less lean ground turkey, you can consider increasing the cooking time to 10-12 minutes.
6. Boil couscous using water and low sodium chicken or vegetable broth. Add cilantro or onions while cooking for added flavor. Set aside, and allow to cool. Add 1 tbsp olive tapenade to couscous if desired.

name: Strawberry Cheesecake Protein Shake
description: This shake takes Dairy Queen's Strawberry CheeseQuake Blizzard as its flavor inspiration, but strips away the sugar and calories. Quest Nutrition's Strawberry Cheesecake Quest Bar gives you that crucial crust texture, along with GG Bran Sprinkles, which are a flaked form of GG Bran crispbread. Both are low in net carbs and diabetic-friendly.
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries, frozen - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 1¼ cup', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'Quest Nutrition Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Bar - ½ bar', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Strawberry Banana - 1 scoop', 'fiber scandinavian sprinkle - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all of the ingredients except the Quest bar in a blender, Magic Bullet, or other mixer.
2. Pour this mixture into your ice cream machine for 10-15 minutes.
3. While you are waiting, cut 1/3 of a Strawberry Cheesecake Quest Bar into small pieces using scissors.
4. Once the soft serve is ready, serve in a cup and add your Quest Bar pieces to the top.

name: Stuffed Muscle Eggs With Pita Bread
description: Don't be fooled by the looks of this meal. Between the eggs, yogurt, and fish, it packs quite a protein punch. Eat it for breakfast or lunch, and I guarantee you'll feel energized to attack your daily workouts.
recipeIngredient: ['canned salmon - 1 can drained solids (total)', 'hard-boiled egg - 2', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'lettuce - 1 leaf', 'cherry tomatoes - 5', 'Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - ½ pita, small  (4" dia)', 'goat cheese - 1 tbsp', 'mustard - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Boil 2 eggs. Peel them and slice them in half. Remove the yolk from 1 egg (or both eggs) and add to a bowl.
2. Add 1/2 can wild salmon to the bowl along with 1 tbsp Greek yogurt, onions, and your other choice of seasonings.
3. Mix the ingredients together; then stuff the eggs. Or, add egg whites to the mixture to create a salmon salad.
4. Eat the meal with pita bread or stuff the pita with the salad, lettuce, and tomatoes.

name: Spicy Flank Steak Kabobs With Sweet Potato
description: If I could only prep 3 meals per week, they'd definitely be breakfast, lunch, and my post-workout meal. The last thing you want after an amazing training session is to be unprepared. Use this post-workout meal—full of vitamins B, E, iron, and antioxidants—to refuel your body, replenish nutrients, and aid in muscle building and recovery.
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 5 oz', 'sweet potato - 1', 'zucchini, sliced - 1', 'green bell pepper - 1', 'blueberries - ⅛ cup', 'almonds, slivered - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 405°F.
2. Wrap the sweet potato in foil and place in the oven. If you cannot find a whole sweet potato close to your serving size, then simply cut the sweet potato into small pieces, measure them to ensure your serving size portion and bake them on a baking sheet lined with aluminum foil. Bake for about 45 minutes depending on the size. If they are cut in chunks, then bake for only 25-30 minutes.
3. Cut flank steak into very small pieces. Season with your choice of seasonings.
4. Chop 1 zucchini and 1 bell pepper into small pieces for the kabob.
5. Assemble the kabobs, alternating between beef, bell pepper, and zucchini.
6. Place the assembled kabob on a baking sheet/pan and bake for 8-12 minutes depending how well you like your meat cooked.
7. Note: when preparing this meal for the week, if you choose to add blueberries and almonds, keep those items separate and do not freeze.

name: Wild Game And Black Bean Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: You 'mirin?! Well, if not, you should. Wild game is a fantastic protein source that's generally much lower in fat than beef and is often a better source of iron, zinc, and omega-3 fatty acids. Not sure how to cook that gamey meat? Mix it with some black beans and a little salsa, stuff it in a bell pepper, and BOOM—certified muscle-building meal.
recipeIngredient: ['wild game meat - 6 oz', 'low-sodium black beans - ½ cup', 'red bell pepper - 2', 'salsa - 4 tbsp', 'goat cheese - 2 tbsp', 'parsley, dried - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 405°F.
2. Cut tops off bell peppers and remove the seeds inside.
3. Spray a baking sheet and place the bell peppers on the sheet with the open-side facing down. Bake for 10-12 minutes.
4. Lightly spray a skillet with coconut oil and place on medium heat. Add the diced onions.
5. Add ground wild game meat to the skillet. When the meat is nearly finished, add in beans, fresh parsley, 2 heaping tbsp of pico de gallo, salsa, or diced tomatoes. Mix with a spatula.
6. Remove the bell peppers from the oven and flip them over. Add in game and beans mixture. Top with goat cheese (or low fat mozzarella cheese) and fresh parsley (if desired).
7. Bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes.

name: Roman Fritz's Attach Dog Shake
description: Roman "Rex" Fritz is a German IFBB Pro. He's known for his precision, meticulous approach to bodybuilding, and attack-dog intensity in the gym.
recipeIngredient: ['animal chocolate whey - 2 scoop(s)', 'ground oats - 1 cup', 'liquid egg whites - 1 cup', 'water - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: BBQ Chicken Wrapped Asparagus
description: Hands down, this is one of my favorite meals. It's a super easy way to get your daily dose of veggies, and it's easily customizable so you can really make the meal your own. Go seasonal with your farmer's market faves or put a new spin on flavor by mixing in different spices.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast, thinly cut - 3 oz', 'asparagus spears - 12', 'low-sodium barbecue sauce - 2 tbsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'green bell pepper - 1 cup, sliced', 'brown rice - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 405°F.
2. Measure and cut chicken breasts into thin, 2-3 oz pieces. Feel free to further flatten the chicken with a mallet.
3. Season chicken cutlets with 1 tbsp barbecue sauce (for each piece) and your choice of seasonings.
4. Chop the ends off asparagus and wrap the chicken around 6 asparagus spears.
5. Place the chicken on a baking sheet with the open facing down.
6. Bake in the oven for about 8-10 minutes.

name: Anna Sward's Protein Waffles
description: I have a passion for weightlifting, nutrition, and great-tasting food. My specialty is cooking with protein powder. Ask me a question and I'll turn it into a delicious, protein-filled recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - ½ cup', 'whey protein powder isolate - ¼ cup', 'ground flaxseed - ¼ cup', 'oat flour - 3 tbsp', 'pea protein powder - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Get your waffle maker really hot and spray it with some nonstick spray.
2. Using a handheld blender, food processor, or standing blender, blend all of the above ingredients together to create a pancake-type batter.
3. Pour the waffle mix on the waffle maker and close it until the light goes off and the waffles are cooked.
4. Plate up! Top with your favorite nut butter, some fruit, maple syrup, or some Walden Farms calorie-free maple syrup!
5. Note: Try using the protein waffles as the bread for a sandwich or burger. Add a little sweet to those savory lunches? Yes, please!

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Cup Cookie Dough Shake
description: Just say the title of this shake three or four times out loud and try not to start jumping around like a little kid. My healthy chocolate treat is topped with Quest Cravings Protein Peanut Butter Cups and nuggets of Quest's Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bars. These gems raise this creamy treat to a whole new level of guilt-free decadence. The peanut butter cups taste just like candy, but because they're not made with sugar and are high in protein, you can have one without compromising your healthy lifestyle.
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, Triple Chocolate Brownie - ¾ scoop', 'Cellucor COR-Performance, Peanut Butter Marshmallow - ¼ scoop', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup', 'zucchini, sliced - ¼ cup', 'Quest Bar, chocolate peanut butter - ½ bar', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'Quest Nutrition Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Bar - ¼ bar']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend the protein, almond milk, and zucchini together in a blender, Magic Bullet, or other mixer. Ensure the zucchini is completely pureed.
2. Pour this mixture into your ice cream machine for 10-15 minutes.
3. While you are waiting, cut peanut butter cup and Quest bar into tiny pieces with scissors.
4. Serve in a cup and drizzle with 2 tbsp Walden Farms Sugar Free, Calorie Free Pancake Syrup (this is optional, but delicious) and add your Quest pieces.

name: Dorian Hamilton's Anabolic Nightcap Shake
description: Dorian "Heavy D" Hamilton is an up-and-coming bodybuilder from Canada. Despite various injuries, his passion and will to succeed keep him on the road to success.
recipeIngredient: ['Animal chocolate whey - 1 scoop(s)', 'avocado - 1 cup, pureed', 'coconut flakes - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Frank McGrath's Pre-Wrath Shake
description: Frank "Wrath" McGrath is an iconic pro bodybuilder and has long been an Animal athlete. After a car accident that nearly killed him in 2010, Frank has come back stronger than ever.
recipeIngredient: ['animal chocolate whey - 2 scoop(s)', 'banana - ½ medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'ice - ½ cup', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Jason Huh's Get Huge Skake
description: Jason "Huge" Huh is a pro bodybuilder who marches to the beat of his own drum. Defying convention and the mainstream, Jason is truly a unique figure in the sport.
recipeIngredient: ['Animal vanilla whey - 3 scoop(s)', 'Universal Glutamine - 2 tsp', 'Universal Creatine - 2 tsp', 'orange - 1 fruit (2-7/8" dia)', 'basmati rice - 1 cup', 'frozen mixed berries - 1 cup', 'apple juice - 1 cup', 'apples - 1 small (2-3/4" dia)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Sweet and Sour Slow Cooked Chicken
description: Sweet, sour, and spicy! This healthy take on sweet and sour chicken packs a serious flavor punch without sabotaging your gains.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast, cut into 1-inch pieces - 1½ lb', 'arrowroot starch - 3 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1½ tbsp', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 whole', 'orange zest - ½ tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, pureed - 2 tsp', 'liquid aminos - ¼ cup', 'honey - 3 tbsp', 'sriracha - 2 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'sesame seed oil - 2 tsp', 'water - ¼ cup', 'arrowroot starch - 1½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add ingredients for chicken in a large bowl. Mix everything together, ensuring the chicken pieces are coated, then set aside.
2. Mix all ingredients for sauce together except the water and arrowroot powder, and set aside.
3. Set a large nonstick skillet on medium heat and add olive oil. Once the oil is hot, add the chicken pieces and cook until the outsides are seared golden brown, about 6 minutes. The chicken does NOT have to be cooked all the way through at this point since it will finish cooking in the slow cooker.
4. Add the chicken pieces to the slow cooker and pour in the sauce. Add the 1/4 cup of water if needed to cover chicken. You can also add additional orange juice or liquid aminos.
5. Cook on high for no more than 2 hours, or on low for 2-3 hours.
6. About 30 minutes before the end of the cooking cycle, remove lid and stir the ingredients. Add arrowroot powder for thickener and additional liquid if needed. Stir everything together again and replace lid, allowing the sauce to thicken as chicken finishes cooking.
7. Serve the chicken with your choice of rice or vegetables. Garnish with sesame seeds (add per serving since these add calories) and green onion and enjoy!

name: Protein Pumpkin Loaf
description:
Protein is important for building a great physique. Heck, this macronutrient is so important that it can be boosted with protein powder in your baked goods! This pumpkin loaf is perfect for the holiday season and won't bankrupt your calorie count.

If you need an egg-free option, replace the eggs with 1 banana and 1/3-1/2 cup of water or rice milk. You can also add in an additional tablespoon of coconut oil. Always start with less milk or oil; it's easier to add more of the wet ingredients than it is to subtract them.
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice flour - 1 cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'sea salt - ¼ tsp', 'egg - 3 whole', 'powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'pumpkin puree - 8 oz', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
2. Whisk eggs and Stevia together.
3. Add pumpkin pie mix to wet ingredients, mix.
4. Add dry ingredients and blend mixtures together.
5. Add coconut oil last.
6. Place in a baking pan and bake for 22-24 minutes.

name: The Perfect Healthy Stir-Fry!
description: It's time to add some diesel to the standard stir-fry. Combine a delicious pile of protein, veggies, and carbs in this easy-to-make recipe, and give your gains some serious fuel!
recipeIngredient: ['liquid aminos - 3 tbsp', 'ginger, pureed - ½ tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 whole', 'arrowroot starch - 1½ tbsp', 'chicken breast, cut into cubes - 1½ piece', 'edamame - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'stalk celery - ⅓ cup', 'mushrooms, crimini - ½ cup sliced', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'green onion, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'garlic, minced - ⅓ tbsp', 'extra virgin olive oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all of the sauce ingredients in a small bowl. Ensure all of the white clumps from the starch have been removed.
2. Set a nonstick skillet or wok on medium-high heat, and add 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add the raw, chopped chicken breasts, and cook for about 5-6 minutes, until the chicken is about 80 percent cooked. (There should be no visible pink pieces.) Set the chicken aside in a bowl so you can cook the veggies.
3. Set the same nonstick skillet or large wok on medium-high heat and add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add the garlic and chopped green onions, and begin to sauté for about 2 minutes. The green onions should be brown.
4. Add the raw veggies to the skillet and begin to sear them. You want some "crunch" in the veggies when you eat the stir-fry, so be careful not to overcook them.
5. Cook the veggies for about 7-8 minutes, then add the chicken back to the stir-fry and mix everything together.
6. Reduce the heat to medium, and move the chicken & veggie mixture to one side of the skillet to create room for the sauce.
7. Pour the sauce into the empty side of the skillet and allow the sauce to simmer. Once it begins to simmer, quickly mix everything together. Instant restaurant-style stir-fry!
8. Divide into your meal-prep containers with your choice of complex carbohydrate.
9. Tip: The arrowroot starch acts as a thickening agent when heated, so make sure to let the sauce heat up and begin to simmer before mixing.

name: Banana Protein Fluff
description: Protein fluff: Once you try it, you can't stop making it. Your taste buds will like it as much as your muscles will!
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 1', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'unsweetened coconut milk - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a bowl and blend until smooth, frozen mixture has been created.
2. Using an electric whisk, whisk mix for 5-8 minutes until it gains volume.
3. Top with walnuts and grated coconut.
4. Eat immediately.

name: No-Bake Chocolate Chia Peanut Butter Balls
description: I know I am not the only one who gets the occasional craving for that amazing combo of chocolate and peanut butter. These little gems are guilt-free, rich, and satisfying!
recipeIngredient: ['powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 tbsp', 'oat flour - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
2. Form mixture into small, golf-ball sized balls.
3. Put balls on a plate, cover, and put in the fridge.

name: Blueberry Protein Fluff
description: Protein fluff: Once you try it, you can't stop making it. Your taste buds will like it as much as your muscles will!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'milk (2% fat) - ¼ cup', 'frozen blueberries - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a bowl and blend until smooth, frozen mixture has been created.
2. Using an electric whisk, whisk mix for 5-8 minutes until it gains volume.
3. Eat immediately.
4. Note: You can also use banana or strawberry whey protein powder in place of vanilla.

name: Sun-Dried Tomato And Chicken Meatballs With Spaghetti Squash
description: This recipe is phenomenal! It's clean, rich, and delicious. Make the meatballs from quality chicken and you can't fail. The squash can be a bit of a challenge if you've never dealt with this particular gourd, but even new cooks can quickly get the hang of it.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken - 1½ lb', 'sun-dried tomatoes - 3 oz', 'sea salt - 1 tbsp', 'oregano - 2 tbsp, ground', 'basil, dried - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'spaghetti squash - 1 whole', 'sea salt - 1 pinch', 'chives - 1 tsp chopped', 'basil, dried - 1 tsp, leaves', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Meatball directions: In a bowl mix chicken, tomatoes, salt, oregano, and basil.
2. Add paper baking cups to a 12-cup muffin tin.
3. Roll mixture into meatballs with your hands and place into baking cups.
4. Bake at 350 F for 23-25 minutes.
5. Spaghetti squash directions: Microwave for about a minute at 50 percent power.
6. Cut the squash lengthwise down the middle.
7. You can remove the seeds prior to baking or after.
8. Place both halves of squash face down in a casserole dish with about an inch of water and cover with foil.
9. Bake at 375 F for about 40 minutes.
10. Remove from oven and flip halves face-up.
11. Bake another 5 minutes with foil on, then remove from oven and let cool for about 5-8 minutes.
12. Remove any remaining seeds, then brush a fork over the squash to make thin strands that look like spaghetti. Add sea salt to taste, chives, basil, and 1-2 tbsp of coconut oil.
13. Use the squash as a bed for your meatballs and serve!

name: Venison Chili
description: Wild game is different. It doesn't taste like regular beef or chicken. But that's part of the fun. If you have a picky eater, or one who's NOT interested in eating wild boar, have them help you prepare the meal. Here's a venison chili recipe for any occasion.
recipeIngredient: ['ground venison - 16 oz', 'dark kidney beans - 8 oz', 'low-sodium black beans - 4 oz', 'onions - 1 small', 'tomato sauce, canned - 15 oz', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'table salt - 1 dash', 'cumin seed - 1 tsp, whole', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'safflower oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Soak and cook beans according to package directions.
2. Coat pan lightly with safflower oil and slightly brown venison.
3. Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
4. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, longer if you want thicker chili.
5. For faster cooking time, use only 1/2 can of tomato sauce.

name: Almond-Crusted Walleye Pike And Asparagus
description: I love using palm oil when cooking white fish. It makes the fish a little crispy and adds great flavor. The walleye pike is among the leanest freshwater fish you can get. A lot of white fish—sea bass and cod, for example—go well with almond meal, so mix up your protein sources!
recipeIngredient: ['walleye pike fillet - 2 fillet', 'asparagus - 1 lb', 'almond meal - ½ cup', 'palm oil - 2 tbsp', 'almond oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for fish: Preheat a skillet on medium heat.
2. Coat skillet with 1-2 tbsp of palm oil.
3. In a pie dish, add almond meal, sea salt, and pepper to your liking.
4. Coat fish with almond meal breading.
5. Pre-heat skillet; add in fillets.
6. Cook 3-4 minutes on each side.
7. Directions for asparagus: Preheat a second skillet.
8. Coat with 1-2 tbsp almond oil.
9. Add asparagus to skillet.
10. Season with sea salt and pepper.
11. Cover and cook over medium heat until sizzling, then reduce heat to low until asparagus is tender, not mushy. This takes approximately 12-20 minutes.
12. Squeeze lemon juice over both fish and asparagus when done.

name: Chocolate and Peanut Butter Shake
description: Check out this great protein smoothie recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['water - 12 fl oz', 'chocolate protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tbsp', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'heavy whipping cream - 2 tbsp', 'ice - 10 cubes']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Roasted Turkey With Sweet Potato Puree
description: When I prepare a bird, I want it to be super tender and juicy. They say you should roast a turkey 10-12 minutes for every pound, but that wasn't long enough in my case, so be sure to check your turkey with an internal thermometer. The sweet potato puree also stands alone as a great post-workout meal!
recipeIngredient: ['turkey breast, boneless and skinless - 4 lb', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ cup', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 3 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'sweet potato puree - 1 can (404 x 307)', 'unsweetened applesauce - ⅓ cup', 'cinnamon - 1¼ tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tbsp', 'ground cloves - ¼ tsp', 'raisins, seedless - ½ cup (not packed)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for roasted turkey: 
Combine marinade ingredients in a bowl; whisk together.
2. Roll and rub turkey breast in vinaigrette.
3. Place in a Ziploc bag; pour in remaining marinade.
4. Let turkey marinade in a refrigerator for a few hours.
5. Preheat oven to 350 F.
6. Bake turkey for 1 hour, then reduce the temperature to 275 F and bake 2 more hours, or until it reaches proper internal temperature (160 F).
7. Directions for sweet potato puree: 
Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir well.
8. Place in refrigerator to chill for 3-4 hours.

name: Valentine's Day Truffles
description: Valentine's Day means two things: cuddles and calories. Trade in the latter for guilt-free protein truffles. Grow your love, and your gains, with this recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'coconut flour - 2 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - ⅛ cup', 'unsweetened coconut milk - ¼ cup', 'rum extract - ½ tsp', 'dark chocolate - 4 square']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all of the filling ingredients in a big bowl. Pay attention to the flavor of the batter and tweak to fit your loved one's tastes. If they like Nutella, for example, use hazelnut butter and a really chocolatey whey protein powder, like Cellucor. If your partner is the first to dive into a Reese's cup, add peanut butter to the batter. You can even throw in a handful of almonds!
2. Once you achieve the right texture, shape the batter into eight balls and set them aside. Remember that if your batter is too sticky to shape, you should add a bit more cocoa powder. If it's too dry or crumbly, add a bit more milk.
3. Melt your dark chocolate by sticking it in the microwave or, if you're feeling fancy, melt it in a bain marie, which is just a glass bowl on top of a pot of boiling water.
4. When your dark chocolate has melted, dunk the balls in them and transfer them to a plate or chopping board that's covered in foil or baking paper. This will help prevent the balls from sticking when you unmold them.
5. Finally, top your truffles with melted white chocolate (optional, but awesome), chopped nuts, chocolate flakes, or coconut flakes!

name: Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Balls
description: Cake balls and cookie dough tubes are a teenage slumber party staple, but that doesn't mean they belong in a healthy meal plan. If you train hard, then you need to rise above your high-school-diet standards and fuel your body the right way. These cookie-dough flavored protein balls are the perfect muscle-building treat!
recipeIngredient: ['BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - 1 scoop', 'coconut flour - 2 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'semisweet chocolate chips - 2 tbsp', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'quinoa flour - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix ingredients together in a medium bowl until well blended.
2. Roll into small balls.
3. Place in the freezer and allow to freeze completely.
4. Thaw for 15 minutes before eating.

name: Peanut Butter Cookie Balls
description: Keep your peanut butter cup cravings at bay with some chocolate peanut butter cookie balls! Quick and easy, throw these in the freezer and enjoy them on a hot day or after a tough workout. The combination of protein and carbs are perfect to refuel. Twenty-five grams of protein per serving is just what your muscles need to start repairing!
recipeIngredient: ['BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - 1 scoop', 'oat flour - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'semisweet chocolate chips - ¼ cup chips (6 oz package)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix ingredients together in a medium bowl until blended.
2. Roll into small balls.
3. Place in the freezer and allow to freeze completely.
4. Thaw for 15 minutes before eating.

name: Turkey Jalapeno Poppers
description: Jalapeno poppers are central to every football-themed spread. Take this all-star, easy-to-follow dish to the next level by wrapping these spicy pepper bites in protein-rich turkey bacon. The addition of Greek yogurt and absence of fried, breaded coating make this a treat that's sure to bring the festivities to life for your taste buds. There's no faster way to get the party started!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - ½ lb', 'jalapeno peppers, halved - 9', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 9 strip', 'garlic, minced - 1 oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¾ cup', 'goat cheese - ⅓ cup', 'oregano - ½ tbsp, ground', 'dill - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
