description: Pancakes are a favored breakfast for many, but unfortunately they also usually contain far too many calories and fat. Here is a lighter recipe that will fit much better with your overall meal plan.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 3 large', 'raw oats - ⅓ cup', 'banana or vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'Splenda - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the egg whites, cottage cheese and vanilla extract in a bowl until well mixed.
2. Next add in the dry oats and whey protein powder along with the Splenda until well mixed.
3. Once a batter has been formed, cook as you would a regular pancake, flipping at half-time.
4. Drizzle with sugar free syrup or serve with fresh fruit.

name: Protein Pumpkin Parfait
description: Add some flair to your dessert, or your breakfast, with this ridiculously good, muscle-building pumpkin parfait!
recipeIngredient: ['Labrada ISO Whey - 1 scoop', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'pumpkin, canned - ½ cup', 'granola - ½ cup', 'allspice, ground - ½ tbsp', 'cinnamon -  to taste', 'organic honey - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, combine protein, Greek yogurt, pumpkin, vanilla extract, and spices. Mix together with a spoon until the consistency is smooth.
2. Once mixed, simply top with your favorite store-bought or homemade granola. You can also add your choice of nuts or seeds. I recommend almonds or walnuts.

name: Lemon-Lime Margarita
description: Missing your Monday margarita? Now you can make it without having to feel guilty! This recipe is fun to drink, super easy to make, and tastes great. It's the perfect fix for any nutrition-conscious margarita connoisseur.
recipeIngredient: ['Cellucor Alpha Amino - 1 scoop', 'water - 6 fl oz', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Tzatziki Sauce
description: This classic Greek sauce is already pretty healthy, but it can be hard to find at some stores. But why buy what you can easily make at home? You won't run out of uses for it! Tzatziki is delicious in wraps and fish tacos, spread over turkey burgers, or used as a dip for chicken skewers, fresh vegetables, and pita chips.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'cucumber, chopped - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'dill - 1½ tsp', 'Kosher salt - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Strain off excess liquid from yogurt, and add to a medium mixing bowl.
2. Peel one medium cucumber and scoop out seeds. Grate cucumber using a box grater and squeeze out excess liquid in a paper towel.
3. Add cucumber, minced garlic, and remaining ingredients to yogurt, stirring until smooth.
4. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Cinnamon Swirl Protein Cupcakes
description: Make sure your cheat is still a muscle-building treat with this sweet, protein-rich recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'rolled oats - 1½ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'Splenda - 1½ tbsp', 'vanilla, nonfat greek yogurt - 1 container (5.3 oz)', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - 2½ tsp', 'baking powder - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend rolled oats into oat flour.
2. Combine all ingredients into a bowl and mix.
3. Place silicone cups on a baking sheet and coat them with nonstick cooking spray.
4. Evenly distribute mix into the cups, filling them only about 3/4 of the way.
5. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-15 minutes.
6. Allow the cupcakes to cool, then top with fat-free vanilla Greek yogurt.

name: Pesto Sauce
description: I love traditional Italian pesto! Unfortunately, a two-tablespoon serving packs 100-160 calories—not the best bang for your dietary buck. This lighter version has less than 50 calories for the same amount, plus it has all that authentic flavor we love. Try it spread over salmon or chicken, mixed with pasta, or used as a dip with crisp breads!
recipeIngredient: ['fresh basil leaves, chopped - 2 cup', 'water - ½ cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'pine nuts - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'Kosher salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Toast pine nuts in a nonstick skillet over medium heat until golden.
2. Add toasted pine nuts and all other ingredients to a blender or food processer.
3. Blend or process until smooth.
4. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Sweet and Sour Sauce
description: This Asian-inspired sauce is perfect for dipping spring rolls and pot stickers, and it makes a delectable glaze for chicken and shrimp! Did I mention it tastes even better than the bottled stuff for less than half the calories? Mmm hmm.
recipeIngredient: ['orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 cup', 'rice vinegar - ¼ cup', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 1½ tbsp', 'low-sugar ketchup - 2 tbsp', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'cornstarch - 1 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine orange juice, vinegar, brown sugar, and ketchup in a small saucepan.
2. Simmer over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
3. Combine water and cornstarch to make a slurry, then add to saucepan.
4. Reduce heat to medium-low, and stir until thickened.
5. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Mustard-Crusted Pork Tenderloin
description: This pork tenderloin is full of flavor, not calories. It's guaranteed to make your mouth water and your hungry muscles happy!
recipeIngredient: ['pork tenderloin - 1½ lb', 'balsamic vinegar - ½ cup', 'brown mustard - ¼ cup', 'garlic, minced - ¼ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ¼ cup', 'black pepper - 2 tbsp, ground', 'thyme - 2 tbsp, ground', 'rosemary - 2 tbsp', 'dill - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place pork tenderloin in a large bowl or dish and cover with balsamic vinegar. Roll the tenderloin over several times to ensure it is well covered, then set aside.
2. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.
3. In a separate bowl, mix mustard, garlic, dried onion, pepper, thyme, rosemary and dill. It will form a thick paste.
4. Line a baking sheet with nonstick aluminum foil. Place the tenderloin on it and pour any remaining balsamic vinegar on top of it.
5. Use your hands to press the mustard mixture into the top of the tenderloin, covering it evenly.
6. Bake at 425 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
7. Remove tenderloin from oven and allow it to rest for 5-10 minutes before serving.
8. Slice the tenderloin against the grain. Serve warm and enjoy!

name: Tartar Sauce
description: I can't tell you how many times I've checked the nutrition facts panel on a jar of tartar sauce, only to hang my head and put it back on the shelf. Well, no more! This tartar sauce is amazing—even better than the fast-food kind—for less than half the calories. Try it on salmon burgers, oven "fried" fish, and even in tuna or egg salad!
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'dill pickles - ¼ cup, chopped or diced', 'onion, finely chopped - 3 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'pickle juice - 1 tsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl, stirring until smooth.
2. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Peanut Butter Marshmallow Protein Cheesecake
description: Cheesecake is delicious—there's a reason there's a whole factory named after the stuff! Swap out cream-and-sugar-packed slices and customize your cake with this high-protein, lower-calorie alternative.
recipeIngredient: ['almonds, chopped - ⅜ cup', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'agave syrup - 1 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - ½ tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1¼ cup', 'Cellucor COR-Performance, Peanut Butter Marshmallow - 2 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Make your base by mixing all the base ingredients together and pressing the mix into the bottom of a 6-8 inch nonstick springform pan.
2. Then, make your filling by blending the whey, egg whites, and yogurt. Zero percent Greek yogurt works well because the base is already packed with healthy fats, but if you're feeling a bit indulgent and want to use 2 percent or full-fat yogurt, go for it! You could even add some ricotta for extra creaminess.
3. Pour the filling on the base and stick it in an oven set to 340 degrees F. Bake for 45-50 minutes or until the center wobbles slightly but the cheesecake feels cooked on the sides. Cook time varies with this recipe, so carefully monitor your cake. You do not want to wait until the center cooks all the way through, or it will dry up. Remove the cake while it still feels a bit "raw" in the center. As it cools, it will set into a nice, creamy consistency.
4. Set your cheesecake on the counter to cool for an hour. Then, refrigerate it for at least 4-5 hours. Garnish with peanut butter, melted chocolate, nuts, or fresh fruit. Just go crazy with it. Above all, enjoy!

name: Creamy Cilantro Lime Dressing
description: Tired of searching for a low-cal ranch dressing that tastes halfway decent? Look no further! This creamy dressing adds Mexican flare to salads, wraps, loaded baked potatoes, and more. It even makes an incredible marinade for chicken!
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'cilantro - ½ cup', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'lime juice - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Strain off excess liquid from Greek yogurt and add to blender along with remaining ingredients. Optional ingredient: Dry ranch dressing mix, 2-3 tbsp.
2. Blend until smooth and creamy.
3. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Homemade Barbecue Sauce
description: This sweet and tangy sauce has fewer calories and less sugar than your typical bottled brand, and cuts out high-fructose corn syrup and other yucky additives. It's finger-lickin' good over pulled pork or slow-cooker chicken, mixed with turkey meatloaf, drizzled over salad, or slathered over flatbread pizza.
recipeIngredient: ['low-sodium tomato sauce - 1 cup', 'apple cider vinegar - ¼ cup', 'Worcestershire sauce - 3 tbsp', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 2 tbsp', 'Pyure organic stevia blend - 2 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - ½ tsp', 'ground mustard - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients to a medium saucepan. Optional ingredients: Liquid smoke, 1/4 tsp. Hot pepper sauce, 1 dash.
2. Simmer over medium heat for 15-20 minutes, stirring every so often until thickened.
3. Store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Casein Pumpkin Custard
description: When you're not in the mood for Jell-O and pudding just won't do, it's clear that custard is what you're really craving. Skip the half-and-half and artificial sweeteners and opt for this mixture of protein, spices, and vitamin A-rich pumpkin. It will blow your gourd!
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin puree - 2 cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'water - 1 cup', 'musclepharm vanilla casein - 2 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
2. Blend and enjoy.

name: Beef and Broccoli Bowl
description: Expand your flavor horizons by pairing protein-rich red meat with heart-healthy broccoli and antioxidant-packed blackberries. Why didn't we think of this sooner?
recipeIngredient: ['lean flank steak - 24 oz', 'broccoli - 3 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'yellow pepper, sliced - 1', 'beef stock - ½ cup', 'light soy sauce - ½ cup', 'blackberries - 1 cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'ground ginger - 1 tbsp', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tbsp', 'arrowroot flour - 2 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1½ tbsp', 'organic honey - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, whisk together beef stock, liquid aminos, ginger, sesame oil, arrowroot starch, and rice wine vinegar.
2. Set a saucepan or small skillet on medium-high heat, and spray it with a little olive oil. Once the pan is hot, toss in garlic and blackberries. Sauté the blackberries for about 6-8 minutes, allowing them to explode under the heat. Using a spatula, gently mash down the berries, continuously stirring them so they don't burn.
3. Add the bowl of sauce to the skillet. Reduce the heat to medium, and stir the sauce so it begins to thicken. If you want the sauce to be sweeter, add organic raw honey, and stir. Once the sauce is smooth, remove it from the heat and set it aside.
4. Set a stir-fry wok or large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Once the wok is hot, toss in thin slices of beef and cook for about 4 minutes, or until the majority of the beef is no longer pink.
5. Add diced bell peppers to the skillet, and stir quickly. Try to sear the bell peppers. Cook for about 3 minutes, then add the broccoli florets.
Tip: If you prefer to have a sear on the veggies, remove the beef from the skillet before adding in the greens. Once the veggies are seared, add the beef back to the skillet.
6. Cook the beef and broccoli together for about 5 minutes, and continue to stir with a spatula. Reduce the heat to medium, and pour in the sauce. Stir the mixture or shake and toss the food in the wok to ensure the stir fry is evenly coated in the sauce. Cook and stir for another 2-3 minutes.
7. Garnish with green onions and sesame seeds. Enjoy the stir fry with a serving of brown rice or quinoa.

name: Chicken Collard Wraps
description:
For a fresher approach to lunch wraps, try using collard greens instead of flour-based tortillas. They are sturdy enough to hold a pile of roasted chicken and other fillings, but come without the starchy carbs. To cut the bitter taste, smooth these wraps are smoothed over with your favorite hummus.

This delightful lunch option delivers a wonderful array of appetizing, textural contrasts along with plenty of hunger-quelling dietary fiber. It can be prepared the night before if your harried mornings leave little time for meal prep.
recipeIngredient: ['collard greens - 8 leaf', 'hummus - 1 cup', 'chicken, rotisserie, chopped - 2 cup', 'carrots, sliced - 2 medium', 'roasted red pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'broccoli sprouts - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut off the firm, white stalks of the collards. With a sharp knife, fillet off the thickest parts of the remaining stalks that run down the backsides of the leaves. Place two collard leaves head to foot (stalks at opposite ends), and partially overlap the leaves.
2. Spread a quarter of the hummus down the center, and top it with a quarter of each of the chicken, carrot, roasted red pepper and microgreens. Tightly roll the leaves, beginning from the bottom, tucking in the sides as you go. Cut them in half on a bias to serve. If needed, insert toothpicks to keep the rolls intact. Repeat with the remaining ingredients.

name: Chicken Farro Soup
description:
This Italian-inspired soup will bowl you over with big-time flavor and plenty of nutritional highlights, including a payload of muscle-building protein and hunger-fighting fiber. It's proof that an awesome soup need not be an all-day kitchen project.

The grain of choice, farro, is an ancient Egyptian grain that eventually made its way to Italy and became a popular pasta alternative. Although farro softens when cooked, it still retains a crunch. If farro isn't available, this soup can be made with quinoa or rice.
recipeIngredient: ['canola oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1', 'carrots, chopped - 3 medium', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'Italian seasoning - 2 tsp', 'White wine - 1 cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 4 cup', 'farro - ¾ cup', 'chicken, rotisserie, chopped - 2 cup', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'flat-leaf parsley - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion, carrots, and salt; sauté for 6 minutes. Add the celery and garlic to pan, and cook for an additional 2 minutes. Place the tomato paste, Italian seasoning, and a pinch of black pepper in the pan, and heat for 30 seconds.
2. Add the wine to the pan, bring it to a boil, and let it cook for 3 minutes. Place the broth and farro in the pan. Return the mixture to a boil, reduce the heat to medium-low, and simmer covered until the farro is tender, about 20 minutes. Stir in the chicken and lemon juice, and heat through. Add more broth if needed. Serve garnished with parsley.

name: Sloppy Jane
description: These wonderful recipes are true originals. If meat isn't in your diet, or you just need a break from it, then earn some protein points in healthy ways!
recipeIngredient: ['mushrooms, sliced - 2 cup', 'red onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'tomato, diced - 1 small whole (2-2/5" dia)', 'tomato paste - 3 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'english muffin - 4 muffin', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ¼ cup', 'dill pickles - 1 spear, small', 'sloppy joe mix - 1 package', 'liquid smoke - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium sauce pan bring 1 3/4 water to a boil. Mix in tomato paste. Stir frequently. Lower heat and simmer.
2. Pour Sloppy Joe mix into water and tomato paste. Stir until ingredients thicken. Cover and simmer.
3. In a separate pan, add oil and lightly brown onions. Set aside.
4. In same pan, saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons of Liquid Smoke and parsley until light golden brown.
5. Toast the english muffins.
6. Add all of the fixings and serve.

name: Chicken Pesto Pasta
description: With a taste reminiscent of pizza, each forkful of this pasta salad will excite your taste buds and provide a bounty of nutritional goodness. Consider enjoying it after a hard workout to take advantage of the dynamic duo of protein and carbs. And since it can be served warm or chilled, it's also a good option for deskbound lunches in the days to come.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-grain pasta - 1¼ cup penne', 'pesto - 3 tbsp', 'chicken, rotisserie, chopped - 2 cup', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'bocconcini - 4 oz', 'baby spinach - 3 cup', 'kalamata olives (pitted) - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a pot of salted boiling water, prepare the pasta according to package directions. Drain the pasta, reserving 1/3 cup of the cooking liquid, and return to the pan.
2. Toss the pasta with pesto, stirring in small amounts of the reserved cooking liquid as needed to help pesto cling to the pasta. Stir in the chicken, tomatoes, bocconcini, spinach, and olives.

name: Meatless Nachos
description: So if your taste buds and food sensibilities are begging for a change? Ah! Not another chicken breast!? Why not try this meatless nacho recipe?
recipeIngredient: ['black beans, drained and rinsed - ¼ cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ¼ cup', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'lean ground sausage - 4 oz', 'tortilla chips - 4 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix the black beans and Gimme Lean Ground Sausage in a microwave safe bowl. Heat the bean and "sausage" mixture for 1-2 minutes until hot.
2. Sprinkle with cheese and red chili pepper flakes if you're brave enough. Eat with tortilla chips!
3. Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of the home-made guacamole recipe below for added flavor and a boost of healthy fats and protein from nutritious avocado and quinoa!
4. Optional: Serve nachos on a bed of fresh spinach.

name: Latin Salmon Pineapple Wrap
description: Ditch the usual scoop of deli-counter tuna salad on a bagel! Instead of going for the same old fish, dig into some salmon. Paired with fresh pinapple for a citrus kick, and topped with creamy avocado dressing for a dose of healthy fats, this wrap is something you'll want to sink your teeth into.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-wheat tortilla (10-inch) - 1', 'wild salmon - 6 oz', 'endive - 1 cup, chopped', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper - ⅓ cup, chopped', 'red onion, sliced - ⅓ cup', 'pineapple - ¼ cup, chunks', 'avocado - ½', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'green chilies, diced - 5 oz', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'cumin - 1½ tsp', 'cilantro - ⅔ cup', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'sea salt - 1 pinch', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor, blend together all the ingredients for the creamy avocado green chili dressing until smooth, then season to taste with sea salt and pepper. Place the dressing in an airtight container to enjoy at a later time.
2. Place all the salad ingredients on a large cutting sheet. Using the longest and sharpest knife you have, begin to chop up the salad to desired thickness.
3. Once the salad is chopped, add it to a mixing bowl and add 1/5 of the dressing, and refrigerate the remaining dressing in a tightly sealed container. Mix the salad together with a spatula, then place some of the contents on a whole-wheat tortilla. Fold in the sides, and tightly roll up the wrap.
4. Enjoy any leftover chopped salad by itself.

name: Turkey Bolognese Zucchini Pasta
description: Losing weight isn't about skipping meals. Learn how to shed unwanted fat the right way, and eat more in the process.
recipeIngredient: ['extra virgin olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'stalk celery - 1 whole', 'salt to taste - 1 ', 'pepper - 1 pinch', 'roasted red pepper - ¼ cup, chopped', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'tomatoes, crushed, canned - 2 cup', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'brown sugar - 1 tsp', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ¼ cup', 'zucchini, finely shredded - 6 whole', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
2. Add ground turkey, onion, and celery. Season with salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes.
3. Sauté the turkey mixture, breaking the turkey into small pieces, until turkey is cooked through, about 10 minutes. Add garlic, and sauté for 1 minute.
4. Add the crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, diced tomatoes, oregano, and brown sugar.
5. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 minutes. Add basil, and stir to combine everything really well.
6. Prepare the zucchini noodles using a spiralizer or mandolin slicer.
7. In another skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the zucchini noodles and cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
8. When the zucchini noodles are ready, place them on four plates, top with Bolognese sauce, and garnish with cheese.

name: Tuna Salad and Fresh Dill
description: A great tuna recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['tuna, canned in water - 7 oz', 'stalk celery - ¼ cup', 'fresh dill - ¼ cup sprigs', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch', 'dijon mustard - 2 tbsp', 'pepper - 1 dash', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
2. Serve on lettuce, pita bread, baked potato, pasta or rice.

name: Scrambled Eggs and Veggie
description: Check out these great egg and potato breakfast recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 8 large', 'onion, finely chopped - 3 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ⅓ tsp', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'diced tomatoes - 1 cup', 'potatoes - 1 cup, diced', 'zucchini, finely shredded - 1 cup', 'water - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Beat egg whites, onion, garlic powder, and water until mixture is slightly frothy.
2. Wipe bottom of a nonstick skillet with a paper towel soaked in olive oil
3. Cook and stir tomatoes, potatoes, and zucchini for 2 minutes in frying pan.
4. Pour egg mixture over vegetables.
5. As mixture begins to set at bottom and sides of the pan, gently lift cooked portions with spatula so that the uncooked portions can flow to the bottom of the pan.
6. Continue this process until eggs are thick and cooked but still moist.

name: Big Bill's Sloppy Gyms
description: A great sloppy joe recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1 lb', 'oregano - ¼ tsp, leaves', 'fresh basil leaves - ¼ cup', 'thyme - ¼ tsp, leaves', 'peppers, hot chili, red - ⅛ cup, chopped or diced', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'chili powder - ⅛ tsp', 'Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - 4 pita, large (6-1/2" dia)', 'Ragu sauce - 1 can']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brown meat in a skillet and drain all fat.
2. Pour Ragu cooking sauce onto meat and simmer for 5 minutes with oregano, basil, thyme, hot pepper, black pepper, and chili powder.
3. Spoon into whole wheat pita rounds and serve.

name: Asian Ramen Peanut Chicken Wrap
description:
Put packaged ramen to good use with this healthy chop that kicks up the conventional college-student staple and turns it into a restaurant-worthy entrée. This salad-turned-wrap brings color to your plate with purple cabbage, crisp green bok choy, and green and orange shreds of broccoli slaw.

The added zing of the sweet-and-spicy peanut dressing make this one meal you don't want to miss!
recipeIngredient: ['whole-wheat tortilla (10-inch) - 1', 'chicken breast - 5 oz', 'uncooked ramen noodles, crushed - 2 tbsp', 'bok choy - 1 cup, shredded', 'broccoli slaw - ⅔ cup', 'purple cabbage - ⅓ cup, chopped', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - ⅓ cup', 'cilantro - 1 tsp', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'water - 3 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1½ tsp', 'honey - 1 tsp', 'ginger, pureed - 1 tsp', 'sweet chili sauce - 1 tsp', 'Chinese 5-spice seasoning - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together the ingredients for the peanut dressing, and season to taste with sea salt and pepper.
2. Place all the salad ingredients on a large cutting sheet. Using the longest, sharpest knife you have, chop the salad to desired thickness.
3. Once the salad is chopped, put it in a mixing bowl, then add the peanut dressing. Mix the salad together with a spatula, then place some of the contents on a whole-wheat tortilla. Fold in the sides, and tightly roll up the wrap.
4. Enjoy any leftover chopped salad by itself!

name: Spinach Gluten-Free Lasagna
description: A great spinach lasagna recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice lasagna noodles - 1 lb', 'red onion, sliced - 2 whole', 'garlic, chopped - 1 clove', 'White wine - ¼ cup', 'lean ground beef - 2 lb', 'tomatoes - 4 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'tomato paste - 7 oz', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 2 cup', 'oregano - 2 tsp, leaves', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'spinach - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Boil noodles until tender. Drain
2. Braise onions and garlic in white wine for 4 minutes. Add ground beef. Cook until no longer pink. Drain fat.
3. Add pureed tomatoes, tomato paste, and herbs. Simmer for 20 minutes
4. In a blender, mix cottage cheese, egg whites, and spinach. Puree.
5. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place a layer of meat sauce in a large baking pan. Layer with noodles and spinach mixture. Repeat layers, ending with noodles. Arrange tomato slices on top. Bake for 45 minutes.
6. Add tomato slices and a dash of mozzarella on top if your diet allows.

name: Pesto Skirt Steak and Vegetables
description: This meal comes together from three pieces: grilled steak, blended pesto, and raw vegetables. I used a Gefu spiral slicer to make the zucchini pasta. I love this kitchen tool! The right tools matter in the workshop and the kitchen.
recipeIngredient: ['sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - 6 oz', 'olive oil - ¼ cup', 'fresh basil leaves - ¼ cup', 'garlic, minced - ½ clove', 'zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'roasted red pepper - 1 cup, chopped']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all pesto ingredients in a food processor.
2. Broil or grill the skirt steak to your liking. (Be careful as you cook. Many grills and broilers cook at different speeds.)
3. Spread 1-2 tbsp of pesto on skirt steak during the last 3-5 minutes of cooking.
4. Separately, cut up red peppers or tear them by hand.
5. Cut the zucchini with a spiral slicer.
6. Cut the zucchini with a spiral slicer.

name: Protein Buns
description: It's no fun eating a burger with a fork, but buns don't always fit in a fitness diet. Try these protein burger buns on for size! They're low-carb, high-protein, and totally delicious.
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'oat flour - ¼ cup', 'egg whites - ½ cup', 'pea protein powder - ⅛ cup(s)', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 320 degrees F (160 C).
2. Blend all ingredients together.
3. Separate batter into fourths.
4. Place batter as four "blobs" on cookie tray.
5. Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until an inserted knife comes out clean. They don't brown too much, so keep a close eye on them!
6. Allow to cool before slicing.

name: The Vegetarian Pasta Dish That's Ridiculously High In Protein
description: Looking for an easy, filling, and absurdly high-protein pasta dinner you can serve to anyone without shame? Maybe you just didn't know you were looking for one. But this one just found you. And it's delicious!
recipeIngredient: ['edamame pasta - 1 lb', 'ricotta cheese (skim-milk) - 2 cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon - 1 whole', 'sea salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set a pot of water to boil. When it boils, add a few teaspoons of salt and the pasta.
2. In a metal bowl wide enough to fit over the top of the pot, mix together the ricotta, Parmesan, olive oil, juice and zest of lemon, salt, and black pepper. When there are about 2 minutes remaining in the pasta's cooking time, place the bowl over the pot and slowly stir the ricotta and other ingredients. You should see it loosening as it warms.
3. When the pasta is al dente, drain it, add the basil to the bowl of sauce, and toss it with the drained pasta. Serve immediately.

name: Apple Ginger Glazed Ham
description: Bored of your current menu? Check out this great bodybuilding recipe! Taste tested and bodybuilder approved.
recipeIngredient: ['sugar-free jelly (raspberry or cranberry) - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'ham (whole) - 14 lb']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 325°F.
2. Place ham on a rack in a large roasting pan.
3. Bake 1-1/2 hours.
4. Heat apple jelly and ginger to boiling in a saucepan over medium high heat.
5. Boil 2 minutes.
6. Brush ham with some glaze.
7. Bake ham 30 minutes to 1 hour longer, brushing occasionally with remaining glaze until meat thermometer reaches 140°F. (15-18 minutes per pound total cooking time.)
8. When ham is done, place on a large platter. Let stand 20 minutes for easier slicing.

name: Mediterranean Greek Wrap
description: You can't go wrong with Greek! This chopped chicken wrap combines olives, tomatoes, cucumbers, and goat-cheese crumbles for an authentic taste with a protein-packed punch. Add some zest with the lemon vinaigrette, and you'll hit all the right notes.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-wheat tortilla (10-inch) - 1', 'chicken breast - 5 oz', 'goat cheese - ⅛ cup', 'romaine lettuce - 3 leaf outer', 'butter leaf lettuce - ⅔ cup, shredded or chopped', 'flat-leaf parsley - ⅓ cup', 'fresh basil leaves - ¼ cup', 'red onion, sliced - ⅓ cup', 'cucumber, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'cherry tomatoes - 5', 'kalamata olives (pitted) - 5', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'oregano - ½ tsp, ground', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1½ tsp', 'sea salt - 1 pinch', 'pepper - ⅛ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together the ingredients for the lemon vinaigrette, and season to taste with sea salt and pepper.
2. Place all the salad ingredients on a large cutting sheet. Using the longest and sharpest knife you have, begin to chop up the salad to desired thickness.
3. Once the salad is chopped, add it to a mixing bowl. Add 1/3 of the lemon vinaigrette, and refrigerate the remaining dressing in a tightly sealed container. Mix the salad together with a spatula, then place some of the contents on a whole-wheat tortilla. Fold in the sides, and tightly roll up the wrap.
4. Enjoy any leftover chopped salad by itself.

name: Popeye's Spinach Helper
description: A super strong popeye-style dish.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1½ tsp', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - ½ clove', 'green onion, chopped - 1 whole', 'green bell pepper - ½ small', 'lean ground beef - ½ lb', 'mushrooms, sliced - 16 oz', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'non-fat vanilla yogurt - ½ cup (8 fl oz)', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 3 tbsp', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'oregano - 1½ tsp, leaves']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil in skillet. Sauté onion, garlic, green onion, and green pepper until tender.
2. Add ground beef, and cook until just browned.
3. Add mushrooms and spinach. When spinach is limp, add remaining ingredients. Heat through and serve.

name: BBQ Pork Chops
description: Lean pork chops make a nice change from eating chicken, and the leanest cuts—from the loin—are leaner than chicken thighs, so don't feel guilty about eating pork chops from time to time. As with all meats, be sure to trim any excess fat before cooking. These barbecued pork chops are tangy and delicious.
recipeIngredient: ['lean pork chops - 4 chop without refuse (yield from 1 raw chop, with refuse, weighing 259g)', 'Worcestershire sauce - 2 tbsp', 'low-sugar ketchup - 4 tbsp', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'brown sugar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix cider vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, and chili powder in a small bowl. Place pork chops in a large resealable plastic bag.
2. Marinades can tenderize the surface of the meat only to about 1/4 inch. That's why it's important to make sure the marinade covers the entire surface of your meat. It also helps to score the meat (cut into the surface about 1/4 inch deep with a sharp knife in several places) before coating it with marinade.
3. Pour marinade into bag and cover chops with it.
4. Marinate for at least 4-6 hours in the refrigerator.
5. Preheat grill or broiler.
6. Spray grill with high-temperature nonstick cooking spray before heating; or spray broiler rack while broiler is heating.
7. Place marinated chops on grill or broiler and cook until done, about 5 minutes per side.

name: Challenge Chili
description: A tasty and fun winter recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1 lb', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'green bell pepper - 1 small', 'diced tomatoes - 1 can', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'roasted red pepper - ⅛ cup, chopped', 'kidney beans, canned - 1 oz', 'chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'corn - 1 15 oz can', 'tomato paste - 1 can (6 oz)', 'water - 6 fl oz', 'cumin - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook ground beef in large skillet until no longer pink. Drain fat.
2. Add remaining ingredients, first rinsing and draining beans, chick-peas and corn.
3. Stir to ensure equal distribution.
4. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

name: Tuna Fruit Salad
description: A tasty tuna and fruit salad.
recipeIngredient: ['pineapple - 1 slice (4-2/3" dia x 3/4" thick)', 'tuna, canned in water - 1 can', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'curry powder - ½ tsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'raisins - ¼ cup', 'apples - ¼ cup, quartered or chopped', 'butter leaf lettuce - 4 leaf, medium', 'pear, sliced - 1 small']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients except lettuce, tossing until well combined.
2. Line a large plate with lettuce leaves.
3. Arrange mixture on lettuce leaves and serve chilled.

name: Chipotle Black Bean And Chicken Sweet Potato Toast
description: The combo of smoky black beans and protein-packed chicken make this sweet potato stack a healthy option for lunch or dinner. Plus, using sweet potato as a bread substitute provides a nutritional upgrade.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 2', 'olive oil - 1½ tbsp', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ⅓ cup', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce - 1 pepper', 'lime juice - 2 tsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'chicken breast, shredded - 2 cup', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Cut ends off sweet potatoes, then cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
3. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and arrange slices in a single layer.
4. Brush slices with 1 teaspoon olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
5. Roast for 10 minutes, flip potato slices, brush with 1 teaspoon olive oil, and heat for another 10 minutes or until fork tender.
6. To make the black bean spread, place beans, yogurt, 1 tablespoon oil, tomato paste, chipotle chili pepper, lime juice, garlic powder, cumin and a couple pinches salt in a blender or food processor container, and blend until slightly chunky.
7. Spread bean mixture on sweet potato toast and top with chicken and cilantro.

name: Apple Slaw
description: A fast and tasty apple slaw recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['granny smith apple - 1 small', 'carrots, sliced - 2 small (5-1/2" long)', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 1 whole', 'onion flakes - ¼ tbsp', 'garlic powder - ¼ oz', 'thyme - 1 to taste', 'raisins - 1 tbsp', 'green cabbage - 1 cup, chopped', 'Walden Farms Raspberry Vinaigrette - 4 tsp', 'organic acai juice - ¼ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a salad bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, celery, onion flakes, garlic powder, thyme, raisins, and apple.
2. Separately combine vinegar, apple juice concentrate, and yogurt. Pour over cabbage mixture
3. Chill for a few hours or overnight.

name: Mayan Chocolate Sweet Potato Pudding
description: Here's proof that dessert doesn't need to derail your diet. All the sweetness in this pudding comes from sweet potatoes and dates, so there's no need to add processed sugar.
recipeIngredient: ['chopped dates - ⅓ cup', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 1', 'nonfat milk - ½ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - ¼ scoop', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place dates in a bowl, cover with hot water, and let soak 20 minutes.
2. Place sweet potato cubes and 1 tablespoon water in a microwave-safe bowl. Cover with plastic wrap, and poke a few holes in plastic to allow for venting. Microwave on high for 6 minutes, or until potato is easily pierced with a knife. The bowl will be very hot, so remove carefully from microwave. Let sweet potato cool.
3. Place milk, drained dates, sweet potato cubes, cocoa powder, protein powder, coconut oil, vanilla, cinnamon, cayenne, and a pinch of salt in a blender and blend until smooth. If needed, add a bit more milk to help with blending. Chill pudding for at least 2 hours before serving.

name: Quinoa Chicken Soup
description: A bowl of chicken soup will always comfort the soul, but this version packs extra nutrition and health benefits. Quinoa makes for a healthier alternative to processed noodles, while chicken thighs provide a juicy, flavorful source of protein to feed your muscles. Whip up a bigger batch, and stash individual portions in the freezer.
recipeIngredient: ['canola oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, diced - 1 large', 'carrots, chopped - 2 medium', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'chicken thighs, slice (boneless and skinless) - 1 lb', 'crimini mushrooms, sliced - ½ lb', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'tomato paste - 2 tbsp', 'Italian seasoning - 2 tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - ¼ tsp', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 5 cup', 'quinoa, cooked - ¾ cup', 'red wine vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'flat-leaf parsley - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the oil in a large saucepan or pot over medium heat. Add the onion, carrots, and salt, and cook until the onion is softened and darkened, about 6 minutes.
2. Add the chicken, mushrooms, celery, and garlic to the pan; cook 5 minutes more. Stir in the tomato paste, Italian seasoning, and chili flakes; heat for 30 seconds.
3. Add the broth and quinoa to the pan and bring the soup to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the quinoa is tender, about 20 minutes.
4. Stir in the red wine vinegar and serve garnished with parsley and freshly ground black pepper.

name: Oat-Crusted Chicken With Lemon Yogurt Sauce!
description: Stop eating the same baked chicken over and over. Add a little crunch, spice, tang, and zing to tonight's dinner with this oat-crusted chicken recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 4 piece', 'egg - 1', 'raw oats - 1½ cup', 'canola oil - 2 tbsp', 'paprika - 2 tsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'table salt - ¾ tsp', 'water - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 3 cup', 'lemon - 1', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'fresh dill - 3 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients for the yogurt sauce into a small bowl and stir until evenly mixed.
2. In a shallow dish, mix paprika, garlic powder, cumin, salt, and oats.
3. In a second dish, beat the egg and water with fork until frothy.
4. Place the chicken in a plastic bag and flatten it by beating firmly on each side.
5. Heat the stove to medium; add canola oil to the pan.
6. Dip chicken into the egg mixture, then coat with seasoned oats mixture.
7. Cook the chicken in the pan until golden brown on both sides.
8. Drizzle yogurt sauce on a serving dish, and place the chicken on top.

name: Two-Grain Apple Porridge
description: Quinoa and hearty steel-cut oats team up to raise the ante on breakfast oatmeal. Apple and warming spices make it taste extra comforting. By soaking the grains overnight, the cooking time in the morning is significantly shortened. For extra protein, you can stir in some protein powder or serve it alongside your favorite omelet.
recipeIngredient: ['quinoa, cooked - ½ cup', 'steel-cut oats - ½ cup', 'skim milk - ¾ cup', 'apple, grated or chopped - 1', 'raisins - ⅓ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'ginger, powdered - ½ tsp', 'nutmeg - ¼ tsp', 'pecans, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'maple syrup - 4 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium saucepan, bring the quinoa, oats, a pinch of salt, and 3 cups water to a slight simmer. Immediately turn off the heat, cover the pan, and let it sit overnight.
2. In the morning, stir in the milk, apple, raisins, cinnamon, ginger powder, and nutmeg. Heat over medium-low for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve topped with pecans and maple syrup.

name: Quinoa Salmon Bowl
description: This dish will "bowl" you over with great flavors, textures, and a healthy balance of macronutrients. Plus, by serving everything in a bowl, all the ingredients are deliciously mixed together instead of getting pushed around on a plate. The quinoa, salmon, and mango sauce can be prepared ahead of time and kept chilled separately for up to 3 days.
recipeIngredient: ['raw quinoa - 1 cup', 'wild salmon - 16 oz', 'mango, peeled and sliced - 1', 'lite coconut  milk - ½ cup', 'curry powder - 2 tsp', 'rice vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'sea salt - ¼ tsp', 'baby spinach - 4 cup', 'cucumber, chopped - 1', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'avocado - 1', 'pumpkin seeds - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring the quinoa and 1-3/4 cups water to a boil with a couple pinches salt in a medium saucepan.
2. Reduce the heat to medium-low, and simmer, covered, until the quinoa is tender and the liquid has been absorbed, about 15 minutes. Set aside covered for 5 minutes, then fluff the quinoa with a fork.
3. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Place the salmon on a greased or parchment-lined baking sheet, skin-side down. Season the fish with salt and pepper. Bake for 12 minutes, or until the fish is just cooked through in the center. Let the salmon rest 5 minutes, then gently break it apart into large chunks.
4. Blend together the mango, coconut milk, curry powder, rice vinegar, ginger, garlic and salt until smooth.
5. To serve, divide the quinoa, spinach, cucumber, tomatoes, avocado, and salmon among four serving bowls. Drizzle on mango sauce and garnish with pumpkin seeds.

name: Buffalo Pear Recovery Burger
description: Wheat germ may be one of the most underused ingredients in healthy cooking, but it's an ingredient every alpha male should know about. Wheat germ is the most vitamin-rich part of the wheat kernel. It's loaded with fiber and vitamin B. It's also known to help improve muscular energy, reflexes, and the utilization of oxygen during exercise, making it a perfect addition to your daily diet. Plus, it creates a great crust for "frying" proteins and veggies.
recipeIngredient: ['ground buffalo - 6 oz', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 1 serving', 'goat cheese - 1 tbsp', 'pear, sliced - 2 slice', 'tomatoes - 4 slice, thin/small', 'romaine lettuce - 2 leaf outer', 'wheat germ - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Seasonings (to taste): Paprika, Mrs. Dash Chipotle seasoning, sea salt, pepper, cayenne pepper.
2. Season the ground meat with Mrs. Dash Chipotle seasonings, sea salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper. Form a hamburger patty.
3. On a plate or in a bowl, add wheat germ. Coat the patty in the wheat germ flakes.
4. Set a skillet on medium heat and lightly spray with coconut oil. When the skillet gets hot, add the patty to the skillet and cook until desired readiness (remember to cook all sides).
5. Toast the wheat bun in a toaster oven and then assemble the burger. The pear is optional but recommended since it adds a faint sweet flavor that pairs nicely with the goat cheese and buffalo.

name: Lime Spinach Dip with Naked Blue Tortilla Chips
description: Going to a watch party sans spinach dip is like showing up to the gym without your workout clothes. I mean, you could jog in a suit, but it'd be awkward for you and everyone else. Don't be that person, especially when you don't have to.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - ½ cup', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'lime - 1 fruit (2" dia)', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add Greek yogurt, goat cheese, freshly squeezed lime juice, and seasonings together in a food processor or blender. Pulse the mixture in a blender.
2. Add spinach to the blender and pulse blend until the mixture is smooth yet chunky.
3. Refrigerate for at least 1-2 hours or place in the freezer for 45 minutes. Serve the dip cold. I highly recommend eating with fresh veggies or Simply Sprouted Naked Blue Tortilla Chips.

name: Brussels Sprouts In A Blanket
description: Brussels Sprouts In A Blanket
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 1 cup', 'turkey bacon - 1 strip']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350
2. Line cookie sheet with foil
3. Wrap uncooked turkey bacon around Brussels sprouts
4. Bake for 20 minutes, or until bacon is done

name: Spicy Barbecue Bison Stuffed Sweet Potato With Grilled Asparagus
description: It's a simple formula: Eat big to get big. This great post-workout meal will reward your muscles for a job well done. Caution: After sinking your teeth into this, you'll never see a sweet potato the same way again. Sorry.
recipeIngredient: ['bison steak, cut into cubes - 6 oz', 'sweet potato - 250 g', 'asparagus - 1 cup', 'low-sodium barbecue sauce - 2 tbsp', 'goat cheese - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Seasonings (to taste): Cayenne pepper, paprika, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder.
2. Set oven to 405 degrees. Puncture the raw sweet potato with a fork or knife, lightly spray it with coconut oil, and then wrap in foil. Place it in the oven to bake for 40-50 minutes.
3. Cut bison flank steak into small pieces. Season with cayenne pepper, paprika, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder. Once seasoned, rub 1 tbsp barbecue sauce on the bison pieces.
4. Set a skillet on medium-high heat and lightly spray with coconut oil. Toss in bison flank steak. When it's nearly done, add 1 tbsp of barbecue sauce and reduce the heat to low. Turn off when the meat is to desired readiness.
5. Lightly spray a separate skillet with coconut oil and set on high heat. Toss in 1 cup of asparagus and sear for 5-7 minutes. While searing, add garlic and a pinch of sea salt.
6. Remove the sweet potato from the oven and unwrap the foil. Cut the potato open with a knife and fluff the contents with a fork.
7. Place the barbecue bison on top of the sweet potato.
8. Add 1 tbsp of goat cheese and devour like an alpha male!

name: Strawberry Shortbread Whipped Pie
description: Here's a cool Valentine's Day recipe for strawberry shortbread whipped pie.
recipeIngredient: ['Keebler Ready Crust, Graham Pie Crust, reduced fat - 1 crust', 'sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - 1 box', 'strawberries, sliced - ¼ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'dairy-free reduced fat whipped topping - ⅓ container', 'water - 1 fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Wash and slice strawberries, toss with 2 packets of stevia sweetener.
2. Layer the bottom of your pie crust 1-inch deep with whipped topping, and cover with 3/4 of the strawberries.
3. Mix cheesecake pudding dry mix with 1 cup cold water, adding more until a thick, creamy consistency is achieved.
4. Layer pudding over berries and whipped topping, then add another layer of whipped topping over pudding.
5. Chill for half an hour and top with remaining strawberries.

name: Getting Lighter With Your Gravy
description:
One of the biggest calorie culprits of your Thanksgiving plan is gravy. When you dish this up by the spoonful over your turkey, potatoes, stuffing, and whatever other foods you enjoy it on you can easily add an additional three hundred or more calories to the meal.

To lighten the calorie load, the key changes you'll want to make is using the stock from the roasting pan that has been skimmed of the fat as well as avoiding adding additional butter to the gravy, which significantly boosts the total calorie content.
recipeIngredient: ['onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - ½ cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'parsley, dried - 2 tbsp', 'turkey stock - 2 cup', 'cornstarch - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a saucepan, begin heating the onion, mushrooms, and parsley with about 1/2 cup of the turkey stalk until tender. In a separate bowl, combine cornstarch, pepper, and 1/2 cup of the broth, being sure to stir until completely dissolved.
2. Add this mixture to the broth in the saucepan and blend until well mixed. Finally add the remaining turkey broth and then bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring throughout until it's thickened.

name: Cajun Venison Dirty Rice
description: Fire up that oven and break out your cast-iron skillet like a true alpha male. This recipe takes a Southern classic and turns it into a muscle-building meal like none other.
recipeIngredient: ['ground venison - 6 oz', 'low-sodium black beans - ½ cup', 'brown and wild rice mix - ½ cup', 'red onion, sliced - ⅓ cup', 'red bell pepper - ¼ cup, chopped', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Seasonings (to taste): Pinch of sea salt, pepper, cumin, paprika.
2. Set oven to 405 degrees.
3. Place a cast iron skillet on medium heat and lightly spray with coconut oil. Toss in red onions and garlic to saute.
4. Season venison with sea salt (pinch), pepper, cumin, and paprika. Add to the skillet. Chop the meat finely with a spatula as it cooks.
5. When the meat is nearly 85 percent cooked, add black beans (with a little juice), cooked instant rice, and red peppers. Mix with a spatula.
6. Remove the skillet from the heat and place it in the oven.
7. Bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes. Remove it from the oven and top with green onions.

name: Pumpkin-Nut Cream Cheese Icing Cake
description:
Pumpkin pie is the traditional dessert served at Thanksgiving but unfortunately, unless you are willing to complete forgo the crust, it's a difficult one to make lighter. Fortunately this is a quick fix if you opt for a more nutritionally sound pumpkin-nut loaf.

This serves as an excellent wind down to a Thanksgiving meal served along with a cup of flavored coffee or tea.
recipeIngredient: ['canola oil - 2 tbsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - 2 tbsp', 'pumpkin puree - ¾ cup', 'organic honey - ½ cup', 'brown sugar - 3 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2', 'whole-wheat flour - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'all-purpose flour - ½ cup', 'ground flaxseed - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'allspice, ground - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'ground cloves - ¼ tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'almonds, slivered - 2 tbsp', 'pecans, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'fat-free cream cheese - ¼ cup', 'Splenda - 8 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by preheating the oven to 350 degrees F and coat an 8 by 4 inch loaf pan with cooking spray. Set aside.
2. In a large bowl combine the canola oil, applesauce, pumpkin puree, honey, brown sugar Splenda, and egg and egg whites.
3. In another bowl, mix together the flour, oatmeal, protein powder, flaxseed, baking powder, and spices. Add this mixture to the pumpkin mixture and using an electric mixer on medium speed, beat until well blended.
4. Finally, pour the batter into a prepared pan and then sprinkle with slivered nuts over the top of the batter. Place in the oven and bake for between 50 and 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out lean. Carefully remove the loaf from the pan and allow to cool on the counter completely.
5. Once cool, in another bowl microwave the cream cheese until slightly soft (for easier spreading) and then stir in the Splenda and vanilla extract. Smear this over the top of the loaf and then cut into slices and serve.

name: Bleu Cheese Petit Sirloin
description: Rich and Sarah chose to make petit sirloin steaks with bleu cheese crumbles, sauteed zucchini, and garlic grilled potatoes. For dessert, Sarah made a strawberry shortbread pie. Can you really eat all this on a diet? Yes, you can. Try the recipes and check the nutrition facts.
recipeIngredient: ['sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - 8 oz', 'Kosher salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'onion flakes - ½ tbsp', 'garlic powder - ¼ tsp', 'roasted red pepper - ⅛ cup, chopped', 'thyme - ¼ tsp, leaves', 'rosemary - ¼ tsp', 'coriander - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat skillet on high; coat with cooking spray.
2. Rub steak with seasoning on both sides, then add to hot skillet.
3. Grill 3-4 minutes or until browned on the first side.
4. Flip steaks and top each with 1/4 cup bleu cheese.
5. Cook until the desired amount of doneness, about 3-4 minutes more for a medium rare steak. The bleu cheese will have melted to perfection over each steak.

name: Wild Boar Meatball Sub
description: With football season in high gear, now's the time to start thinking about good eats for tailgating and game-watching parties—and who can resist a meatball sub? Especially one this diesel. Next game, serve up this certified alpha male food.
recipeIngredient: ['wild boar, ground - 6 oz', 'whole-wheat hoagie roll - 1 roll', 'cherry tomatoes - 5', 'red onion, sliced - ¼ cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'marinara sauce - 2 tbsp', 'goat cheese - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Seasonings (to taste): pepper, 1 tbsp coriander, fresh parsley, cayenne pepper, pinch of sea salt
2. Set oven to 405 degrees.
3. Season the ground meat with pepper, 1 tbsp coriander, fresh parsley, cayenne pepper, minced garlic, and a pinch of sea salt. Divide the meat into three equal portions and form meatballs.
4. Set a skillet on medium heat and lightly spray with coconut oil. Toss in the red onions to saute or grill.
5. Add the meatballs to the skillet with red onions and cook the meatballs until they are 90 percent done.
6. Slice the hoagie down the middle and add meatballs. Drizzle with 2 tbsp marinara and sprinkle goat cheese. Cut the cherry tomatoes in half and place around the meatballs. Add fresh parsley.
7. Place the sub on a baking sheet and place in the oven. Bake for 8-10 minutes.

name: Chipotle Chili Turkey Cheese Fries
description: Move over, disco fries! Who needs all that grease, gravy, and artery-clogging cheese when you can have this version of a healthy cheat? Dig into this pile of guilt-free spuds that are topped with all the fixings.
recipeIngredient: ['red potato, baked - 2 potato large (3" to 4-1/4" dia.', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 5 oz', 'part-skim mozzarella cheese - ⅓ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - 1 whole', 'red chili sauce - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'coconut oil - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 405 degrees Fahrenheit.
2. Slice red potatoes into wedges, or use a mandolin slicer to make fries.
3. Dry the fries on a paper towel, then place them in a large bowl. Spray the fries with coconut oil and season with sea salt and chipotle chili seasoning.
4. Spread the fries on a baking sheet with parchment paper or on a baking rack. Bake for 13 minutes.
5. Remove from the oven and flip the pieces over. If you're impatient like me, you can just shake the pan to cause them to flip. Season with a bit more chipotle chili seasoning and a pinch of sea salt. Bake for another 10-13 minutes. Be careful not to let them burn.
6. Remove the fries from the oven and allow them to cool on a baking rack so they do not become soft or soggy.
7. In a nonstick skillet, cook ground turkey with garlic paste.
8. Place the fries in a cast iron skillet or oven-safe dish. Sprinkle with cooked turkey and shredded mozzarella. Bake in the oven for about 3 minutes. Remove the fries from the oven and sprinkle with chopped green onions.
9. Eat with a fork and enjoy!

name: Workout Chicken and White Wine Sauce
description: A post workout chicken and white wine sauce recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 4 piece', 'mushrooms, sliced - ¼ cup', 'White wine - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'dried dill - ½ tsp', 'skim milk - ½ cup', 'bread crumbs - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place chicken breasts between two sheets of waxed paper and pound flat with small mallet.
2. Simmer mushrooms in white wine, lemon juice, and dill until white wine is almost evaporated.
3. Spread mushrooms on flattened chicken breasts, roll them up, and fasten them with toothpicks.
4. Roll breasts in evaporated milk and bread crumbs, completely covering chicken.
5. Arrange chicken in nonstick baking pan and bake in a 350 degree oven for 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.

name: Thai Turkey Satay Skewers
description: This quick and easy turkey satay recipe is the perfect addition to your healthy meal plan. It's tickle-your-taste-buds yummy and packed with clean protein!
recipeIngredient: ['turkey breast tenderloins, cubed - 40 oz', 'garlic, minced - 1½ tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 3 tbsp', 'turmeric - ½ tbsp', 'curry powder - 2 tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'wasabi powder - ½ tsp', 'ginger, powdered - 1 tsp', 'lime juice - 3 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients except the turkey.
2. Place the turkey in a large, sealable bag.
3. Pour spices mixture into bag with turkey.
4. Massage turkey in the bag so that it is well covered with sauce. Refrigerate for 1-2 hours to allow to marinate.
5. Place 4-5 turkey cubes on metal or bamboo skewers.
6. Grill or broil 10-15 minutes, turning over once.
7. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Protein-Packed Pancakes
description: Figure competitor Lindi Carter's ultra-quick pancake recipe is the perfect breakfast for people with a hectic schedule. "The first time I tried these, I fell in love," says Carter. "Now, they're a staple in my meal prep. You'd never guess they were protein pancakes!"
recipeIngredient: ['pancake mix - 1⅓ cup', 'MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein - 1 scoop', 'egg whites - 6', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together.
2. Pour onto a heated pan in 5-inch circles.
3. When bubbles form, flip and cook until done.

name: Chili-Stuffed Sweet Potato
description: You can't beat building muscle on less than $3 per serving! Not only will this meal satisfy your wallet, but it will also put your muscles on the road to recovery. This is a perfect combo of sweet and savory flavors with high-quality protein and complex carbohydrates. Even better, it's an easy meal you can prep in advance-just top it with chili when you're ready to eat. Now, go grow!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 6 oz', 'sweet potato - 150 g', 'tomatoes - ¾ italian tomato', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - ⅛ cup', 'green onion, chopped - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bake a sweet potato in the oven until soft.
2. Set a skillet on medium heat and add ground meat.
3. Break apart the meat in the skillet with a spatula and, as it's cooking, add seasonings. When the meat is 70 percent finished, add tomatoes, green onions, and black beans. Mix together.
4. Reduce the heat to low, cover the skillet, and cook for another 5-8 minutes.
5. When the sweet potato has finished baking, slice it in half and scoop out just a little from the top to create a small hole.
6. Top the sweet potato with the chili mixture.
7. Enjoy!

name: Peanut Butter Banana Smoothie
description: This recipe is bodybuilder Kyle Glickman's all-time favorite shake. It's rich in protein, high in healthy fats, and has just enough carbs to keep your energy up throughout your day. Try it next time you're in a hurry!
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, Triple Chocolate Brownie - 1 scoop', 'banana - 1', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 12 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients (along with ice) except the whipped cream in a blender and blend.
2. Top with whipped cream (optional) and serve.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Waffle
description: When bikini competitor Nicole Christine wakes up, she does breakfast right! Her high-protein peanut butter and chocolate waffle is the perfect mix of nutrients for a healthy start to the day. This waffle is made with PB2 in order to keep the total fat content down, so it's great if you need a lower-fat breakfast.
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1 cup', 'MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, Triple Chocolate Brownie - 1 scoop', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'egg whites - 1', 'water - 1 cup', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'cinnamon - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a blender and mix well.
2. Pour mixture into a preheated waffle maker.
3. Cook 3-5 minutes.
4. Enjoy with some honey or PB2.

name: Performance-Boosting Pre-Workout Shake
description:
Whether your goals are performance- or physique-based, pre-workout nutrition is essential to success. Lifestyle coach and bodybuilder Jase Stevens knows the right pre-workout shake can make all the difference in his workout, so he uses this recipe to fuel his body properly.

This shake is the perfect blend of high-quality protein, carbohydrates, and some healthy fats. "I use one teaspoon of cinnamon to help increase insulin sensitivity and assist my body in dispersing carbs efficiently to the muscle cells," says Stevens. "I also add some sea salt so I get enough sodium to avoid cramping."
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein - 2 scoop', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'natural almond butter - 2 tbsp', 'banana - ½', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'water - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.

name: Cookie Dough Protein Treats
description:
Need a break from your usual protein shake? Try this delish cookie dough option instead. Bodybuilder and fitness model Jay Primarolo is the creator of these excellent treats! They offer a perfect blend of protein and healthy fats with just a touch of carbs to provide well-balanced nutrition.

If you're really watching your carbs, you can decrease the count further by opting for sugar-free maple syrup.
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, French Vanilla Creme - 2 scoop', 'almond flour - 1 cup', 'natural peanut butter - ½ cup', 'maple syrup - ¼ cup', 'semisweet chocolate chips - ¼ cup mini chips']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix all ingredients together.
2. Form into bite-sized balls.
3. Place in fridge until ready to eat.

name: Honey-Stuffed Purple Sweet Potato
description: Nope, your eyes aren't playing tricks on ya! That's definitely a purple sweet potato, and it's delicious. If you're like me, you probably have pretty aggressive sweet cravings after a tough workout. The first thing on your mind might be smashing a pint of ice cream. Try this recipe instead! In addition to the regular vitamins and minerals that sweet potatoes provide, a single serving of purple sweet potatoes are loaded with more antioxidants than a single serving of blueberries. Crush your goals and get those nutrients in!
recipeIngredient: ['purple sweet potato - 150 g', 'blueberries - ⅛ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 2 tbsp', 'organic honey - 1 tbsp', 'coconut oil - ½ tbsp', 'granola - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bake a purple sweet potato in the oven until soft. If you are unable to find larger purple sweet potatoes, simply bake several small purple sweet potatoes to meet your desired serving size.
2. Set a skillet on medium heat and lightly spray with coconut oil. Toss blueberries into the skillet and saute until they appear as if they are going to burst open—about 5-6 minutes.
3. Remove purple sweet potato from the oven. Remove the insides with a spoon and place in a bowl.
4. In the bowl, add almond milk, coconut oil, 1/2 tbsp honey, and cinnamon. Mix together to form a puree.
5. Add the mixture back to the potato. Top with sauteed blueberries, granola, and 1/2 tbsp honey.
6. Remember to add your choice of protein! I recommend grilled chicken breast or baked white fish.

name: Protein Banana Muffins
description: Made with just a few wholesome ingredients, you'll feel good about trying this recipe. Powerlifter Sam Amorim loves to eat them as a post-workout snack. They're also great to carry with you when you know you'll need a protein-rich treat!
recipeIngredient: ['flour - ½ cup', 'banana - 1', 'MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein - 1 scoop', 'cashew milk - 1 cup', 'egg - 1', 'baking powder - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Mix all ingredients.
3. Pour into non-stick muffin tins.
4. Bake for 12-15 minutes.

name: Coconut Protein Almond Bark
description: "It's one of my favorite recipes for sure," says men's physique competitor Blake Muracco. "It's a great contest-prep treat because it provides healthy fat and lots of protein." Not only does this recipe taste great, it's super easy to make. Plus, it's made from ingredients you probably already have in your kitchen!
recipeIngredient: ['extra virgin coconut oil - 1½ tbsp', 'MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein, Triple Chocolate Brownie - 1½ scoop', 'almonds, chopped - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a glass bowl and microwave for 15-30 seconds, or until the oil is liquid.
2. Stir until the consistency is even, and pour onto parchment paper.
3. Place in the freezer for 25-30 minutes.
4. Break apart and eat up!

name: Protein Almond Bark
description: Health coach and bikini competitor Caroline Tusiuk swears by this delish recipe to combat her sweet tooth. Prepared with crushed almonds and almond butter, this bark provides a hearty dose of healthy fats. Add in a scoop of protein powder in any flavor and you're looking at the perfect sweet treat for any low-carb diet plan.
recipeIngredient: ['MuscleTech 100% Whey Advanced protein - 1 scoop', 'almonds, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'extra virgin coconut oil - 3 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'coconut flakes - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Melt coconut oil and mix with protein powder.
2. Pour mixture on parchment paper and spread.
3. Top with almond butter, crushed almonds, and coconut.
4. Refrigerate 2-3 hours.
5. Remove and break apart.

name: Salmon-Stuffed Red Potato
description: If you want to build muscle and add size, eating salmon and potatoes is the way to go. It's hands-down delicious when you prepare it the Fit Men Cook-style. Adding salmon is a great way to "dress up" a staple bodybuilding meal. You may never eat salmon and red potatoes the same way again. Ever.
recipeIngredient: ['wild salmon - 6 oz', 'red potato, baked - 240 g', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ⅛ cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - ¼ cup', 'coconut aminos - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 375 F.
2. Bake a red potato until soft.
3. Season wild salmon with 1 tbsp coconut aminos, pepper, and Mrs. Dash chipotle seasoning.
4. Bake salmon in the oven for about 10 minutes until finished. Then, flake the salmon with a fork and set it aside.
5. Once the potato's finished, slice it down the middle and remove the insides with a spoon. Place the contents in a bowl.
6. Mix the potato contents with Greek yogurt, green onion, and fresh garlic. Keep stirring until the contents are creamy.
7. Add salmon to the mixture and blend with a fork. Season with sea salt to taste.
8. Top with parmesan cheese (if desired) and enjoy!
9. Note: Serve with 1 cup grilled asparagus for a nutritious side.

name: Piri Piri Chicken Livers
description: Use this recipe from sports nutritionist Matt Lovell after a training session or anytime you want a new take on that tired old chicken.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken liver,  washed and cubed - 1 lb', 'onion, sliced - 1', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'piri piri seasoning - ½ tsp', 'allspice, ground - ½ tsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'flat-leaf parsley - ½ cup', 'White Rice - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put oil in a pan and put it on medium heat.
2. Once it's good and warm, chuck in the onion, peppers, and garlic, and saute until they brown. Smells good, doesn't it?
3. Now lob in the chicken livers and all the spices.
4. Let it simmer for 5-7 minutes. Then scrunch up the spinach and add it in so it can wilt.
5. Lather it over your rice. Top with a few sprinkles of parsley for a dish that's tasty yet so affordable that you'll have enough to spring for a decent bottle of red.

name: Canned Chicken Parmesan Balls
description: When money is tight, the next best thing after the "chicken of the sea" is actual shredded chicken from a can. We're going to transform these into something like a sort of balled-up chicken parmesan. They're easy and scrumptious, and they're even better if you top them with some tomato sauce and mozzarella cheese!
recipeIngredient: ['canned chunk chicken breast, drained - 2 can (5 oz) yields', 'egg - 2', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 56 g', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 40 g', 'wheat germ - 64 g', 'tomato sauce, canned - 61 g', 'basil, dried - ½ tsp, ground', 'oregano - ½ tsp, ground', 'parsley, dried - ½ tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Drain your canned chicken and then combine all your ingredients into a bowl.
3. Mix ingredients together until everything is incorporated.
4. Take out a baking sheet, coat it with some nonstick cooking spray, and shape your mix into about 7 balls.
5. Bake for about 20-25 minutes.

name: Comfort Stew
description: This recipe from "Palm Sized Plan," by Matt Lovell (Buckingham Book Publishing, 2011), is a hearty meal that'll serve a handful of your friends for less than the cost of buying them each a round.
recipeIngredient: ['lamb neck fillets, diced - 400 g', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'onion, finely diced - 3', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'coriander - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'tomatoes, canned - 440 g', 'beef stock - 2¼ cup', 'carrots, sliced - 2', 'green lentils, cooked - 400 g', 'bay leaf - 4', 'lemon - 1 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Trim any skin or excess fat from your meat.
2. Cube the meat, put a pan on the stove, and place coconut oil in the pan over a medium heat.
3. Add the garlic, onions, and spice, and stir until the onions soften.
4. Stir in the tomatoes, stock, carrots, lentils, and bay leaves.
5. Simmer for 20 minutes or until the lamb is cooked.
6. Drizzle lemon juice and zest just before serving.

name: Lemon Pie Overnight Protein Oatmeal
description: Overnight oatmeals are one of my favorite recipes because they're incredibly easy to make, and you can make huge batches of them. For the purposes of this article, I'll be making one serving (or two, if you'd like to split it) of this protein-infused oatmeal that I swear tastes just like lemon pie! Make this the night before you want to eat it, and it'll be ready to hit you right in the taste buds in the morning.
recipeIngredient: ['unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ½ cup', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1½ scoop(s)', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'banana - ½', 'fat-free lemon Greek yogurt - 2½ oz', 'sugar-free fat-free lemon pudding - 8 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. Simply throw your ingredients into a bowl (or jar) and mix them together.
2. Cover your bowl with plastic wrap or with a lid, if available.
3. Put your oatmeal into the fridge overnight (or 2-3 hours if you're really hungry).
4. Devour!

name: Brown Sugar Spice Wings
description: In my family, I'm famous for my delicious chicken rub recipe. I want to share it with you! The brown sugar and spice are a perfect pairing. These wings are sure to be a crowd favorite.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - ¼ cup', 'paprika - ½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tbsp', 'chili powder - ½ tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tbsp', 'onion powder - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse and pat dry chicken, then trim off visible fat.
2. Place chicken in a large pot. Fill pot with cold water until chicken is covered by two inches.
3. Bring water to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
4. While chicken is boiling, put remaining ingredients in a large Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
5. Set broiler to high with the rack about 6 inches from the flame.
6. Once chicken is done, remove from water and add to Ziploc bag.
7. Shake until all wings are fully covered with marinade.
8. Place chicken on a baking sheet and broil for 6 minutes on each side until skin starts to crisp.
9. Enjoy!

name: Frank's Red Hot Wings
description: Make your own traditional hot wings with this recipe. Frank's offers many different flavor variations to its hot sauce, but I went for Franks Original—my personal favorite. It is neon orange and absolutely delicious.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'red hot sauce - ¼ cup', 'Walden Farms Bleu Cheese dressing - 2 tbsp', 'stalk celery - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse and pat dry chicken, then trim off visible fat.
2. Place chicken in a large pot. Fill pot with cold water until chicken is covered by two inches.
3. Bring water to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
4. Set broiler to high with the rack about 6 inches from the flame.
5. Once chicken is done, remove from water and place on baking sheet.
6. Broil chicken for 6 minutes on each side until skin starts to crisp.
7. In a large bowl, cover chicken with Frank's Hot Sauce.
8. Serve with celery and Walden Farm's blue cheese dressing.
9. Enjoy!

name: Crispy Pork Belly
description: All that fat is a waste unless it's turned to crunchy crackling, so we turned to the king of crisp, celebrity chef and restaurateur Jamie Oliver, for his take on getting your pork up to scratch.
recipeIngredient: ['pork belly - 1½ lb', 'red onion, sliced - 2', 'carrots, sliced - 2', 'stalk celery - 2', 'garlic, minced - 10 clove', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, ground', 'water - 600 ml']
recipeInstructions:
1. Flip your cooker to the hotter-than-hell setting (its maximum) to preheat it.
2. Slice a few knife wounds into the belly's fat and rub with salt, then stack it skin side up in a roasting tray.
3. Place it in the oven for an hour until the crackling starts to pop, then chuck in the veggies to keep it company.
4. Flick down the heat to 180º C and let it sit there for another hour.
5. Serve with roasted spuds for a cheap dish you'll wish you had in your trough every night.

name: Braised Beef Cheeks
description: Enjoy this recipe from Allinson that'll turn cheap ingredients into an expensive-tasting feast.
recipeIngredient: ['beef cheeks - 3 whole', 'carrots, sliced - 4', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 4', 'turnips, peeled and chopped - 4', 'red wine - 1 serving (5 fl oz)', 'bay leaf - 1', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1', 'rosemary - 1 tsp', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, leaves']
recipeInstructions:
1. Strip the tough membrane from the cheeks.
2. Chewing cud makes the cheeks tougher than Chuck Norris's bodyguard, so they need to be braised in the oven or in a pan for 5-10 minutes.
3. Slap half the ingredients into a large pot and splash in enough water to cover the meat.
4. Pour a glass of wine, drink it, then pour one for the pot.
5. Cook for two hours, then throw in the rest of the veggies and continue cooking until they're to your liking.
6. The result? Beef so tender it chews like a mouthful of merlot, with enough extras for freezing.

name: Coriander Lime Wings
description: This is my take on jerk chicken wings. The lime juice adds a bright citrus tone to the Caribbean spices. Careful, they'll get eaten fast!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tbsp', 'coriander - ½ tbsp', 'ginger, powdered - ½ tbsp', 'cumin - ½ tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse and pat dry chicken, then trim off visible fat.
2. Place chicken in a large pot. Fill pot with cold water until chicken is covered by two inches.
3. Bring water to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
4. While chicken is boiling, put remaining ingredients in a large Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
5. Set broiler to high with the rack about 6 inches from the flame.
6. Once chicken is done, remove from water and add to Ziploc bag.
7. Shake until all wings are fully covered with marinade.
8. Place chicken on a baking sheet and broil for 6 minutes on each side until skin starts to crisp.
9. Enjoy!

name: Honey Dijon Wings
description: Who doesn't love a little honey-mustard action? It's especially great on chicken wings! These are surprisingly moist and full of flavor. Use Dijon, stone ground, or course-grain mustard for some added depth of flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'dijon mustard - 4 tbsp', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse and pat dry chicken, then trim off visible fat.
2. Place chicken in a large pot. Fill pot with cold water until chicken is covered by two inches.
3. Bring water to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
4. While chicken is boiling, put remaining ingredients in a large Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
5. Set broiler to high with the rack about 6 inches from the flame.
6. Once chicken is done, remove from water and add to Ziploc bag.
7. Shake until all wings are fully covered with marinade.
8. Place chicken on a baking sheet and broil for 6 minutes on each side until skin starts to crisp.
9. Enjoy!

name: Cottage Cheese And Bananas On Brown Rice Cakes
description: This is the protein-rich snack you've been waiting for. It'll keep you full, refuel your muscles after hard training, or help you meet that protein daily intake standard you've been missing!
recipeIngredient: ['rice cakes, caramel - 2 cake', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ¼ cup', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Spread cottage cheese on rice cakes, top with sliced bananas.

name: Medium-Rare Bunless Buffalo Burger
description: Good riddance to buns! This burger stands alone on the plate, and will become an instant favorite in your gains-chasing diet.
recipeIngredient: ['ground buffalo - 1 oz', 'shallots - 1 tbsp chopped', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch', 'cornichon finely chopped - 2 tsp', 'tabasco sauce - 1 dash', 'light soy sauce - 2 tsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients except egg and form into a thin patty. Sear briefly on high heat, about 2 minutes per side.
2. Fry egg separately and serve on top of buffalo burger.
