name: Blueberry Protein Shake
description: Meet the best protein shake you've never tried. It's a perfect breakfast, post-workout refuel, or a meal replacement any time of day!
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 2 tbsp', 'blueberries - 1 cup', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'skim milk - 1½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Egg White Scramble on Whole Grain Avocado Toast
description: Boring old egg whites, or egg whites and mashed avocado on toast? Seriously, there's no comparison. This is a simple, game-changing breakfast you can make in minutes.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - ½ cup', 'avocado - ½ fruit, without skin and seed', 'multi-grain bread - 2 slice regular', 'table salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Halve one avocado. Use a spoon to scoop the flesh out of the skin. Mash the flesh with a fork and add just a pinch of salt.
2. Heat oil in a nonstick pan on medium heat. Sprinkle a little salt onto the egg whites. Add them to the pan and cook, stirring frequently, until the whites have solidified.
3. Spread avocado mash on two slices of toasted whole-grain bread. Top with egg whites.

name: Grilled Chicken Breast, Mashed Sweet Potato, and Spinach
description: Grilled Chicken Breast, Olive Oil Mashed Sweet Potato
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1 piece', 'sweet potato - 1 whole', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Season chicken breast with a few drops of olive oil and some salt. Peel the sweet potato and cut into medium-sized chunks.
2. Put the sweet potato chunks in a pot of water on high, and boil until tender. Mash with a fork, adding about 2 tablespoons olive oil and salt to taste.
3. Throw the chicken on a hot grill, and cook about 5 minutes each side, or until the chicken registers an internal temperature of 165 degrees F.
4. Add a few tablespoons of water and a squeeze of lemon to a hot pan. Wilt the spinach on high heat, just enough to soften the leaves.
5. Make a stack of sweet potato, spinach, and chicken, in that order.

name: Turkey Bacon and Eggs and Whole Grain Toast
description: Start your day right with this simple, classic protein-rich breakfast. Add a little hot sauce (or don't) and you're good to go!
recipeIngredient: ['turkey bacon - 4 strip', 'egg - 2 whole', 'multi-grain bread - 1 slice regular']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook the turkey bacon in a pan on medium heat, until crispy.
2. Meanwhile, heat some olive oil in a separate nonstick pan. When the oil is hot and smoking slightly, crack the eggs carefully into the oil. Let them fry until the edges get brown and crispy. When the white is set, flip and cook the other side as long as you want, depending on if you like runny yolks or not.
3. Serve turkey bacon and eggs with toast.

name: Grilled Salmon and Broccoli
description: Only have a few minutes? Here's dinner. Add your favorite seasonings, get the grill hot, and get a blast of protein and veggies!
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 5 oz', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Gently brush the salmon filet with olive oil, and sprinkle with salt.
2. Cut broccoli into small florets. Steam the broccoli for about 3 minutes, just until bright green.
3. On a hot grill, place the salmon skin side down. Let it cook about 3-4 minutes. When you try to flip the salmon, don't force it if it sticks. The skin will release when it is ready.
4. Flip the salmon and cook another 3 minutes, or longer if you like your fish well done.

name: Tuna Avocado on Grilled Portabello
description: Tuna mashed with avocado? Yup. Trust us: You'll return to this recipe over and over again. The savory mushroom base might just become your new bread!
recipeIngredient: ['tuna, canned in water - 5 oz', 'avocado - ½ fruit, without skin and seed', 'green onion, chopped - 3 whole', 'portabella mushrooms, sliced - 2 piece whole', 'olive oil - 1 spray', 'table salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a spoon, carefully scrape the gills out of the mushrooms. Toss mushrooms with olive oil and salt, and bake at 400 degrees F, for about 10 minutes.
2. Drain the tuna and add it to a bowl with the avocado and onions. Mash all this up with a fork, and season to taste with salt.
3. Once the mushrooms cool, spread the tuna avocado mash on the roasted mushrooms and serve.

name: Peanut Butter Oat Bars
description: You can't beat nuts for a perfect blend of fats and protein, and the addition of honey and rolled oats gives an unbeatable one-two carb dose as well. Sub out the peanuts butter for the nut butter of your choice, and take these with you for whenever you need a solid nutrient-packed snack!
recipeIngredient: ['natural peanut butter - 1¼ tbsp', 'honey - ¼ cup', 'rolled oats - 1¼ cup', 'almonds, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add the honey and peanut butter to a saucepan on med-low heat. Once they are soft, add the remaining ingredients.
2. Using a spatula, turn the mixture into a baking pan lined with waxed paper. Let cool, then cut into bars.

name: Beef and Broccoli Brown Rice Bowl
description: You can make this stir-fry-style dish in no time flat, but it'll satisfy you for hours. Double the recipe, and you'll find it's even better the day after!
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 5 oz', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'brown rice - 1 cup', 'shallots - 1 tbsp chopped', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 2 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice the beef as thinly as possible and marinate with the shallot, ginger, soy sauce, sesame oil, vinegar, and cayenne.
2. Cut the broccoli into small florets and throw them into a hot pan with a few drops of oil. Cook for about a minute, shaking the broccoli around the pan to cook evenly.
3. Add the sliced beef and the marinade. Continue to cook on high, until beef is as done as you like. Pour this over a bowl of brown rice.

name: Teriyaki Wings
description: These Asian-inspired wings are sticky with sweet and spicy flavor. Warning: you may need wet wipes for these ooey-gooey chicken treats!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 2 lb', 'Walden Farms Asian Marinade - 2 tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tbsp', 'sriracha - 2 tsp', 'sesame seeds - ½ tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse and pat dry chicken, then trim off visible fat.
2. Place chicken in a large pot. Fill pot with cold water until chicken is covered by two inches.
3. Bring water to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
4. While chicken is boiling, put remaining ingredients into a large Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
5. Set broiler to high with the rack about 6 inches from the flame.
6. Once chicken is done, remove from water and add to Ziploc bag.
7. Shake until all wings are fully covered with marinade.
8. Place chicken on a baking sheet and broil for 6 minutes on each side until skin starts to crisp.
9. Enjoy!

name: Crispy Rice Cereal Proats
description: A warm bowl of oatmeal will stick to your ribs and keep you full for hours on its own. Add some protein, almond butter, and spices like cinnamon and cocoa powder to the bowl, and you'll get even more bang for your buck. To further elevate the texture of this treat, just sprinkle your favorite crispy rice cereal on top!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - ¼ tsp', 'crispy rice cereal - ¾ cup (1 nlea serving)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring 1 cup water to a boil on high heat.
2. Combine the oats, protein powder, sea salt, cinnamon, and cocoa in a bowl.
3. Add boiled water slowly to the bowl, stirring constantly until desired consistency is achieved.
4. Top with almond butter and cereal. Stir, and enjoy!
5. Note: For a more pronounced "crisp," try adding the cereal last, and refrain from further mixing.

name: Chocolate Chunk Peanut Butter Protein Pancakes
description: When you add delicious chunks of a Quest bar to a protein peanut butter pancake, you do more than boost the protein content; you also seriously upgrade the flavor and texture. Now, imagine that pancake with peanut butter icing on top. Talk about a winning combination!
servingSize: 3-4 pancakes and 2 tbsp peanut butter icing
recipeIngredient: ['baking soda - ¼ tsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - ¼ tsp', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'raw oats - ⅓ cup', 'Quest Bar, chocolate peanut butter - 1 bar', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'water - ', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients except the Quest bar in a blender, and blend until smooth.
2. Dice up the Quest bar into chunks the size of chocolate chips. To make cutting easier, store the Quest bar in the fridge ahead of time for at least one hour.
3. Heat a skillet on the stove over medium heat, then coat it with cooking spray.
4. Spoon the batter onto the skillet to form 3- to 4-inch pancakes. Add a few Quest bar chunks to each pancake.
5. Cook until lightly browned on one side, flip, and repeat.
6. Plate the pancakes, and top them with peanut butter protein icing or your favorite topping.
7. Peanut butter protein icing directions: Add the whey, Greek yogurt, and PB2 to a bowl and stir until fully combined. Add water very slowly until you've reached your desired consistency. Drizzle the icing over your delicious protein packed pancakes, or just eat it with a spoon!

name: Maple Cream And Coffee Milkshake
description: You just crushed a grueling workout and need to rebuild, refuel, and rehydrate stat. What better time to deliver a tasty, sugary treat than now? Cool off with this sweet shake.
recipeIngredient: ['sugar-free maple syrup - 2 tbsp', 'low-fat frozen yogurt - ½ cup', 'brewed coffee, cold - 1½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'whipped topping, frozen, low fat - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine everything (including ice cubes) except the whipped cream in blender, and blend until smooth.
2. Top with whipped cream, and enjoy!

name: Protein Mug Cake
description: If only there were a way to eat cake on the run without making a mess, while simultaneously hitting your leucine threshold. Wait, there is! This moist mug cake will quickly become your next favorite portable protein treat! For an even sweeter treat, top your cake with fresh berries, cocoa powder, or cinnamon.
recipeIngredient: ['baking soda - ¼ tbsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray a mug with nonfat cooking spray.
2. Add all the ingredients except maple syrup and peanut butter to the mug.
3. Microwave the mug on high for 1 minute.
4. Remove the mug from the microwave, top the cake with nut butter and syrup, and enjoy.

name: Low-Carb Chicken Fettuccine Alfredo
description: Skip the guilt of traditional sauce-covered noodles and indulge in this plate of protein-rich comfort food. This reimagined alfredo recipe will satisfy your pasta cravings without leaving you in a food coma.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1½ lb', 'light margarine - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'tapioca flour - 2 tbsp', 'unsweetened cashew milk - 2 cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 oz', 'fat-free cream cheese - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'tofu shirataki fettuccine noodles - 24 oz', 'portabella mushrooms, sliced - 8 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. If you are using regular pasta, start it now.
2. Cut the chicken breast into bite-sized pieces. Season it with garlic powder, kosher salt, and black pepper.
3. Cook the chicken in the oil for 3-4 minutes undisturbed. Flip the chicken pieces and cook an additional 3-4 minutes until lightly browned. Set the chicken aside.
4. Rinse your skillet, reduced the heat to medium, and melt the margarine in the skillet.
5. Sauté the mushrooms for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to ensure even cooking.
6. Add the garlic, and sauté briefly until fragrant (about 30-60 seconds).
7. Add the starch, and stir enough to coat the mushrooms and garlic.
8. Pour in the milk, parmesan cheese, and cream cheese, stirring until smooth and thickened (about 2 minutes).
9. Add the lemon juice, lemon zest, salt, and pepper. Taste and adjust the seasonings if needed.
10. Cover the sauce, and remove the skillet from the heat.
11. Rinse the shirataki noodles (or regular pasta) thoroughly with hot water, then drain them in a colander.
12. Transfer the noodles to a large bowl, and toss them with alfredo sauce.
13. Portion out the fettuccine alfredo, and top it with cooked chicken. Garnish each portion with more parmesan and black pepper if desired.
14. Top with 3 ounces of cooked chicken.

name: Cumin And Coriander Flank Steak
description: This dry rub is easy to whip up and can be made stronger by sitting overnight. Pair with a fresh black bean salsa for color, texture, and a little extra protein.
servingSize: 1 steak (with marinade and 1/4 black bean salsa)
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 8 oz', 'cumin - 2 tbsp', 'coriander - 2 tbsp', 'red onion, diced - ¼ cup', 'roasted red pepper - ¼ cup, chopped', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 cup', 'vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'cilantro - ⅛ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix cumin and coriander, making sure to meld.
2. Rub into flank steak. Grill or sauté for about 4 minutes on each side, or until internal temperature reaches 135 degrees F.
3. While the steak cooks, combine red onion, roasted red pepper, cilantro, black beans, vinegar, and olive oil. Mix, and garnish with salt and pepper.

name: Flank Steak With Jicama Salsa
description: The tuber jicama is a great base for a steak-paired salsa. Its crisp texture and fresh taste make it the perfect base for the tomato and tomatillo blend. Whip the salsa up the night before to give the flavors time to meld.
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 8 oz', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'tomatillos - ¼ cup, chopped or diced', 'jicama - ¼ cup slices', 'tomatoes - ¼ cup, chopped or sliced', 'lemon juice - ⅛ cup', 'olive oil - ¼ cup', 'cilantro - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. For the salsa, combine chopped tomatillos, tomatoes, jicama, oil, cilantro, and lemon juice. Add a pinch of salt and pepper.
2. Cover in plastic wrap, and place the salsa in the fridge.
3. For the marinade, combine a chopped jalapeno, garlic, oil, and lemon juice. Blend.
4. Allow flank steak to marinate overnight.
5. Grill or sauté for about 4 minutes on each side, or until internal temperature reaches 135 degrees F.
6. Cut steak at an angle.
7. Pro tip: If you find your cutting board sliding as you slice, place a wet paper towel underneath it to eliminate shifting.

name: High Protein Oatmeal
description: When it comes to cooking, I like to keep it quick, simple, and nutritious. Why not get the most of each meal by kicking the protein percentage to the max? I like to add protein powder into my oatmeal, and then pack in more flavor by topping it with almonds.
recipeIngredient: ['almonds, slivered - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'BPI Sports Whey-HD, vanilla caramel - 1 scoop', 'instant oatmeal packets - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pour two packets of instant oatmeal into a bowl.
2. Mix with one scoop of Whey-HD Vanilla Caramel protein powder. Add cinnamon.
3. Add hot water and mix to the consistency you prefer.
4. Top with crushed almonds.

name: Curry Chicken
description: Get ready for an intense meal with this spicy dish. The heat from the curry powder in this dish helps you burn fat while you eat. Win-win.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 oz', 'cumin - 1 tbsp', 'curry powder - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Make a dry rub by combining curry powder, cumin, and minced garlic. The juice from the garlic will help wet the mix.
2. Dip the chicken breast in the mix and rub.
3. Wrap in plastic and leave in the fridge until you're ready to grill.
4. Cook chicken for five minutes on each side until it reaches an internal temperature of 185 degrees F.

name: Protein Blueberry Muffin
description: Not only are these muffins rich in protein, but they're also packed with antioxidant-rich blueberries, potassium-filled bananas, and heart-healthy walnuts.
recipeIngredient: ['flour - 1½ cup', 'powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'baking soda - 2 tsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'banana - 3 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - 1 cup', 'vanilla caramel protein powder - 1 scoop', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In large bowl, mix together flour, Stevia, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and protein powder.
2. In another bowl, mix together applesauce, egg whites, almond milk, and banana.
3. Slowly add dry ingredients to the egg white mixture. Once all ingredients are incorporated, fold in the blueberries and walnuts.
4. Drop generous tablespoons of mixture onto a nonstick muffin tin.
5. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

name: Golden Mustard Wings (With A Lil' Curry)
description: Add an extra element to honey-mustard chicken with these wings. The addition of turmeric and curry powder will give them a flavor-packed taste and bright-yellow hue that people can't help but gravitate toward.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 3 lb', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'turmeric - ½ tsp', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'honey - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 420 degrees F.
2. Trim excess fat and large pieces of skin from the drummettes or wings using a sharp knife or food scissors. This is important to reduce the amount of calories—just be careful not to cut the protein. You can cut the calories of each chicken wing by up to 15 calories! So, imagine if you eat 10 wings—that's 150 fat calories you saved!
3. Place the wings in a bowl, add a few pinches of sea salt and pepper, and mix together.
4. Place the wings on a baking rack (recommended) or a nonstick baking sheet. Before placing the wings in the oven, spray them with olive oil so that the outside gets somewhat crispy while baking.
5. Bake in the oven for about 35 minutes at 420 degrees F. Keep in mind that cooking times may vary depending on the amount of chicken.
6. Set a nonstick or cast-iron skillet on medium-high heat and add the coconut oil. Once it has melted, toss in all of the ingredients for the sauce. Stir it together with a spatula, and bring it a simmer.
7. Once it has simmered for about 2 minutes, remove the skillet from the heat and allow the sauce to thicken.
8. Place about a pound of the wings in a large bowl and add a few tablespoons of the sauce from the bowl. Toss the wings in the sauce until all of them are fully coated. A little sauce goes a long way, so don't overdo it! Repeat until all the wings have been covered.
9. Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon.

name: Jamie Eason's Peanut-Butter Chocolate Protein Pie!
description: Who doesn't love a good slice of pie? From cherry and coconut cream to lemon and pecan, pies are always a win. But when a sliver of the good stuff threatens to ruin your entire day of training and eating clean, the indulgence suddenly doesn't seem as sweet.
recipeIngredient: ['jamie eason signature whey protein isolate - ¼ scoop', 'almond flour - 2 tbsp', 'xylitol - 2 tbs', 'raw cacao powder - 1 tsp', 'fat-free cream cheese - ¼ cup', 'yogurt, fat-free - ¼ cup (8 fl oz)', 'maple syrup - 1 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'coconut oil - ¼ tbsp', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'semisweet chocolate chips - ¼ cup mini chips']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a mini 4.5-inch springform pan with cooking spray. Set aside.
2. Combine all crust ingredients together in a small mixing bowl. Blend together until a chocolate crumble forms.
3. Add in half a teaspoon of water, and stir. The mixture should hold its shape when pressed together.
4. Spoon this mixture into the springform pan and press down, molding the mixture to the bottom of the pan to form a crust.
5. Bake the crust in the oven for 5 minutes, then set aside to let cool while making the pie.
6. Using a handheld blender, mix together the cream cheese, peanut butter, and Greek yogurt until completely smooth. Add in the remainder of the pie ingredients and blend until smooth.
7. Pour pie mixture into springform pan, on top of chocolate pie crust. Smooth down with a spoon and place in the freezer for at least 1 hour.
8. After the pie has chilled, take it out of the freezer. Gently remove from the springform pan and transfer to the serving dish.
9. Drizzle melted chocolate on top of entire pie and slice into 6 even pieces. Serve immediately, and enjoy!

name: Savory "Cold Brew" Wings
description: Nothing says party time like a serving of good-ol wings. These coffee-inspired nuggets turn tradition on its head. The combination of coffee beans, cayenne, and smoked paprika will give you that extra kick, while the addition of cinnamon and coconut sugar add a touch of sweetness.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 4 lb', 'coffee - ⅓ cup', 'paprika - 2 tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 420 degrees F.
2. Trim excess fat and large pieces of skin from the drummettes or wings using a sharp knife or food scissors. This is important to reduce the amount of calories—just be careful not to cut the protein. You can cut the calories of each chicken wing by up to 15 calories! So, imagine if you eat 10 wings—that's 150 fat calories you saved!
3. Add the ingredients for the rub into a food processor. Blend until it becomes a fine powder with a few coarse pieces of coffee grounds.
4. Place about a pound of the wings in a large bowl, and add a heaping tablespoon of the rub mixture to the bowl. Add a few pinches of sea salt and pepper and 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil. Mix it all together. Repeat until all of the wings have been coated.
5. Place the wings on a baking rack (recommended) or a nonstick baking sheet.
6. Bake in the oven for about 35 minutes at 420 degrees F. Keep in mind that cooking times may vary depending on the amount of chicken.
7. Garnish with lime and sea salt crystals.

name: Peanut-Butter Honey Cookies
description: Bring these cookies to the next family gathering or take them to the office—they're sure to be a hit. The classic combination of honey and peanut butter will put a smile on even the grumpiest faces. These treats are a great alternative to the rich peanut butter cookie, but they're still plenty sweet! Try them as a post-workout snack.
recipeIngredient: ['oat flour - 1 cup', 'BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - 2 scoop', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'egg whites - 5 large', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - ⅓ cup', 'honey - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven at 350 degrees.
2. Mix ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
3. Roll small spoonfuls of dough into balls and place them on a pan.
4. Press with a fork on top.
5. Bake for 8-10 minutes.

name: Grilled Mustard Chicken
description: Protein from the chicken combined with 11 grams of protein per cup of mustard makes this dish a muscle-building powerhouse. Throw in some dill and citrus for added flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 oz', 'dill - 1 oz', 'dijon mustard - 3 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor, blend mustard, dill, and lemon juice.
2. Place chicken in mustard marinade for at least 4 hours.
3. Place marinated chicken on grill.
4. Coat chicken in olive oil and cook for five minutes on each side until it reaches an internal temperature of 185 degrees F.

name: Garlic And Fresh Herb Chicken
description: Instead of dousing your food in salt and pepper to add flavor, opt for fresh herbs. Pro tip: Use the back of the knife to break the stems of the rosemary and release the herb's natural oils for even more flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 oz', 'rosemary - 2 tbsp', 'oregano - 2 tbsp, ground', 'thyme - 2 tbsp, ground', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine roughly chopped oregano, thyme, and rosemary in a bowl. Add chopped garlic, oil, and lemon juice.
2. Marinade the chicken in the refrigerator until you're ready to use it.
3. Cook chicken for five minutes on each side until it reaches an internal temperature of 185 degrees F.

name: Tangy Balsamic Glaze Wings
description: Bring the punch of balsamic glaze to life with this sweet recipe. When combined with the tartness of the lime and garnished with the fresh taste of chopped green onions, it's a clear win-win. Prefer a spicy kick? Add a sprinkling of chili powder to take things up a notch.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken drumette - 4 lb', 'balsamic vinegar - ⅓ cup', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 420 degrees F.
2. Trim excess fat and large pieces of skin from the drummettes or wings using a sharp knife or food scissors. This is important to reduce the amount of calories—just be careful not to cut the protein. You can cut the calories of each chicken wing by up to 15 calories! So, imagine if you eat 10 wings—that's 150 fat calories you saved!
3. Place the wings in a bowl, add a few pinches of sea salt and pepper and mix together.
4. Place the wings on a baking rack (recommended) or a nonstick baking sheet. Before placing the wings in the oven, spray them with olive oil so that the outside gets somewhat crispy while baking.
5. Bake in the oven for about 35 minutes at 420 degrees F. Keep in mind that cooking times may vary depending on the amount of chicken.
6. Mix together the ingredients for the sauce in a glass bowl. Before tossing the baked wings in the sauce, heat the sauce in the microwave for about 1 minute.
7. Place about a pound of the wings in a large bowl and add a few tablespoons of the sauce of the bowl. Toss the wings in the sauce until all of them are fully coated. A little sauce goes a long way so don't overdo it! Repeat until all the wings have been covered.
8. Garnish with chopped green onion, lime, and sea salt crystals.

name: Chef Robert Irvine: Summer Cucumber Salad
description: Robert Irvine's summer cucumber salad is a simple, elegant and fresh accompaniment to any meat, fish, or sandwich.
recipeIngredient: ['cucumber, chopped - 1 cucumber (8-1/4")', 'red onion, sliced - ¼ whole', 'tomato, diced - 1 small whole (2-2/5" dia)', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'grapeseed oil - 3 tbsp', 'rice wine vinegar - 3 Tbsp', 'lemon, cut into wedges - ¼ whole', 'lemon zest - ⅛ tsp', 'fresh dill - 1 sprigs', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'kalamata olives (pitted) - 6 olive']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add cucumber, red onion, tomatoes, olives, and pinch of salt to a bowl. Mix gently. This is your salad.
2. In a separate bowl, whisk Dijon mustard and grapeseed oil until emulsified (well mixed). Whisk rice wine vinegar and the juice of one lemon wedge, in that order, into the Dijon and grapeseed emulsification, then add lemon zest. This is your dressing.
3. Add dressing to the salad, followed by a pinch of dill. Mix, then serve.

name: Mustard Flank Steak
description: While an inexpensive and typically tough cut of meat, flank steak has great flavor and is very versatile. With the help of a tasty marinade, it can be tenderized. This first marinade uses mustard as an emulsifier that thickens and flavors at the same time. Combined with the salty-sweet tang of balsamic, this marinade will have you recreating this recipe till the cows come home.
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 8 oz', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - ¼ cup', 'mustard - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Make a simple marinade using the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, and mustard. Use whichever type of mustard you prefer (Dijon used here). Whisk together.
2. Place steak directly in the marinade. Cover in plastic wrap.
3. Leave in the refrigerator for a few hours.
4. Sauté or grill the steak for about 4 minutes on each side, or until internal temperature reaches 135 degrees F. When finished, slice at an angle to cut through the toughness of the muscle.
5. Garnish with basil.

name: Apple Cinnamon Protein Oatmeal
description: Come fall, a cold bowl of mushy cereal won't cut it. Trade in your boxed breakfast for a bowl of protein-packed oats—and a kick of cinnamon—hot off the stove.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'almond milk - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'cinnamon - 2 tbsp', 'apples - 1 cup slices']
recipeInstructions:
1. To make the oatmeal, add milk, oats, and cinnamon sticks to a pot. Bring to a boil.
2. Once it boils, turn the heat down to medium low and simmer it until the oatmeal reaches your desired level of creaminess—some people like it runny, others like it thick as dough.
3. Remove your oatmeal from the heat and add the steamed apples—either on top or mixed in.
4. Then, add your whey. You don't want to add the whey when you cook the oats because you don't want it cooked. It won't be ruined but it can curdle if you boil it. Yuck.
5. Sprinkle some extra cinnamon on top, and boom! It's set to devour.

name: Texas Gold Rush Chicken Breast
description: This recipe melds sweet and savory into a flavor bomb that will brighten up your plate and palate. I dubbed this one "the gold rush" because of the yellow-orange glow, but it's also a muscle-building recipe worth its weight in gold. It's easy to make in large batches and can always be customized to meet your goals and any occasion.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1½ lb', 'ground mustard - 4 tbsp', 'yellow mustard - 2 tbsp', 'organic honey - 2 tbsp', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1½ tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'paprika - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 400 F.
2. In a bowl, mix together the ingredients for the gold rush sauce.
3. Rub half of the mixture on the chicken breasts.
4. Set a nonstick skillet on medium-high heat and spray with coconut oil. Add chicken breasts to the pan and cook for about 3 minutes on each side.
5. Pour the remaining sauce over the chicken breasts. If your skillet is all metal, place the chicken in it and allow it to bake in the oven for 10 minutes. If your skillet cannot be placed in the oven, transfer the chicken breasts to a baking sheet, and bake for 10 minutes.
6. Garnish with green onions.

name: Black-Eyed Pea And Sausage Rice
description: Every rice dish starts with a hot pan. If the pan is not hot, we can't toast the rice. Toasting the rice is what opens the kernel up and brings flavor. Not in the mood for sausage? Make this dish your own with chorizo, flank steak, or salmon instead. Don't love black-eyed peas? Replace with your bean of choice. Once you add the orange juice to layer flavor and cut fat, you'll smell the delight of a finished product.
recipeIngredient: ['cooked brown rice - 1 cup', 'black-eyed peas - 4 oz', 'Italian sweet sausage - 1 link 3 oz', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 whole', 'scallions, sliced - 2 tbsp', 'onion, sliced - ½', 'grapeseed oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn the heat up. Add grapeseed oil to the pan and allow to heat.
2. Dice onion and place in pan to caramelize.
3. Add the sausage and sauté with the onion. Add black-eyed peas.
4. Add cooked brown rice to the pan. Mix.
5. Add salt and pepper to taste.
6. Squeeze in the juice of an orange.
7. Garnish with scallions.

name: Cauliflower Rice
description: Make the most of cauliflower with this dish that makes vegetables the star. The added crunch from protein-rich nuts and fresh aroma from the picked basil make this one well-rounded meal.
recipeIngredient: ['grapeseed oil - 1 tbsp', 'cauliflower - 4 oz', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'brown rice - 1 cup', 'water - ', 'pecans - 1 oz', 'fresh basil leaves - 1 oz', 'table salt - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add grapeseed oil to the pan and allow to heat.
2. Add in cauliflower florets. Allow to caramelize to a golden brown.
3. Add garlic and rice. Allow flavors to meld.
4. Add water to steam and allow cauliflower to cook al dente.
5. Add toasted pecans and a pinch of salt.
6. Pick basil instead of chopping to keep the flavor intact and the herb green. Add to dish and serve.

name: Crispy Omega-3 Protein Chicken Fingers
description: These faux-fried chicken fingers are bread crumb, egg, and oil-free, and they're 100-percent delicious. With a boost of omega-3s in the form of walnuts and added protein with a coating of low-carb, baked Quest chips, they pack a texture and flavor punch that will rival the once-tempting, grease-covered fast-food staple!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1 lb', 'Quest Nutrition protein chips - 2 bag', 'walnuts, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'dijon mustard - 3 tbsp', 'organic honey - 1½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 400 F.
2. Crush bags of Quest protein chips to create crumbs. Add the crumbs to a sealable bag.
3. Add crushed walnuts to the sealable bag.
4. In a bowl, mix mustard, honey, and cayenne.
5. Slice the chicken breasts into tenders or fingers.
6. Rub the mustard mixture over the tenders and ensure they're all covered. Careful not to drench the tenders in sauce because this will cause the crust to be soggy.
7. Place the tenders in the sealable bag one by one. Gently shake the bag. Remove the tenders from the bag and place on a baking sheet or baking rack. The baking rack is preferred because it will leave all sides crispy.
8. Bake in the oven for 12-15 minutes. Be careful not to let the crust burn. Remember, the chicken should cook a bit faster since the pieces are smaller.

name: Strawberry Protein-Filled Dark Chocolate Bites
description: If you're looking for the perfect Valentine's Day gift to surprise your fit sweetie, here it is. Make your own protein chocolates and display them in a box of your own design! Awww.
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra Charge, Strawberry - 1 scoop', 'ground almonds - ¼ cup', 'coconut flour - ⅛ cup', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'sweetened condensed milk - ½ cup', 'dark chocolate chips - 50 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a big bowl, mix protein powder, ground almonds, coconut flour, oats, and milk.
2. Melt 2.5 squares of chocolate and divide it between 10 or 11 chocolate molds. If you don't have chocolate molds, just use cupcake-tin liners. Move the chocolate around the edges of the mold or liner so it covers the sides and doesn't pile up at the bottom.
3. Put the molds in the freezer for 20 minutes.
4. Remove the molds from the freezer. The chocolate should have set on the bottom and sides of the mold, creating a chocolate case.
5. Fill each mold with the protein mixture.
6. Once you fill each mold, melt another 2.5 squares of dark chocolate and cover up the filling.
7. Stick the chocolates back in the freezer for 20 minutes.
8. Remove chocolates from casings and enjoy!

name: Spicy Coconut Chicken Curry
description: Who doesn't love a good curry dish? If you're not already reaping the benefits, it's time to add the joys of curry—which include blood sugar control, heart health, and the anti-inflammatory benefits of turmeric—to your diet. When plain chicken just won't do, add this spin on a traditional Indian favorite to your list.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1 lb', 'red onion, sliced - ½ cup', 'lite coconut  milk - ¾ cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'ginger root - 1 tbsp', 'curry powder - 1 tbsp', 'turmeric - ½ tbsp', 'paprika - ½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut the chicken breasts into small pieces. Spray a nonstick skillet with coconut oil and set on medium-high heat. Cook the chicken breasts. Do not worry about seasoning—that part comes later.
2. Spray another nonstick skillet with coconut oil and place on medium heat. Add the red onion, garlic, and ginger. Saute until the red onion is nearly translucent.
3. Add chicken broth, coconut milk, and seasonings to the skillet. Stir with a spatula. Let the sauce simmer, and then cover. Reduce to low heat to allow the sauce to cook and thicken.
4. Add cooked, chopped chicken breasts into the coconut curry mixture. Stir with a spatula and cook covered for about 5 minutes on low heat. Season with sea salt and pepper to taste.
5. Remove the skillet from the heat and allow the sauce to thicken.

name: Spicy "Cup O' Joe" Chicken
description: Best described as an explosion of robust flavors, this dish brings the #BOOM. The smoky, spicy, and sweet flavors all collide to hit your palate with a winning combination. During the winter months when it's too cold to grill, there's always a Cup o' Joe (COJ) to provide the grilled flavors we love. The good thing about making your own chicken rub is that you can customize it to fit your needs and tastes. So, feel free to tweak the ingredients to your liking but just go easy on the coconut sugar!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1 lb', 'liquid aminos - 2 tbsp', 'coffee - ¼ cup', 'paprika - 1½ tbsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'coconut sugar - 1½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'allspice, ground - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 400F.
2. Place the ingredients for the Cup o' Joe chicken rub in a high-powered blender or food processor. Pulse blend until the coffee beans are semi-blended, yet still somewhat coarse.
3. Combine Bragg Aminos and 1 1/2 tbsp chicken rub and massage it onto the chicken.
4. Set a nonstick skillet on medium-high heat and spray with coconut oil. Add the chicken breasts to the pan and cook for about 3 minutes on each side.
5. If the skillet is all metal, place it in the oven to bake for 10 minutes. If your skillet cannot be placed in the oven, transfer the chicken breasts to a baking sheet, and then bake for 10 minutes.

name: Spicy Chicken Fried Quinoa
description: If you're in the market for a comfort-food overhaul, you've found the right dish. Kiss the temptation of that sauce-covered, fried favorite goodbye with this healthy modification. With quinoa and chicken—hello, protein overload!—this comfort food recipe will leave you feeling full and satisfied. Throw in some edamame for added color and that extra boost of protein.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken - 1 lb', 'egg - 3 whole', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 2 cup', 'raw quinoa - 1 cup', 'carrot, shredded - 1 cup', 'red onion, diced - 1 cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'coconut oil spray - 1 g', 'liquid aminos - 2 tbsp', 'sriracha - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, pureed - 1 tbsp', 'teriyaki, sauce, reduced sodium - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook quinoa according to the instructions on the package, but use low-sodium chicken broth instead of water, or 1 cup chicken broth and 1 cup water. Set the quinoa aside and allow it to cool to room temperature.
2. In a small bowl, mix together the ingredients for the sauce.
3. Set a nonstick skillet on medium heat and spray with coconut oil. Add garlic, carrots, and red onions. Cook until the red onions become clear.
4. Toss in ground chicken breast and completely cook the meat. Use a wooden spoon or spatula to chop up the chicken.
5. Increase the heat to medium-high and add the cooked quinoa. Before adding, make sure the quinoa has cooled and is "dry" (or not carrying a lot of moisture). Stir.
6. Pour in the sauce and stir quickly so that it does not burn.
7. Add eggs to the skillet and stir and chop so that the egg spreads evenly throughout the mixture.
8. Finally, reduce heat to medium and add frozen edamame beans. Stir until the beans are completely thawed.
9. Note: If you cannot find ground chicken breast in your local grocery store, you can put chicken breast cutlets into a high-powered blender or food processor and pulse blend to create minced meat.

name: Chickpea And Cilantro Rice
description: Turn a vegetarian meal into a complete protein with this new take on rice and beans. After coating your pan in grapeseed oil, add your chickpeas to the pan. With this dish, the real flavor punch comes from the combination of cilantro, curry powder, and lemon juice.
recipeIngredient: ['cooked brown rice - 1 cup', 'chickpeas, canned - ¼ can drained', 'curry powder - 1 tbsp', 'onion, sliced - ½', 'grapeseed oil - 1 tbsp', 'water - ', 'lemon - ½', 'cilantro - 1 oz', 'table salt - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn the heat up. Add grapeseed oil to the pan and allow to heat.
2. Dice onion and place in pan to caramelize. Allow to sizzle.
3. Add chickpeas and curry powder.
4. Add cooked rice to the pan. Stir and allow flavors to meld.
5. Add water to the pan to create a sauce.
6. Squeeze the lemon juice into the pan to bring the flavors together. Add cilantro.
7. Add salt to taste.

name: Creamy Salmon Spinach Salad
description: This spinach salad recipe is loaded with protein and healthy fats, making it the perfect option for people who follow a lower-carbohydrate diet plan.
recipeIngredient: ['spinach - 2 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - ½ cup', 'canned salmon - 1 can drained solids (total)', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 4 tbsp', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 tbsp', 'walnut, pieces - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine together the canned salmon, mayonnaise, and Parmesan cheese.
2. Toss with spinach leaves and sliced mushrooms and then top with walnut pieces before serving.

name: Creamy Turkey Salad
description: This cucumber salad works great as a light lunch while you're at your desk. It offers a unique flavor that will be sure to please.
recipeIngredient: ['turkey breast, white meat - 8 oz', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - 2 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 1', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'skim milk - ⅛ cup', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'poppy seeds - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine mayonnaise, skim milk, apple cider vinegar, and poppy seeds in a bowl and set aside.
2. Slice cucumbers and celery; toss together with turkey.
3. Drizzle salad dressing over the top and toss to coat.

name: Cucumber Radish Salad
description: This salad is easy on your waistline and also benefits your overall health, since both veggies contain healthy plant chemicals and fiber. Not sweet enough? Add a little agave nectar. It's a great alternative to high fructose corn syrup.
recipeIngredient: ['carrot, shredded - 1', 'radishes, greens removed - 6', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - 1', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'agave syrup - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients to a medium size bowl.
2. Toss and serve!

name: Hearts Of Palm And Avocado Salad
description: What's the ingredient for the ultimate chef? Fish sauce! Add a little savory succulence with this Eastern seasoning staple. Although it sounds fishy, this salad is as delicious as it is nutrient-dense. Rich in vitamins and minerals such as C, K, E, B, and potassium, a little avocado goes a long way. This side dish is a great alternative to other thigh-curdling barbecue must-haves.
recipeIngredient: ['hearts of palm, canned - 16 oz', 'avocado - 1', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'fish sauce - ½ tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients to a medium bowl.
2. Toss gently and serve.

name: Tomato And Shrimp Salad
description: This shrimp-based salad is perfect for the seafood lover looking to lighten up their diet and boost their vitamin and antioxidant intake. It's loaded with nutrients; you can't go wrong!
recipeIngredient: ['cucumber, thinly sliced - 1 cup', 'tomatoes, sliced - 1', 'red onion, sliced - ¼ cup', 'yellow pepper, sliced - 1', 'baby corn - ½ cup', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 30 shrimp', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 1 oz', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'white vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - ½ tsp', 'Splenda - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice vegetables and then toss together with shrimp.
2. In a small bowl, combine all dressing ingredients and stir until well mixed.
3. Drizzle over salad to coat.
4. Toss and then sprinkle with cheese before serving.

name: Corn and Turkey Salad
description: This salad is more energy dense but still lighter than a traditional winter meal. Corn constitutes the healthy carbs in this recipe; avocado adds the healthy fats. Ground turkey provides the protein to round out the dish, adding plenty of flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 8 oz', 'low-sodium chicken broth - ⅛ cup', 'romaine lettuce - ½ cup shredded', 'corn - 1 cup', 'avocado - 1', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - ½ cup', 'salsa - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by heating the chicken broth over medium heat.
2. Add ground turkey to the skillet and cook until no longer pink inside, and crumbly.
3. Combine corn, avocado, and cucumber and then combine with browned ground turkey.
4. Spoon salsa over top and mix until combined.
5. Place this mixture over lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Citrus Summer Slaw
description: If the Colonel's famous slaw keeps showing up at the neighborhood feast, it's time to make a change. Confect this citrus summer slaw instead. The assortment of fruits and veggies make this recipe light and summery. If you prefer oranges to grapefruit, make the switch. Both fruits pack a punch of vitamins C and A, as well as potassium and calcium. Just avoid the bucket of fried chicken and your beach body will not be bested.
recipeIngredient: ['cabbage - ½', 'red onion, diced - ½', 'tomato, diced - 1', 'cucumber, chopped - 1', 'red bell pepper, chopped - ½ medium (approx 2-3/4" long, 2-1/2 dia.)', 'grapefruit - 1', 'rice vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - ½ tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients to a large bowl.
2. Toss and serve!

name: Broccoli And Chicken Salad
description: This recipe is full of fiber, antioxidants, calcium, and will help to provide you with a good dose of lean protein to support your lean mass-building goals.
recipeIngredient: ['broccoli - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'mandarin oranges, drained - ½ cup', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'chicken breast, shredded - 6 oz', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - ⅛ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'red wine vinegar - 1 tsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut the grilled chicken breasts into thin strips.
2. In a bowl, combine broccoli, red pepper, oranges, and spinach leaves with chicken and toss.
3. In another small bowl, combine lemon juice, red wine vinegar, orange juice, and Dijon mustard.
4. Once well mixed, drizzle over salad and toss one more time to coat.
5. Serve immediately.

name: Roasted Sweet Potato And Kale Salad
description: What the kale? Just when you thought your diet regimen couldn't get any better, we went and added some green to your sweet potato. Similar to spinach, kale contains plenty of copper and iron as well as vitamins A, C, K, folic acid, calcium, and potassium. Tuck Edna's potato salad recipe back in the cookbook where it belongs and make the switch to sweet.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato, peeled - 1', 'onion, sliced - ½', 'purple kale - 1 cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. In a medium bowl, mix 1/2 tbsp olive oil with salt and pepper.
3. On a baking sheet, spread sweet potatoes in a thin layer and roast for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned and tender.
4. While the potatoes roast, heat 1/2 tbsp olive oil in a pan over medium heat.
5. Add garlic and onions and saute until caramelized.
6. Cut kale leaves from stem and into bite-sized pieces. Add to pan with garlic and onions. Cook until wilted.
7. In a large bowl, pour kale and onion mixture. Drizzle mixture with balsamic vinegar and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
8. Add roasted potatoes to bowl and mix.
9. Place bowl in refrigerator until salad as cooled to room temperature.

name: Strawberry And Feta Cheese Salad
description: This refreshing spring salad recipe is loaded with protein both from the chicken breast and the goat cheese, so it is perfect for those who are looking to boost their protein intake.
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries, sliced - ½ cup', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'pecans, chopped - ¾ oz', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 2 oz', 'chicken breast, shredded - 6 oz', 'lemon juice - ⅛ cup', 'dijon mustard - ¼ tsp', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'poppy seeds - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice the strawberries, and then combine with spinach leaves, pecans, and cheese. Toss. Layer the chicken on top.
2. In a small bowl, combine lemon juice, mustard, olive oil, and poppy seeds until well mixed.
3. Drizzle over top and toss one more time before serving.

name: Shrimp Ceviche
description: Shrimp, shrimp, shrimp—we love shrimp! If you're looking to pack your palate with a little protein, this is your go-to side. Shrimp is low in calories, high in protein, and boasts 18 vitamins and minerals. It's also almost completely carb-free. Reap the benefits!
recipeIngredient: ['small shrimp, peeled and deveined - ½ lb', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'red onion, sliced - ¼', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'avocado - ½', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add ingredients to a medium bowl.
2. Toss and refrigerate before serving.

name: Roasted Red Pepper Goat Cheese And Bacon Zucchini Pasta
description: Looking for a low-carb, low-calorie recipe that tastes amazing and will keep you satisfied? This quick, five-ingredient recipe takes less than 10 minutes to make and can be easily doubled or tripled if you need to feed more people. It's a tasty, healthy meal that will provide lots of protein from the shrimp, plus micronutrients like folate from the zucchini.
recipeIngredient: ['zucchini, sliced - 2', 'shrimp, precooked and diced - 3 oz', 'goat cheese (roasted red pepper flavor) - 1 oz', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 1 strip', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 2 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice thin strips of zucchini with a spiralizer or vegetable peeler to make "noodles."
2. Heat a nonstick saucepan over medium heat.
3. Add bacon and cook until desired texture is reached.
4. Remove bacon and add zucchini to pan.
5. While zucchini is cooking, chop bacon into small bits.
6. After 2-3 minutes, add bacon and shrimp to zucchini.
7. Cook 2 minutes.
8. Mix in goat cheese and stir until melted.
9. Serve in bowl and top with parmesan.

name: Butternut Squash And Apple Soup With Seared Scallops
description: One of the most comforting meals during the cold months is a big ol' bowl of soup! With only a few ingredients, you can make a healthy, high-protein version that tastes great and fits your macros. Make a big batch for a crowd or enjoy it by yourself.
recipeIngredient: ['low-sodium butternut squash soup - 1 cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - 2 tbsp', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'scallops - 4 oz', 'Sweet Spreads Cinnamon Roll Coconut Butter (Coconutter) - ½ tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat soup on stove or in microwave.
2. Mix in 2 tbsp applesauce.
3. Stir in fresh spinach.
4. Pour soup in bowl.
5. Top with seared scallops.
6. Drizzle with SweetSpreads Cinnamon Roll CocoNutter.

name: Pork Tenderloin With Cinnamon Apples
description: Sometimes your tastes buds crave sweet and savory satisfaction at the same time. With this delicious twist on pork tenderloin, you can satisfy that urge! Pair this dish with a side of steamed broccoli and you can enjoy a low-carb, high-protein meal.
recipeIngredient: ['pork tenderloin - 1 lb', 'apples - 2', 'Sweet Spreads Cinnamon Roll Coconut Butter (Coconutter) - 2 tbsp', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook pork tenderloin in the oven or on the grill.
2. In a medium nonstick pan, add onion and apple.
3. Sauté until tender.
4. Mix Sweet Spreads CocoNutter with apples and onions.
5. Serve pork tenderloin topped with cinnamon apple mixture.

name: Cherry, Pistachio, And Salmon Quinoa Salad
description: This quick dish is packed with protein. Because it has more calories and carbs than you may want in a regular meal, it makes for a perfect post-workout snack. It's delicious warm or cold, so you can pack it with you anywhere!
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 4 oz', 'quinoa, cooked - ½ cup', 'dried cherries -  tbsp', 'light pistachio nuts - 2 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Warm quinoa in a bowl.
2. Add flaked fish to quinoa.
3. In a separate bowl, mix together vinegar and mustard.
4. Dress quinoa and salmon with mixture.
5. Stir in cherries and pistachios.

name: Skinny Buffalo Chicken Dip
description: Everyone's favorite dip goes a bit "lighter" with this skinny Buffalo chicken creation. It might be lower in calories and fat, but it's big on flavor! And there's three easy ways to prepare it. Just make sure not to blow all the calories on chips.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cream cheese - 4 oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'part-skim mozzarella cheese - 1 cup', 'red hot sauce - ½ cup', 'blue cheese - ½ cup, crumbled, not packed', 'ranch seasoning - 1 tbsp', 'chicken breast, shredded - 3 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Oven instructions: Preheat oven to 350 F. In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed. Transfer mixture to a small greased baking dish, and bake for 30 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the edges begin to slightly brown. Remove and serve immediately.
2. Stove directions: Stir all ingredients together in a medium saucepan until combined over medium-low heat. Continue heating for about 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the cheese is melted and the dip is simmering. Remove and serve immediately.
3. Slow cooker directions: Stir all ingredients together in a slow cooker until combined. Heat on low for 4 hours or until the cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

name: Sausage Supreme Pita Pizza
description: I'm really picky when it comes to my pizza, especially about the sauce. That's why I am so freaking stoked about this dish. Not only does it have over 30 g protein and only 415 calories per pizza, but the sauce is perfect. If you like a crispy-crust pizza with flavorful sauce, you'll love this.
recipeIngredient: ['Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - 1 pita, large (6-1/2" dia)', 'low-sodium tomato sauce - ¼ cup', 'part-skim mozzarella cheese - ¼ cup', 'andouille chicken sausage - 1 link', 'mushrooms, sliced - ¼ cup', 'green bell pepper - ¼ cup, sliced', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 F.
2. Bring sauce ingredients (download recipe PDF for Sarah's healthy sauce recipe) to a boil over stovetop, then simmer 30-45 minutes.
3. Remove sausage casing and brown meat in skillet over medium heat, breaking it up with a turner or spatula as it cooks.
4. Spray a cookie sheet with cooking spray and bake pita for 10 minutes or until slightly stiff, but not crispy.
5. Take out pita, and turn oven up to 500 F.
6. Place pita on a cookie sheet and cover with sauce, cheese, sausage, and veggies, in that order.
7. Put back in the oven at 500 F for 5-7 minutes, watching closely. Pizza is done when crust is crispy and cheese is melted.
8. Top with parmesan and red pepper. Devour the entire thing!

name: Instant Pot Turkey Chili
description: Chili is a delicious, soul-warming recipe perfect for a lazy evening at home. A great source of protein and complex carbs, this is an ideal meal after a hard workout session.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1½ lb', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 5 clove', 'tomato, diced - 1 cup, chopped or sliced', 'kidney beans, canned - 1 14 oz can', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'white beans - 1 cup', 'cumin seed - 1 tsp, whole', 'oregano - 1 tsp, leaves', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 whole', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 small', 'Beef Broth - 1 cube', 'fish sauce - 1 tbsp', 'tomato paste - 3 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tsp', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn your Instant Pot to sauté setting and add olive oil.
2. When oil is hot, add ground turkey breast, salt and pepper to taste, and cook for 5 minutes.
3. Remove the juice from the ground turkey to prevent boiling. Set juice aside. Continue cooking chicken for another 5 minutes or until brown.
4. Add the diced vegetables to the Instant Pot along with the cumin seed and chili powder. Cook together with turkey for 5 minutes.
5. In a bowl, combine broth, fish sauce, light soy sauce, tomato paste, and cocoa powder. Pour half cup of broth mixture into Instant Pot and stir, being sure to scrape the bottom.
6. Pour meat juice back onto pot along with beans and tomatoes. Close lid and cook on manual setting with high pressure for 10 minutes.
7. Relive pressure, spoon chili into bowls and serve garnished with cheese.

name: Banana Coconut Ghosts
description: They're better for you than ice cream and they taste just as good! This ghostly treat will please kids and adults alike.
recipeIngredient: ['banana - 2 large (8" to 8-7/8" long)', 'coconut flakes - ¼ cup', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'grapes, sliced - 4 grape', 'cranberries - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel bananas and cut into halves.
2. Stick Popsicle stick or toothpick into flat end of banana and place in freezer until firm.
3. Once firm, roll bananas in coconut oil and then roll in dried coconut flakes.
4. Lay coated bananas on a plate and use quartered grapes for the eyes and cranberries for the mouth.
5. Serve immediately

name: Thai Spicy Beef Salad
description: One of my all-time favorite summer salads is this Thai Spicy Beef Salad. It's clean, fresh, and loaded with flavor! So fire up the grill and impress your meat-loving guests with this zesty, protein-packed salad.
recipeIngredient: ['sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - ½ lb', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'mixed salad greens - 4 cup', 'mint leaves - ⅛ cup', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ⅛ cup', 'cilantro - ⅛ cup', 'green onion, chopped - 2', 'lemongrass, finely chopped - ½ tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'fish sauce - 2 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Season steak with salt and pepper and grill to desired temperature.
2. In a small bowl, mix greens, mint, basil, and cilantro.
3. In another small bowl, mix lemongrass, green onions, lime juice, soy sauce, fish sauce, chili flakes, and Stevia.
4. Slice steak and place on top of greens.
5. Pour dressing over greens and steak.
6. Toss lightly and serve.

name: Sweet Potato Hash With Soft-Boiled Egg
description: Shredded sweet potato is the ultimate kitchen hack for serving meals in a flash. To grate, use the large holes on a box grater or shredding blade of a food processor. Cook the sweet potatoes for a couple of minutes in a skillet, then top everything off with a runny soft-boiled egg and a punchy pesto dressing to give this dish serious restaurant-caliber appeal.
recipeIngredient: ['canola oil - 1 tbsp', 'shallots - 2 tbsp chopped', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'sweet potato - 1', 'thyme - 2 tsp, ground', 'kale, diced - 2 cup', 'egg - 2', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add shallot and garlic; heat 1 minute. Place sweet potato, thyme, and a couple pinches salt in pan and cook, stirring regularly until potato shreds are tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in baby kale and remove skillet from heat.
2. In a saucepan, add water to a depth of 3 inches; bring to a boil. Gently lower eggs into water; boil exactly 6-1/2 minutes, adjusting heat to maintain a gentle boil. Use a slotted spoon to transfer eggs to a bowl of ice water and chill 2 minutes. Softly tap eggs against counter to break shell in several spots, and gently peel starting from wider end. Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
3. Whisk together pesto, olive oil, and cider vinegar. To serve, place sweet potato mixture on plates and top with soft-boiled egg halves and pesto dressing.

name: Malaysian Curry Prawns
description: This is a highly requested dish in my family. I love coming home to the smells of garlic, Malaysian curry, steaming-hot coconut milk, and prawns. Prawns are high in protein and low in fat. Pair them with some brown rice and steamed veggies for a balanced and very tasty meal.
recipeIngredient: ['prawns - ½ lb', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, chopped - 1 Tbsp', 'lite coconut  milk - 1½ cup', 'curry powder - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat coconut oil in large pan over medium high heat.
2. Add fresh garlic.
3. Rinse prawns and lightly salt and pepper.
4. Add prawns to pan and sprinkle with curry powder.
5. Saute for 2-3 minutes until all prawns are well-seasoned.
6. Add coconut milk and turn heat to low.
7. Simmer for 5 minutes.
8. Serve.

name: Japanese Sushi Bowl
description: Sushi is my usual meal option when I'm dining out because I can usually stick with simple, clean sashimi, substitute brown rice, or have cucumber-wrapped rolls. I was determined to recreate a sushi bowl at home on my low-carb day, and this little recipe was the result. Even the rice-lover at home was impressed by the cauliflower "rice." The key is to add some zesty flavors to the cauliflower when making the rice—it's much more palatable that way.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon, smoked - 6 oz', 'head cauliflower, chopped - ½', 'carrot, shredded - ¼ cup', 'avocado - 1', 'cucumber, chopped - ½', 'garlic powder - ½ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'seaweed sheets - 2 sheet']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor, add steamed and chopped cauliflower, shredded carrots, lime juice, soy sauce, garlic, and cayenne to make the "rice."
2. To serve, place cauliflower rice, 3 oz of smoked salmon, 1/2 avocado, and cucumber.
3. Eat with chopsticks or use seaweed sheets to wrap rice, fish, and veggies for a mini hand roll.

name: Ginger-Grilled Salmon
description: Ginger and salmon blend together perfectly. You'll enjoy the flavor almost as much as you will the health benefits!
recipeIngredient: ['ground ginger - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'light soy sauce - ⅓ cup', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - ¼ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'onion, finely diced - ½ whole', 'salmon fillet - 3 fillet']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ginger, garlic, soy sauce, orange juice, and Stevia in a bag.
2. Add the salmon and onions to the bag and let sit a few hours to marinate, flipping the bag after 1.5 hours.
3. Cook salmon on grill until it flakes easily with a fork.
4. While cooking, brush salmon with any excess marinade.
5. When done, sprinkle with orange rind and serve.

name: Salmon Salad
description: Need something different than your regular chicken and broccoli? Salmon salad is a perfect take-to-work option.
recipeIngredient: ['canned salmon - 1 can drained solids (total)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ⅓ cup', 'garlic, minced - ½ tsp', 'fresh dill - 1⅞ sprigs', 'onion, finely chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, minced garlic, dill, and diced onions.
2. Add salmon and stir until salad is formed.
3. Serve with lettuce, on whole wheat or Ezekiel bread, in a low-carb wrap, or with whole grain crackers.

name: Protein Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: I have a passion for weightlifting, nutrition, and great-tasting food. My specialty is cooking with protein powder. Ask me a question and I'll turn it into a delicious, protein-filled recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1 whole', 'Gaspari Nutrition MyoFusion Advanced Protein, Milk Chocolate - ½ scoop', 'coconut flour - ¼ cup', 'baking soda - ¼ tsp', 'coconut flakes - ¼ cup', 'sweetened condensed milk - ¼ cup', 'brazilnuts - 1¼ oz (6 kernels)', 'semisweet chocolate chips - 1 cup chips (6 oz package)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 340 F or 170 C.
2. Mix together egg, protein powder, coconut flour, baking soda, coconut, milk, and ground nuts.
3. Once dough is formed, stir in chocolate chips.
4. Using a spoon, divide mixture into 12 cookies and place on a sprayed cookie sheet.
5. Put in oven for 15-20 minutes. Remove them from the oven as soon as they cook through. It's good if they're a bit soft in the center. Make sure you don't overcook them because they'll dry up and lose their charm if you do.
6. Let them cool, pour yourself a tall glass of milk and boom! Enjoy a couple of cookies!

name: Spinach And Rice
description: Check out this rice and spinach recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['White Rice - ⅓ cup', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 3 tbsp', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch', 'fresh dill - 2 sprigs', 'pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'baby spinach - 2 cup', 'bread crumbs - 3 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
2. In a mixing bowl, combine rice and cottage cheese
3. In a small bowl, mix together egg white, parsley, dill, and pepper.
4. Add spinach and egg white mixture to rice mixture. Mix well. Pour into casserole dish, and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
5. Bake for 40 minutes.

name: Teriyaki Salmon
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 3 fillet', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 3 tbsp', 'low-sugar ketchup - 3 tbsp', 'onion powder - 2 tbsp', 'Splenda - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine olive oil, soy sauce, sugar-free ketchup, onion soup mix powder, and Splenda in a bag.
2. Put salmon filets in the bag and then let sit for about an hour to marinate.
3. Remove filets from bag and place on the grill for 4-5 minutes per side.
4. Serve with freshly-steamed vegetables and quinoa or brown rice.

name: Decadent Chilled Protein Pudding
description: This must-try creation is definitely my new favorite. No more need to be tempted by yogurt-covered raisins. The ingredient list might be short, but this makes for one flavorful combination.
recipeIngredient: ['muscle milk natural chocolate protein - 1 scoop (s)', 'sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - ¼ box', 'liquid egg whites - ¼ cup', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, mix together protein and pudding.
2. Add liquid egg whites and water. Mix to a thick consistency.
3. If the texture is runny, add more powder.
4. Spoon out the batter and plop on a small plate.
5. Freeze for 30 minutes.
6. Use a zester on a ripe orange to garnish with orange peel. Serve with accompanying fruit slices!

name: Muscle Density Broccoli Salad
description: Check out this great broccoli salad recipe
recipeIngredient: ['sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - ½ lb', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 1 cup', 'Green Beans - 1 cup 1/2" pieces', 'mushrooms, sliced - ½ cup', 'green onion, chopped - 1 whole', 'red wine vinegar - ½ tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ tbsp', 'yogurt, fat-free - ¼ cup (8 fl oz)', 'yellow mustard - ½ tsp or 1 packet', 'pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'lettuce - 2 cup', 'tomatoes - ½ medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch']
recipeInstructions:
1. In large salad bowl, combine steak, broccoli, green beans, celery, mushrooms, and onion.
2. In a screw-top jar, combine the vinegar, lemon juice, yogurt, mustard, and pepper, and shake until thoroughly mixed for the salad dressing.
3. Arrange salad on a bed of lettuce leaves. Garnish with tomato slices and parsley.

name: Protein Carrot Cake
description: Vegetables might be in the name, but traditional carrot cake isn't necessarily a health food. Turn an occasional guilty pleasure into a clean cheat with this take on the dessert from fitness model Jamie Alderton! The combination of sweet vanilla, savory apples, pineapples, raisins, and—of course—carrots, along with aromatic cinnamon, ginger, and orange zest, will please your palate and meet your macros.
recipeIngredient: ['ground oats - 120 g', 'egg - 2', 'egg whites - 3', 'almond milk - 200 mL', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Killa Vanilla - 3 scoop', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 30 g', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'baking soda - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'ground ginger - 2 tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'raisins - 30 g', 'sweet carrots - 200 g', 'orange zest - 1 tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'Quark - 1 cup', 'almond milk - 100 mL', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Killa Vanilla - 3 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add eggs and egg whites to bowl and whisk.
2. Add remaining cake ingredients to the bowl, and mix.
3. Peel and grate carrots, then add to the mix.
4. Spray two nonstick baking trays with cooking spray, and pour ingredients into the trays.
5. Place in the oven at 350 degrees F for 20-25 minutes.
6. For the frosting, mix all ingredients in a bowl. Once carrot cake is cooked, leave to cool for 30 minutes and then frost the cake!
7. Note: Mix in dried apple and pineapple pieces to taste.

name: Salmon With Tomatoes
description: Mixing tomatoes with salmon is something most people don't ever consider. You'll be glad you did! The lycopene in this recipe offers additional antioxidant benefits.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 2 fillet', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'paprika - ¼ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ⅛ tsp', 'tomatoes, sliced - 2 slice, medium (1/4" thick)', 'carrots, sliced - 1 small (5-1/2" long)', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil.
2. Add salmon and sprinkle with cayenne pepper and paprika
3. Cook for two minutes each side; add seasoning to the second side.
4. Add tomatoes, chopped carrot, garlic, and parsley, and continue to cook for another 2-4 minutes to allow the flavors to blend.
5. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and then serve alongside side of your choice.

name: Superpower Trout Almondine
description: A super power fish recipe for bodybuilders.
recipeIngredient: ['trout - 2 serving (4oz)', 'White wine - ¼ cup', 'light butter spread - ¾ tsp', 'lemon juice - ¼ lemon yields', 'almonds, slivered - ⅛ cup', 'parsley, dried - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Braise trout in white wine until done.
2. Remove trout, and drain off fat.
3. In the skillet, add butter and lemon juice, and sauté almonds until lightly browned.
4. Mix in chopped parsley, and pour almond mixture over trout.
5. Serve immediately.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Pancakes
description: Chocolate and peanut butter have long been a delicious combination. Instead of getting your fix in the form of candy or chocolate—true diet disasters—pile on the sweet with this protein-laden treat!
recipeIngredient: ['liquid egg whites - 1 cup', 'all-purpose flour - ⅛ cup', 'PB2 Chocolate Powdered Peanut Butter - ⅛ cup', 'Monster Milk Chocolate Protein - ½ scoop (s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a bowl until they form a thick batter.
2. Pour batter onto a greased skillet and cook like a pancake.
3. Pour batter onto a greased skillet and cook like a pancake.

name: Protein Frappuccino
description: A tasty frappuccino recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['labrada carb watchers mrp - 1 packet', 'coffee - 16 oz', 'heavy whipping cream - 1 tbsp', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Strawberry Frotein Fluff
description: Protein fluff's filling and low-calorie nature is precisely what makes it a staple among many dieters. It is also extremely easy to make and requires just three basic ingredients: milk, protein powder, and fruit—pretty much the same stuff you'd use in a protein shake or smoothie.
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'whole milk - ¼ cup', 'strawberries, frozen - 1 cup', 'xanthan gum - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a bowl and blend to a smooth, frozen mixture.
2. Using an electric whisk, whisk mix for 5-8 minutes until it gains volume.
3. Eat immediately.

name: Peanut Butter And Jelly Protein Cups
description: End your last meal of the day on a high note with this classic mixture of peanut butter and jelly that's likely been a favorite since you were a tot. These cups are a protein creation that fitness athlete Vinny Russo loves. "The combination of strawberry whey/casein protein powder, organic peanut butter, and chocolate remind me of a good ol' peanut butter and jelly sandwich—with a little extra chocolate delight thrown in there," he says. With a short ingredient list and huge taste, this recipe is a convenient, good-for-you indulgence.
recipeIngredient: ['liquid egg whites - 200 g', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Strawberry - 50 g', 'natural peanut butter - 28 g', 'Walden Farms Calorie Free Chocolate Syrup - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Mix egg whites and Hydra 6 together until you have a thick, pancake-like mix.
3. Spray a muffin tin with coconut-oil spray. Add egg-white mixture to the muffin tin, filling each tin 1/3 of the way.
4. Put the muffin tin in the oven and let the mixture bake for approximately 10 minutes, keeping a close eye on it.
5. Once finished, take out the muffin tin and let it cool for 3 minutes.
6. Weigh out your peanut butter and heat it in the microwave until it becomes liquid-like in texture.
7. Using a spoon, add the melted peanut butter to each cup.
8. Top off each PB&J cup with some Walden Farms chocolate syrup. Enjoy!

name: Monster Milk Breakfast Cake
description: What's better than breakfast for dinner? Dessert for breakfast! Eat cake guilt-free with this monster of a muscle-building recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['Monster Milk Chocolate Protein - ½ scoop (s)', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) -  tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
2. Cook in a microwave for 1-2 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed by the oats.
3. Top with all-natural peanut or almond butter, or sugar-free maple syrup.

name: Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Truffles
description: Looking for a healthy take on that bowl of chocolate chip cookie dough you've been dreaming about eating? Try this sweet, protein-packed alternative!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'chickpeas, canned - ¾ can drained', 'coconut sugar - 1 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'dark chocolate - 1 square']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor, mix all ingredients together except for the chocolate chips. Mix until you've formed a paste or dough. Taste the cookie dough to make sure it's sweet enough! If not, add more sweetener.
2. Add in the chocolate chips. If your mix is too sticky, add a tiny bit more of the coconut flour—just a half teaspoon at a time—until you get your desired consistency.
3. Optional topping: 2 dark chocolate squares. If you want to coat your truffles, melt the dark chocolate and dunk your truffles before placing them on an aluminum-foil-lined tray.
4. Set in the fridge for a couple of hours before serving.

name: Hot Cod
description: Enjoy this delicious recipe for hot cod
recipeIngredient: ['cod atlantic - 12 oz', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 4 whole', 'coconut oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Coat pan with palm or coconut oil.
2. Coat cod in salt and chili powder.
3. Add to pan.
4. Cook 8-12 minutes on medium heat; flip the cod twice and serve!

name: Curried Chicken Kabobs
description: Chicken breast is a staple in any healthy meal plan, so it's probably already in your fridge or freezer. Instead of popping it in the oven like usual, try it in a flavorful kabob. The Greek yogurt adds some casein protein and the curry will provide some wonderful anti-inflammatory properties. Altogether, this recipe is a health win.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 20 oz', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - 1', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'ground ginger - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'coriander - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Start grill.
2. Skewer chicken slices, spray with cooking spray; cover liberally with all spices.
3. Place skewers on grill and cook about 10 minutes each side, or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
4. Serve with Greek yogurt and cucumber slices.

name: Workout Energy Salad
description: Check out this great energy packed salad for after your workouts
recipeIngredient: ['lettuce - 1 cup', 'spinach - ⅓ cup', 'cucumber, chopped - ⅓ cup slices', 'tomatoes - ⅓ medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'bean sprouts, canned - ⅓ oz', 'carrot, shredded - ⅓ cup', 'mushroom - 6 whole', 'avocado - ⅓ fruit, without skin and seed', 'sunflower seeds - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tsp', 'thyme - 1 to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium-sized salad bowl, combine lettuce, spinach, cucumber, tomato, sprouts, carrots, mushrooms, avocado, and sunflower seeds.
2. In a screw-top jar, mix olive oil with lemon juice and herbs. Shake vigorously, and pour over salad.

name: Vegan-Friendly Protein Dinner Recipe
description: If you're vegetarian or vegan, meeting protein needs can be tough. This protein-packed tofu recipe provides the protein your muscles need and the taste your palate deserves!
recipeIngredient: ['brown sugar - ¼ cup', 'light soy sauce - ¼ cup', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'sesame seed oil - 2 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'tofu, firm - 12 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix brown sugar, soy sauce, chili flakes, sesame oil, garlic cloves, ginger and sea salt in a small bowl and set aside.
2. Pour olive oil into sauce pan and heat.
3. Fry tofu in pan for about 10 minutes.
4. Pour sauce into pan and cook for 3-5 minutes. Sauce will thicken and the tofu will absorb much of it.
5. When tofu is done, pour over your favorite carb source and eat up!

name: Ahi Tuna Salad
description: If you're a fan of sushi, this salad will be a home run. Seared ahi tuna forms the protein source in this dish and will blend great with the other flavors in the dish.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - ½ tbsp', 'salad greens - 2 cup', 'mango - ½ whole', 'peanuts salted - ¼ cup, shelled', 'avocado - ½ cup, pureed', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - ½ tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'ahi tuna - 1 6 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
2. Add tuna steaks and cook for approximately 1-2 minutes per side to sear.
3. Combine mixed salad greens, mango, chopped peanuts, and avocado in a bowl.
4. In another bowl, mix olive oil, lime juice, balsamic vinegar and cilantro leaves.
