5. Stir until well combined.
6. Drizzle over top of salad and toss.
7. Layer tuna over the top before serving.

name: Chocolate Chip Peanut Butter Protein Cookies
description: I think we can agree chocolate and peanut butter are a match made in heaven, right? Well, these cookies taste heaven-sent: surprising, because I kind of threw this recipe together! It's not often that things come out perfect on the first try. These cookies are thick and chewy, with a crunchy outside and gooey chocolate chips inside. It took all my willpower not to eat them all at once!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 50 g', 'powdered peanut butter - 50 g', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 2 tbsp', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'sugar-free maple syrup - ¼ cup', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 oz', 'Labrada Lean Body Protein Bar, Peanut Butter Chocolate Chip - 1 bar', 'table salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Whisk together dry ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
3. Mix in peanut butter, syrup, egg white, and vanilla until a dough forms.
4. Mix in chocolate chips and chopped-up protein bar.
5. Bake for 10-12 minutes until firm on the edges. The center will set once the cookies cool.
6. Enjoy immediately, or store in the fridge up to one week (freezing not recommended).

name: Tuna Protein Wraps
description: You've got to love tuna! It's versatile, clean, easy to find, and, well, it's pretty cheap. Many people eat it like you do, on top of or alongside a salad, though tuna is also popular on sandwiches. Of course, if you get creative, there are many other ways you can enjoy it!
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'psyllium husk powder - 2 tbsp', 'buckwheat flour - ¼ cup', 'whole milk - ¼ cup', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'tarragon - ½ tbsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a handheld blender or food processor, blend all the above ingredients.
2. Spray nonstick pan with PAM or coconut oil and turn heat to high.
3. Once the pan is sizzling hot, pour 1/4 cup of the batter onto the center.
4. Turn the heat down to medium and spread the mixture around the pan with a spoon so it's thin and cooks evenly.
5. When it has cooked, flip the wrap and let the other side cook for another minute. Remove from pan.
6. Repeat the process. Get the pan hot again, spray, pour the batter, turn down the heat, spread the batter, flip.
7. When all your wraps are done cooking, let them cool.
8. While you wait, make tuna filling. Mix a can of tuna with some chopped olives, low-fat mayo, sugar-free ketchup, sea salt, and tarragon. Or, you can dress your tuna however you like!
9. Fill a wrap with tuna and enjoy! Or, wrap your wrap in tinfoil and take it with you for a healthy lunch.

name: Waikiki Universal Chicken
description: Check out this great chicken recipe from the islands!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 20 oz', 'ground ginger - ½ cup', 'green pepper, cut into strips - ¼ whole', 'all-purpose flour - ½ cup', 'olive oil - ¼ tsp', 'pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'pineapple - ½ cup, chunks', 'water - ½ cup', 'cider vinegar - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Wash and dry chicken and coat with flour.
2. In a nonstick skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
3. Place chicken in shallow roasting pan.
4. Sprinkle with pepper.
5. Make sauce of pineapple juice, water, vinegar, and ginger.
6. Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.
7. Add pineapple slices and green pepper rings.
8. Cook for 15 minutes and serve.

name: Field of Greens
description: A delicious veal and green salad.
recipeIngredient: ['veal - 6 oz', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'chives - 1 tbsp chopped', 'romaine lettuce - 3 cup shredded', 'macadamia nuts - 1 each', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat ghee in skillet to coat the pan. Insert veal. Season with salt and chives.
2. Brown meat and flip a few times—it cooks pretty quick—on medium heat for about 10 minutes.
3. Toss romaine with oil and vinegar; serve immediately.

name: Swap Stuffing For Rice Stuffing
description: Stuffing is one of the higher fat culprits sitting on your Thanksgiving dinner table because of all the oil that drips into it from inside the turkey. In addition to this you must remember that stuffing is essentially a very heavy hit of white bread, which as you likely already know can do a number on your fat loss diet plan.
recipeIngredient: ['dried cranberries - ⅛ cup', 'raisins - ⅛ cup', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - ¼ cup', 'almonds, slivered - 1 cup', 'chicken bone broth - ½ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'wild rice, uncooked - 2 cup', 'water - 5 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. First combine the fruit and juice together and then place either in the microwave or in a small pot on high heat until hot.
2. Heat olive oil in a pan until hot and then toss in the nuts, stirring slightly until they have taken on a crisp texture. Remove and set aside.
3. In another saucepan, heat chicken broth. Once hot, add in onion, celery, and garlic gloves until tender. Stir in wild rice along with five cups of water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, cover and cook over very low heat for about 25 minutes or until rice is finished and water is absorbed.

name: Monster Balls
description: A creepy take on the popular protein energy balls, these protein treats are perfect for a post-workout meal or fun family snack. There aren't many calories in these, so feel free to eat the whole batch! If you do, just make sure you make more for the rest of your family to enjoy.
recipeIngredient: ['fiber one cereal - ½ cup', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 10 oz', 'BSN Syntha-6 Peanut Butter Cookie Protein - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
2. Using hands, form mixture into five messy balls.
3. Top each ball with two dark chocolate chips for eyeballs.
4. Place in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
5. After balls set, share or enjoy by yourself!

name: Sweet Potatoes Over Mashed
description: The next way to lighten your Thanksgiving meal this year is to opt away from making traditional potatoes which do tend to be quite high in calories and fat when made traditionally and instead choose sweet potatoes.
recipeIngredient: ['water - ¼ cup', 'brown sugar - 2 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'sweet potato - 2 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. First preheat your oven to about 375 degrees Fahrenheit. Next you are to lightly coat a baking pan with cooking spray and then set aside.
2. Slice potatoes into very thin slices or shoestrings, and then combine the water, Splenda, syrup, and olive oil in a small bowl. Using a brush, lightly brush the surface of the potatoes, flip, and then brush the other side.
3. Cover and bake in the oven for 45 minutes or until they are tender, flipping twice throughout baking time and re-brushing with glaze. Once they are finished baking, transfer them to a serving tray and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

name: Curry Shrimp on Rice
description: Check out these great recipes from chicken to tuna!
recipeIngredient: ['White Rice - 2 cup', 'oregano - 1 tsp, leaves', 'table salt - 1 dash', 'shrimp, precooked and diced - 16 oz', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'tomato, diced - 1 small whole (2-2/5" dia)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Sprinkle rice with oregano and dash of salt.
2. Sprinkle shrimp with curry powder and cayenne pepper.
3. Surround shrimp with rice and sliced tomatoes and serve.

name: Mediterranean Fish
description: Mediterranean Fish
recipeIngredient: ['cod atlantic - 1 lb', 'tomatoes - 4 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'green olives - 6 olive', 'capers, canned - 3 tbsp, drained', 'garlic, chopped - 1 Tbsp', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'chicken bone broth - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'spinach - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a large saute pan over medium heat. Add olive oil, fresh garlic, and whole tomatoes.
2. Cover and let simmer for five minutes, or until tomatoes begin to soften.
3. Add chopped onion, bell pepper, olives, capers, chicken broth, and salt and pepper.
4. Add chopped onion, bell pepper, olives, capers, chicken broth, and salt and pepper.
5. Add cod to pan, cover, and poach for about 5-7 minutes.
6. In the last minute, add spinach to top.

name: Chicken Avocado Spinach Salad
description: This recipe also provides an excellent balance of quality proteins and healthy fats to keep you satisfied throughout the day, without overdoing it on the carbohydrate count.
recipeIngredient: ['baby spinach - 2 cup', 'avocado - ½ cup, pureed', 'arugula, raw - 1 cup', 'sunflower seeds - ¼ tbsp', 'dried cranberries - ⅛ cup', 'chicken breast - 6 oz', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'avocado oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by slicing the avocado and then tossing with the spinach and arugula leaves, sunflower seeds, and dried cranberries.
2. Slice chicken and then add on top.
3. In a separate bowl, combine lemon juice, minced garlic, Dijon mustard, and avocado oil.
4. Drizzle over top of the salad, toss, and then serve.

name: Protein Packed Tuna Melt
description: For those days when you need a warm meal on the go, this tuna melt works perfectly. Unlike most tuna melts that are high in saturated fat and carbs, this one is moderate in carbs and packs the protein-punch of a can of tuna to support your lean muscle building goals. Due to the small size, this one cooks perfectly in a toaster oven.
recipeIngredient: ['english muffin - 1 muffin', 'tuna, canned in water - 1 can', 'low-sodium tomato sauce - ⅛ cup', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 2 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice the English muffin and then smear with the tomato sauce, one tbsp on each half.
2. Top with the tuna, sprinkle on some oregano, and place one slice of cheese on either side.
3. Place the mini-melts in the toaster oven and broil for 2-3 minutes or until cheese is just melted.

name: Spicy Kung Pao Chicken
description: Who doesn't love the classic flavor of succulent Kung Pao chicken? If you're anything like me, the spicy concoction of garlic, aromatic ginger, red chili sauce, and rice vinegar is enough to make your mouth water.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 lb', 'garlic, chopped - 8 Tbsp', 'snow peas - 2 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 2½ cup, chopped', 'cashews, chopped - 1 cup', 'extra virgin olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'liquid aminos - 4 tbsp', 'water - 4 tbsp', 'tomato paste - 2 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'coconut sugar - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tbsp', 'corn starch - 1 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - 1 tbsp', 'red chili sauce - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, add ingredients for the sauce and whisk together.
2. Set a nonstick skillet on medium-high heat, and spray with extra-virgin olive oil.
3. When the skillet is hot, toss in garlic and sear for about two minutes.
4. Add chopped chicken breast.
5. Cook the chicken for about 6-8 minutes, or until the outside is seared.
6. Next, toss in chopped bell peppers and sear for about three minutes. Stir the mixture with a wooden spatula.
7. Slowly pour in the tomato sauce, stirring frequently.
8. Toss in the raw cashews and stir.
9. Garnish with green onions and enjoy with brown rice or quinoa!

name: Singapore Chicken Rice
description: Singapore's national signature dish is chicken rice. To most dieters and competitors, this recipe probably sounds bland and all too familiar. But Singapore chicken rice has one special component: the sauce. The yummy sauce ties all the ingredients together and sets the recipe apart from your usual chicken and rice fare. I took a crack at this recipe, thanks to my stepmom, and I came up with an even healthier version with a few minor adjustments.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'cucumber, chopped - 1 cucumber (8-1/4")', 'brown rice - 1 cup', 'chicken bone broth - 1 cup', 'garlic, chopped - 4 Tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 4 tbsp', 'sesame seed oil - ½ tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 3 tbsp', 'sriracha - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Prepare brown rice with 1 cup chicken broth and 1 cup water; add half of the sliced ginger to rice while it cooks.
2. Bring water in a cooking pot to a boil, reduce to a low rolling boil and add chicken breasts. Cook for 8 minutes or until done.
3. Heat a saute pan over medium heat and add sesame oil, fresh garlic, and remaining ginger.
4. Stir continually until garlic begins to crisp. Add soy sauce.
5. When chicken is done, cut it into bite-sized pieces.
6. To serve, put 1/2 cup of brown rice, 4 oz diced chicken, and 1/4 of sliced cucumber in a bowl. Top with garlic mixture.
7. For added spice, top with Sriracha or chili paste.

name: Grilled Prawn And Peach Butter Leaf Salad
description: Prawns are a great source of clean protein. They're almost completely fat- and carb-free, making them a perfect ingredient if you're preparing for a contest. The sweet peach and honey flavors pair perfectly with the vitamins and minerals you'll be getting from the lettuce. Eat up!
recipeIngredient: ['butter leaf lettuce - 12 leaf, medium', 'peach, sliced - ½', 'prawns - 6 prawn', 'olive oil - ½ tbsp', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'honey - ½ tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Ignite grill.
2. Skewer prawns and spray with cooking spray, add salt and pepper to taste.
3. Skewer peach slices.
4. Place prawns and peaches on grill and cook for about three minutes on each side, or until prawns are cooked thoroughly and peaches have nice grill marks.
5. In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lime juice, honey, cilantro, salt, and pepper.
6. Arrange lettuce leaves on a plate, top leaves with peaches and prawns, and drizzle dressing over the top.

name: Sriracha Tuna Chili
description: The high note of this recipe is that each serving packs 32 whopping grams of protein. If you ask me, that's quite a catch! If you're feeling cheesy, I like to top a bowl with some reduced fat or fat-free cheese, too.
recipeIngredient: ['tuna, canned in water - 6 can', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'kidney beans, canned - 1 14 oz can', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 16 oz can', 'salsa - ¾ cup', 'sriracha - 10 tsp', 'tomatoes - 1 small whole (2-2/5" dia)', 'garlic, minced - 4 cup', 'canola oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Take out, drain, and rinse your dark red kidney and black beans. Drain your tuna.
2. Prepare a large stove top pan, turn your burner on medium heat, and add in your cooking oil.
3. After your pan heats up, add in your pepper stir-fry, then the rest of your ingredients while occasionally stirring everything around.
4. After your pan heats up, add in your pepper stir-fry, then the rest of your ingredients while occasionally stirring everything around.

name: Peanut Butter Oatmeal Protein Cookies
description: If you love a crunchy, chewy cookie, these peanut butter oatmeal cookies are for you! The flavor strikes the right balance of sweet and salty without being too rich. Not to mention, six of these crave-worthy cookies total just over 300 calories, and they're high in protein and low in fat—perfect for a post-workout snack.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 30 g', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 1 tbsp', 'Pyure organic stevia blend - 1 tbsp', 'baking soda - ⅛ tsp', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'butter extract - ¼ tsp', 'semisweet chocolate chips - 2 tbsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
3. Add peanut butter and remaining wet ingredients, mixing until combined.
4. Fold in chocolate chips (mini).
5. Lightly coat a baking sheet with cooking spray.
6. Scoop cookie dough onto prepared sheet by rounded tablespoonfuls.
7. Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until edges are firm and golden brown.
8. Let cool 5-10 minutes before eating. Store any leftovers up to one week at room temperature.

name: Frosted Protein Sugar Cookies
description: Even if you're on a strict diet, two or three of these "healthified" sugar cookies won't blow your nutrition. Did I mention they're soft, with just the right amount of "bite," and that the frosting is to die for?
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 80 g', 'coconut flour - 6 tbsp', 'Pyure organic stevia blend - ¼ cup', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'baking soda - ¼ tsp', 'cashew butter - 2 tbsp', 'Smart Balance light buttery spread - 2 tbsp', 'water - 3 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ cup', 'tapioca flour - 1 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 2 tbsp', 'Smart Balance light buttery spread - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Whisk together dry cookie ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
3. Add wet ingredients, and mix until a dough forms.
4. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly spray with cooking spray.
5. Form balls of dough with a tablespoon and place 2" apart on sheet.
6. Press balls flat to roughly half an inch thick using the back of a spatula or your hand.
7. Bake for 8-10 minutes until edges are firm but center is still soft (cookies will set upon cooling). I flattened mine a little more fresh out of the oven with the back of a spatula.
8. While cookies cool, combine frosting ingredients in a separate mixing bowl until smooth.
9. Spread frosting over cookies and decorate with sprinkles if desired. Enjoy!
10. Cookies can be stored at room temperature for several days or frozen up to a month.
11. Note: You may need to adjust water (3 tbsp) depending on the kind of protein powder you use.

name: Grilled Halibut With Cherry Tomatoes
description: Grilled fish, what could be better? Not only is halibut chock-full of protein, but it's also a great source of those awesome Omega-3 fatty acids that seem to be missing from most of our diets. Top the halibut with your favorite herbs for a tasty treat.
recipeIngredient: ['halibut - 4 oz', 'olive oil - ½ tbsp', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'parsley, dried - 1 tbsp', 'basil, dried - 1 tbsp, ground', 'lemon - ¼', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Light grill.
2. Brush fish with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
3. Place fish and sliced tomatoes on grill.
4. Cook fish about 4 minutes each side, or until thoroughly cooked. When finished, tomatoes will be slightly charred.
5. Top fish with tomatoes, fresh herbs, and a squeeze of lemon.

name: Red Velvet Muscle Milk Pancakes
description: No need to douse this breakfast griddle cake in loads of sugary syrup. It's already tasty and sweet enough! Follow the recipe below to serve up some guilt-free sweet treats.
recipeIngredient: ['all-purpose flour - ⅓ cup', 'egg whites - ¼ cup', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'beets, cut into cubes - ½ cup', 'muscle milk natural chocolate protein - 1 scoop (s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat greased skillet on medium heat.
2. Combine all ingredients until batter is smooth.
3. Pour into heated skillet.
4. Once bubbles form and one side is golden brown underneath, flip pancake.
5. Cook on other side until golden brown.
6. Serve with butter or cream cheese whipped with agave nectar.

name: Grilled Kale, Pear, And Walnut Salad
description: Kale is a great source of vitamins A, C, and K. It also offers a boatload of minerals your body needs to stay healthy. Add some healthy fats from the walnuts and some natural carbs from the pear and you're looking at a nutritional profile worth singing about. To make this a more complete meal, add some lean protein.
recipeIngredient: ['kale - 6 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'pear, sliced - 1', 'walnuts, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - ½ tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Ignite grill.
2. Massage kale leaves with 1/2 tbsp olive oil until lightly tender.
3. On grill, evenly spread kale leaves and pear slices.
4. Cook 2-3 minutes each side.
5. In a small bowl, whisk together 1/2 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, apple cider vinegar, mustard, Stevia, salt, and pepper.
6. Top kale with pear slices, 1 tbsp chopped walnuts, and drizzle with dressing on plate.

name: Turn Green Beans For A Side
description: Most people always will include stuffing in their Thanksgiving meal as a side, but this year to really cut back on the calories you may want to consider an alternative side of green beans.
recipeIngredient: ['Green Beans - 4 cup 1/2" pieces', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'yellow pepper, sliced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'onion powder - ½ tsp', 'sweet pepper, red - 1 small']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by slicing the beans in easy to manage pieces and then bring a large saucepan with a small amount of water inside to a boil. Drop the green beans into the pan and proceed to cook until desired tenderness is reached; up to three minutes.
2. Drain the water from the beans and then drop into cold water to prevent them from cooking further while you continue on with the recipe.
3. Next, in another saucepan lightly fry the peppers over medium heat in the olive oil. Once they are slightly softened, add the green beans to the mix along with the red pepper flakes, garlic, sesame oil, salt, pepper, and onion powder. Serve immediately once the spices have been distributed evenly.

name: White Chocolate Pumpkin Protein Cookies
description: I love white chocolate; if you ask me, it's always pumpkin o'clock somewhere. I can't resist the rich pumpkin and warm spices combined with melty white chocolate! I may or may not have eaten half the batch the first day. Luckily, half the batch totals only 390 calories. Did I mention these are full-sized cookies, about the size of the ones at Subway?
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 60 g', 'coconut flour - ¼ cup', 'Pyure organic stevia blend - ¼ cup', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - 1½ tsp', 'pumpkin, canned - ⅔ cup', 'egg whites - ¼ cup', 'Smart Balance light buttery spread - 2 tbsp', 'white chocolate chips - 1 oz', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'maple syrup - ¼ tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degres F.
2. Whisk together dry ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
3. Mix in wet ingredients until smooth.
4. Stir in white chocolate chips.
5. Lightly spray a full baking sheet with cooking spray, then drop batter by rounded tablespoons onto sheet.
6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden brown underneath and cooked through. I flatten my cookies with the back of a spatula right after they come out to make them chewier and less fluffy, but that's optional.
7. Let cool 5-10 minutes and enjoy!
8. Store any leftovers in the fridge up to one week or the freezer up to one month.

name: Grilled Steak, Onion, And Mushroom Arugula Salad
description: Need a low-carb, high-protein meal? Say no more! With this steak salad, you'll get all the protein you want without the carbs you don't. The arugula will also provide a big hit of vitamins A, K, and Folate as well as some Calcium and Potassium. The best part, however, is the yummy Asian-inspired flavor!
recipeIngredient: ['arugula, raw - 2 cup', 'flank steak - 4 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'red onion, sliced - ½ cup', 'crimini mushrooms - ½ cup sliced', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'ground ginger - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large Ziploc bag, combine garlic powder, onion powder, ginger, chili powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, soy sauce, and brown sugar. Shake thoroughly to mix well.
2. Add flank steak to bag and make sure rub thoroughly covers steak. Allow to marinate for 15 minutes.
3. Place sliced onions and mushrooms in tin foil and drizzle with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
4. Light grill.
5. Grill steak to desired temperature. Place veggies on grill for about 5-10 minutes, or until caramelized.
6. Top arugula with veggies, sliced steak, and drizzle with balsamic vinegar.

name: Vanilla Spice Chia Pudding
description: Don't fear the chia seed. Use it for what it's best at: Making nutrient-rich, delicious puddings like this one for any time of day!
recipeIngredient: ['Nourish & Bloom Vanilla Spice Whole Foods Shake - 2 packet', 'unsweetened coconut milk - 4 cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 4 tbsp', 'honey - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'black chia seeds - 12 tbsp', 'banana - ⅛ small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'mixed berries - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add coconut milk, Whole Food Shake, honey, peanut butter, and vanilla extract to a blender. Blend on high until smooth.
2. Divide mixture into eight mason jars, (or whatever container you'd like), and add 2 tablespoons of chia seeds to each jar. Use a spoon to incorporate the chia seeds into the mixture. Seal jars and shake each one well before placing them in the refrigerator.
3. Refrigerate overnight. Give mason jars a nice shake 45 minutes after refrigeration to make sure chia seeds don't sink to the bottom. Do this a few times to ensure proper blending. If chia seeds are being stubborn, open jar and use a spoon to mix.
4. When mixture is ready, layer with your topping of choice, such as banana slices or fresh berries.

name: Egg And Potato Breakfast
description: This recipe is a fun twist on the classic breakfast hash. You'll need a bowl that fits inside the pot to make this. When the eggs are cooked, turn the bowl upside down to reveal a molded dish. It's a great lazy morning meal that's a nice balance of proteins, carbs, and fats.
recipeIngredient: ['turkey bacon - 6 strip', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 2 cup', 'egg - 2 whole', 'egg whites - 1 cup', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 small', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'green onion, chopped - 2 whole', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn Instant Pot to sauté.
2. When pot is hot, add chopped bacon and sauté until crispy. Remove and drain on paper towel.
3. Add the olive oil and vegetables to pot. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.
4. Add sweet potatoes and cook for 5 more minutes.
5. Remove all ingredients from Instant Pot.
6. Spray the interior of a bowl that will fit inside Instant Pot with non-stick cooking spray.
7. Add the eggs and egg whites, milk, cheese, salt, and pepper to bowl. Whisk until combined. Add the bacon, sweet potatoes, and vegetables to mixture.
8. Place trivet in bottom of Instant Pot. Add 1 1/2 cups water to Instant Pot. Place bowl on top of trivet. Water should surround bowl.
9. Cover Instant Pot and cook at high pressure for 20 minutes.
10. Release pressure, and remove bowl from pot. Bowl will be hot!.
11. Loosen the food from the edges from the bowl; turn bowl upside down and release egg dish onto plate.
12. Carefully cut egg dish into slices. Serve each slice garnished with cheese.

name: Reindeer Mug Cake
description: What's Christmas without a little Rudolph in your life? This microwavable cake is easy to make, requires almost no cleanup, and can be prepped in a matter of minutes—leaving you with plenty of time to decorate the tree, wrap presents, and set the holiday mood.
recipeIngredient: ['Walden Farms Syrup - 1 tbsp', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tbsp', 'chocolate protein powder - 1 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix the ingredients together in a bowl.
2. Spray a large-diameter mug with nonstick cooking spray.
3. Pour the batter into the mug. Microwave on high for about two minutes.
4. Turn the mug over onto a plate. The cake will slide out.
5. Create your personalized reindeer: Decorate with a raspberry nose, chocolate chip eyes, and pretzel antlers!
6. Serve immediately.

name: Cookies-And-Cream Protein Mug Cake
description: It's hard to go wrong with a single-serving recipe that's ready in less than 5 minutes. When it's cookies-and-cream-flavored, it's even harder to mess up! My latest creation uses Sweet Spreads White Chocolate Coconutter (optional, but highly recommended) and Cookies and Cream Chocolites.
recipeIngredient: ['cookies and cream whey protein powder - 20 g', 'oat flour - 2 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'Truvia - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - ¼ tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 3 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'Sweet Spreads White Chocolate Coconutter - 1 tsp', 'butter extract - ¼ tsp', 'Cookies and Crème Chocolite, chopped - 1 piece', 'fat-free cream cheese - 1½ tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'Truvia - 1 tsp', 'butter extract - ⅛ tsp', 'Cookies and Crème Chocolite, chopped - 1 piece', 'Walden Farms Calorie Free Chocolate Syrup - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lightly spray a large coffee mug with cooking spray.
2. Mix together dry cake ingredients in a bowl, then add wet ingredients until combined.
3. Fold in chopped up Chocolite (optional).
4. Pour into an oversized mug and microwave for 2 minutes.
5. Dump your cake onto a plate and allow to cool.
6. Top with frosting, Chocolite bits, and chocolate syrup (optional). Enjoy!

name: Quick And Easy Turkey Chili
description: This chili recipe is mild in terms of heat. For an extra kick, add in Sriracha or some other hot sauce. For additional calories, top your chili with sour cream, cheese, bacon, or anything else you can think of!
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1½ tbsp', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1⅓ lb', 'water - 2 cup', 'red onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 small', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'green chilies, diced - 1 tbsp', 'red pepper, roasted, thinly sliced - ⅛ cup', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 15 oz', 'kidney beans, canned - 16 oz', 'red chili powder - 1 tsp', 'tomatoes, crushed, canned - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a large pan on stove at medium heat.
2. Add olive oil and let that heat up.
3. Add lean ground turkey and brown on both sides, being careful not to overcook.
4. Add remaining ingredients and incorporate everything together, stirring occasionally.
5. Turn up the heat and bring chili to a boil.
6. Cover chili, lower heat, and simmer for another 30-35 minutes.

name: Dark Chocolate Mint Protein Mug Cake
description: Chocolate literally makes me happy inside. If I'm having a bad day, chocolate is the answer. So naturally, I love dark chocolate and mint together! Even if you're not too crazy about mint chocolate, chances are you'll like this. The cake itself is super rich, chocolatey, and moist, and the combination is divine. Still not sold on the mint? Leave out the extract if that's not your thing.
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - 20 g', 'almond flour - 2 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'Truvia - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - ¼ tsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - 3 tbsp', 'unsweetened cashew milk - 3 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'mint extract - ¼ tsp', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 20 g', 'mint extract - ⅛ tsp', 'unsweetened cashew milk - ¼ cup', 'Truvia - ½ tsp', 'Walden Farms Calorie Free Chocolate Syrup - 1 tsp', 'sugar-free dark chocolate mint chocolate, shaved into curls - 2 square']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lightly coat an oversized mug with cooking spray and set aside.
2. Mix together cake ingredients in a bowl.
3. Spoon batter into mug and microwave for 2 minutes.
4. Dump your cake out onto a plate to cool.
5. Mix up your frosting and heat coconut butter for 10 seconds in the microwave.
6. Top cake with mint frosting, coconut butter, and sugar-free chocolate curls.

name: Chocolate Brownie Protein Mug Cake
description:
Chocolate is one of those cravings that's easy to fall victim to. When your sweet tooth calls for chocolate, whip up this easy microwavable cake. The mug cake is made with chocolate whey isolate, almond flour, unsweetened cocoa powder, egg whites, and unsweetened applesauce for added moisture. I chose almond flour to keep the cake moist, but you can also try a gluten-free baking blend, oat flour, or wheat flour (basically anything except coconut flour).

Feel free to substitute nonfat plain Greek yogurt or pumpkin puree for the applesauce! Feeling extra indulgent? Use straight up butter or coconut oil.
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - 15 g', 'almond flour - 2 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1½ tbsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - 2 tbsp', 'liquid egg whites - 3 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'table salt - 1 dash', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'coconut flour - 2 tbsp', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 1½ tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1½ tsp', 'vanilla extract - ⅛ tsp', 'butter extract - ⅛ tsp', 'table salt - ⅛ tsp', 'semisweet chocolate chips - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all brownie ingredients in a mixing bowl, stirring until smooth.
2. Lightly spray the inside of a large coffee mug with cooking spray, and pour in the
batter.
3. Microwave on high for 1-1/2 minutes, or until cooked through.
4. Dump your cake on a plate to cool while you prepare your topping.
5. Combine all topping ingredients except chocolate chips and mix until a dough is formed.
6. Fold in chocolate chips and roll into six even-sized balls.
7. If desired, break each ball in half to make six mini balls (I used four mini balls to top my mug cake)!

name: Creamy Beet Salad
description: The earthiness of oven-roasted beets makes them a great base for this salad. In addition to being a stellar source of potassium, they're hearty and take on a beautiful purple hue when plated. Combined with the essential oils of the orange and tangy taste from the sour cream, it's a dish you're sure to enjoy.
recipeIngredient: ['beets - 1', 'reduced-fat sour cream - ¼ cup', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1', 'poppy seeds - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Roast fresh beet. Dice, and place in a bowl.
2. Place sour cream in a bowl. Add fresh squeezed orange juice and zest (make sure not to grate the bitter, white pith).
3. Add poppy seeds to your dressing.
4. Spoon dressing over beets. Mix until you've achieved a beautiful blush color.
5. Place orange segments and cilantro on top as garnish. Add pepper to taste.

name: Steel Cut Apple Cinnamon Oats
description: Oatmeal should be a morning staple of every fitness enthusiast's diet. It's high in complex carbs, low in sugar, and provides a good dose of fiber. When it comes to oatmeal varieties, steel cut is best. It takes a while to cook it on a stovetop, but with an Instant Pot, it happens fast!
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 3 cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'apple, red - 2 small', 'cinnamon - ½ tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'walnuts, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn on Instant Pot to porridge setting and lightly coat with cooking spray.
2. Add oats, almond milk, cinnamon, and Stevia to pot.
3. Close lid and cook on manual for 4 minutes.
4. Once the cooking is done and the pot beeps, use the natural pressure release method and let the oats sit about 10 more minutes.
5. When pressure is released, remove lid, stir in the applesauce and apples, and let stand for 5 more minutes without lid to thicken and soften the apples slightly. Top with walnuts before serving.

name: Pesto Carrot Salad
description: Colorful carrots are the stars of this pesto dish! When creating the pesto, feel free to make it your own. If you don't have marcona almonds on hand, add any kind of nut you'd like. Don't worry if your nuts aren't completely blended. The added crunch over the tender carrots makes for a perfect pairing.
recipeIngredient: ['carrots - 2', 'almonds - 1 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 oz', 'grapeseed oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel fresh carrots and cut them into bite-sized pieces.
2. Blanch in boiling, salted water for about two minutes. Refresh in cold water.
3. Add marcona almonds, cilantro, grape seed oil, salt, and pepper to a blender. Blend.
4. Mix dressing into carrots.

name: Chocolate Chia Protein Pancake
description: These pancakes are dense, hearty, and full of chocolaty goodness. They're great as a post-workout meal or as a filling breakfast before an intense morning workout!
recipeIngredient: ['Dymatize Elite 100% Whey Protein, Chocolate Cake Batter - 1 scoop', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'black chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tbsp', 'pumpkin, canned - 2 tbsp', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'egg whites - 4 large', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients.
2. In a greased, pre-heated pan, pour batter into small circles.
3. Cook for two minutes each side or until lightly browned.
4. Top with berries and sugar-free maple syrup. If you're feeling indulgent, smear with your favorite nut butter!

name: Dyno Amino Refresher
description: Looking to add some extra oomph to your pre-workout? Let the flavors of the tropical forest get you pumped for your workout by mixing in half a scoop of DyNO fruit punch to your watermelon aminos! This combination delivers extra essential amino acids and gives you the intense energy you need to crush your workout.
recipeIngredient: ['rsp nutrition regen bcaa - 1 scoop', 'rsp nutrition dyno - ½ scoop', 'water - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. blend and enjoy

name: Instant Pot Chicken with Peppers
description: Meal prep doesn’t get any easier! This chicken goes well with just about any side dish. If you want a leaner version of this dish, remove the skin after cooking. If you’re a keto dieter, though, that extra fat might fit right into your plan
recipeIngredient: ['whole chicken (3lbs) - 1 whole chicken', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'yellow pepper, sliced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 5 clove', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'basil, dried - ½ tsp, ground', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'chicken bone broth - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brush chicken with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
2. Place sliced onion, peppers, and garlic inside the chicken’s cavity and tie legs together.
3. Turn Instant Pot to sauté and add remaining oil.
4. When oil is hot, add chicken and brown on all sides.
5. Remove chicken and set aside.
6. Place trivet in bottom of Instant Pot; add the heated chicken broth to pot (don't add cold liquids to hot oil).
7. Place chicken breast on trivet. Season it with a sprinkle of spice mixture and a drizzle of lemon juice.
8. Place cover on Instant Pot, set pot to manual, and cook chicken at high pressure for 25 minutes.
9. After 25 minutes, turn off pot and allow chicken to stand for 15 minutes more to allow for natural release of pressure.
10. Once Instant Pot is depressurized, open lid, remove chicken to serving platter.
11. Let chicken rest 10 minutes before carving.

name: Regen Watermelon Smoothie
description: Forget the weather outside: Cold or hot, this drink lets you sip on the sweet taste of summer year-round. Sip it poolside for a refreshing but healthy warm-weather treat, or drink it during your workout for extra intra-workout power!
recipeIngredient: ['rsp nutrition regen bcaa - 1 scoop', 'lemon - 1 whole', 'water - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Green Chia Protein Smoothie
description: My go-to protein shake almost always consists of a big handful of spinach, blueberries, and flaxseed. For this recipe, I replaced the flaxseed with chia seeds and swapped the blueberries for a banana! The banana and chia seeds add a thick consistency to this green goodness.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'black chia seeds - 1 cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - 1 cup', 'banana, frozen - 1 cup, mashed', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Tender Roast And Sweet Potatoes
description: This recipe also includes a dose of vegetables to maintain your fiber intake, along with sweet potatoes for some complex carbs to keep your muscle glycogen stocked and your anabolic hormones, like insulin, high.
recipeIngredient: ['lean eye of round roast - 2 pound', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 4 whole', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'carrots, sliced - 2 small (5-1/2" long)', 'onion, sliced - 2 whole', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 4 whole', 'mushrooms, sliced - 2 cup', 'Beef Broth - 1 cube', 'light soy sauce - ½ tbsp', 'fish sauce - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'rosemary - 1 to taste', 'thyme - 1 to taste', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn your Instant Pot to sauté setting; add olive oil.
2. When oil is hot, add roast; flip every minute until evenly browned.
3. Remove roast from pot and set aside.
4. Add onions, mushrooms, and garlic to pot; sauté.
5. Stir in beef broth, top with remaining herbs and spices.
6. Place roast and potatoes into pot with broth, cover, set timer to cook for 45 minutes.
7. After 45 minutes, add carrots and celery to pot. Cover and cook for another 5 minutes.
8. After 5 more minutes, relieve pressure using either method.
9. Once pressure has dropped, remove roast to serving dish, surround with vegetables and serve.

name: Broccoli Orange Slaw
description: Because it's so rich in antioxidants and fiber, broccoli is a true nutritional powerhouse. With vibrant green broccoli as the base, this salad pumps up the protein with egg, adds a touch of sweetness with grapes, and includes a bit of crunch with sunflower seeds.
recipeIngredient: ['broccoli, steamed - 4 oz', 'red grapes - 1 oz', 'hard-boiled egg - 1', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - ½', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'sunflower seeds - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Separate broccoli florets from the stems.
2. Blanch florets in boiling, salted water for about two minutes. Refresh in cold water.
3. Add sliced grapes, grated egg yolk, and grated egg whites. Add seeds.
4. Combine olive oil and rice wine vinegar. Mix with a whisk to form the base of your dressing. Add salt and pepper, then squeeze in orange juice.
5. Add dressing to dish. Plate and serve.

name: Overnight Chia Oats
description: Old-fashioned oats are a breakfast staple for most fit-minded people. This slow-digesting, fiber-rich carb is perfect for the morning meal. This no-cook recipe is perfect for those rushed mornings. When you combine the power of chia seeds with protein-rich Greek yogurt, you get one filling and nutritionally-dense breakfast!
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ⅓ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ½ cup', 'black chia seeds - 2 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'blueberries - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients except the blueberries to a jar or container with a lid (I use my magic bullet cup and lid).
2. Put lid on top and shake well.
3. Remove lid and add blueberries.
4. Replace lid and pop container in the fridge. Leave it overnight.

name: Instant Pot Sweet Potato Meal
description: Sweet potatoes are delicious in the Instant Pot, and hardly take any time at all to prepare. Add a few toppings once finished and you're all set for some serious hypertrophy-supporting food.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 4 whole', 'water - 1 cup', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 2 cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'green onion, chopped - 2 whole', 'sesame seeds - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add water to Instant Pot and place wire steamer rack inside pot.
2. Rinse sweet potatoes and slice off both ends. Remove any bad spots on potato.
3. Place potatoes on wire rack. Turn on Instant Pot and cook at potatoes at high pressure for 15-20 minutes, depending on how soft you like your sweet potatoes.
4. To depressurize the pot, turn the pot off and let the potatoes sit inside for another 10 minutes.
5. Once pot is depressurized, open lid and remove potatoes.
6. Slice open each potato and, while potato is still warm, spoon cottage cheese on top. Garnish with shredded cheddar cheese, green onions, and sesame seeds.
7. Serve immediately.

name: Angry Bruce Banner Smoothie
description: Help bring the fictional, superhuman strength of Bruce Banner—aka the Incredible Hulk—to life with this shake. It's a favorite of trainer Ed Honn, who uses it as his morning breakfast shake. "The balanced mix of complex carbohydrates, healthy fats, and lean protein are just what I need to stay energized for the day ahead," he says. When you're on the road, far from home, or just having a jam-packed day, this shake can also be used as a meal replacement.
recipeIngredient: ['muscletech nitro-tech whey plus isolate gold - 2 scoop(s)', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'ground oats - ½ cup', 'frozen mixed berries - 1 cup', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'almond milk - 6 oz']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Nuts For Chocolate Smoothie
description: NPC bikini athlete Katie Miller likes to make sure her protein smoothies meet her macros. To keep her shakes low in carbs, moderate in fat, and high in protein and taste, she customizes them. Her secret ingredient: cashew milk. Just a small amount allows her to keep her lactose intake down while still achieving that creamy consistency she craves.
recipeIngredient: ['muscle tech nitro-tech whey protein - 1 scoop(s)', 'PBfit peanut butter - ½ serving (2 tbsp)', 'cashew milk - ½ cup', 'water - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Cheesy Pumpkins
description: This creamy snack is perfect for a Halloween party. Feel free to get creative with your pumpkins!
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cream cheese - 8 oz', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ¼ cup', 'pretzels - 1 cup', 'crackers multigrain - 10 crackers']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat cream cheese at medium heat until cheddar cheese has melted.
2. Place cheese in fridge and cool for at least one hour.
3. Once cool, form cheese into small balls and place on top of crackers.
4. With a toothpick, draw lines from top to bottom of the cheese balls to create grooves like a pumpkin has.
5. Stick half a pretzel stick on the top of the cheese balls to create the stem.
6. Place in fridge until ready to serve.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Smoothie
description: When he's looking to stack on the mass, team MuscleTech athlete Jesse Hobbs likes to balance his shakes by adding healthy fats, energy-boosting carbs, and a little extra protein. With a quick prep time of 2-3 minutes, the simplicity of this shake means there's no excuse not to fuel your body right.
recipeIngredient: ['water - 8 fl oz', 'smooth peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup', 'muscle tech nitro-tech whey protein - 2 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Canada Day Jello-O
description: Oh, dessert: Picnics just aren't the same without it! This low-carb, protein-rich dessert is your solution to the dessert conundrum. It'll keep your blood sugar levels stable and your metabolic rate strong. Have your Jell-O and eat it, too!
recipeIngredient: ['jello - 1 serving', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Strawberry Banana - 1 scoop', 'skim milk - 1 cup', 'strawberries - 2 cup', 'fat-free whipped cream - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Prepare Jell-O according to package.
2. Once the Jell-O powder is almost dissolved, add in the protein powder and continue stirring until it's dissolved.
3. Pour mixture into a 9 x 12 inch dish and place in the fridge to set.
4. As Jell-O sets, beat whipped topping with skim milk, according to package directions. If you want to boost protein content, add one scoop of vanilla protein powder and a package of Stevia for added sweetness.
5. Top set Jell-O with whipped topping and decorate with sliced strawberries to form the Canadian flag.
6. Keep chilled until serving.

name: Blueberry And Cottage Cheese Insanity
description: Enjoy this delicious cottage cheese recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cottage cheese - 1 cup', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'buckwheat flour - ¾ cup', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'lemon juice - 1½ tsp', 'blueberries - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine cottage cheese, skim milk, and flour in a bowl.
2. Beat egg whites until frothy but not stiff and add to cottage cheese mixture.
3. Add lemon juice, stir, add blueberries, and stir again.
4. Pour all of the batter into a nonstick frying pan and turn when tops begin to bubble and bottom is lightly browned.
5. Divide into four wedges and serve.

name: Vanilla Caramel Protein Crepe
description: Give us just 45 seconds of your time, and we'll show you how to whip up a delicious batch of Vanilla Caramel Protein Crepes!
recipeIngredient: ['ground oats - ⅔ cup', 'vanilla caramel protein powder - 2 scoop', 'almond milk - 1 cup', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'egg whites - 2', 'coconut oil - 1½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ingredients in blender.
2. Pour 1/3 cup batter onto a greased skillet and cook over medium heat. When bubbles begin to form, flip the crepe and cook for another minute.
3. Add desired toppings and enjoy!

name: Pumpkin Carrot Muffins
description: The pumpkin flavor gives these muffins the feel of the season, but the low-cal ingredients deliver solid nutrition. They're a great addition to Halloween festivities.
recipeIngredient: ['almond flour - 1 cup', 'oat flour - ¾ cup', 'baking powder - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'agave syrup - ¼ cup', 'pure pumpkin - 1 serving (1/2 cup)', 'carrots - ½ cup chopped', 'raisins - ¼ cup', 'skim milk - ½ cup', 'coconut oil - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Combine flours, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and pumpkin spice.
3. In another bowl, mix egg, agave syrup, milk, raisins, and coconut oil.
4. Purée carrots and pumpkin together and then combine with wet ingredients.
5. Mix wet and dry ingredients and then pour batter into a non-stick muffin tin.
6. Bake for 15-18 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
7. If desired, top muffins with fat-free cream cheese.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Muffins With Chocolate Chips
description: Peanut butter fans will love the one-two punch of natural PB and the flavored protein powder. Feel free to experiment with other flavors, though. There are no rules here!
recipeIngredient: ['all-purpose flour - 1 cup', 'Dymatize ISO-100 Whey Protein, Peanut Butter - 1 scoop', 'coconut sugar - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'egg - 2 whole', 'semisweet chocolate chips - ½ cup mini chips']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all dry ingredients into mixing bowl and stir.
2. Stir in peanut butter and almond milk.
3. Add the eggs and chocolate chips, and combine well.
4. Pour batter into six wells of a greased or lined muffin pan and bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes, until slightly firm.

name: No-Bake Peanut Butter Protein Bars
description: These bars have rock-solid macros and the flavor to smash any craving. Keep a few in the fridge just to be safe!
recipeIngredient: ['natural peanut butter - ⅓ cup', 'honey - ½ cup', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'Dymatize ISO-100 Whey Protein, Peanut Butter - 1 scoop', 'semisweet chocolate chips - ½ cup mini chips']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
2. Pour batter into a nonstick 9x9 pan and place in fridge until completely cooled, then cut into 9 pieces.

name: Carrot Eyes
description: Need a low-cal, spooky treat? Try these carrot eyes. They only take a few minutes, but everyone will love them.
recipeIngredient: ['carrots - 3 large (7-1/4" to 8-/1/2" long)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'blueberries, dried - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel carrots and cut them into inch-thick slices.
2. Top each carrot with a spoonful of Greek yogurt.
3. Place two dried cranberries on top of the yogurt to form eyes.
4. If preferred, use olives instead of cranberries.

name: Fruit Pizza
description: This is a great party dessert recipe that's lighter in calories but still high on taste.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - 1¼ cup', 'fat-free cream cheese - ½ cup', 'Splenda - 8 tbsp', 'low-sugar strawberry jam - 4 tbsp', 'heavy whipping cream - ½ cup, whipped', 'strawberries - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'frozen peaches - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the oats, cream cheese, and Splenda in a bowl.
2. Once well mixed, press into a pie plate until firm.
3. Spread the sugar-free jam on top of crust and then spoon over that Cool Whip topping.
4. Arrange fruit over the cool whip and set aside.
5. In a saucepan, combine the sugar, salt, corn starch, orange juice, lemon juice, and water.

name: Pudding Parfaits
description: At this time of year, trying to forgo your cravings for chocolate may feel like mission impossible. Instead of stealing candy from your kids, whip up this low-calorie pudding as a chocolatey snack.
recipeIngredient: ['sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - 1 box', 'skim milk - 2 cup', 'cookies and cream whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'whipped cream topping - 1 cup', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Beat together skim milk and pudding powder.
2. Once mixed, beat in protein powder.
3. When mixed, place in separate serving dishes.
4. In a separate bowl, combine whipped topping and orange juice.
5. Once fully mixed, spoon on top of each pudding serving.

name: Green Machine Smoothie
description: To start her day off right, fitness competitor Danielle Beausoleil turns to a well-balanced shake that gives her the protein, antioxidants, fiber, healthy fats, and energizing carbs she needs to forge through the day ahead. Her recipe takes nutrition to a new level by incorporating both greens and super fruits to pack as much of a nutritional punch as possible into one cup.
recipeIngredient: ['muscletech nitro-tech whey plus isolate gold - ½ scoop(s)', 'black chia seeds - ½ tsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'ginger, pureed - 1 tsp', 'spirulina, seaweed - 1 serving', 'water - 8 fl oz', 'muscletech platinum 100% glutamine - 1 scoop', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'mint leaves - 1 tsp', 'almond milk - 4 oz']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Pumpkin Spice Smoothie
description: To prepare her perfect shake, IFBB figure pro Elissa Martis adds some cacao powder to the mix. The benefits are twofold: the added cacao enhances taste and delivers healthy antioxidant power. If you want a lean shake that'll keep you burning fat for hours to come, this is a great go-to recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['muscletech nitro-tech whey plus isolate gold - 1 scoop(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'pumpkin puree - ¼ cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'water - 8 fl oz', 'pumpkin pie spice - 1 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Orange Cream Smoothie
recipeIngredient: ['muscle tech nitro-tech whey protein - 1 scoop(s)', 'whipped topping, frozen, low fat - 1 cup', 'orange zest - 1 tbsp', 'orange ice cream (artic zero) - 2 scoop', 'almond milk - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Strawberry Siege Nighttime Mousse
description: Another favorite of Alderton's is this fruit-based mousse. From the light and fluffy texture to the muscle-building protein content, this dessert has it all. It's a perfect, airy way to finish your day and top off a well-rounded meal plan.
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra Charge, Strawberry - 1 scoop', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 1 cup', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'jello - ½ serving']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix 10 ounces of boiling water with half a pouch of sugar-free Jell-O. Allow to cool for 10 minutes.
2. Once cooled, add the cottage cheese and Hydra 6 to a blender with the Jell-O mix. Blend for 1 minute.
3. Once blended, chop up 200 g of strawberries into a container. Add the mixture.
4. Refrigerate for 6 hours, then enjoy!

name: Tasty Oat Squares
description: See you later, oatmeal! These tasty protein-filled squares are a great way to appease the nighttime snacker in us all. Each square is packed with a hearty dose of complex carbs that's sure to leave you satiated and ready to hit your morning workout. Dig in!
recipeIngredient: ['light butter spread - ¾ cup', 'honey - 1¼ cup', 'chopped dates - ¾ cup', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'coconut - 1 cup, shredded', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Killa Vanilla - 3 scoop', 'raisins - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Melt butter, honey, and chopped dates.
2. Stir in oats, coconut, raisins, and three scoops of Grenade Hydra 6.
3. Cook at 325 degrees F for 20 minutes. Enjoy!

name: Chocolate and Peanut Butter Cookies
description: Who said that in order to stay in shape you had to lay off the sweets? Not in this case! Here's a cookie recipe from Chef Murphy that uses protein powder and healthy fats to make dessert meet your macros.
recipeIngredient: ['MET-Rx Ultramyosyn Whey Vanilla Protein Powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'coconut flakes - 1 cup', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'banana - 1 cup, mashed', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven 350 degrees F.
2. In a large bowl, mash banana until smooth.
3. Add remaining ingredients and mix until combined.
4. Lay a sheet of parchment paper on an oven tray and spoon bite-sized portions of cookie mix onto tray.
5. Bake for 15 minutes.

name: Strawberry Ghosties
description: Strawberries are good, vanilla protein is good, and chocolate chips are good. Combine all three and you have a great recipe. It's the easiest recipe ever, but the product looks much more difficult. Enjoy the smiles these little guys bring out!
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari MyoFusion Advanced Protein, Peanut Butter Cookie - ½ scoop', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'dark chocolate chips - 2 oz', 'fiber one cereal - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix protein, Greek yogurt, and syrup to make a sauce.
2. Dip strawberries in sauce until coated.
3. When strawberries are covered, use chocolate chips to make eyes, and pieces of cereal to make a mouth.
4. Serve immediately.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Cupcakes
description: Model, actor, and Body Fortress athlete Mike O'Hearn doesn't have much time to spend in the kitchen baking. But when he decides to make himself a tasty breakfast treat to kick-start the morning, he whips up these bad boys. Try them for yourself, and let your inner superhero loose!
recipeIngredient: ['cocoa powder, unsweetened - 6 tbsp', 'egg whites - 4 large', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ½ cup', 'baking soda - ½ tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'semisweet chocolate chips - 1 tbsp', 'Body Fortress Super Advanced Whey Protein - 2 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F, and spray cupcake tin with nonstick cooking spray.
2. Mix all ingredients together using blender or food processor, and divide evenly into 12 cupcake tins.
3. Bake for 12-15 minutes.

name: Oatmeal Pancakes
description: A delicious oatmeal protein pancake recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1 cup', 'unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'egg whites - 3 large', 'water - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 1½ tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - 1½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
2. Cook in a microwave for 1-2 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed by the oats.
3. Top with all-natural peanut or almond butter, or sugar-free maple syrup.

name: Greek Yogurt
description: So if your taste buds and food sensibilities are begging for a change? Ah! Not another chicken breast!? Why not try vegetarian for a day?
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 8 oz', 'almonds, slivered - ½ cup', 'dried apricots - ½ cup, halves', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine all the above ingredients and chow down!

name: Sugar Free Chocolate Craze Pudding
description: When you're in a time crunch and need to get out the door as soon as possible, having a quick breakfast already prepared will help you resist the urge to walk out the door on an empty stomach. I keep a bowl of this delicious pudding in the refrigerator at all times for just such occasions!
recipeIngredient: ['water - 16 fl oz', 'fat-free pistachio instant pudding mix - 2 tbsp', 'MET-Rx Meal Replacement Chocolate - 1 packet']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix 1 packet of MET-Rx Meal Replacement Chocolate with 16 ounces of ice-cold water.
2. Blend at low speed for 20 seconds.
3. Add 2 tablespoons of your favorite Jell-O Sugar-Free Instant Pudding.
4. Blend at high speed for 1 minute, refrigerate for 1 hour, and serve.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Shake
description: Thanks to sugar substitutes and flavored protein powders, you can still satisfy your sweet tooth without also eating a lot of carbs. Here's a recipe for one of my favorite shakes. Feel free to adjust the ingredient amounts as necessary to fit your macros. You can also substitute low-fat or nonfat cottage cheese if that's what you've got on hand.
recipeIngredient: ['almond milk - 1 cup', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ½ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 3 tbsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Chocolate Malt - 1 scoop', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Edamame, Hummus, Whole-Grain Crackers
description: So if your taste buds and food sensibilities are begging for a change? Ah! Not another chicken breast!? Why not try vegetarian for a day?
recipeIngredient: ['edamame - 1 cup', 'hummus - 1 cup', 'crackers multigrain - 10 crackers']
recipeInstructions:
1. This one is simple: Hold, dip, munch. Construct an edamame and cracker tower with hummus as cement. Challenge yourself?how high can you stack?
2. Annoy your cubicle buddies with the sound of crunching. After all, it's good for your health, and that's what matters.

name: Chocolate-Covered Protein Pretzels
description: Turn the treat of chocolate-covered pretzels into a protein-packed creation with this healthy twist on the original.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'coconut oil - ⅛ cup', 'coconut flour - 4 tbsp', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'dark chocolate - 5 square']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together the whey, coconut oil, coconut flour, and milk until you get dough. Make sure your coconut oil is melted before you do this, by the way. (If it isn't, just stick it in the microwave for a few seconds).
2. Roll out the dough on a nonstick cookie tray or on top of some baking parchment.
3. Get out your pretzel cutter, and cut out 14 pretzel shapes.
4. Bake the pretzels on a nonstick cookie tray or on top of baking parchment at 320 F (160 C) for about 10 minutes, or until they're cooked though but not super hard. You don't want to bake them to death. They shouldn't brown at all; they just need to cook through.
5. Melt your chocolate in a bain marie (a glass bowl on top of a pot of boiling water) or double boiler, and dip the pretzels in there. Decorate by sprinkling with candy chunks, chocolate flakes, or honeycomb. I added some strawberry sprinkles; they're awesome because they add crunchiness to the pretzel, which is delicious.
6. Put the pretzels in the fridge for a couple of hours or the freezer for 30 minutes and BOOOOM! Ready!

name: Chocolate Banana Late-Night Escape
description: For those times when you're craving the classic combination of sweet cocoa and fruit, reach for this recipe. It's a tasty, pre-bedtime snack that's a favorite of fitness athlete Melih Cologlu, and it's sure to satisfy your sweet tooth. As an added bonus, the bite-size slices of banana make portion control easy when you're feeling tempted to devour the entire pot.
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra Charge, Chocolate Charge - 1 scoop', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'banana - 1 medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'dark chocolate - ½ square']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix Greek yogurt with Hydra 6 Chocolate Charge protein powder.
2. Slice one medium banana.
3. Using a small spoon, apply the chocolate cream onto each slice.
4. Sprinkle with a dash of grated dark chocolate.

name: Protein Pumpkin Mousse Pie
description: There are times when Jell-O just doesn't hit the spot and pudding's consistency doesn't feel quite right. That's when mousse is the perfect solution! There's nothing quite like that creamy thickness that also carries an airy consistency. Get your fill of this flavorful treat with bodybuilder Amber Passini's pumpkin-filled dessert!
recipeIngredient: ['Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 1½ scoop', 'milk, fat-free - ½ cup', 'pumpkin pie spice - 1 tbsp', 'sugar-free vanilla pudding mix - 1 package', 'whipped topping, frozen, low fat - 1 cup', 'Keebler Ready Crust, Graham Pie Crust, reduced fat - 1 crust']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, whisk together milk and spices. Add pumpkin and stir until combined.
2. Add pudding mix and protein powder.
3. Beat with wire whisk for 1-1/2 minutes. Stir in half of the whipped topping. Spread the mixture into the premade crust.
4. Top with remaining whipped topping.
5. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

name: Green Monster
description: Go green! Start the day right with this veggie-powered that packs a solid protein punch.
recipeIngredient: ['stalk celery, finely diced - 3 stalk, small', 'kale - 1 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'pineapple - 1 slice (4-2/3" dia x 3/4" thick)', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Valentine's Day Red Velvet Pancakes
description: "Start the day by making a romantic breakfast with these sexy red velvet pancakes," Lawrence suggests. "If you really want to be special, use a cookie cutter to cut the pancakes into hearts."
recipeIngredient: ['ground oats - 1 cup', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'baking soda - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - ¾ tsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1½ tbsp', 'red food coloring - 1 tsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'club soda - 1½ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 3 tbsp', 'powdered sugar - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat milk - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the pancake griddle or skillet to 350 degrees F, or to medium heat.
2. Grease cooking surface with coconut oil.
3. In a large bowl, quickly mix together all the ingredients, except for glaze ingredients. Don't overmix the batter.
4. Pour about 1/4-cup pancake batter onto hot pan or griddle. Cook until bubbles form on surface, then flip and cook the other side for an additional minute or so.
5. Repeat with the remaining batter.
6. Glaze Directions:
Mix ingredients together until smooth.
7. Spread glaze on top of cooked pancakes. Add sugar-free maple syrup if desired.
8. Serve hot.

name: Avocado-Egg Hybrid
description: If you want to go paleo, you have to cook. Trust me, this isn't a bad thing. Here are a few freshman-level eats you can throw together in even the measliest dorm kitchen.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 1 fruit, without skin and seed', 'egg - 2 whole', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice a ripe, medium-to-large avocado lengthwise. Remove the seed.
2. With a spoon, carve out a slightly bigger crater for one whole egg to rest in.
3. Place the 2 halves into an oven-safe tin. Make sure the halves are stable, or the eggs may slip out.
4. Season to taste; I like a few fresh-cut green onions, sea salt, and chili pepper flakes.
5. Crack your egg into the avocado crater and season a bit more if desired.
6. Broil at 350 degrees for about 15 minutes or until the egg is cooked to your liking.

name: Chicken Burger Topped With Feta, Roasted Red Bell Pepper & Arugula
description: Chicken is a great source of lean, high-quality protein. Add in roasted red pepper, feta cheese, and arugula, and you've got a meal that's not only high in protein, potassium, and antioxidants, but also offers a mouthful of savory Mediterranean flavors.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken - 1 lb', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - ½ cup', 'red pepper, roasted, thinly sliced - ¼ cup', 'tomatoes, sliced - 1', 'fresh basil leaves - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'whole-wheat sandwich thins - 8 slice']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat grill.
2. In a bowl, mix 1 lb. ground chicken with feta cheese, chopped basil, roasted bell pepper, salt and pepper.
3. Form 4 small burgers, approximately 4 oz. apiece.
4. Cook thoroughly on grill, about 10 minutes each side.
5. Place on sandwich thins and top with sliced tomato, feta, roasted red bell pepper, and arugula.

name: Optimum Pumpkin Protein Bars
description: Protein bars are great go-to snacks. They're portable, easy, and give you something to reach for in lieu of that bag of chips. More often than not, you can also add delicious to the list. If you're looking for a pumpkin bar recipe that doesn't fall short, reach for this one from Optimum athlete Sean Royer.
recipeIngredient: ['smooth peanut butter - 2 cup', 'honey - ½ cup', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 2¼ cup', 'raw oats - 3 cup', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, microwave the peanut butter and honey for about 60-90 seconds. Stir well.
2. Mix the peanut butter and honey mixture with the remaining base ingredients until combined. Stir in the add-ins on low speed until the mixture is well combined. Mixture should be about the consistency of Play-Doh. If mixture is too thin, add more oatmeal. If it's too thick, add more honey.
3. Cut a length of wax paper long enough to line the bottom of an 8x12 pan with the sides extending slightly over the rim, which will help you remove the mixture from the pan for easy cutting.
4. Spread the mixture into the prepared pan. Press the mixture flat in all corners with a piece of wax paper. Sprinkle some extra oatmeal and dried raisins or nuts on the top of the bars, and press lightly to set.
5. Chill until firm. Pull on the wax paper to remove bars from the pan. Cut into 24 pieces and wrap individually in wax paper. If not used right away, wrapped bars can be frozen in a freezer bag.
6. Optional add-ins:
1/3 cup chopped mixed nuts,
1/4 cup raisins,
1/4 cup wheat bran or wheat germ,
1/4-1/2 cup shaved unsweetened coconut,
2 tbsp flax seeds,
1/8 cup carob chips (mini version works best)

name: Pumpkin Cranberry Streusel Bars
description: Who doesn't love baked goods with crumbly topping? Throw in pumpkin and cranberries, and you've got athlete Maria DiNello's winning recipe that's sure to top your list of seasonal favorites.
recipeIngredient: ['Splenda - 8 tbsp', 'pumpkin, canned - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - 1½ tsp', 'baking soda - 2 tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'egg whites - 3 large', 'vanilla extract - 1½ tsp', 'oat flour - 1 cup', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 1½ scoop', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'pecans, chopped - ¼ cup', 'sugar-free jelly (raspberry or cranberry) - ⅓ cup', 'Splenda - 3 tsp', 'coconut oil - 3 tbsp', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Cover an 8x8 glass dish with nonstick spray.
3. Combine all ingredients except pumpkin, walnuts, and oat flour. Once mixed, add in pumpkin, walnuts, and flour.
4. Spread half of the batter into the glass dish.
5. Spread sugar-free jelly over batter, and pour remaining batter on top of jelly.
6. In a separate bowl, mix the last four ingredients together. The mixture should be clumpy. Break it into pieces over batter for streusel topping.
7. Bake for 20 minutes. Cut into 12 squares.

name: Protein Pumpkin Rolls With Protein Cream Cheese
description: Don't fall prey to the temptation of warm cinnamon buns. Instead, try this recipe by Optimum athlete Kate Osman. With pumpkin-flavored dough and a sweet, cream cheese glaze, these rolls are sure to taste like a full-on cheat meal without the hefty nutritional price tag. Coming in at under 200 calories and packed with 17 grams of protein, they're fitness-pro approved!
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin, canned - ¼ cup', 'coconut flour - 2 tbsp', 'egg whites - ⅓ cup', 'baking powder - ¼ tbsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 1½ scoop', 'fat-free cream cheese - ⅓ cup', 'Optimum Gold Standard 100% Casein, Vanilla - ½ scoop', 'water - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Directions for rolls: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. In a bowl, mix all ingredients together. Spray a cupcake pan with nonstick cooking spray and spoon in batter to make 4 rolls.
3. Place in oven and bake for about 10 minutes.
4. Using a knife, loosen the rolls from the pan and flip them over. Continue baking for 2-5 minutes. Be careful not to overcook. Insert a toothpick and make sure it comes out clean to ensure rolls are baked through.
5. Remove from oven to cool.
6. Directions for protein cream cheese frosting: Mix cream cheese and casein powder together in a bowl. Add sweetener and water if needed. Just try not to eat it all before you ice the rolls.
7. Frost and dig in!

name: Grilled Portobella And Zucchini Burger
description: Indulge in nature's burger! The thick, meaty texture of portobella mushrooms makes it a favorite among meat lovers and vegetarians alike. This shroom also offers an antioxidant blast on par with far more famous vegetables, and at a minimal calorie cost: One cup only has 42 calories. Fire up the fungus!
recipeIngredient: ['portabella mushroom caps - 2', 'zucchini, sliced - ½', 'red pepper, roasted, thinly sliced - ½ cup', 'low fat cheese - 2 slice (1 oz)', 'spinach - ½ cup', 'whole-wheat sandwich thins - 4 slice']
recipeInstructions: 1. Heat grill.

name: Coconut Greens Shake
description: This refreshing take on a greens shake has a velvety-smooth consistency thanks to the coconut oil. It's great for a pre- or post-workout meal!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'coconut water, unsweetened - ½ cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'coconut flakes - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients except for coconut flakes in a blender and blend until smooth.
2. Pour into glass and top with coconut flakes.

name: Pumpkin Pie Peanut Butter Cups
description: Peanut butter cups: delicious. Pumpkin: equally tasty. What could be better than having both of these things in one day? Having them both in one meal, of course! Create the perfect treat with this recipe from IFBB Physique pro Alex Carneiro.
recipeIngredient: ['cocoa powder, unsweetened - ¼ cup', 'coconut oil - ¼ cup', 'Splenda - 2 tbsp', 'pumpkin puree - 2 tbsp', 'smooth peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - ½ scoop', 'pumpkin pie spice - ⅛ tsp', 'water - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Stir the cocoa powder, coconut oil, and sweetener together until they form a sauce. Fill the bottom of cupcake liners or candy molds with the sauce, and save the rest of the mixture. Freeze the liners for 10 minutes.
2. While freezing, mix the remaining ingredients. Add water one tablespoon at a time until the mixture forms a paste. Take the liners out of the freezer, and top with one teaspoon of pumpkin mixture.
3. Add one more layer of the chocolate mixture, and put liners back in freezer for 10 minutes.
4. Remove, let sit for 3 minutes, and enjoy!

name: Coconut-Oat Bars
description: Before I travel, I like to prep this meal. It's perfect for packing and it's easy when your mornings are busy and hectic. The coconut adds great flavor and fiber to the usual homemade protein bar!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ½ cup', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ½ scoop(s)', 'coconut flakes - 1 cup', 'coconut extract - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon -  to taste', 'powdered Stevia -  to taste', 'coconut milk - ¼ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
2. Spray 8x8 pan with non-stick spray.
3. Blend all ingredients in a blender and pour into pan.
4. Bake for 15 minutes.
5. Cut into squares.

name: Coconut Peanut Butter Protein Cake
description: Protein mug cake anyone? Yes please! Try this decadent, creamy concoction and you'll forget you're on a diet. It's a treat without the guilt and is great for a bedtime snack!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'egg - 1', 'coconut flakes - 1 tbsp', 'coconut extract - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'coconut flakes - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray the inside of a mug with non-stick cooking spray.
2. Add protein, flour, egg, 1 tbsp coconut flakes, and extract to mug and mix well.
3. Microwave for 75 seconds.
4. Top cake with almond butter and coconut flakes!

name: Split Pea Vegan Soup
description: This is a nutritious and hearty recipe for chilly winter days or evenings. Good for the body and warm for the soul.
recipeIngredient: ['green split peas - 1 cup', 'white onion - 1 sliced', 'carrots, sliced - 1 small (5-1/2" long)', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2 stalk, medium', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'liquid aminos - 3 tbsp', 'water - 8 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a crock pot slow cooker. Heat on low.
2. Check for water evaporation every 3-4 hours. Add water as needed.
3. Cook until tender about 12-14 hours.

name: Lemon Garlic Leg Of Lamb & Red Wine Sauce
description: If you're a red-meat aficionado, you know there are few things as satisfying as sinking your teeth into a perfectly-done leg of lamb. My slow-and-low method results in an insanely tender roast that's delectable with or without the savory red wine sauce.
servingSize: 5 oz. cooked lamb and 1/4 cup sauce
recipeIngredient: ['boneless leg of lamb roast - 5 lb', 'lemon juice - ¼ cup', 'garlic, minced - 8 clove', 'rosemary - 3 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 2 cup', 'red wine vinegar - 1 cup', 'cornstarch - 1 tbsp', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. For the lamb: Place lamb in a roasting pan and rub with lemon juice, then pat garlic and rosemary over the skin evenly. Salt and pepper to taste.
2. Let roast sit at room temperature at least one hour before roasting. This is a good time to prepare your vegetables from the next recipe.
3. If you want a nice crust on the outside of your roast, broil lamb at 450° F for 5 minutes right-side-up, then flip and broil another 5 minutes underneath prior to roasting. This is optional.
4. Preheat oven to 325° F.
5. Cook roast for another 2-3 hours depending on desired doneness. For a 4-7-pound roast, cook 20 minutes per pound for medium rare, or until the internal temp is 140° F. For medium, cook 25 minutes per pound for medium, until the internal temp is 150° F. For well-done, cook 30 minutes per pound, until the internal temp is 160° F.
6. Remove from roasting pan and let rest for 15-20 minutes before carving.
7. For the sauce: Place roasting pan over stovetop burners.
8. Add chicken broth and red wine or vinegar to pan drippings and bring to a low boil.
