9. Continue to cook for 5 minutes while scraping up browned bits from the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon.
10. Mix cornstarch with water and add to pan.
11. Simmer and stir one minute until thickened. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
12. Strain gravy through a colander or sieve into a gravy boat before serving.
13. Slice lamb and serve with sauce drizzled over the top.

name: Salmon Burger With Sautéed Onions & Yogurt Dill Sauce
description: Pack in the omega-3 fatty acids with this tangy, flavorful fish dish! Not only is salmon low in fat and calories, but one 4 oz. serving has 24 grams of protein. Top with sautéed onions and yogurt dill sauce for that perfect hot-cold combination!
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 8 oz', 'Mesquite seasoning - ¼ tsp', 'red onion, sliced - ¼', 'arugula, raw - 1 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup', 'dill - 1 tsp', 'whole-wheat sandwich thins - 4 slice']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat grill.
2. Sprinkle salmon with mesquite seasoning.
3. Grill fish to desired temperature (8-12 minutes).
4. In a small bowl, mix together Greek yogurt and dill.
5. Sauté red onion in small sauté pan until caramelized.
6. Spread a thin layer of yogurt sauce on sandwich thin. Place salmon fillet on top and garnish with red onions and arugula.

name: Coconut Chocolate Clusters
description: One of my favorite flavor combos is chocolate and almond butter. Add coconut and some oats and you have a well balanced snack on the go.
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'coconut flakes - 4 tbsp', 'almonds, slivered - 2 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - ¼ cup', 'coconut milk - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
2. Drop spoonfuls on baking sheet with parchment paper and place in freezer for 30 minutes.

name: Crustless Protein Pumpkin Pie
description: Who says you can't have your pie and eat it, too? Cut carbs and fat—and keep the taste—with this healthy take on traditional protein pie from IFPA and NGA Bikini pro Ashley Leahy. The best part? If you whip it up for Thanksgiving, you can help yourself to a guilt-free serving of seconds. Of course, Thanksgiving's not until November, so feel free to run a test batch or two in the interim. It's just that good!
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin, canned - 2 cup', 'almond milk - 12 oz', 'liquid egg whites - ¾ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - ½ scoop', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'liquid Stevia - 40 drop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Mix all ingredients together with a wire whisk, then pour batter into a greased pie pan.
3. Bake for 50-55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

name: Jerky Power
description: Plain sliced apples are kids' stuff. Add some crushed red pepper for a metabolic boost and that delicious sweet 'n' spicy combo. Trade in that Happy Meal for a few strips of jerky. You'll get all the benefits of red meat with less fat.
recipeIngredient: ['apple, sliced - 1 whole', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'beef jerky - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions: 1. Season apple slices with crushed red pepper and enjoy with beef jerky.

name: Pumpkin Million Dollar Pie
description: Bikini competitor Dayna Tappan's favorite fall flavor comes with a hefty price tag—a cool million, to be exact. With pecans, almonds, and a graham cracker crust—not to mention a generous serving of pumpkin—this pie is well worth its name.
recipeIngredient: ['whipped cream topping - 12 oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 6 oz', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 2 scoop', 'pumpkin, canned - 1 cup', 'pecans, chopped - 1 cup', 'graham crackers - 2 cracker']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all the ingredients together (except for the pie crusts) in a large mixing bowl.
2. Add Truvia or Stevia and the pumpkin spice to taste. Tailor this pie to your desired sweetness level—add more yogurt for tartness, or pumpkin to increase the sweetness.
3. Spoon the mixture into the pie crusts.
4. Let pies sit in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

name: Teriyaki Tofu Burger
description: The zesty Asian flair of this burger will make you a tofu believer! Savor the pairing of caramelized onions with spicy chili flakes and Sriracha, all supported by the sweet smokiness of Teriyaki marinade. If you need any further convincing, tofu contains all of the essential amino acids and packs in 6 grams of protein per 3 oz. serving.
recipeIngredient: ['tofu, firm - 6 oz', 'teriyaki, sauce, reduced sodium - 1 tbsp', 'sriracha - 1 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'red onion, sliced - ¼', 'carrots, sliced - ¼ cup strips or slices', 'lettuce (butterhead) - 2 leaf, large', 'Flat Out sandwich wraps - 2 flatbread']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat grill.
2. Marinate tofu in teriyaki marinade, red chili flakes and Sriracha.
3. Sauté red onion in pan until caramelized.
4. Grill tofu for 3-4 min on each side.
5. Place on Flat Out wrap. Top with butter leaf lettuce, shredded carrots, and caramelized red onion.

name: Pumpkin Pie Ice Cream
description: Warm weather may be on its way out, but that doesn't mean ice cream is off-limits. Put a seasonal spin on this delicious delicacy—and lighten things up with protein-rich yogurt—with Dayna Tappan's recipe for a cool, refreshing treat.
recipeIngredient: ['whipped cream topping - 12 oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 12 oz', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Pumpkin Pie - 2 scoop', 'pecans, chopped - 1 cup', 'graham crackers - 4 cracker', 'Walden Farms Caramel Syrup - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all the ingredients together.
2. Add Truvia or Stevia and pumpkin spice to taste, then swirl in the caramel.
3. Crumble nuts and graham crackers, and swirl into the mix.
4. Freeze.
5. Top with caramel and enjoy!

name: Fruit Tart With Protein Crust
description: The protein pie crust recipe would be great for any pie, but it's absolutely perfect with this light and fruity tart filling! You can also make this the night before and garnish with fruit just before serving. Make two if you would like more generous helpings. Trust me, you will!
recipeIngredient: ['oat flour - 1½ cup', 'Jamie Eason Signature Series Whey Protein Isolate - 120 g', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'coconut oil - 3 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'water - 2 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 16 oz', 'powdered Stevia - ½ cup', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'kiwi - 1', 'blueberries - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350° F.
2. Combine crust ingredients, and knead to form a dough. Add another water if dough is too crumbly too stick to itself.
3. Press dough in an 8- or 9-inch cake pan or tart pan and bake for 10-15 minutes.
4. Combine Greek yogurt, sweetener, and vanilla until smooth. I recommend splurging on a high-quality brand like Fage. If your Greek yogurt doesn't have a thick pudding-like texture, leave it in a fine sieve coated with cheesecloth or coffee filters for a couple hours to drain off excess liquid.
5. Spread yogurt mixture over cooked pie crust, and leave in fridge for 30-45 minutes until set.
6. Garnish with fruit and slice into 12 pieces.

name: Tilapia Tacos
description: My favorite dish to order at Mexican restaurants is fish tacos. I love the combination of flaky white fish, crunchy red cabbage, creamy avocado, and bright flavors from the lime and cilantro. But let's face it: when you have serious fitness goals, you probably aren't frequenting Mexican restaurants. The chips and salsa alone do me in! I was determined to come up with my own healthy version of fish tacos. This recipe is sure to make you forget you're dieting!
recipeIngredient: ['corn tortilla - 4', 'tilapia - 4 fillet', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'avocado - 1', 'red cabbage - ½ cup, shredded', 'lime - 1', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to 375 degrees, wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven while cooking tilapia.
2. Heat coconut oil in medium pan over medium heat.
3. Season tilapia filets evenly with all spices.
4. Place filets in pan and cook 3-4 minutes each side, or until cooked thoroughly.
5. Once tilapia is fully cooked, assemble tacos. Place one tilapia filet in each corn tortilla with 1/4 sliced avocado, red cabbage, and garnish with cilantro and lime.
6. Note: Add 1 tbsp fat-free plain Greek yogurt for a great sour cream alternative!

name: Healthy Shrimp & Sausage Jambalaya
description: For the main course, it's hard to beat a hearty jambalaya! This flavorful take on the classic recipe gets extra protein from chicken breast and added fiber from wild rice. My husband says this is the best jambalaya he's ever had, and I humbly agree. Make sure to use a Cajun seasoning you love and trust. My favorite is Bearded Butcher Blend.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2', 'sweet pepper, red - 2 cup, chopped', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'garlic, minced - 4 clove', 'chicken breast, cut into cubes - 1 lb', 'andouille sausage, sliced - 9 oz', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 3 cup', 'tomatoes, crushed, canned - 2 cup', 'wild rice, uncooked - 1½ cup', 'Cajun seasoning - 2 tbsp', 'bay leaf - 3', 'thyme - ½ tsp, ground', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1 lb', 'okra - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oil in a large soup pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
2. Add onion, celery, sweet peppers, jalapeño (optional), and minced garlic; cook until onion is translucent.
3. Add raw diced chicken and sausage, and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring often, until chicken is no longer pink.
4. Add chicken broth, crushed tomatoes, wild rice, and seasonings. Stir to combine, then simmer (covered) over medium-low heat for about 25-30 minutes until rice is softened.
5. Add shrimp and okra, simmering just 3 minutes until shrimp is pink.
6. Remove bay leaves and discard before serving.
7. Note: Enjoy hot or divide into six equal portions and store in airtight containers for meal prep. Leftovers will keep up to one week in the fridge or up to one month in the freezer.

name: Mexican Frittata
description: While the name frittata is Italian, this version has a Mexican twist. Most dieters avoid Mexican food altogether since so many restaurant dishes contain chips, tortillas, tons of oil, and lots and lots of cheese. But, with this recipe, you can enjoy your favorite Mexican flavors without screwing up your diet.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 4 whole', 'liquid egg whites - 1 cup', 'green pepper, chopped - 1', 'white onion - ½ sliced', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'tomato, finely diced - 1', 'taco seasoning - 1 tbsp (1 serving)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Heat a large, non-stick, oven-safe saute pan on high.
3. Saute bell pepper and onion in olive oil until soft. Gradually add spices.
4. Remove from heat.
5. In a separate bowl, mix eggs and egg whites and then pour on top of pepper and onion mixture.
6. Sprinkle diced tomatoes.
7. Put pan into preheated oven.
8. Cook for 10-12 minutes.
9. If your diet allows for some extra fats, you can top the frittata with some guacamole, jack cheese, or both. You can also top with your favorite hot sauce or salsa.

name: Cajun Crab Cakes
description: Kick off the festivities with these crab cakes. They're easy to throw together using canned lump crab meat, and they cook in just minutes in a nonstick skillet. Pair them with my healthy homemade tartar sauce for a diet-friendly take on this classic tasty treat.
recipeIngredient: ['crab meat - 2 can (6.5 oz), drained', 'bread crumbs - ¾ cup', 'green onion, chopped - 2', 'red bell pepper - ¼ cup, chopped', 'egg, beaten - 1', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'light butter spread - 1 tbsp', 'Cajun seasoning - ½ tsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients to a large bowl, mixing with hands until just combined.
2. Heat large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Spray lightly with cooking spray when ready to cook crab cakes.
3. Scooping out 1/3-cup portions, form mixture into patties and place in preheated skillet.
4. Cook patties over medium heat for 4 minutes per side or until golden brown.
5. Set cooked patties on a plate and enjoy with healthy tartar sauce!

name: Healthy Tartar Sauce
description: Nonfat Greek yogurt is a healthy alternative for a variety of dips and dressings and a higher-protein substitute for sour cream. Paired with tart dill pickles and spicy Dijon mustard, this tangy tartar sauce is bursting with flavor and ideal for your favorite seafood delights.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'dill pickles - ¼ cup, chopped or diced', 'green onion, chopped - 3 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'pickle juice - 1 tsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, mixing until thoroughly combined.
2. Serve immediately or store in the fridge up to one week.

name: Smoked Salmon And Baby Dill Crostini
description: Don't let the fancy name fool you! These crostinis are easy-peasy to throw together. I'm talking "Oh crap, the guests are already here?" easy. Not to mention, they taste incredible, like something you would order at a great restaurant.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon, smoked - 8 oz', 'rye melba toast crackers - 16', 'light garlic and herbs cheese spread - 1 container (8 oz)', 'fresh dill - 3 sprigs']
recipeInstructions:
1. Layer each toast with one tablespoon of garlic herb cheese spread, half an ounce of smoked salmon, and a pinch of fresh dill.
2. Serve immediately, or store in fridge.

name: Lemon Pepper Tilapia
description: This is one of my favorite flavor combinations. It's the go-to lunch I look forward to. The secret is to use a knife and fork to mix it all together like fried rice!
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 4 fillet', 'brown rice - 2 cup', 'asparagus spears - 15 whole', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'lemon pepper seasoning - ', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Place tilapia fillets on a sprayed baking sheet.
3. Top fillets with lemon juice and lemon-pepper seasoning.
4. Bake 20 minutes.
5. In a bowl add 1/2 cup cooked brown rice, tilapia, and asparagus spears.
6. Top with cracked black pepper.
7. Mix all ingredients with a knife and fork.

name: Pumpkin Protein "Ice Cream"
description: This recipe is a low-cal, filling treat for those of you with a sweet tooth. It's not really ice cream, but the taste and texture are certainly close enough! Plus, the addition of pumpkin adds lots of volume without too many extra calories—a perfect trick for the dieting, hungry bodybuilder. One difference between this "ice cream" and regular homemade ice cream is that you do not want to let it firm up in the freezer. Since it hardly has any sugar or fat—just a lot of water content—it will end up more like an ice block than ice cream. Eat it right out of the ice cream maker like soft serve.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin, canned - 2 cup', 'powdered Stevia -  to taste', 'plain Greek yogurt - 2 cup', 'cinnamon -  to taste', 'nutmeg -  to taste', 'almond milk - 1 cup', 'table salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend pumpkin, yogurt, milk, sweetener, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.
2. Pour into ice cream maker and churn until frozen.
3. Enjoy!

name: Roasted Spring Vegetables With Dijon Maple Glaze
description: Some things are just better roasted. For example, brussels sprouts, yellow baby potatoes, fennel, and radishes. If you've never tried roasted radish—I hadn't until recently—you're in for a treat. This tart root takes on a much milder, sweeter profile when cooked and pairs delightfully with the Dijon maple glaze.
recipeIngredient: ['potatoes - 1½ lb', 'fennel bulb, stalks removed - 2 bulb', 'radishes, greens removed - 1 lb', 'Brussels sprouts - 1 lb', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'Kosher salt - ½ tsp', 'lemon juice - 3 tbsp', 'maple syrup - 1 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450° F.
2. Wash vegetables thoroughly, and prepare as follows: quarter potatoes lengthwise; remove fennel stalks and core, then cut into 1" pieces; trim both ends of radish, quarter lengthwise; trim bottoms of Brussels sprouts, and cut in half.
3. Toss prepared vegetables in olive oil, salt, and pepper.
4. Arrange vegetables in one or two baking dishes in a single layer, not heaped on top of each other.
5. Roast vegetables in oven for 30-40 minutes until easily pierced with a fork.
6. Whisk together lemon juice, maple syrup, and Dijon to make a glaze.
7. As a final step, toss vegetables in lemon glaze. Serve warm.

name: Ginger Basil Chicken And Rice
description: This easy recipe is perfect for a post-workout meal. Chicken and rice is one of the most common bodybuilding diet meals, but most guys make it boring and bland as hell. Fortunately, just a few additions can make it into a meal that tastes almost like a delicious restaurant stir-fry, just without all the oil, cornstarch, and sugar.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 8 oz', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'carrots, sliced - 1', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'canola oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'ground ginger - 1 tbsp', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook peppers, carrots, and broccoli in olive oil until desired doneness.
2. Once veggies are cooked, add chicken breast slices, and cook until chicken is just about done.
3. Add garlic, ginger, and soy sauce (to taste).
4. Remove from heat and mix in chopped basil leaves.
5. Mix with white rice.
6. If desired, add honey, cilantro, green onions, and lime juice.

name: Mozzarella, Asparagus, And Leek Mini-Quiches
description: Ditch the crust for an appetizer that's light lower in carbs yet full of flavor! These little guys are surprisingly hearty thanks to the protein from the egg whites and the fiber from all those veggies. Did I mention the cheese? Yeah, that's probably my favorite part. Plus, you can either prepare these the night before and serve them cold, or whip them up fresh in the morning and serve warm. They're great either way!
recipeIngredient: ['asparagus, ends trimmed and chopped into 1/2-inch pieces - 1½ cup', 'leeks, bulb and lower leaf-portion, chopped - 1 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'egg - 6 whole', 'egg whites - 6', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ½ cup', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'basil, dried - ½ tsp, ground', 'nutmeg - ⅛ tsp', 'part-skim mozzarella cheese - 1½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350° F.
2. Generously coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
3. Sauté chopped asparagus, leeks, mushrooms, and garlic in skillet until onions are translucent and garlic is fragrant, about 5 minutes.
4. While veggies cool, beat together whole eggs, egg whites, cottage cheese, spices, and 1 cup of mozzarella or feta until frothy.
5. Lightly coat cups of a muffin pan with cooking spray and divide sautéed vegetables between cups.
6. Pour egg mixture over vegetables, dividing evenly between cups.
7. Sprinkle quiche tops with remaining half cup of cheese.
8. Bake for 30-40 minutes until golden brown. Enjoy warm right away or store in the fridge to serve later.

name: Spinach, Sunflower Seeds And Salmon Salad
description: If you're looking at a demanding day of butt-kicking, the nutrients in salmon can be your kung-fu power. The thiamine in the sunflower seeds will also enhance memory and cognitive function. The protein and healthy fats in fish can also help to keep your energy levels stable because they help maintain blood glucose levels already within a normal range.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 8 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - 2 whole', 'parsley, dried - 1 tbsp', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'sunflower seeds - 2 tbsp', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'Splenda - ½ tbsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'oregano - ⅛ tsp, ground', 'table salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pan-fry the salmon fillets in olive oil and set aside.
2. In a bowl, mix spinach and green onions.
3. In a small bowl, whisk vinegar, olive oil, sugar, parsley, pepper, oregano, and salt. Drizzle over salad and toss.
4. Place salmon on salad and top with sunflower seeds before serving.

name: Tilapia Veracruz
description: This dish seems to have a lot going on, but it comes together easily in just less than 30 minutes. It's light, flavorful, and festive enough to serve to guests. Don't worry, your macronutrient profile is still safe.
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 4 fillet', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'tomato, diced - 2', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'green olives, sliced - ¼ cup', 'capers, canned - 4 tbsp, drained', 'cilantro - ⅛ cup', 'oregano - ½ tsp, ground', 'marjoram, dried - ¼ tsp', 'bay leaf - 1', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Spray baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes.
3. While fish is baking, add olive oil, garlic, and onion to a pan over medium heat.
4. Add tomatoes, green olives, jalapeno, capers, oregano, marjoram, bay leaf, and salt and pepper to pan.
5. Reduce to simmer and cook for another 8-10 minutes until all flavors all well blended.
6. When fish is done, top each filet with generous amount of cooked mixture.
7. Add cilantro to top and add lime to side of the dish.

name: Greek Yogurt With Apple And Flaxseeds
description: If you're in the habit of having a bowl of Greek yogurt as your mid-afternoon snack or your pre-bed meal, consider having it for breakfast instead.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 cup', 'apple, red - 2 small', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'Splenda - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'ground flaxseed - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 375° F.
2. Slice apples into thin slices; place them on a non-stick pan; and then sprinkle them with cinnamon, Splenda and a dash of salt.
3. Place prepared apples (covered) in the oven for about 45 minutes or until tender.
4. Remove and allow them to cool for 30 minutes.
5. Place one cup of Greek yogurt in each bowl and then top with apples and 2 tbsp flaxseeds.

name: Coconut Halibut With Green Beans
description: Pair the muscle-building power of halibut with heart healthy coconut. It's a win-win. In addition to the star protein, you'll get the benefits of coconut, which includes a slight boost to your metabolic rate to give you extra energy as you head into your day.
recipeIngredient: ['coconut oil - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'ginger, minced - 2 tsp', 'coconut milk - 1 cup', 'Thai green curry paste - ½ tsp', 'halibut - 6 oz', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'carrot, shredded - 2', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'coconut flakes - 2 tbsp', 'Green Beans - 4 cup 1/2" pieces']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large skillet, cook the garlic, ginger, and coconut oil for about 30-60 seconds.
2. Add in the coconut milk (preferably full fat, however light can be used if watching your calorie intake) and curry paste.
3. Bring to a boil, and then reduce heat to simmer.
4. Add fish, sliced red pepper, and carrots. Cook for 4 minutes, flip fish, and then cook for another 2-3 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
5. Remove fish and vegetables from the skillet with a slotted spoon. Allow the sauce to continue to simmer for about 6-8 minutes or until thickened.
6. Add in lime juice and spoon over the fish.
7. Top with dried coconut flakes. Serve alongside steamed green beans.

name: Zesty Orange Halibut
description: This halibut recipe is a great way to keep your calories low while taking the flavor profile of your diet to an all-time high. The addition of the orange zest sets this recipe apart and takes the dish to a whole new level and helps ensure that it is one that you will come to love.
recipeIngredient: ['bok choy - 1 head', 'red bell pepper, chopped - 1', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'halibut - 12 oz', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'green onion, sliced - 3', 'orange zest - 1 tsp', 'sesame seeds - 1 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 3 tbsp', 'rice vinegar - 1½ tsp', 'sesame seed oil - 1½ tsp', 'ginger root - 2 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil, ginger root, and garlic.
2. In a large parchment bag, combine the vegetables, fish, and sauce.
3. Bake in the oven for 15 minutes at 400 degrees F.
4. Once finished, remove and serve on top of a brown rice pilaf.

name: Asian Salmon
description: Get your vitamin C and a great, tangy taste with this recipe. Because it's served with brown rice, it's a good option for long-term energy.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 1 fillet', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 cup, chopped', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'rice wine vinegar - 2 Tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'brown sugar - 2 tbsp', 'Splenda - ½ tsp', 'brown rice - 3 cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'snow peas - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, whisk together olive oil, rice vinegar, low sodium soy sauce, brown sugar, Splenda, and minced garlic.
2. Place salmon and sliced vegetables in an oven-safe dish and drizzle with sauce.
3. Place in the fridge for about an hour to allow the sauce to marinate the salmon.
4. Bake salmon at 350 degrees F for about 30 minutes, or until the salmon flakes easily with a fork.
5. While baking, prepare brown rice according to package directions.

name: Pro JYM Edible Cookie Dough
description: Parents used to tell their kids not to eat the cookie dough but, let's face it, that stuff is irresistible to most humans. This cookie dough recipe is full of vanilla and almond goodness, along with a good dose of protein. You can even add nuts, marshmallows, or chocolate chips to the mix. It's all good!
recipeIngredient: ['Pro JYM, Tahitian Vanilla Bean - 1 scoop', 'PBfit peanut butter - 1 serving (2 tbsp)', 'unsweetened almond milk - 4 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 dash', 'table salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients except almond milk in a bowl.
2. Slowly add in almond milk one tablespoon at a time until the dry ingredients start to absorb it. You want a doughy consistency.
3. Once all the milk is worked in, chill dough in fridge or freezer for 20-30 minutes.
4. Sprinkle with salt and devour.
5. Optional add-ins: Chopped nuts, coconut, Walden Farms calorie-free syrup, marshmallows, chocolate chips.

name: Quinoa with Chicken
description: If fish doesn't float your boat, consider grilled chicken breast and quinoa. Quinoa is hearty, and contains more protein than most other grains. It's also rife with fiber, a necessary nutrient for long-term health support.
recipeIngredient: ['quinoa, cooked - 1 cup', 'chicken bone broth - 2 cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, pureed - 1 tsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'chicken breast - 2 piece', 'zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 whole', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2 whole', 'onion flakes - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large pot over medium heat, bring the quinoa and chicken broth to a boil.
2. Reduce the heat and allow to simmer for about 12 minutes or until the quinoa is fluffy and the broth is absorbed.
3. Heat one tbsp of the oil in a large skillet and then add garlic, onion, zucchini, pepper and celery.
4. Cook for 2-3 minutes or until tender, and remove.
5. Heat the second tbsp of olive oil in the pan, then add chicken breasts, cooking for 5-8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
6. Place the removed vegetables and quinoa back in the pan and add in onion flakes and any other spices you desire.
7. Cook for 1-2 more minutes to allow the flavors to blend.

name: Post Workout Paella
description: Seafood—it's what's for dinner. I love this easy-to-make, savory dish. It's comforting, rich in protein, and serves up a hearty dose of carbs to replenish your glycogen stores post-workout.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 1½ lb', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1½ lb', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'brown rice - 4 cup', 'chicken bone broth - 2 cup', 'red onion, diced - ½ whole', 'tomatoes - 1 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'snow peas - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'saffron - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rice according to the instructions on the packet and set aside. To save time and space in the kitchen, I use a rice cooker.
2. Chop raw chicken breasts and shrimp into small pieces.
3. Set a cast-iron skillet on medium-high heat and add 2 tbsp coconut oil. Once it's melted, add red onion and garlic paste. Stir with a wooden spoon and cook until the edges of the onion have browned.
4. Toss in raw, chopped chicken breasts and cook until the chicken is 75 percent done. Don't be alarmed if some parts of the chicken are still pink.
5. Toss in raw shrimp and stir with wooden spoon or spatula. Cook until the shrimp is about 75 percent cooked.
6. Add paprika and a pinch of sea salt and pepper. Stir.
7. Add in cooked rice and diced tomatoes. Stir and reduce heat to medium.
8. Pour in the chicken broth and add saffron. Allow the contents to simmer, and gently stir.
9. Allow everything to cook for about three minutes. If you'd like to, add fresh lemon juice.
10. Add frozen peas and stir. Allow the paella to simmer for about five minutes, then garnish with freshly chopped parsley.

name: Chicken Stir-Fry
description: Stir-fry dishes are simple to create and typically only take ten minutes tops. If you purchase pre-chopped vegetables already, your prep time will be further reduced. There are many different variations of sauces you can come up with so be sure to try a variety of your own. Keep in mind that with a few ingredient swaps, you can also really improve the nutritional content of most sauce recipes.
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice - 1 cup', 'honey - ½ tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1½ tsp', 'chicken bone broth - ½ cup', 'soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'snow peas - 1 cup', 'onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'mushrooms, sliced - ½ cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - ⅛ cup, sliced', 'chicken breast - 3 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by bringing 1 cup of water to a boil and then toss in brown rice, covering, and allowing to simmer according to package directions.
2. Next, heat half of the olive oil in a pan. Cook chicken until tender and set aside. Toss the vegetables in the pan with juices from the chicken along with 1 tbsp of the chicken broth. Saute all the vegetables until tender.
3. Next, mix together the remaining olive oil, chicken broth, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, and honey in a small bowl. Pour over vegetables, add chicken back to the pan, and stir-fry for another 1-2 minutes.
4. Serve on top of the bed of rice.

name: Protein Ice Cream
description: This recipe works with casein or protein blends—it makes the ice cream even creamier! If you use other types of protein, you may have to add a couple of tablespoons of milk to the mix if it's too thick.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ½ cup', 'banana or vanilla protein powder - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a food processor, handheld blender, or mixer, blend all ingredients together. Don't use a whisk or spoon because the aim is to end up with a mixture that's creamy, not lumpy.
2. Place the mixture in a Tupperware container and stick it in the freezer for an hour.
3. After an hour, remove the container and give the ice cream a good stir. You want to make sure that it freezes evenly. Think of yourself as a human ice cream machine.
4. Put container back in the freezer. Wait for another hour before taking it out and giving it another churn.
5. Repeat steps three and four until the ice cream is nicely set and ready to be munched with gusto.

name: Tuna Burger Salad
description: This is a great alternative to eating your tuna that boasts a high protein content and a healthy level of dietary fat.
recipeIngredient: ['Salad dressing, KRAFT Mayo Light Mayonnaise - 1 tbsp', 'romaine lettuce - 2 cup shredded', 'mixed salad greens - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'tuna, canned in water - 1 can']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together the chunk light tuna, egg white, and dry oats and form into a patty.
2. Heat the oil in a non-stick skillet on medium heat.
3. Once heated, placed patty on and grill, flipping at half time.
4. Serve alongside a lettuce salad with vegetables and low-fat salad dressing.

name: Dijon Mustard Halibut In Parchment Paper
description: This tangy halibut dish is a fast-and-easy meal that will provide you with a hearty dose of protein. If you're on a lower-carb diet, simply add more vegetables to the bag and forgo the brown rice or quinoa. Feeling indulgent? Consider doubling the sauce.
recipeIngredient: ['halibut - 8 oz', 'diced red bell pepper - 1', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'flat-leaf parsley - 1 bunch', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'red onion, diced - ¼', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'Worcestershire sauce - 1 tsp', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'carrots, sliced - 2', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend together the red pepper, garlic, parsley, Dijon mustard, purple onion, olive oil, Worcestershire sauce, and lemon juice.
2. Place fish, sauce, and remaining diced vegetables in a large parchment baking bag.
3. Bake at 370 degrees for 20 minutes.
4. Serve alongside some brown rice or quinoa.

name: Italian Shrimp Pasta
description: Shrimp is an excellent source of protein and when purchased pre-cooked, requires very little prep time at all. Take 5 minutes to prepare this in the morning to take with you.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-wheat pasta - ¾ cup spaghetti', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 15 shrimp', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 oz', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 cup, chopped', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'Italian dressing - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a pot, bring water to boil and then cook pasta according to package direction.
2. Next, heat two of the tablespoons of salad dressing in a pan. Toss in peppers, broccoli, and shrimp, and lightly stir fry for 2-3 minutes.
3. Next, heat two of the tablespoons of salad dressing in a pan. Toss in peppers, broccoli, and shrimp, and lightly stir fry for 2-3 minutes.

name: Cajun Halibut With Corn
description: This Cajun-style meal is sure to please your taste buds and offer up plenty of antioxidants in the form of corn and salsa. The added cayenne pepper is ideal for people looking to boost their metabolic rate a few hours after consumption since it contains capsaicin—the same lipophilic chemical found in chilli peppers—which offers a nice spike to your metabolic rate.
recipeIngredient: ['table salt - 1 tsp', 'oregano - ½ tsp, ground', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'paprika - ½ tsp', 'garlic, minced - ½ tsp', 'thyme - ½ tsp, ground', 'halibut - 12 oz', 'tomato, diced - 1', 'green pepper, cut into strips - 1', 'onion, sliced - ½', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'corn - 2 cup', 'salsa - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, combine the sea salt, oregano, cayenne pepper, paprika, thyme, and 1 tbsp olive oil. Rub onto the halibut and let sit in the fridge for one hour (or, for more flavor, overnight).
2. Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add remaining 1 tbsp of olive oil and, once it's heated, add halibut fillets, diced onion, garlic, and green pepper.
3. Cook for about 3-4 minutes, flip, and then cook for another 3-4 minutes on the other side (or until fish flakes easily with a fork).
4. Top with tomato slices and serve alongside corn and salsa.

name: Tomato Basil Halibut
description: This rustic take on halibut is a great dish for a cozy dinner in. The olives provide a good dose of heart-healthy fats while the tomatoes provide plenty of antioxidants to keep you in top health.
recipeIngredient: ['halibut - 12 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, sliced - 1', 'orange pepper, thinly sliced - 1', 'black olives, sliced - ¼ cup', 'diced tomatoes - 3 cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'fresh basil leaves - ¼ cup', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by stabbing the sweet potatoes and then baking for 45 minutes until just about finished.
2. Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add the pepper and onion and cook for 4-5 minutes.
3. Add in the olives, tomatoes, and sweet potatoes along with fish. Cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes. Serve immediately.

name: Chocolate Chip Peanut Butter Pro JYM Brownies
description: This recipe gets you brownies—and a whole lot less. Made with stevia and calorie-free chocolate syrup, these tasty treats come in at a little over 100 calories per. Full of vanilla, chocolate, and protein, this dessert will make the perfect end to your next wholesome meal!
recipeIngredient: ['Pro JYM, Tahitian Vanilla Bean - 2 scoop', 'PBfit peanut butter - 40 g', 'dark chocolate chips - 30 g', 'powdered Stevia - 8 g', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'egg - 2', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour into greased baking pan (an 8x8 pan works well).
3. Pour syrup on the top and lightly swizzle into batter with a knife.
4. Bake for 10 minutes.
5. Let cool, cut into nine equal pieces, and serve.
6. Optional topping: Walden Farms calorie-free chocolate syrup

name: Pro JYM Brownie in a Mug
description: When you're watching your carbs and calories, any healthy dessert recipe that contains the word "brownie" is bound to grab your attention. Add to that the words chocolate, cinnamon, and pancake syrup, and you know this is something you have to try!
recipeIngredient: ['Pro JYM, Chocolate Mousse - 1 scoop', 'PBfit peanut butter - 1 serving (2 tbsp)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 dash', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 1 tbsp', 'egg - 1', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
2. Combine all wet ingredients in a separate bowl; beat in egg until incorporated.
3. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until there are no clumps.
4. Pour batter into a greased mug and microwave for 60-90 seconds.
5. Enjoy immediately.

name: Banana And Cinnamon Protein Milkshake
description: This winter, give yourself the gift of post-workout gains. When you're looking for a shake with a little bit of edge, reach for this dessert-like option that's a favorite of NPC physique competitor Melih F. Cologlu. Not only is it a great way to make the most of overripe fruit, but the classic combination of sweetness and spice is sure to hit your taste buds with delightful, protein-rich goodness. Channel the flavors of the season—without packing on the pounds—with this muscle-building shake!
recipeIngredient: ['skim milk - ½ cup', 'non-fat vanilla yogurt - ½ cup (8 fl oz)', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Killa Vanilla - 1 scoop', 'banana - ⅓', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients (along with 6 ice cubes).
2. Top with more cinnamon to taste. Drink and enjoy!

name: Pro JYM Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: With sugar from applesauce, body from pumpkin, and protein from JYM, these cookies will satisfy your sweet tooth while providing good protein and fats. Like grandma's—only healthier!
recipeIngredient: ['Pro JYM (flavor of choice) - 2 scoop', 'coconut flour - 25 g', 'liquid egg whites - 92 g', 'unsweetened applesauce - 40 g', 'pure pumpkin - 40 g', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 60 g', 'powdered Stevia - 6 g', 'unsweetened almond milk (vanilla) - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 30 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Lightly grease baking sheet, or line with parchment paper.
3. Combine all ingredients in a bowl, adding nuts and other extras as desired.
4. Spoon eight equal portions of dough onto baking sheet.
5. Bake for 8-10 minutes.
6. Transfer cookies to cooling rack.
7. Serve when cookies are cool.
8. Optional add-ins: Chopped nuts, raisins

name: Jamie Eason's Protein Oatmeal Raisin Cookies
description: In the mood for fresh-baked oatmeal raisin cookies? Bake up a batch of these protein-rich morsels to satisfy your sweet tooth and support your fitness goals!
recipeIngredient: ['natural almond butter - ¼ cup', 'maple syrup - 2 tbsp', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'unsweetened applesauce - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'raw oats - 1½ cup', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'xylitol - 16 tbsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'raisins - ¼ cup', 'jamie eason signature whey protein isolate - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with foil, spray with cooking spray, and set aside.
2. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the almond butter, maple syrup, egg whites, applesauce, and vanilla extract until smooth.
3. In a separate bowl, stir together the oats, flour, whey isolate, xylitol, baking soda, and cinnamon. Stir the dry mixture into the wet mixture, a little at a time, then add the raisins.
4. Form a cookie with about three tablespoons of batter. Place each cookie onto the baking sheet at least 1 inch apart. Repeat this process until 12 cookies are made.
5. Bake in the oven for 12-14 minutes, or until center of cookie is cooked through.

name: Protein King Cake
description: What Mardi Gras party would be complete without king cake? This protein-packed version has only 5 grams of sugar and a surprising 14 grams of protein per slice.
recipeIngredient: ['all-purpose flour - 1¾ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 120 g', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - 4 tsp', 'baking soda - 2 tsp', 'light butter spread - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - 3 tbsp', 'pecans, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'raisins, seedless - ¼ cup, packed', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'light butter spread - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 60 g', 'unsweetened almond milk - 2 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ cup', 'light butter spread - 1 tbsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Whisk together dry dough ingredients (flour through baking soda) in a large mixing bowl.
3. Add wet ingredients (buttery spread through applesauce) and mix until a soft dough forms. Set aside.
4. For the filling, combine pecans, raisins, brown sugar, cinnamon, and buttery spread in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring until butter is melted.
5. Remove saucepan from heat and mix in protein powder and milk. Set filling aside.
6. On a lightly floured surface, roll dough into a 10x16-inch rectangle, cutting off jagged edges and pressing them into the center.
7. Spread filling over the dough rectangle.
8. Working from the 16-inch side, roll dough on top of itself to form a long roll (this is where you can hide the plastic baby).
9. Place roll in a lightly greased 9-inch round pan and pinch ends of dough together, forming a ring.
10. Make small slits around the top of the dough circle using a sharp knife.
11. Bake for 12-15 minutes until top is light golden brown.
12. While cake cools, mix together frosting ingredients until smooth. Spread frosting over cake and garnish with purple, green and gold sprinkles, if desired.

name: Strawberry Banana No-powder Protein Smoothie
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat milk - 1 cup', 'banana - ½ small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'liquid egg whites - 9 tbsp', 'non-fat vanilla yogurt - 1 container (4 oz)', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'water - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Protein Flower Pastry
description: Who knew that vegetable you tried to push off your dinner plate as a child could actually form the base of a delicious protein dessert? This pastry combines vitamin-rich cauliflower with protein for a surprisingly yummy combination. It's a favorite of physique competitor Vinny Russo and helps satisfy his sweet tooth without breaking his daily calories.
recipeIngredient: ['head cauliflower, chopped - 1 tbsp', 'Grenade Hydra 6 - ¾ scoop', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 1', 'water - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add blended raw cauliflower to a medium-sized bowl.
2. Mix in protein, egg, egg white, and water. Stir until blended.
3. Microwave for three minutes.
4. Top with your favorite Walden Farms syrup or peanut or almond butter.

name: The Clutch OG Shake
description: Sometimes, you've just got to go for the classic. With bananas and peanut butter topping off a protein flurry of almond milk and ice, this shake begs the question: Is there anything better than the Clutch original?
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'water - 2 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'banana - ⅓ small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Peanut Butter And Jelly Shake
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'water - 2 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'mixed berries - ½ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Mocha Nut Shake
description: Skip that boring cup of Joe and reach for this shake instead. The 2-ounce espresso shot is sure to get you going, the banana and almond butter will fill you up, and the three scoops of protein powder will help keep you full while you build muscle!
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'water - 2 cup', 'almond milk - 2 oz', 'espresso shot - 1 shot', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Lais DeLeon's Almond Banana Protein Shake
description: Whether you're short on time and can't sit down for breakfast or just hankering for a super smoothie, this delicious almond banana protein shake will save you!
recipeIngredient: ['almond milk - 1 cup', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'banana, frozen - 1', 'NLA For Her: Her Whey, Vanilla Cupcake - 1 serving (2 scoops)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Measure out one cup of almond milk and pour into a blender.
2. Add two scoops of whey into the blender.
3. Add one banana to the blender.
4. Add 1 tablespoon almond butter and a handful of ice. Blend all of the ingredients together and pour.

name: Cottage Cheese And Watermelon
description: This snack is ideal because it doesn't hit you with a load of carbs, which will just make you sleepy. Instead, it gives you a few carbohydrates from the watermelon and some very slow-digesting protein from the cottage cheese to keep you going until dinner. "My all-time favorite between-meal snack is cottage cheese and watermelon," says Cellucor athlete and bodybuilder Calum Von Moger. To change things up, he'll occasionally swap the watermelon out for freeze-dried fruit.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cottage cheese - 1½ cup', 'watermelon - 1 cup, diced', 'honey - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Combine ingredients and enjoy!

name: Peanut Butter Protein Kisses
description: Tired of getting protein from the same ol' savory sources? Try this sweet, protein-packed recipe for Peanut Butter Protein Kisses!
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari MyoFusion Advanced Protein, Peanut Butter Cookie - 1 scoop', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 cup', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'Splenda - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1', 'liquid egg whites - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Wash your hands. Yes, that's important!
2. Preheat oven to 350° F.
3. Mix all ingredients together—except the kisses, of course. A sturdy fork will work in a pinch.
4. Spray or grease a large cookie tray.
5. Mold dough into 1-1.5 inch balls and place on the cookie tray about 1.5 inches apart.
6. Press your thumb in the center of the cookies to flatten the dough and make room for the chocolate kisses.
7. Bake for 7 minutes.
8. Take the cookie tray out of the oven, place the chocolate kisses in the center of the cookies, and then put the tray back in the oven for another 2 minutes.
9. Let the cookies cool before you share them or devour them all. The chocolate will be hot and messy!
10. Notes: The dough shouldn't stick to your fingers when you're molding the cookies because of the oil in the peanut butter, but getting your fingers damp can help.Try your own topping variations! You don't have to use kisses. Try Rolos, Reeses, or even eat your cookies topless!

name: Protein Pumpkin Pie
description: Nothing tops off a holiday feast quite like a sweet slice of pumpkin pie. This year, opt for the guilt-free, protein-fueled version from our Protein Powder Chef!
recipeIngredient: ['ground almonds - ½ cup', 'natural almond butter - 2½ tbsp', 'agave syrup - 2 tbsp', 'pumpkin puree - 15 oz', 'liquid egg whites - ¾ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'toffee extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Make the base by blending the base ingredients until you get compact dough. Press the dough down into the bottom and along the sides of a pie mold. Remember to use a mold with a removable bottom that allows you to unmold your pie easily.
2. Bake the crust at 360 F (180 C) for 10-15 minutes, and then remove it from the oven. This step is optional, but it ensures your base cooks a bit longer than the pie so it's nice and crusty.
3. Make your filling by blending the filling ingredients together using an immersion blender, regular blender, or food processor. Pour this onto the base.
4. Bake at 320 F (160 C) for 45-50 minutes, or until the filling has cooked through. Be careful not to overbake it. To ensure a creamy center, remove your pie as soon as it's cooked through—you'll know when an inserted knife comes out clean.
5. Let the pie cool before slicing and … that's it! Eat with abandon!
6. Note: If you want to make your pumpkin pies without crust—thereby removing most of the carbs and the fat—just bake the filling inside of silicone muffin molds for 35-40 minutes at 338 F (170 C). Let the muffins cool before uncasing them, and voila: crust-free mini pumpkin protein pies!
7. Note: For the base you can use almond, sesame seed, or peanut butter.

name: The Clutch-Berry Meal Replacement Shake
description: Not all meal replacement shakes are created equally. This one offers up a serving of frozen berries for that extra dose of vitamins and minerals—and a sweet flavor punch. It's berry-licious!
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'water - 2 cup', 'black chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'coconut milk - 6 oz', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'mixed berries - ¼ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'oatmeal, cooked - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Antioxidant-Infused Berry Smoothie
description: This smoothie is a good option for those of you who are looking for a quick afternoon snack to help get you through your afternoon or who are in need of a fast meal replacement. Eat with one ounce of nuts for a complete meal.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'strawberry nonfat Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'whole milk - ½ cup', 'ice - 2 cubes', 'mixed berries - 1 cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Protein Cookie Delight
description: "I'm a self-proclaimed dessert monster," says Cellucor athlete and WBFF Fitness Pro Jen Jewell. "I'm always on the lookout for delicious and simple ways to have my protein treats while keeping my abs." As such, she has perfected the recipe to achieve this goal—her Protein Cookie Delight.
recipeIngredient: ['frozen mixed berries - ¾ cup', 'raw oats - ¾ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'Cellucor COR-Performance, Red Velvet - 2 scoop', 'honey - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place berries in a bowl and microwave for 45 seconds. Once finished, mash with a fork.
2. Add remaining ingredients to create the batter. Make sure to stir thoroughly so all ingredients are evenly mixed.
3. Place 2-3 tablespoons of batter onto a plate to form each cookie, then place in microwave for 45-60 seconds.
4. Remove, let cool for a minute or two and enjoy.

name: Protein Peanut Butter Balls
description: Rather than making the common mistake of grabbing a sugar-loaded coffee, grab this favorite of Cellucor athlete and strongman Colton Leonard: protein peanut butter balls. His recipe below provides the perfect mix of protein and slow-digesting carbohydrates, which is the requirement of any between-meal snack he eats.
recipeIngredient: ['smooth peanut butter - ½ cup', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'Cellucor COR-Performance Whey, Molten Chocolate - 3 scoop', 'honey - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together, and roll into 1-2 inch balls.
2. Sprinkle extra oats or crushed almonds over tops of rolled protein balls.
3. Place in fridge for several hours, or overnight.

name: Cinnamon Toast Shake
description: Pass on syrup-soaked bread and take a sip of this sweet shake instead. With everything from sweet potato and coconut milk to spices like cinnamon and nutmeg, this shake screams decadence in a cup. It's proof that you can have your sweets in the morning and meet your macros, too!
recipeIngredient: ['unflavored whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'coconut milk - 1 cup', 'sweetened condensed milk - 1 fl oz', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Smoky Sardine Pâté
description: This is a great recipe for sardine newbies, since the tang of the mayo and the smoky spiciness of paprika help subdue the fishy flavor. Spread the pâté on rye crackers, rye bread, toasted English muffins, or thick slices of cucumber. Or wrap up a bit of it in fresh lettuce leaves for high-protein, low-carb wraps.
recipeIngredient: ['sardines, canned in oil - 8 oz', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 3 tbsp', 'scallions, sliced - 1', 'dill - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - ½ tsp', 'table salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place sardines in a large bowl and lightly break up the flesh with a fork.
2. Gently fold in the mayonnaise. Stir in the remaining ingredients.

name: Southwestern Red Pepper Oatmeal
description: Stuffed peppers aren't just for ground meat. Swap your lean protein for a carb-packed pepper by using oatmeal as your filler. This vegetarian-friendly take on the classic dish adds a protein punch with black beans and Greek yogurt, while keeping all the classic flavors with shredded cheese and seasonings like paprika and cumin. One taste, and you'll be hooked.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'mozzarella cheese - ¼ cup', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - ¼ cup', 'corn - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'cilantro - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rolled oats as directed. Set aside.
2. Set oven to 410 degrees F.
3. Slice a bell pepper in half lengthwise, and remove the insides. Place the bell pepper halves on a baking sheet face down. Bake in the oven for at least 15 minutes or until the halves are soft.
4. While the bell pepper halves are baking, mix together the oatmeal, Greek yogurt, beans, corn, paprika, and cumin. Season to taste with sea salt & pepper.
5. Stuff the baked bell peppers with the oatmeal mixture and top each half with 1/8 cup reduced-fat mozzarella cheese.
6. Place the stuffed pepper back in the oven and bake for another 6-8 minutes.
7. Garnish with freshly chopped cilantro.

name: High-Protein Ezekiel French Toast
description: Breakfast doesn't have to come in the form of a protein shake. Serve up healthy slabs of French toast for your next brunch with this recipe from Noah Siegel.
recipeIngredient: ['Ezekial bread - 2 slice', 'egg whites - 3 large', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Graham Cracker - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray pan with non-stick spray and place on medium heat.
2. Combine egg whites, protein powder, and cinnamon together in a large casserole dish.
3. Place a slice of Ezekiel bread in mixture and let each side sit until thoroughly saturated with mixture.
4. Place bread in pan, turning so both sides get done before the center is completely cooked. Make sure temperature is low enough to cook thoroughly without burning.
5. Remove from pan and let cool for about 2 minutes. Add toppings.

name: Loaded Baked Potato Oatmeal
description: Looking for a muscle-building dish that packs a savory punch? Loaded oatmeal could be just what you're craving. Topped with turkey bacon, cheddar cheese, and red potatoes, this dish is a savory mountain of a meal. To carb up for heavy training days, just add a few more potatoes or extra oats for a muscle-building masterpiece.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'Red Potatoes - ⅔ cup, diced', 'low-sodium turkey bacon - 2 strip', 'plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rolled oats as directed. Set aside.
2. Set oven to 410 degrees F.
3. Chop red potatoes into pieces and season with garlic, sea salt, and pepper. Bake in the oven for about 20 minutes or until soft.
4. Cook turkey bacon in a nonstick skillet while the potatoes are baking in the oven. Once the bacon has finished cooking, allow it to slightly cool and harden. Then, chop the bacon into pieces to create "bacon bits."
5. Add the chopped red potatoes, bacon bits, Greek yogurt and shredded cheddar cheese to the cooked oatmeal.
6. Garnish with freshly chopped green onion. Season to taste with sea salt and pepper.

name: Nutty Carrot Cake Oatmeal
description: Who doesn't love a good slice of carrot cake? This dessert-like oatmeal dish takes the spicy, spongy cake and turns it into an easy anytime treat. The dried, unsweetened cranberries pack a lot of sweetness without destroying your macros. So go ahead, and dig into a guilt-free bowl!
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'carrot, shredded - ¼ cup', 'almond milk - 2 tbsp', 'dried cranberries - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'allspice, ground - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rolled oats as directed. Set aside.
2. Add the remaining ingredients to the oatmeal, and stir thoroughly.
3. Garnish with toasted coconut. Add a little extra freshly grated carrots if desired.

name: Salmon-Salad-Stuffed Avocado
description: I love avocado. It's one of my favorite superfoods, not only because it's incredibly good for you, but also because of how versatile it is. I love to make avocado the star of my dishes and eat it at breakfast, lunch, and dinner. This refreshing dish pairs smooth, creamy avocado with flavorful salmon salad for a revitalizing dinner or lunch.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet, pan-seared - 2 fillet', 'dill - ½ tsp', 'champagne vinegar - 6 tsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'scallions, sliced - 4', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'avocado - 1', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - ½', 'grapefruit - ¼']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, mash the salmon with the dill, vinegar, lemon juice, and scallions until combined.
2. Halve the avocado lengthwise and remove the pit.
3. Split the salmon salad into two equal portions, and fill the avocado halves. You can garnish with cucumber and a piece of grapefruit.

name: Sardine Pasta Salad
description: Toss together these ingredients on a Sunday afternoon and you'll be set for a week's worth of lunches that are much more inspiring than turkey and cheese sandwiches. Or use the pasta salad for a quick meal after a hard workout, since it provides a good balance of recovery nutrients.
recipeIngredient: ['whole-grain pasta - 1½ cup penne', 'sardines, canned in oil - 16 oz', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'red pepper, roasted, thinly sliced - 1 cup', 'carrots, sliced - 2', 'flat-leaf parsley - ¾ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - ⅓ cup', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 2 tsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large pot of salted boiling water, cook pasta to al dente according to package directions. Drain pasta and return to pan.
2. Add sardines, tomatoes, roasted red pepper, carrots, parsley and walnuts. Whisk together olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, thyme, salt, red chili flakes and black pepper. Add dressing to pasta and toss to coat.

name: Popeye's Spinach and Kale Savory Oatmeal
description: You'll see Popeye-like with this oatmeal! Your favorite cartoon hero downed a can of the green stuff when he needed a boost of energy; I'm packing in both spinach and kale to get you swole. Both of these superfoods are chock-full of vitamins and minerals, making this dish strong enough to eat by itself or serve as a side dish with some lean protein. It'll help you go strong to the finish!
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'egg - 1', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'kale - 1 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'goat cheese - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - ½ tbsp', 'coconut oil spray - 1 g', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'rosemary -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rolled oats as directed. Set aside.
2. Set a nonstick skillet on medium-high heat, and spray with coconut oil. Toss in the garlic and allow it to sear.
3. Add in chopped kale and cook for a few minutes, until the kale begins to wilt. Add spinach and chopped tomato to the skillet and stir. Allow the tomato to sear. The spinach will begin to wilt in about a minute.
4. Add the braised kale, wilted spinach, and seared tomato to the bowl with the oatmeal.
5. In the same skillet, fry an egg sunny-side up. Place it on top of the oatmeal, and season with sea salt and pepper. Add goat cheese.
6. Garnish with chopped rosemary, and enjoy.

name: Roasted Brussels Sprouts with Cranberries and Pecans
description: If you have a sweet tooth, you're sure to love this recipe. It has fiber from the Brussels sprouts, healthy fats from pecans, and a hint of sweetness from the cranberries. This is the perfect way to get your vegetables, increase your calorie intake, and give your body what it needs to build muscle.
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 1½ lb', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'pecans, chopped - ½ cup', 'dried cranberries - ½ cup', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F
2. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil or parchment paper.
3. Wash and trim the ends from the Brussels sprouts. Remove any dark outer leaves and slice the Brussels sprouts in half from top to bottom.
4. In a large bowl, combine the Brussels sprouts with the olive oil, salt, and pepper, and toss to coat.
5. Arrange the Brussels sprouts on the baking sheet and roast at 400 degrees F for 20-30 minutes or until the sprouts are tender with crispy, dark roasted outer leaves.
6. Remove Brussels sprouts from the oven, toss with the pecans and dried cranberries, then drizzle with the balsamic vinegar.

name: Fisherman's Egg Cakes
description: Bake up a batch of these omega-rich egg cakes and you'll have meals in a hurry for the next few days. They can be served at room temperature or after a few seconds in the microwave. Serve with a salad and roasted sweet potatoes or a cooked whole grain like quinoa.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 8', 'sardines, canned in oil - 8 oz', 'sun-dried tomatoes - ⅓ cup', 'horseradish - 2 tbsp', 'scallions, sliced - 2', 'flat-leaf parsley - ⅓ cup', 'capers, canned - 1 tbsp, drained', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs. Roughly chop sardines and stir into eggs along with sun-dried tomatoes, horseradish, green onions, parsley, capers, garlic, salt, and pepper.
2. Divide among 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups and bake for 18 minutes or until eggs are set. Let cool for a few minutes before unmolding.

name: Roasted Brussels Sprouts with Pomegranate and Nuts
description: Pomegranates contain a very high dose of antioxidants, which combat free radical damage and oxidation. It's also rich in dietary fiber as well as vitamin C. The nuts deliver healthy fat and even more fiber, while giving the recipe a delicious crunchy texture. Protein, fats, and fiber make for a super-simple super dish.
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 1¼ lb', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'Kosher salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'pomegranate - ¼ cup arils (seed/juice sacs)', 'hazelnuts - ¼ cup, chopped', 'almonds, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oven to 425 degrees F.
2. In a medium bowl, toss together Brussels sprouts, oil, salt, and pepper until well coated.
3. Spread Brussels sprouts evenly across a large sheet pan and bake for 25-30 minutes, stirring halfway through. Fully cooked, the Brussels sprouts should be golden brown, crisp on the outside, and tender on the inside.
4. Top finished Brussels sprouts with pomegranate, almonds, and hazelnuts, and serve.

name: Parmesan Brussels Sprouts
description: This cheesy dish is a real crowd pleaser—and one of the easiest ways to serve Brussels sprouts. Because it calls for both butter and cheese, it's the perfect dish to accompany a protein source when you're following a low-carb, high-fat diet plan.
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 4 cup', 'butter, without salt - 2 tbsp', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 4 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Melt butter in a pan.
2. Add Brussels sprouts and cook on low-medium heat for 15-20 minutes or until soft.
3. Add salt and pepper.
4. Remove from pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
5. Toss and serve.

name: Mocha-Cappuccino-Cinnamon Brownies
description: Get your coffee fix in protein brownie form with this recipe from IFBB Pro Bikini competitor Anna Starodubtseva.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2 whole', 'egg yolks - 3 large', 'fat-free cream cheese - 8 oz', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 3 tbsp', 'Splenda - 3 tsp', 'cinnamon - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'optimum nutrition fitness fiber - 4 tsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Mocha Cappuccino - 4 scoop', 'raspberries - ¼ cup', 'Splenda - 1 serving 1 packet', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend egg white separately from yolks until they become foam.
2. Add yolks, Truvia, cacao powder, cinnamon, baking powder, Fitness Fiber, and protein powder and mix in a blender.
3. Manually mix in cream cheese.
4. Bake for 30 minutes.
5. Sauce Directions: Heat a pan with coconut oil.
6. Mix berries with Truvia in a bowl. Cook on medium heat for 3-5 min until the juice comes out of the berries.
7. When the brownies are ready, place them in a fridge for two hours. Serve with warm berry sauce on top.

name: Banana-Peach Frozen Dessert
description: If you like ice cream, you're going to love this dessert. It's especially satisfying after a hard workout but great for any time of the day. Substituting berries for the banana is a great way to reduce the calories without sacrificing flavor. This is an excellent choice when you decide to enjoy this delicious "ice cream" around your training.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 1', 'frozen peaches - ½ cup', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tsp', 'coconut milk - 3 tbsp', 'macadamia nuts - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place the banana, peaches, flaxseed meal, coconut milk, 1/4 cup macadamia nuts, and the almond milk in a blender. Blend on high about 30 seconds or until it resembles a thick frozen dessert.
2. Pour into a bowl and garnish with a dash of cinnamon and a couple of macadamia nuts.

name: Peanut Butter-Coconut Craving
description: Athlete Stephanie Toomey makes this shake every morning. The combination of coconut and almond milk makes for a silky smooth base, while peanut butter kicks the flavor profile up a notch. Go nuts with this flavor combination!
recipeIngredient: ['almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Vanilla Ice Cream - 1 scoop', 'coconut milk - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Roasted Brussels Sprouts and Mushrooms
description: This fantastic side dish is quick and easy to prepare. Mushrooms are surprisingly high in overall dietary protein, with more than 7 grams of protein per dozen, making this is a good option for those who struggle to get enough dietary protein.
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 1 lb', 'mushrooms, sliced - 8 oz', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Wash the Brussels sprouts, trim the stems, and cut in half. Clean and slice the mushrooms.
3. Combine the Brussels sprouts and mushrooms in a large bowl and drizzle with olive oil and season with the garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Toss to coat.
4. Place the Brussels sprouts and mushrooms on a non-stick baking sheet and bake for 20-25 minutes or until the Brussels sprouts have reached desired tenderness.

name: Brussels Sprout Soup
description: Who knew you could make soup from Brussels sprouts? This tomato-based recipe is tasty—and keeps in the fridge. Make a big batch and serve it whenever hunger strikes.
recipeIngredient: ['Brussels sprouts - 1 lb', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'red onion, sliced - 1', 'tomatoes, sliced - 3', 'ginger, minced - ½ tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'low-sodium vegetable broth - 1 cup', 'crushed red pepper flakes - ½ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Wash the Brussels sprouts very well. Trim the nubby ends, remove any discolored leaves, and cut into bite-size pieces.
2. Heat the olive oil in a pot over medium. Add the onion, garlic, and a sprinkle of salt. Cook for about two minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onions are soft and transparent.
3. Stir in the ginger, tomatoes, and red pepper flakes and cook until fragrant—about one minute.
4. Let cool, then transfer this mixture to a blender and purée until smooth.
5. Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Add the Brussels sprouts and the vegetable broth, and bring to a simmer. Cook the Brussels sprouts until tender.
6. Transfer the puréed soup to a saucepan, add the cooked Brussels sprouts and broth, reduce the heat and simmer for about 15 minutes to give the flavors time to meld.
7. Ladle soup into bowls. Top with your favorite garnish, and serve.

name: Strawberry and Banana Nut Bread Oatmeal
description: When it comes to bread, sometimes the bowl beats the loaf. This recipe takes a classic oatmeal dish to the next level by combining bananas and strawberries with the essence of vanilla and zest of lemons. The fresh fruit will satisfy your sweet tooth, while the walnuts and oats will leave you feeling full. It's a fast, simple dish that really packs a punch.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¾ cup', 'banana - ½', 'strawberries - ⅓ cup', 'almond milk - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'walnuts, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook rolled oats as directed. Set aside.
2. Add all of the ingredients except for the strawberries to the bowl of oatmeal and mix thoroughly.
3. Top the oatmeal with freshly chopped strawberries.
4. Garnish with Greek yogurt, chopped walnuts, and poppy seeds.

name: Dark Chocolate Protein Truffles
description: Dark. Chocolate. Truffles. What more is there to say, really? This protein-packed play on the original is sure to power your gains while satisfying your craving for all things cocoa.
recipeIngredient: ['chocolate protein powder - ¾ cup(s)', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2½ tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 2½ tbsp', 'whole milk - ¼ cup', 'almonds, chopped - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together.
2. Shape dough into 12 truffles. If it's too sticky to handle, add a bit more cocoa powder to the mix. Taste your batter to ensure it's sweet enough; add a bit more sweetener if needed.
3. Let truffles set for a few hours or overnight in the fridge.

name: Healthy Protein-Packed Carrot Cake
description: It's moist, flavorful, and packed with a powerful protein punch. Just one bite of this carrot cake will leave you wanting more!
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - 1 cup', 'egg - 4', 'raisins - 4 tbsp', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'carrot, shredded - 4', 'coconut sugar - ¾ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 handful', 'fat-free cream cheese - 24 oz', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 4 tbsp', 'liquid Stevia - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 320 degrees F (160 C). In a bowl, combine the cake ingredients with a spoon.
2. Pour your batter into a brownie pan (I use a silicone one).
3. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until your cake feels almost done but not done-done. This is important, because as you may know by now, whey protein has a tendency to dry up cakes like nobody's business, so you have to take the cake out before it fully cooks through; otherwise, it might end up being hard.
4. Let the cake cool overnight.
5. To make the frosting, just whisk together the frosting ingredients and add it to the cake! Slice into squares or bars. Enjoy!

name: Protein Donuts
description: Ask The Protein Powder Chef: Know A Simple Recipe For Protein Donuts?
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'cashews, chopped - ¼ cup', 'coconut flour - ⅛ cup', 'Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 1 scoop', 'raw oats - ⅛ cup', 'almond milk - ⅛ cup', 'dark chocolate - 50 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 340 degrees F (170C).
2. Blend eggs, cashews, flour, protein powder, oats, and almond milk.
3. Once blended, pour batter into donut tray.
4. Bake donuts for 20 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
5. While donuts are cooling, melt chocolate. (It's best to do it in a glass bowl over boiling water.)
6. Once chocolate liquifies, pour it over donuts and then transfer the donuts to the fridge so the chocolate can set.
7. Eat them all. Don't share.

name: Mug of Mocha
description: This recipe is much healthier than the commercial varieties of hot chocolate, and it'll definitely hit your sweet spot on your romantic night.
recipeIngredient: ['casein protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'coffee - 1 cup', 'skim milk - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Prepare the brewed coffee and fill each cup half-way. Then mix together 8-12 ounces of skim with a full scoop of casein chocolate protein powder.
2. Pour the casein-milk mixture into the half-filled mugs of coffee to create your mocha. Consider preparing some of the whipped topping from the Chocolate Crepes recipe to finish off this protein-packed beverage.

name: Healthy Protein French Toast!
description: Give French toast an extra muscle-building kick with this sweet breakfast recipe that's high in protein and big on flavor!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'almond milk - ½ cup', 'egg - 2', 'multi-grain bread - 3 slice regular']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a big bowl, whisk your whey, eggs, and milk until all lumps disappear.
2. Dunk your bread slices into the egg batter, making sure they're completely submerged. Leave the bread to soak for a couple of minutes so that each slice is fully saturated with the batter.
3. Turn your stove to high and add some coconut oil or nonfat cooking spray to a nonstick pan.
4. Fry up your batter-soaked bread one piece at a time.
5. Flip, plate, and garnish with your topping of choice—maple syrup, calorie-free pancake syrup, nut butter, bacon, ham, or fruit. All go wonderfully well together.
6. Note: Bear in mind that your macros will change depending on what kind of bread you use! Also, if you're watching your fat intake, feel to use egg whites instead of whole eggs.

name: Banana Pancakes
description: Why limit banana flavor to bread? Try this recipe by Jaquelyn Kastelic, Optimum Nutrition athlete and owner of Crossfit Unrivaled. Break the standard baking mold by serving up a batch of these fruit-flavored pancakes.
recipeIngredient: ['coconut flakes - ¼ cup', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Vanilla Ice Cream - 2 scoop', 'egg - 6 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'banana - 1 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'cinnamon - 1 to taste', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 1 tsp', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat your pan to 300 degrees.
2. In a bowl mix eggs, 1/4 cup coconut flakes, 1/2 of a mashed up banana, and 1/2 drop liquid Stevia.
3. Melt coconut oil in microwave and add to mix.
4. Stir in flax meal and protein to a desired creamy consistency. Add cinnamon.
5. Pour on pan and cook a few minutes on each side.
6. Once all pancakes are made, slice up the remaining 1/2 banana and top the pancakes with zero-calorie maple syrup.

name: Dan Green's Boss Breakfast Shake
description: Dan "Boss" Green is one of the greatest American powerlifters of all time. He is the all-time world record holder in the 220 and 242 weight classes, with raw totals of 2,110 and 2, 210 pounds, respectively.
recipeIngredient: ['animal chocolate whey - 2 scoop(s)', 'banana - 1 large (8" to 8-7/8" long)', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'heavy whipping cream - 1 tbsp', 'water - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pour all ingredients into blender.
2. Blend and enjoy!

name: Maple-Glazed Protein Donuts
description: Even though my first love is pizza, I've always had a sweet spot for maple donuts. Sadly, with all that trans fat and processed sugar, they might just be the worst thing for you. This probably explains why I feel like total crap after eating just half of one.
recipeIngredient: ['oat flour - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'powdered Stevia - ¼ cup', 'ground flaxseed - 2 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup', 'egg whites - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ¼ cup', 'coconut extract - 1 tsp', 'butter extract - 1 tsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - ¼ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'gelatin powder - ¼ packet']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 F.
2. Whisk together dry ingredients.
3. Mix in wet ingredients until thoroughly combined.
4. Lightly spray donut pan with cooking spray and distribute between 5 wells.
5. Bake for 10 minutes, then dump out of donut pan on to a plate to cool.
6. Meanwhile, mix up frosting and place in fridge to thicken.
7. When ready, glaze your donuts, add sprinkles, and enjoy!

name: Morning Breakfast Shake
description: Need a powerful morning punch? Noah Siegel has just the recipe. Peanut butter? Good. Berries? Good. Oatmeal? Really good! Really, what's not to love about this shake? With a healthy dose of healthy fats, vitamin C, fiber, and protein, it's a well-rounded meal in a glass.
recipeIngredient: ['Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Vanilla Ice Cream - 2 scoop', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'strawberries, sliced - ½ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'almond milk - 16 oz', 'optimum nutrition amino energy blue raspberry - 2 scoop']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy

name: Sunrise Smoothie
