description: Mornings can be rough. You wake up late, head into work flustered, and spill your morning cup of Joe on your new shirt. Follow Alex's suggestions: Lessen the blow and nix the caffeine with a sweet protein treat.
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries - ½ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'almond milk - 8 oz', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Strawberry Banana - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Homemade Chocolate Bars
description: This recipe for home-made chocolate bars will impress, inspire and delight. Your taste buds will thank you for this sweet, creamy confection, and you won't have to feel guilty about your diet.
recipeIngredient: ['smooth peanut butter - ¾ cup', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'Splenda - 2 tbsp', 'dark chocolate - 2 square', 'casein protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'rice cereal - 1 cup', 'peanuts salted - ¼ cup, shelled']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the natural peanut butter with the skim milk, cocoa powder, and Splenda (or any other sweetener you prefer) in a large pan over medium-high heat. Once everything melts together, add the dark chocolate and continue cooking until the chocolate has melted into the mixture.
2. Next, stir in your favorite casein protein powder and then add in the crispy rice cereal. Once the cereal has been incorporated into the mixture, toss in the peanuts. Mix everything together thoroughly and then transfer into a non-stick baking pan, pressing well to let it set.
3. Place in the fridge for about an hour. When the bar has cooled, cut it into individual serving size pieces (makes about 16 bars).

name: Dark Chocolate Protein Mocha
description: Skip the fat- and sugar-filled frappe and opt for this protein-fueled dark chocolate mocha instead!
recipeIngredient: ['whole milk - ½ cup', 'coffee - ½ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'casein protein powder - ¼ cup(s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. First, make the coffee as strong as you can handle.
2. While your coffee is brewing, heat up the milk until you can stick your finger in it without having to rush to the ER. In other words, warm but not scalding. Be sure not to overheat (or boil) your milk. If you do, the casein will curdle when added.
3. Add the cocoa to the milk. Whisk.
4. Once the coffee has cooled down a bit, add the cocoa-milk and casein (chocolate flavor) to it.
5. Blend it all together so it gets nice, thick, and frothy. Serve and sip!
6. Note: If you want to add a bit of decadence, add a dollop of protein whipped cream. It's a great way to up the protein content of your drink while adding a rich creaminess to the whole thing! To make protein whipped cream, just whisk some quark or low-fat ricotta with 1/4 cup of vanilla whey protein powder and 2-3 tablespoons of milk. Place the mixture in a piping bag and pipe it on the hot chocolate. Yum!

name: Orange And Vanilla Protein Truffles
description: This classic play on a creamsicle comes in a compact, protein-packed ball. Now you can enjoy the much-loved pairing of creamy vanilla and refreshing citrus, minus the sticky mess.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'agave syrup - ⅛ cup', 'ground almonds - ⅓ cup', 'almond milk - 1 tbsp', 'pea protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'orange zest - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together.
2. Shape dough into 10 truffles. If your batter is too sticky to handle, add a bit more pea protein or ground almonds. If it's too dry, add a bit more milk. Make sure you taste your batter to ensure it meets your ideal level of sweetness.
3. Let the truffles set for a few hours or overnight in the fridge.

name: PB&J Protein Smoothie
description: IFBB Pro Alex Carneiro knows that going low(er) carb can be rough. Not only do you have to limit your bread intake, but childhood favorites are off limits—crustless peanut butter and jelly, anyone? Well, there's good news. It turns out you can have your protein PB&J and drink it, too!
recipeIngredient: ['Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Vanilla Ice Cream - 1 scoop', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'raspberries - ¼ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'blackberries - ¼ cup', 'water - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy!

name: Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bars
description: Who doesn't love cookie dough batter? Opt for a healthier alternative with these high-protein bars.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'natural peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'agave syrup - 1 tsp', 'water - 2 tsp', 'dark chocolate - 1 square', 'coconut flour - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a spatula, mix all of the above ingredients together except for the water.
2. Add the water, one teaspoon at a time, until you get a doughy mix. Shape that into four small rectangles. If you batter is too sticky, add a bit more coconut flour. If it's too dry, add water.
3. Once you've shaped your bars, leave them to set in the fridge for a couple of hours. Enjoy your no-bake success!

name: Raspberry And Hazelnut Protein Truffles
description: Move over, Godiva. Gone are the days of shelling out half your paycheck for a bag of chocolate raspberry starfish. Instead of being tempted by fat-filled chocolates, wrap up the delicious pairing of fruit and nuts in a protein truffle.
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'agave syrup - ⅛ cup', 'ground almonds - ⅓ cup', 'almond milk - 1 tbsp', 'pea protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'freeze-dried raspberries - ½ handful']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together, except for the raspberries.
2. Shape dough into 10 truffles. If it's too sticky to handle, add a bit more pea protein or ground almonds. Make sure to taste your batter to ensure it's sweet enough and, if it isn't, add a bit more sweetener.
3. Roll the truffles on the freeze-dried berries. Remember that you can use ground coconut, too!
4. Leave the truffles to set for a few hours or overnight in the fridge.

name: Pumpkin Protein Bars
description: Power-up on protein with these tasty bars! Spices like cinnamon and clove will awaken your flavor palate while alternatives to butter like applesauce spell a lower fat content while still providing the moisture necessary for a delicious cake.
recipeIngredient: ['powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'ground ginger - 1½ tsp', 'ground cloves - 1 cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'baking soda - 1 tbsp', 'table salt - ½ tsp', 'vanilla extract - 2 tsp', 'egg whites - 4 large', 'pumpkin, canned - 1 cup', 'oat flour - 2 cup', 'Optimum Nutrition Gold Standard 100% Whey, Vanilla Ice Cream - 2 scoop', 'walnuts, chopped - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
2. Spray a 9 X 13 Pyrex dish with non-stick spray.
3. Combine first 11 ingredients and mix well.
4. Add the final 3 ingredients and mix together.
5. Spread batter into the Pyrex dish and bake for 30 minutes.
6. Allow to cool. Then cut into 30 squares.

name: Cacao Banana Nut Butter Balls
description: When you cook for someone, it's like putting your heart on a plate! My Cacao Banana Nut Butter Balls are a delicious, sugar-free, additive-free, raw, healthy treat that both your Valentine and kids will enjoy! I can't wait to give these raw cacao banana balls to my Valentine. These are so good that I might just start a nut butter ball business!
recipeIngredient: ['macadamia nuts - ½ cup', 'brazilnuts - 1 oz (6 kernels)', 'banana - 2 small (6" to 6-7/8" long)', 'raw cacao powder - 3 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add Macadamia and Brazil nuts to a Vitamix or blender.
2. Add two bananas and three tablespoons of organic cacao powder.
3. Blend all ingredients and add Stevia to taste.
4. Form the mixture into balls and enjoy!

name: Healthier Banana Bread
description: Say hello to this ultra-moist Banana Nut Protein Bread. It's seriously one of the best banana protein breads I've made.
recipeIngredient: ['almond milk - 1 cup', 'banana or vanilla protein powder - ½ cup', 'banana - 2', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'coconut flour - 3 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tbsp', 'medjool dates - 4 date, pitted', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 handful', 'baking powder - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients together.
2. Pour the batter in a bread muffin mold.
3. Bake at 335 F (170 C) for about 45-60 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
4. Notes: 
To make your bread lower in carbs, you can substitute the banana for some pumpkin or butternut squash puree. As long as you use banana-flavored whey protein powder, you should end up with tasty banana bread. You can also eliminate the dates but, if you do, I suggest you add in some sweetener to ensure the bread hits all the right notes.
If you don't have banana whey protein powder, a vanilla whey protein will work just as well!
If you want to use casein, you can. Just use 1/4 extra cup of liquid egg whites (or two whole eggs).
Consider adding some seeds to the mix! Flaxseeds or poppy seeds are a delicious addition.

name: Chef Robert Irvine: Lamb Burger
description: While ground beef is yummy, if it’s not organic then it’s a heavily processed, industrialized product that’s missing some of the health benefits attributed to always-grass-fed lamb.
recipeIngredient: ['Lean Ground Lamb - 8 oz', 'hamburger bun - 1 serving', 'avocado - 1 fruit, without skin and seed', 'sriracha - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ¼ lemon yields', 'reduced-fat sour cream - ½ cup', 'red onion, diced - ½ whole', 'parsley, dried - 2 pinch', 'table salt - 1 pinch', 'pepper - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lightly salt and pepper ground lamb in a bowl then thoroughly mix.
2. Shape lamb into 2 patties, 4 ounces apiece.
3. Grill the patties to temperature.
4. While patties are cooking (or before or after), make a dressing in a mixing bowl by combining the sour cream with Sambal Oelek, Sriracha or other hot sauce, and parsley and lemon, whisking until consistent.
5. Core and slice the avocado.
6. Lightly toast or grill the bun.
7. Spoon or spread dressing onto bottom layer of bun, then fan avocado slices atop dressing.
8. Place grilled burger atop avocado slices.
9. Top the burger with a ring of grilled onion and remaining half of bun.

name: Peanut Butter Lover's Protein Truffle
description: The butter's back. When it comes to maxing out on flavor, peanuts are the way to go. Add to that a helping of maple extract and these are sure to be the first chocolates picked from any truffle pile—protein or not.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'agave syrup - 3 tsp', 'peanuts salted - 3 oz shelled', 'almond milk - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together.
2. Shape dough into 10 truffles.
3. Leave truffles to set for a few hours or overnight in the fridge.

name: Smoked Salmon Dip
description: Smoked salmon provides a dynamic duo of high-quality protein and those overachieving fats known as omega-3s. It's also just straight-up delicious, especially when paired with dill, lemon juice, and something creamy. That store-bought seven-layer dip can't hold a candle to this in taste or ingredients! To defend against the blitz of caloric overload, opt for reduced-fat Greek yogurt and sour cream, instead of the full-fat versions or mayonnaise.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon, smoked - 12 oz', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'reduced-fat sour cream - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'dill - 2 tbsp', 'horseradish - 2 tbsp', 'capers, canned - 1 tbsp, drained', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until well combined. No food processor? Finely dice the salmon, and then stir it with the other ingredients in a large bowl.
2. Serve garnished with chopped chives alongside sliced vegetables and whole-grain crackers.
3. Note: Capers are optional.

name: Jerky Snack Mix
description:
Jerky is a stellar source of protein that shouldn't be limited only to road trips. The parched meat is a perfect way to jazz up a game-day snack mix. Popcorn adds some low-calorie volume, which makes this snack extra-filling, so you won't feel compelled to OD on the sketchy fare your friends brought to the soiree.

In fact, this sweet-and-salty riff on trail mix has a powerful combination of protein, fiber, and healthy fats to help quell hunger and any risk of stuffing yourself silly. A bit of dark chocolate should help curb cravings for your neighbor's chocolate chip cookies.
recipeIngredient: ['popcorn, plain - 4 cup', 'beef jerky - 3 oz', 'almonds, dry roasted, unsalted, sliced - ¾ cup', 'dried cherries - ⅔ cup', 'soy nuts, roasted - ⅓ cup', 'pumpkin seeds - ⅓ cup', 'coconut flakes - ⅓ cup', 'dark chocolate chips - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Toss all ingredients together, mix, and enjoy!

name: Asian Tuna Balls
description: These portable protein balls are stuffed with star-studded tuna, which will ensure you're reeling in high-quality protein with each bite! Plus, they've got just enough Asian-inspired zing to get you out of your seat yelling for your team—and then heading back to the table for more. Try to prep these guys ahead of time, aiming to have them finished cooking 15 minutes before kickoff so everyone can enjoy them warm.
recipeIngredient: ['potatoes - 1', 'albacore tuna - 10 oz', 'egg - 1', 'sesame seeds - 2 tbsp', 'scallions, sliced - 1', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tbsp', 'fish sauce - 1 tbsp', 'red chili sauce - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Steam or boil potato until tender.
3. Place potato in a large bowl and mash.
4. Stir in all other ingredients.
5. Form into balls slightly smaller than a golf ball. You should have about 16 balls.
6. Arrange on a lightly greased or parchment-paper-lined baking sheet and bake for 35-40 minutes, or until browned and crispy on the outside.

name: Sweet Potato Protein Hummus
description: Sure, you may be able to pick up a container of hummus at your local store, but you can just as easily whip up your own protein-packed version. The flavor of sweet potato lends itself well to the nutty tahini, making this a must-dip for any vegetable, cracker, or finger! Plus, you take the macros to another level with the inclusion of flavorless protein powder. Don't worry, this won't taste like hummus that someone spilled a protein shake into!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato, cut into cubes - 1 lb', 'chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'unflavored whey protein powder - ⅓ cup', 'tahini paste - 4 tbsp', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Steam or boil the sweet potato, then drain and let cool several minutes.
2. Blend together all ingredients until smooth.

name: Quinoa Salad
description: This is one of my favorite summer salads to bring to barbecues or to pot-luck parties. It also serves well for weekly meal planning! This dish isn't your average green side salad, but has a healthy dose of protein, complex carbs and good-for-you fats. Pair it with lean meat for a complete meal.
recipeIngredient: ['quinoa, cooked - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 cup, chopped', 'cilantro - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'edamame - 1 cup', 'Limes, raw - 1 fruit (2" dia)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring 2 cups of water and 1 cup dry quinoa to a rolling boil. Boil for 2 minutes.
2. Reduce to a simmer and cover. Allow to cook for another 15 minutes, then fluff with a fork.
3. In a separate small saucepan, boil frozen edamame in water for 5 minutes, or until fully cooked.
4. Once quinoa and edamame are fully cooked, add all ingredients in a large bowl and mix until all flavors are incorporated.

name: Lentil Marinara Spaghetti Squash
description: When you're dieting for a competition, it's unlikely your nutrition plan allows for pasta. Don't be sad! This recipe tastes just as good as the real thing—just without all the simple carbs. You'll get some healthy, complex carbs from the lentils and extra veggie goodness from the spaghetti squash.
recipeIngredient: ['tomatoes, canned, stewed - 2 cup', 'dried lentils - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - ½ cup, chopped', 'garlic, chopped - 1 Tbsp', 'Italian seasoning - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'summer squash - 1 medium']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Pierce squash with fork multiple times and bake for 60 min, or until outside is softened.
3. In a large pan, heat olive oil and garlic over medium heat.
4. Add lentils, tomatoes, veggies and spices.
5. Bring to a boil and reduce to a simmer for 15 minutes.
6. While sauce is cooking, scrape out spaghetti squash with fork onto plate.
7. Top with about one cup of lentil marinara sauce.

name: Low-Carb Myofusion Pancakes
description: One downside of a low-carb diet is not being able to savor fluffy pancakes, but fret not: These amazing low-carb cakes are here to rescue you! Born from the mind of Ms. Bikini Olympia Ashley Kaltwasser, these protein pancakes will meet your nutrition needs while punching your pancake-loving taste buds.
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 1 scoop', 'egg whites - 1 cup', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'coconut flour - ¼ cup', 'water - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients together in a shaker cup.
2. Spoon out about 2 tbsp of batter at a time onto a pre-heated non-stick skillet.
3. As batter starts to bubble, flip the pancake and allow to cook for another 30-60 seconds on the other side until done.
4. If you don't use all the batter, store the remainder in the fridge.

name: Tofu Bento
description: This is a great protein-packed meal I love to make for lunch during the week. I usually take whatever vegetables I have in the fridge, stir fry them with some lively spices, and add them to brown rice and tofu. Use whatever veggies you'd like—below are my usual ingredients.
recipeIngredient: ['tofu, firm - 1 block', 'brown rice - 2 cup', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, powdered - 1 tsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1 medium (approx 2-3/4" long, 2-1/2 dia.)', 'green onion, chopped - ¼ cup', 'sriracha - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Remove tofu from package and press with paper towels to absorb all excess moisture.
2. Chop tofu into cubes and place in large Ziploc bag.
3. In a large saute pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
4. Add broccolini and bell pepper and stir until lightly softened.
5. Heat another pan to medium heat and add tofu.
6. Cook tofu for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until all sides get cooked.
7. To serve, add 1/2 cup of brown rice and top with tofu, veggies, and green onions.

name: Mexican Style Protein Bowl
description: Give yourself a break from grilled meat and throw these ingredients together for an easy and tasty alternative to the usual. You'll get all the flavor of a Mexican-restaurant meal without the fried fat and unhealthy calories!
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice - ½ cup', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - ⅓ cup', 'salsa - 3 oz', 'avocado - ¼ fruit, without skin and seed', 'hot sauce - 1 tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. In a bowl, combine all ingredients.

name: Stacked Portabellas
description: This is a filling, hearty veggie dish! Even though there's no meat, you'll still need a knife and fork to dig into this meal.
recipeIngredient: ['portabella mushroom caps - 2 piece whole', 'quinoa, cooked - 1 cup', 'tempeh - ½ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'tomato, diced - 1 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 2 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - ½ tbsp', 'cumin - ½ tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tbsp', 'onion powder - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn on oven to high broil. Heat olive oil in a large saute pan over medium heat.
2. Add onion and tempeh to pan and saute for 2-3 minutes, or until onion begins to soften.
3. Add quinoa, spices, salt and pepper and saute a few more minutes.
4. On a baking sheet, place portabello mushrooms brushed lightly with olive oil.
5. Stack mushroom caps with spinach, quinoa mixture, sliced tomatoes, and shredded cheese.
6. Broil for 5 minutes.

name: Pumpkin Pie Shake
description: Pumpkin scares some people off because it has a high glycemic index of 75. Your immediate reaction may be to boycott it because it could cause a marked increase in your blood sugar, ultimately leading to fat storage. However, pumpkin has a low glycemic load of 3 because of its low carbohydrate content. This means pumpkin has a smaller impact on your blood sugar levels than its GI suggests, so don't hesitate to include this nutrient-dense vegetable into your diet.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin, canned - 4 tbsp', 'almond milk - 1¼ cup', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 2 g', 'nutmeg - ⅛ tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - ⅛ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a blender, Magic Bullet, or other mixer.
2. Pour the mixture into your ice cream machine for 10-15 minutes.

name: Lentil And Lima Hearty Soup
description: These wonderful recipes are true originals. If meat isn't in your diet, or you just need a break from it, then earn some protein points in healthy ways!
recipeIngredient: ['dried lentils - 2 cup', 'lima beans - ½ cup', 'white onion - 1 sliced', 'cherry tomatoes - 1½ cup', 'Carrot - 1 diced', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 3 whole', 'peppers, hot chili, red - 2 pepper', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'paprika - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'parsley, dried - 1 oz', 'water - 8 cup', 'bragg liquid aminos - 3 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a crock pot. Fill with alkalized water to the top.
2. Cover and cook on low for 10-12 hours. Check every few of hours to see if more water is needed due to evaporation.

name: Kendall's Kitchen: Garlic And Herb Shrimp
description: This delicious shrimp recipe is big on protein, flavor, and bang! Bring it with you to a summer barbeque or potluck and watch everyone come running.
recipeIngredient: ['fresh basil leaves, chopped - 1 cup', 'Italian seasoning - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1 lb', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a container that can be sealed well.
2. Shake container until shrimp are evenly coated.
3. Place shrimp in refrigerator and marinate for at least two hours.
4. Remove shrimp from refrigerator. Place them on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees F.
5. Cook shrimp 4-5 minutes, then turn over and cook for another 4-5 minutes. When done, shrimp will be opaque and the tails pink.
6. Serve warm and enjoy!

name: Tempeh Lettuce Wraps
description: Many people love P.F. Chang's chicken lettuce wraps. I was inspired to create a cleaner, meat-free version at home! It is quick and tasty, and a great option for a low-carb dinner.
recipeIngredient: ['tempeh - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper, sliced - ½ medium (approx 2-3/4" long, 2-1/2 dia.)', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'garlic, chopped - 1 Tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, powdered - 1 tsp', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'garlic, chopped - 1 Tbsp', 'lettuce - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive and garlic in a large pan over medium heat.
2. Add onion, tempeh, and bell pepper and saute for 3 minutes.
3. Add soy sauce and spices and cook for another 2 minutes.
4. Spoon mixture into lettuce leaves.

name: The Ultimate Meat-Free, Nutrient-Rich Power Bowl
description: Whether on its own or along with a protein source, this filling, nutrient-packed dish will satisfy your cravings and keep you feeling full!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato, cut into cubes - 2 cup', 'head cauliflower, chopped - 2½ cup', 'beets, cut into cubes - 1½ cup', 'Brussels sprouts, halved - 2 cup', 'coconut oil - 4 tbsp', 'salt - 2 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'rosemary - 1½ tsp', 'salad greens - 8 cup', 'cashews, chopped - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Prep ingredients ahead of time, if possible.
2. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F, arranging one rack in the middle and one rack at the bottom.
3. Grease two 9x13 baking dishes and set aside.
4. Place sweet potatoes and cauliflower in one baking dish, and Brussels sprouts and beets in the other. Drizzle vegetables with melted coconut oil, and season with sea salt, black pepper, and fresh herbs. Situate baking dishes on different racks (one in the middle and one on the bottom) in oven and bake for 25 minutes. Use a spatula to move veggies around halfway through baking.
5. While veggies bake, divide salad mix into four salad bowls. Use your hands to gently massage salad mix to ensure vinaigrette coats all leaves evenly. Set aside.
6. Remove veggies from oven and let cool slightly.
7. Add roasted sweet potatoes, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts, and beets to each salad bowl, decorate with sliced oranges, and garnish with a sprinkle of chopped cashews. Enjoy!

name: Sweet Potato Fries And Chips
description: Sweet potato chips/fries make a great side dish. I like to top them with cinnamon, nutmeg, and Splenda for a sweet version, or Cajun seasoning, salt, and pepper for savory.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 1 whole', 'reduced-sodium taco seasoning - 1 packet']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 425°F.
2. Cut up sweet potatoes (fries, wedges, whatever you prefer).
3. Season and spray pan and sweet potatoes with Olive Oil Pam.
4. Season and spray pan and sweet potatoes with Olive Oil Pam.

name: Protein Cauliflower Cheese Bake
description: Sure, cheese has protein, but when it comes to fueling your gains, more is better. Add some extra pow to your diet with this delicious, protein-rich cheese bake!
recipeIngredient: ['head cauliflower, chopped - 1¼ cup', 'pea protein powder - 28 g', 'whole milk - ¾ cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 6 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a pot, combine the milk, protein powder, 4 tbsp of the cheese cheese, garlic, and seasoning. Whisk over medium heat until you get a thick and creamy sauce.
2. Add your cooked cauliflower to a small casserole dish, and cover with the protein cheese sauce.
3. Add remaining 2 tbsp grated cheese on top and place under a broiler or grill for about 10 minutes, or until the cheese on top has melted. Dig in!

name: Low-Carb Protein Crepe
description: If you're a few weeks out from a photo shoot, competition, or other big event, you might be carb cycling. Most of us have a love-hate relationship with carb cycling—I know I do! Those low-carb days don't have to be a drag though. With a little creativity, you can enjoy many tasty meals. Here is one of my favorite breakfasts that tastes more like a dessert!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'liquid egg whites - ¼ cup', 'almond milk - 1 oz', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray sauce pan with non-stick cooking spray and heat.
2. Blend protein powder, egg whites, almond milk, and Stevia.
3. Pour batter in a pan and cook for 3 minutes, or until bubbles appear.
4. Fold in half and continue cooking until done.
5. Mix PB2 powder with water until you reach desired consistency.
6. Top crepe with PB2 and cinnamon.

name: Low Carb Smoothie
description: So if your taste buds and food sensibilities are begging for a change? Ah! Not another chicken breast!? Why not try vegetarian for a day?
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'soy milk, light - 1 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Mix and enjoy.

name: Greek Chicken
description: Turning up the flavor on chicken breast can make your meal sing. A palm-sized portion of grilled chicken provides roughly 25 grams of protein, while the addition of thyme and rosemary add flavor, sans salt. Rosemary, rich in folic acid and vitamins A and C, has been shown to ease muscle pain and indigestion. Just one tablespoon of this fragrant herb also delivers five percent of an adult's recommended daily amount of iron.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'black olives, sliced - ½ cup', 'tomatoes, sliced - 4', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 1 cup', 'olive oil - ⅓ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'rosemary - 1 tsp', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'lemon juice - 2 lemon yields', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix the olive oil, garlic, rosemary, thyme, oregano, pepper, and lemon juice.
2. Cut the chicken into strips. Place the chicken strips, olives, and diced tomatoes in the olive oil mixture. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight.
3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
4. Place chicken mixture in aluminum foil and, creating a pocket, add some of the marinade to keep it moist.
5. Cook for about 30 minutes.
6. Sprinkle with feta cheese before serving.

name: Alaskan Omelet
description: Are you looking for the perfect breakfast recipe to kickstart your metabolism and burn some fat? Consider amplifying your morning eggs with a hint of basil. Revered as the "holy herb," basil's antibacterial properties have been used to treat everything from the common cold and fever to respiratory disorders, kidney stones, and bronchitis and sinus infections. Its high magnesium content also makes basil key to improved blood flow.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1', 'egg whites - 4', 'reduced-fat sour cream - 1 tbsp', 'canned salmon - 2 oz', 'basil, dried - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'scallions, sliced - 1 tbsp', 'parsley, dried - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Beat eggs and pour them in a heated skillet.
2. When the omelet hardens, place salmon on top.
3. Top salmon with sour cream and sprinkle with basil, scallion, parsley, and pepper.
4. Fold in half and cook until done.

name: Provencal Chicken Strips
description: Are you searching for a high-protein recipe that's skimpy on carbs and fats? Try these simple, easy-to-make, downright delicious chicken strips flavored with a dash of parsley and rosemary. Parsley has strong anti-inflammatory properties and serves up more vitamin K than any other herb?just two tablespoons provide half of your recommended daily value. The kick of rosemary acts as an antioxidant.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'tomato, diced - 6', 'shallots - 1', 'parsley, dried - 1 tbsp', 'capers, canned - 1 tbsp, drained', 'red wine vinegar - 1 tsp', 'rosemary - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Saute chicken strips and 2 tbsp of olive oil in a large skillet at medium-high heat for 4 minutes.
2. Add shallot and garlic and cook for another 3 minutes. Stir frequently.
3. Stir in tomatoes, capers, parsley, vinegar, and rosemary.
4. Reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes, or until the liquid evaporates.

name: Lebanese Beef Kebabs
description: Nothing says protein-packed finger food like meat on a skewer. And nothing's better than tender beef marinated with herbs and spices. Enter: Lebanese beef kebabs. Along with the usual favorites of thyme and parsley, which are high in potassium, iron, calcium, and manganese, this recipe also calls for two other great herbs: the bay leaf and mint.
recipeIngredient: ['beef tenderloin - 16 oz', 'olive oil - 4 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'mint leaves - 1 tsp', 'paprika - ½ tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'bay leaf - 1', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'flat-leaf parsley - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor or blender, puree onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and zest, mint, paprika, cumin, thyme, bay leaf, and cayenne.
2. In a big Ziploc bag, combine beef cubes with the mixture, coating the beef completely. Marinate in the fridge overnight.
3. Drain the marinade in a saucepan, and bring to a boil.
4. Skewer beef cubes and place on hot grill. While turning the beef, brush with boiled marinade.
5. Serve in a bowl with the remaining marinade.

name: Tropical Punch Protein Shake
description: Sip on a burst of color anytime with coconut, strawberries, pineapple and banana to tantalize your senses.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'pineapple, raw - ¼ cup', 'banana - ½ medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'strawberries, sliced - 3 whole', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - 1 cup', 'water - 1 fl oz']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Rosemary Marinated Salmon
description: When it comes to eating fish, you can't go wrong with salmon. It is rich in omega-3 fats and high in EPA and DHA content - just four ounces contain more healthy fat than the average adult consumes in days. Salmon helps prevent chronic inflammation, promote cognitive function, and improve vision. Perhaps owing to the high levels of vitamin D and selenium, salmon also lowers cancer risks.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 24 oz', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'rosemary - ½ tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine all ingredients, except salmon, in a bowl. Add pepper to taste.
3. Pour the mixture into the bottom of a small baking dish.
4. Add salmon steaks and turn to coat. Marinate 15 minutes.
5. Wrap each steak in aluminum foil, and bake for about 20 minutes at 350 degrees F.

name: Egg Drop Soup
description: Winter draw nears - hell, it is here - and chances are you'll be on the lookout for comfort meals. Soup fits the bill perfectly.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken bone broth - 3 cup', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'mushroom - 3 whole', 'onion, finely diced - ½ whole', 'carrot, shredded - 2 whole', 'celery, raw - 1 cup chopped', 'bean sprouts, canned - 1 oz', 'Red Potatoes - 1 cup, diced', 'egg - 2 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat 2-3 cups of chicken or beef broth (preferably a low sodium variety) and add desired vegetables. Broccoli, mushrooms, onions, carrots, celery and bean sprouts.
2. If you want carbs, add sliced potatoes, cooked barley or whole wheat pasta.
3. At the end of the cooking process, crack 1-2 eggs into the bowl (or pour in 5-6 egg whites) and continue to heat, stirring occasionally.
4. Once the eggs whiten, remove from heat and serve.

name: Breakfast Champion Shake
description: Try this breakfast smoothie of champions for a quick fix packed with health-boosting ingredients.
recipeIngredient: ['skim milk - 1 cup', 'egg whites - 1 large', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'mixed berries - 1 1 cup', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'almonds, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'ice - 1 handful']
recipeInstructions: 1. Blend and enjoy.

name: Baked Apples Or Pears
description: Apples and pears are great when warm. I just discovered this recently and other than in pies, I've never had it. It's my new found love. Wow! Serve with cinnamon or even stuff with dried fruits (raisins, dates, papaya apricots etc). If you feel like going all out, add some granola on top.
recipeIngredient: ['apples - 1 medium (3" dia)', 'pears - 1 medium', 'granola - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. If you are using pears, cut them in half. Apples; just removed the core (don't cut in half).
2. Take dried fruit mix and stuff apples (core) or place into pear belly.
3. Sprinkle cinnamon. Granola on top if you are using (optional).
4. Sprinkle cinnamon. Granola on top if you are using (optional).

name: Vegetable Salsa
description: I like to make this on Sundays; it will last me until the next Thursday. It is the perfect guilt free treat. I enjoy mine served on Ezekiel bread. Any leftover are great added to chicken, so make a big batch. It's important here that you chop everything up very small.
recipeIngredient: ['tomatoes - 2 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'Eggplant - ½ eggplant, peeled (yield from 1-1/4 lb)', 'onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'turmeric - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'extra virgin olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Grill tomatoes, zucchinis, eggplant and squash until softened. Let them cool off.
2. Chop into small pieces and mix in the rest of the ingredients.
3. Let chill in fridge.

name: Low Carb Protein Bar
description: Thank you to the nutrition's section "Favorite Recipe" and the Keto section's "Keto Recipe's" threads for their helpful suggestions.
recipeIngredient: ['pecans - ½ cup', 'walnut, pieces - 6 tbsp', 'ground flaxseed - ⅓ cup', 'coconut butter - ⅓ cup', 'egg - 6 whole', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'sugar-free maple syrup - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 6 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put on an PAM-ed baking tray and flatten.
2. Bake for 15-20 minutes at 175 Celcius.

name: Sweet And Spicy Sweet Potato Soup
description: This modified Rachel Ray recipe is flavorful, clean, and filling. Yum Yum!
recipeIngredient: ['Carrot - 2 diced', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2 whole', 'onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'chicken bone broth - 5 cup', 'sweet potato - 1 whole', 'vanilla, nonfat greek yogurt - 3 tbsp', 'bay leaf - 1 whole', 'enchilada sauce - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a soup pot over medium-high heat and spray with Olive Oil Pam.
2. Add carrots, celery and onion and cook for 5 minutes.
3. Add the garlic, chipotle, and enchilada sauce and stir to combine.
4. Stir in salt, pepper and a bay leaf and cook for 1 minute.
5. Add stock, cover and raise heat to high. Bring the stoup to a boil, remove cover, and simmer for 10 minutes.
6. Add chicken and sweet potato and simmer 5 minutes or until sweet potatoes are tender and chicken is cooked through.
7. Garnish with dollop of Greek yogurt.

name: Quick And Fancy Apples
description: This one's easy! Mix it up and enjoy!
recipeIngredient: ['apple, sliced - 1 whole', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 tbsp', 'maple syrup - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Another way to snack on apples—this one is quick and sweet and it can be done a million different ways. The best part ... it only takes 2 minutes. Just cut an apple up (I love Fuji apples).
2. Add chopped walnuts, or a mix of nuts if you prefer.
3. Add some maple syrup or have it with almond butter or peanut butter. Up to you.
4. Mix it all up ... Ah, what a delight!

name: Low Carb French Toast
description: This week we went to the Bodybuilding.com message boards to find healthy and tasty Breakfast recipes. Here's a great recipe for low carb french toast
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2 whole', 'nonfat milk - ¼ cup', 'sugar-free maple syrup - ¼ tsp', 'multi-grain bread - 4 slice regular']
recipeInstructions:
1. Soak 4 slices of the bread into the egg/milk mixture put on a frying pan, and fry with PAM, until golden brown.
2. Put them on your plate, then sprinkle some cinnamon on top.
3. Then pour the sugar free syrup on them, and eat them.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Swirl Protein Bars
description: If you love the combination of chocolate and banana, you'll go absolutely bananas for these bars. Created by Jaime Baird, Online Editor-in-Chief of FitnessRx for Women and IFBB Bikini pro, these bars combine the perfect amount of protein and carbs to serve as a post-workout treat. Even if you aren't coming out of a workout, you can still nosh on them anytime during the day. They're perfect for keeping around in the fridge or freezer.
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 3 scoop', 'brown rice flour - ½ cup', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'banana - 1', 'water - ½ cup', 'egg whites - ⅔ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'powdered peanut butter - 4 tbsp', 'egg whites - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
2. Combine the chocolate MyoFusion, brown rice flour, and baking powder in a bowl.
3. In a blender, combine the ripe banana, water, and 2/3 cup egg whites. Stir in the dry ingredients until well-mixed.
4. Spray a glass baking pan with non-stick spray and pour batter into the dish.
5. In another bowl, combine the vanilla IsoFusion with peanut butter powder and 1/4 cup egg whites.
6. Pour this mixture onto the chocolate batter in straight lines.
7. Run a knife across the batter to create the swirled appearance.
8. Bake for 13-15 minutes, or until you can insert a toothpick in the center section of the bars and it comes out clean.

name: Onion Rings
description: Thank you to the nutrition's section 'Favorite Recipe' and the Keto section's 'Keto Recipe's' threads for their helpful suggestions. Here are 5 very simple and delicious recipes used by the stars!
recipeIngredient: ['white onion - 1 sliced', 'cream of wheat - 3 cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 3 large', 'skim milk - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cover baking sheet in tin foil (much easier clean up) and spray with Pam.
2. Preheat oven to 425.
3. Mix milk and eggs in one dish until blended evenly.
4. Mix all dry ingredients (cream of wheat, pepper, salt etc.) in another bowl.
5. Dip rings in wet mixture with one hand and then place in dry mix.
6. Cover rings with dry mixture and press down into mixture with other hand.
7. Shake off excess and place on baking sheet. (They can be close to each other because they won't stick to each other plus they also shrink)
8. Bake for 15-18 minutes then flip them over. The bottoms by now should be browned.
9. Place back in oven for another 5 minutes and this should help brown the other side a little more

name: Healthy Low-Carb Pancakes
description: Thank you to the nutrition's section 'Favorite Recipe' and the Keto section's 'Keto Recipe's' threads for their helpful suggestions. Here are 5 very simple and delicious recipes used by the stars!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 1 cup', 'ground flaxseed - 4 tbsp', 'Splenda - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 dash', 'smooth peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in the blender.
2. Put the mix into a frying pan.
3. Flip until both sides are perfectly browned. Add toppings if desired.

name: Sweet Potato Stir Fry
description: After doing some research and experimentation with purple sweet potatoes, I found they are not quite as sweet as orange sweet potatoes, but are great for more savory dishes, like stir-fry.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 1 whole', 'lean pork chops - 4 chop without refuse (yield from 1 raw chop, with refuse, weighing 259g)', 'green cabbage - 1 cup, chopped', 'head cauliflower, chopped - ½ cup', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place sweet potatoes in oven at 425°F for 15 minutes.
2. Meanwhile, cook pork chop on medium heat until done.
3. Add cabbage, broccoli and cauliflower to skillet and cook until cabbage is wilted. Mix with pork, sweet potato and eggplant and season with salt and pepper.

name: Protein and M&M Cake Jars
description: Not all meals have to be 100 percent clean. Once in a while, you need a treat. This dish serves up a cheat-worthy dessert that will still keep true to your high-protein standards. With an undeniably healthy take on cake, chocolate-covered candy, and 25 grams of protein per serving, it's proof that you can have your cake and eat it, too.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1', 'egg whites - 1', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'coconut flour - 6 tbsp', 'almond flour - ⅛ cup', 'banana - ½', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', "M&M's milk chocolate mini baking bits - 1 serving 0.5 oz, about 1 tbsp"]
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Mix all of the ingredients in a bowl. Add the M&M's last, and mix in by hand.
3. Take out two half-pint size oven-safe jars (or use Pyrex, ceramic or Corningware ramekins, or other oven-safe baking vessels if you have any doubt about your jars), coat them with nonstick cooking spray, and evenly distribute your mix into them. Don't fill to the top, as the cake will rise.
4. Top with a few more M&M's, and bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes.
5. Allow the jars to cool, then screw the lid on to make this perfect protein-rich treat ready for travel!

name: Protein Coconut Macaroons
description: Satisfy your sweet tooth with these flavor-packed, protein-stacked, macro-friendly macaroons!
recipeIngredient: ['liquid egg whites - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 cup(s)', 'granular erythritol - ¼ cup', 'coconut, shredded - ⅞ cup, shredded']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using an electric whisker or standing blender, beat your egg whites to soft peaks (as if you were making meringue).
2. Once your egg whites are fluffy, add in the rest of the ingredients. Use a spatula to fold them in gently until everything is well combined.
3. Divide the mix into four "blobs" and place on a nonstick cookie tray. Bake at 320 F (160 C) for no more than 12-15 minutes. I suggest you check on your macaroons after 10 minutes and remove them as soon as they start to brown on top. If they overbake, they end up very dry.
4. If you want to add an additional layer of decadence to your macaroon, melt a couple of squares—roughly 20 grams—of dark chocolate. Once it's melted, drizzle it on top of the macaroons. Prefer your chocolate on the bottom? Dunk your macaroons in the melted mixture to give them a "chocolate skirt."
5. Place the macaroons in the fridge to cool for a couple of hours before eating.

name: Peach-Mango Sangria
description: Order sangria at a restaurant and you'll get a bunch of sugar with your alcohol. Make a healthier choice and try this low-calorie option. It tastes just as good but doesn't include all of the junk!
recipeIngredient: ['optimum nutrition pro bcaa - 1 scoop', 'frozen peaches - 1 whole', 'mango - 1 whole', 'apples - 1 medium (3" dia)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add 1 scoop of BCAAs to 12 oz of water in a pitcher.
2. Cut up peach, mango, and apple into bite-sized pieces and add them to the pitcher.
3. Add the soda water.
4. Stir!

name: Garlicky Hummus
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'tahini paste - 4 oz', 'lemon juice - ¼ cup', 'extra virgin olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'ground ginger - 1 cup', 'cumin - ¼ tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'tomatoes - 1 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'scallions, sliced - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bust out the food processor for this one (or a magic bullet if you have one).
2. Combine chickpeas and liquid with tahini, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons oil, garlic, ginger, and cumin and puree.
3. Stir in cilantro, tomato, and scallions, season with salt and pepper.
4. Drizzle remaining oil over the top of the hummus.
5. Taste. Feel free to add in more of that yummy roasted garlic ... don't be shy!

name: Sweet Potato Pancakes and Waffles
description: What better way to start the day than with a plate of sweet-potato pancakes? This breakfast of champions will fuel your day and leave you licking your plate! On top of being delicious, they offer a whopping 40 grams of protein.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 1 whole', 'my protein impact whey vanilla - 1 scoop', 'egg whites - 3 large', 'walnuts, chopped - ⅓ tbsp', 'baking soda - ½ tbsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients until smooth.
2. Cook batches in pre-sprayed skillet/waffle maker on medium high temperature until bubbles form on the surface, then turn over and cook until dark golden brown.
3. Serve with cinnamon and sugar-free syrup.

name: Bacon 'N Cheese Sweet Potato
description: This meal is quick, easy, and a great way to refuel after a grueling workout!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 1 whole', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ½ cup', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 3 oz', 'turkey bacon - 2 strip', 'peppers, hot chili, red - ¼ cup, chopped or diced', 'broccoli - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Top sweet potato with cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese, chopped broccoli, turkey bacon, and crushed red pepper.
2. Microwave for 90-120 seconds, or until cheese is melted.

name: Easy Protein Bars
description: Easy protein bars
recipeIngredient: ['Dymatize Elite Whey Protein (Vanilla) - 8 scoop', 'raw oats - 3 cup', 'fat-free pistachio instant pudding mix - 3 tbsp', 'skim milk - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and spread in the bottom of a pan.
2. Place in the fridge overnight and cut into 8 individual squares the next morning.

name: Chef Robert Irvine: Grilled Mahi-Mahi Sandwich
description: Nothing beats the gorgeous presentation and flavor of mahi-mahi. Gently grill this clean, light protein source, and either plate it with a radiant yogurt slaw or sandwich it between toasted whole-wheat halves.
recipeIngredient: ['mahi-mahi - 1 3 oz', 'Sara Lee whole-wheat thin-style bun - 1 bun', 'cumin - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'rice wine vinegar - 2 Tbsp', 'lime juice - 1 tsp', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1 tbsp', 'red cabbage - 1 cup, shredded', 'lettuce - 1 leaf', 'avocado - ¼ fruit, without skin and seed', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'mango - ½ cup', 'pineapple - ½ cup, chunks', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lightly grill a piece of mahi-mahi for 3 minutes on each side, then remove from grill and let rest. This important step allows the juices of the fish, previously constricted during cooking, to return to all corners.
2. Make a dressing out of the cumin, yogurt, honey, rice wine vinegar, lime, and jalapeno by combining in a mixing bowl with a whisk. Start by whisking slowly, then more vigorously, until the dressing is consistent.
3. Combine the cabbage, garlic, pineapple, and mango in a separate mixing bowl to create the slaw, or salad.
4. Salt and pepper the slaw to taste.
5. Add half the dressing to the slaw, setting aside the other half.
6. Spread a light amount of the reserved dressing onto the base of the whole-wheat bun, then stack butter lettuce, slaw, and mahi-mahi, in that order. Top with the other half of the whole-wheat bun.
7. For a bread-free alternative, plate the mahi-mahi atop a brush stroke of dressing and slaw, then finish with a fan of avocado slices!

name: Homemade Cucumber Pickles
description: Skip all the usual steps of heating and cooking and 'pickling' and try this short cut version. In my opinion this is an underestimated staple to healthy snacking. Cucumbers are super low cal and having them pickled adds a ton of flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['cucumber, thinly sliced - 1 whole', 'white vinegar - 4 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Let it sit (the longer the better) ... it's that simple!

name: Kiwi Strawberry Blitz
description: BCAAs usually taste great on their own, but adding real fruit to your refreshing cup of muscle-building aminos just makes a good thing better. If you like kiwi and strawberry, then you'll love this delicious drink. Bottoms up!
recipeIngredient: ['kiwi - 1 whole', 'strawberries - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'water - 4 fl oz', 'Gaspari Nutrition Aminolast - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add 1 scoop of aminos to 4 oz of water in a glass.
2. Cut up strawberries and kiwi and add them to the glass.
3. Add lemon juice and ice.
4. Top it off with soda water if you like bubbles.

name: Raspberry-Lemon Mojito
description: Whoever decided that adding mint to a beverage was a good idea is a true hero. Combining mint with the always-yummy lemon-raspberry duo makes for a doubly yummy treat. It's difficult to make your BCAAs taste any better than this.
recipeIngredient: ['raspberries - 1 cup', 'mint leaves - 1 cup', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'optimum nutrition pro bcaa - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Muddle raspberries and mint leaves.
2. Add 8 oz water.
3. Add 8 oz water.
4. Stir in BCAAs.
5. Pour over ice.

name: Overnight Protein And Berry Oats
description: Simple, protein-packed, and undeniably healthy, this breakfast recipe is worth setting aside a few minutes the night before to make!
recipeIngredient: ['rolled oats - ½ cup', 'black chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'Nourish & Bloom Vanilla Spice Whole Foods Shake - 1 packet', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup', 'frozen blueberries - ¼ cup', 'organic honey - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl or cup.
2. Refrigerate overnight.
3. Top with more blueberries and a sprinkle of cinnamon.
4. Enjoy!

name: Summer Tea
description: Make this delicious beverage, and you'll imagine sitting on a front porch swing enjoying the evening breeze. Or, you might imagine how the BCAAs are helping your muscles grow. Put the two images together and you have yourself a swole 1940s gentleman suitor!
recipeIngredient: ['signature bcaa - 1 scoop', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'lemon, cut into wedges - 1½ whole', 'tea bag black - 1 bag']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brew a cup of your favorite tea in about 6 oz of water. I use black tea.
2. Add the sweetener of your choice while the tea is still hot.
3. Add a handful of ice to tea.
4. Stir in 1 scoop of BCAAs and add lemon wedges.

name: Orange Rosemary Cooler
description: Rosemary and cinnamon add adult complexity to your drink's flavor profile. Say goodbye to your super sweet BCAAs and enjoy something different. This is a recipe you can double or triple and bring to a party—it's really that good.
recipeIngredient: ['water - 4 fl oz', 'soda water - 4 oz', 'orange - ¼ fruit (2-7/8" dia)', 'rosemary - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'optimum nutrition amino energy orange cooler - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Chop rosemary stalks into small pieces.
2. Mix cinnamon and rosemary into water. Pour into ice-cube trays. Let freeze.
3. Stir 1 scoop of BCAAs in 4 oz of water.
4. Cut up orange and add it to glass.
5. Add soda water.
6. Pour drink over cinnamon and rosemary ice cubes.

name: Protein Powder And Oatmeal
description: Instead of resorting to unhealthy items, why not try and find something that you can substitute your shake with that will offer you the same nutritional profile? Then you get the best of both worlds: a nutrition meal and a break from the everyday.
recipeIngredient: ['protein powder (unflavored) - 1 scoop', 'oatmeal, cooked - 1 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook through to your preferred method
2. Add protein after cooking

name: Sweet And Salty Party Mix
recipeIngredient: ['Wheat Chex - 1 cup', 'peanuts salted - 1 cup, shelled', 'honey nut cherrios - 1 cup', "milk chocolate m & m's - ½ cup", 'pretzels - 2 cup', 'raisins - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients into large bowl and mix thoroughly.
2. Turn on a movie, or put the mix in a bag and send the kids out to play!

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Hummus
description: Chocolate, peanut butter, and…beans!? Yup, this unique combination will make you and your children rethink hummus! This sweet version provides plenty of fiber and fun. Just make sure to make enough for everyone.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, cooked - 2 cups', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 3 tbsp', 'smooth peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Open chick pea can and drain liquid until there’s roughly 25 percent of the liquid left. Pour beans and liquid into food processor or blender.
2. Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
3. Use as dip for fruit, pretzels, pita chips, crackers—you name it!

name: Loco Moco
description: Prepare to have your mind blown. My brothers at Lift Big Eat Big posted this the other day, and it has changed the course of history. Unlike our College Boy (see below), this meal requires a little bit of prep work, but it is more than worth it. It is a great way to start your day toward packing on the beef, and will give you a genuine mouth-gasm.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1½ lb', 'White Rice - 2 cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ¼ cup', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'egg - 6 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook the beef and onions prior to loading them in your Crock-Pot.
2. Add cooked beef and onions to Crock-Pot; add rice, gravy mix, and water to the pot.
3. Press the rice down firmly to stop the eggs from running through. Now crack the eggs on top of the rice one at a time.
4. Cook on low all night or on high for half the night. Set a timer so the pot turns off when it is done.

name: The Carnivore
description: I love a hearty breakfast, but half the time I just make a protein shake and head out the door unsatisfied. That's why a Crock-Pot omelet is freaking magical. I can prepare the meal right before I go to bed and awaken to a killer breakfast that's ready to go, even if I'm not. Now if I could only get that automatic coffee-maker working!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 6 whole', 'Red Potatoes - 1 cup, diced', 'chopped ham - 4 oz', 'turkey bacon - 2 oz', 'sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - 3 oz', 'onion, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'pepper to taste - 1 tsp', 'red bell pepper - ½ small']
recipeInstructions:
1. Dice or chop all of the meats and vegetables. (Here's the neat trick; use a food processor and all of this chopping can be done in less than a minute.
2. Dump meats and vegetables into the Crock-Pot.
3. In a small mixing bowl, mix eggs and spices and pour that into the bowl too.
4. Turn the Crock-Pot to low heat and leave it on while you go to sleep. You can thank me in the morning. (That's what she said. Right?)
5. Top with cheese a few minutes prior to serving.

name: The Make-It-Bacon Paleo Chicken Classic
description: Our prehistoric kin probably never ate anything like this, but there is a reason they gave up hunting and gathering—pigs and chickens are delish! This in-the-pot recipe will leave you licking the bottom for scraps. I throw this together a few hours before dinner.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 lb', 'bacon - 4 oz, chopped', 'white onion - 1 sliced', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'ground chipotle powder - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place uncooked bacon pieces in the Crock-Pot. Stir bacon in among cubed chicken, onion, and seasonings.
2. If you like, give it a light olive oil glaze. It will taste good and help keep your chicken from sticking to the pot.
3. Cook your bird on high for 3-4 hours.
4. Top with your chipotle sauce upon serving.

name: Fruit and Cheese Kabobs
recipeIngredient: ['grapes - ¾ cup', 'cheese, swiss, low fat - 12 cubic inch', 'blueberries - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place one grape, one cheese cube, and one blueberry on each skewer in this order.
2. Repeat twice more so that there are three of each item on the skewer.
3. No running while eating!

name: Microwavable Scrambled Eggs
description: Don’t trust your child around the stove yet? Let them cook their eggs using the microwave instead! This high-protein, fluffy snack (or meal), can be made in minutes without getting near a flame or another heating element. Even better, they're fun for kids to make!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2 whole', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Crack two eggs into coffee mug. Whisk for 10-20 seconds.
2. Microwave on high for approximately 90 seconds.*
3. Remove mug from microwave.
4. Add low-fat cheese and seasonings of choice. Stir.
5. Place coffee mug back in microwave and heat for an additional 30-60 seconds.*
6. Let eggs cool down for a minute or two, give each kid a fork, and watch them go!

name: Portable Protein Roll-Up
description: We need a lot of protein when we're young, the time our brains and our bodies are being fully formed. Unfortunately, kids tend to love snack foods that are high in added sugars and fats and low in protein. As a result, their diet often lacks sufficient protein.
recipeIngredient: ['low-fat deli turkey - 2 oz (1 serving)', 'mozzarella string cheese - 1 piece']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lay one slice of deli meat on top of the other on a plate.
2. Place string cheese at the end of the slices and roll so that deli meat surrounds the string cheese.
3. Enjoy!

name: Lighter Chicken Marsala
description: Chicken Marsala is definitely a comfort food—there's just something about that rich wine sauce, tender chicken, and mushrooms! This lighter, healthier version still has all the delicious flavor of my favorite dish, and whether you're into traditional Italian or trying out new flavors, I'm sure you'll love it!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'Kosher salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'butter, without salt - 2 tbsp', 'extra virgin olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'portabella mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup diced', 'Marsala cooking wine - ½ cup', 'chicken bone broth - ½ cup', 'flat-leaf parsley - ¼ cup', 'quinoa fusilli pasta - 6 oz', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 2 tbsp', 'butter, without salt - 1½ tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'kale, diced - 3 cup', 'garlic powder - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Either slice chicken breasts lengthwise so they're half as thick, or wrap each chicken breast with cling wrap and use a meat mallet to pound them until they're 1/2-inch thick. Season both sides with salt and pepper.
2. Heat one tablespoon each of butter and olive oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
3. Cook chicken breasts in skillet 4-5 minutes per side until browned and cooked through. Set aside.
4. Add one tablespoon of sliced mushrooms to same skillet and sauté until golden brown.
5. Add back chicken breasts, plus cooking wine, chicken broth, and one tablespoon of butter, cooking 1 minute until slightly reduced (you may add 1 tbsp cornstarch to thicken, if desired).
6. Cook fusilli according to package directions, drain, and rinse with hot water.
7. Sauté kale with olive oil and garlic powder until wilted.
8. Toss cooked pasta with sautéed kale, 1-1/2 tbsp butter, and shredded parmesan cheese.
9. Serve chicken and mushroom sauce over pasta. Enjoy!

name: Taco Turkey Casserole
description: This delicious twist on a classic casserole is layered like lasagna, using gluten-free corn tortillas instead of noodles, and salsa instead of marinara sauce. Enjoy all your favorite south-of-the-border flavors by topping this delicious taco treat with diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce, black olives, and nonfat plain Greek yogurt (It tastes just like sour cream!).
recipeIngredient: ['corn tortilla - 12 whole', 'fat-free refried beans - 15 oz', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'reduced-sodium taco seasoning - ¼ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'red bell pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 cup', 'salsa - 1 cup', 'reduced-fat Mexican cheese - 1 oz', 'iceberg lettuce - 1½ cup shredded', 'diced tomatoes - 1½ cup', 'black olives, sliced - ½ cup', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Pan-fry meat over medium-high heat until cooked through.
3. Add taco seasoning, water, onions, and peppers. Sauté until vegetables are tender.
4. Lightly coat a 9x13-inch casserole dish with cooking spray and cover bottom with six corn tortillas.
5. Spread half a can of fat-free refried beans over the tortillas, followed by half of the taco meat, half a cup of salsa, and one cup of cheese.
6. Arrange six more tortillas over first layer, followed by remaining beans, taco meat, cheese, and another half cup of salsa.
7. Bake for about 30 minutes, or until heated through and cheese is melted.
8. Cut into eight equal pieces.
9. Before serving, top with shredded lettuce, diced fresh tomatoes, sliced black olives, nonfat plain Greek yogurt (omit if vegan), and fresh cilantro.

name: Healthy Shrimp and Sausage Gumbo
description: This Creole-inspired dish is loaded with andouille sausage, plump shrimp, onion, peppers, and okra in a flavorful onion broth with a hint of tomato and just a little heat.
recipeIngredient: ['small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1 lb', 'smoked sausage,  cut into 1/4-inch slices - 8 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'flour - ¼ cup', 'low-sodium vegetable broth - 6 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 3 stalk, medium', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 cup', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'Worcestershire sauce - 1 tbsp', 'bay leaf - 2', 'salt-free Creole seasoning - 1 tbsp', 'okra - 3 cup', 'green onion, chopped - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Thaw shrimp in fridge overnight, or place bag in lukewarm water for an hour until thawed through.
2. Brown the sausage in the bottom of a large saucepan or soup pot with oil and onions over medium-high heat.
3. Add flour and stir to coat evenly.
4. Add broth, celery, garlic, bell pepper, tomato paste, Worcestershire, bay leaves, and Creole seasoning (like Tony Chachere's). Simmer over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
5. Add okra and cook for 5 minutes until softened.
6. Add shrimp with juice from bag and simmer briskly for 2 minutes.
7. Serve hot over rice and garnish with green onions.

name: Grilled Chicken and Lemon Skewers
description: Serve on bed a quinoa or rice and pair it with a yummy green veggie for a healthy, filling, gluten-free meal. Seriously, this couldn't be any simpler…or more delicious!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'lemon, cut into wedges - 1 whole', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ¼ cup', 'mustard - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat grill. If you are using bamboo skewers, soak them overnight or as indicated by the manufacturer's instructions.
2. Skewer a cube of chicken alternating with a slice of lemon that's folded in half.
3. Mix lemon juice, garlic, salt, pepper, olive oil, basil, and mustard in a small bowl.
4. Brush sauce over both sides of skewers.
5. Grill over med-high heat for about 4 minutes on each side and serve.

name: Avocado Egg Sweet Potato Toast
description: Sometimes the best recipes are also the simplest ones. You'll only need a couple of minutes to prepare this delicious treat, but the payoff in nutrients and taste is huge!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 1 whole', 'egg - 2 whole', 'avocado - ½ fruit, without skin and seed', 'chives - 2 tbsp chopped', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice sweet potato into 4 slices, lengthwise.
2. Poke slices with a fork and microwave for two minutes, flipping 1/2 way through until soft, yet slightly firm.
3. Toast in toaster oven until tender when pierced.
4. Over medium heat, melt coconut oil and fry eggs until edges start to brown, place on top of sweet potato.
5. Cut avocado and layer on top of egg.
6. Sprinkle with chopped chives, salt and cracked pepper to taste.

name: Honey Mustard Dressing
description: Top off your kale salad with simple grilled chicken thighs and a homemade honey mustard dressing, and you have a light and healthy alternative to save you from heavy winter meals.
recipeIngredient: ['mustard - 2 tbsp', 'rice wine vinegar - 2 Tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'grapeseed oil - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine mustard, rice wine vinegar, lemon juice, and honey in a bowl.
2. Add oil in a slow stream while continuously whisking to emulsify the dressing, making it thicker and more stable.
3. Add a pinch of salt and pepper to taste.

name: Kale and Citrus Chicken Salad
description: It seems kale is everywhere, but many people still shy away from this leafy, vitamin-packed superfood. Yet as celebrity chef Robert Irvine explains, this may have more to do with kale's tough texture than with its taste and health benefits.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken thigh - 2 piece', 'orange - 1 fruit (2-7/8" dia)', 'kale, diced - 3 cup', 'tomatoes, sliced - 2 large whole (3" dia)', 'red onion, sliced - ½ whole', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ½ cup', 'flat-leaf parsley - ½ cup', 'scallions, sliced - ½ cup', 'sesame seeds - 2 tbsp', 'Honey Mustard Dressing - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Season chicken thighs with salt and pepper and place them on the grill on medium-high heat. Grill on both sides until cooked all the way through. Set aside.
2. To supreme the orange, chop the top and the bottom off so it sits flat on your cutting board.
3. Using a small knife, slice the peel off the orange in sections all the way around, carefully removing all of the bitter white pith.
4. Once you have the orange completely peeled, take knife down the side of the vein, twist at the bottom, and pop out each orange segment.
5. Roll up the basil, mint, and parsley and slice into thin slices--also known as a chiffonade. Run your knife through everything a few times once more in the other direction to chop up the herbs.
6. Place the kale in the bowl with the dressing. Sprinkle with chopped herbs and mix to combine.  Add chopped tomatoes, sliced red onions, diced scallion, and orange supremes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, and sesame seeds.
7. Plate the salad and top with grilled chicken thighs. Finish with additional orange segments and scallions.

name: Easy DIY Yogurt Recipe
description: Whether you want to save a little cash, make just the right kind of yogurt for your taste buds, or have large quantities of a great protein source on hand, this simple recipe tells you all you need to know so you can do it yourself!
recipeIngredient: ['whole milk - 8 cup', 'yogurt with live cultures - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the milk in a slow cooker on the "low" setting for 2-1/2 hours.
2. Turn the slow cooker off and let the warmed milk rest for 3 hours.
3. Add the yogurt to the milk and stir to combine. Cover the slow cooker with two heavy towels and let rest for 8-12 hours, depending on desired consistency. Refrigerate after set.
4. Special Equipment: Slow cooker, Heavy towels to insulate slow cooker.

name: Ultimate Omelet
description: There's nothing complicated or difficult about this recipe. Let's get into the kitchen and build some muscle!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 4 oz', 'egg - 3 whole', 'egg whites - 6', 'avocado - ¼ cup, pureed', 'sun-dried tomatoes - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brown ground turkey in a skillet over medium/high heat. Once finished, drain excess juice out of the skillet and place turkey in a bowl.
2. Beat together whole eggs and egg whites. Pour eggs into skillet.
3. While eggs cook, mix sun-dried tomatoes with ground turkey.
4. When eggs are cooked firmly enough to flip, place ground turkey on one half of the cooked eggs.
5. Flip open side of eggs over to cover the ground turkey. Let cook for 2-3 minutes, then flip omelet. Cook until eggs are not runny.
6. Place omelet onto a plate and then pour pureed avocado over the top.

name: Quick And Easy Zesty Broccoli
description: This is one of my favorite broccoli recipes because it's quick, easy, and above all, delicious. It's extra special because the ingredients actually add to the fat-loss process.
recipeIngredient: ['broccoli, steamed - 1 cup', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'scallions, sliced - 1']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix scallion, apple cider vinegar and mustard in a large bowl.
2. Pour over steamed broccoli, toss, then serve.

name: Moroccan Spiced Salmon
description: This zesty, no-carb dish gets its zip from cumin, coriander, and turmeric: spices with antioxidant properties that protect your cells from everyday damage. No salmon? Halibut and cod fillets work just fine. Marinate the fish the night before or in the morning.
recipeIngredient: ['garlic, minced - 4 clove', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'salt - ¾ tsp', 'coriander - ½ tsp', 'turmeric - ¼ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'salmon fillet - 24 oz', 'cilantro - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put the marinade ingredients in a large ziplock bag, then place the fish in the bag, making sure that the marinade coats both sides of the fish. Refrigerate for 4-6 hours.
2. Add 2 tbsp water to the slow cooker. Cover and cook 2 hours on low. When done, let the fish sit, uncovered, for 5 minutes before serving.
3. Use a spatula to remove the fish from the slow cooker and transfer to a plate. Gently remove any bones from the fish.
4. To serve, divide the fish between plates, serve it on top of couscous or rice, and garnish each portion with cilantro.

name: Combat Tropical Strength Shake
description: There's nothing complicated or difficult about this recipe. Let's get into the kitchen and build some muscle!
recipeIngredient: ['MusclePharm Combat Power (Vanilla) - 2 scoop', 'Silk coconut milk - 1 cup', 'water - 1 cup', 'frozen mango pieces - ½ cup', 'frozen papayas - ½ cup 1" pieces']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients into a blender.
2. Blend for 20 to 30 seconds, or until desired consistency.

name: Protein Pizza Crust
description: Bye, bye, Boboli. Make your pizza crust from scratch—and power it up with some muscle-building protein—with this delicious thin-crust recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'pea protein powder - 10 g', 'unflavored whey protein powder - ¼ cup', 'rolled oats - ⅜ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 2 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Using a hand-held blender or food processor, blend all the ingredients together until you get a thick pancake-like batter.
2. Heat a nonstick pan, and add a teaspoon of coconut oil or some low-calorie cooking oil/spray. Turn the heat to high until your oil begins to sizzle.
3. Add 1/2 of the batter to the pan, spreading it on the surface of the pan thinly with a spatula. Turn the heat down to medium to ensure your crust cooks evenly and doesn't burn.
4. Once the bottom of the crust has cooked, flip it.
5. Remove the crust from the pan and add your toppings. Begin with tomato paste, and then add your choice of topping. Finish by topping with cheese.
6. Place the crust with all of your toppings under the grill or oven broiler for 5-10 minutes or until the cheese has melted and the pizza looks done. That's it. Bon appétit!

name: Esto Es La Pera
description: Dinner fit for a matador. The recipe is great for days when that 12-ounce T-bone steak just seems like a bit much. Pears are the quiet stepsister to the spotlight-hogging apple, so give her a dance and don't retreat to the comfortable arms of the applesauce-glazed chops just yet. Round out a successful paleo-inspired day with vitamins C and A, folic acid, and potassium on top of your meat.
recipeIngredient: ['lean pork chops - 16 oz', 'pears - 2 medium', 'red onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'rosemary - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Heat olive oil in a large cast iron skillet over medium heat.
3. Season pork chops with salt and pepper on both sides and place in skillet. Sear for 2-3 minutes on each side. Let stand.
4. Then sauté the pear and onion slices in the skillet for 2 minutes, or until the pear slices are slightly browned.
5. Drizzle balsamic vinegar over the pear and onion, and arrange the pork chops and fresh rosemary on top.
6. Bake in the oven for approximately 10 minutes or until the meat is thoroughly cooked.

name: Blueberry And Cucumber Quinoa Salad
description: Keep it colorful with a fruit and veggie salad. Enjoy as an afternoon snack or add a little meat for a great meal. Although quinoa breaks from strict paleo, this staple food of the Inca contains more protein than rice or wheat, so it's probably worth the rule-breaking.
recipeIngredient: ['quinoa, cooked - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'cucumber, chopped - 1 cucumber (8-1/4")', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, combine the quinoa, cucumber, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
2. On a plate, arrange the fresh spinach leaves, quinoa mixture and top with fresh blueberries. (Serve with grilled chicken or lean fish for a complete meal.)

name: Super Hero Chicken
description: There's nothing complicated or difficult about this recipe. Let's get into the kitchen and build some muscle!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 12 oz', 'honey - 1 tsp', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 tsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Coat a baking pan with Pam spray and then place chicken in pan.
3. In a separate bowl, combine honey, orange juice, and lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
4. Cover pan with tin foil and bake for 10 minutes.
5. Remove pan from oven to flip chicken, and then return it to the oven for another 10-15 minutes.
6. For a full meal, pair chicken with green vegetables and, depending on your carbohydrate needs, a starch.

name: Grilled BBQ Flank Steak
description: There's nothing complicated or difficult about this recipe. Let's get into the kitchen and build some muscle!
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 24 oz', 'light soy sauce - ⅓ cup', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 tsp', 'sesame seeds - 1 tsp', 'scallions, sliced - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a mixing bowl, combine soy sauce, pepper, sesame oil, garlic, and sesame seeds.
2. Put mixture and flank steak in a Ziploc bag.
3. Allow to marinade in the fridge for 30 minutes.
4. Heat grill to high heat.
5. Cook flank steak for 4-5 minutes per side, or until desired temperature.
6. For a full meal, pair steak with green vegetables and, depending on your carbohydrate needs, a starch.

name: Bill Phillips Back To Fit Recipes: Homestyle Turkey Meatloaf
description: This recipe puts a healthy spin on that mashed classic. Use turkey instead of greasy ground beef. Keep the onions and ketchup. Add some mashed potatoes and green beans, and you have a complete meal!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1½ lb', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'egg whites - 4 large', 'salsa - 1 cup', 'raw oats - ¾ cup', 'onion soup mix powder - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'low-sugar ketchup - 3 tbsp', 'Red Potatoes - 2 cup, diced', 'Green Beans - 1 cup 1/2" pieces', 'skim milk - ¾ cup', 'Butter, without salt - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. In a large mixing bowl, combine ground turkey, onion, egg whites, salsa, oats, soup mix, and black pepper. Press mixture into 9x5 loaf pan and spread ketchup over top. Bake in preheated oven until meatloaf is no longer pink in the center and juice is clear, about 60 minutes.
3. Approximately 25 minutes after putting the meatloaf in the oven, cut potatoes into one-inch chunks. Place cut potatoes in a large saucepan, cover with cold water, and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
4. Cut stems off green beans and place in a large saucepan with one inch of water in the bottom. Heat to boiling over high heat; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 6-8 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
5. Remove meatloaf from oven and let sit for five minutes before slicing.
6. Drain the potatoes and return them to the pan. Mash while adding skim milk a little at a time. Add Butter Buds and mash vigorously until potatoes are light and fluffy.
7. Place a portion of meatloaf and mashed potatoes along with about a cup of green beans on each plate. Serve and enjoy!

name: Chef Robert Irvine: Thousand Island Dressing
description: Chef Robert Irvine's zesty, homemade version of this popular dressing is a great addition to your favorite foods. Enjoy it on everything from salads to burgers!
