recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'zucchini, sliced - 2 whole', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'Eggplant - 1', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 whole', 'baby spinach - 2 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'tomato sauce, canned - 15 oz', 'tomato paste - 12 oz', 'egg whites - 2', 'ricotta cheese (skim-milk) - 2 cup', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 8 oz', 'salt - 1½ tsp', 'black pepper - 1½ tsp, ground', 'basil, dried - 1 tbsp, ground', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, ground', 'nutritional yeast - 4 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Lightly salt zucchini slices and place in a large, microwaveable bowl. Cover with plastic wrap, and make one small slit in the cover. Microwave for 6-8 minutes.
2. Place steamed zucchini in strainer to drain.
3. Prepare eggplant using the same process as zucchini.
4. In a large pot, place ground turkey, salt, and pepper. Cook over medium heat to brown turkey for about 5 minutes.
5. Add minced garlic, green bell pepper, and onion. Allow to sauté for 5 more minutes.
6. When meat is completely cooked, add tomato sauce, tomato paste, basil, and oregano, and mix well.
7. Once sauce comes to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
8. In a separate bowl, mix ricotta, egg whites, and parsley until well blended.
9. Lightly grease a 9x13 baking pan. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
10. Layer lasagna in the following order: 1/3 meat sauce, 1/3 zucchini slices, 1/2 ricotta mixture, 1/2 eggplant slices, 1/3 meat sauce, all spinach, 1/3 layer zucchini slices, 1/2 ricotta mixture, 1/2 eggplant slices, all mushrooms, remaining meat sauce, 1/2 mozzarella, 1/3 zucchini slices. Top with remaining mozzarella, and sprinkle with nutritional yeast.
11. Cover with aluminum foil, place pan on baking sheet, and bake at 350 degrees F for 45 minutes.
12. Remove foil and cook additional 15 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to cool for at least 10 minutes.
13. Once the lasagna has cooled, slice into 9 squares.

name: Mango Chicken With Coconut Cauliflower Rice
description: This simple-to-make, low-carb mango chicken is served over coconut cauliflower rice. With a little fresh ginger and habanero, it packs a flavorful punch!
recipeIngredient: ['coconut oil - 2½ tsp', 'ginger, minced - 1½ tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'habanero pepper, diced - ½ tsp', 'orange mango juice - ¾ cup', 'coconut aminos - ½ tbsp', 'tapioca flour - 1 tsp', 'tapioca flour - 3 tbsp', 'chicken breast - 8 oz', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'head cauliflower, chopped - 3 cup', 'coconut oil - 2 tsp', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 2 tbsp', 'frozen mango pieces - ½', 'cilantro - 1 tsp', 'green onion, sliced - 1 tsp', 'sesame seeds - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Sauce Directions: Heat 1-1/2 teaspoons of coconut oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
2. Add in the ginger, garlic, and habanero pepper, and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add in the juice and coconut aminos. Raise the temperature to high heat, and bring to a boil. While liquid is boiling, place the tapioca flour in a small bowl.
3. Once the liquid comes to a boil, add 2 teaspoons of it to the bowl with the tapioca flour and whisk until smooth. While stirring constantly, pour the tapioca mixture into the sauce and boil for 2 minutes.
4. After the sauce has boiled, reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring frequently, until the sauce reduces by about 1/4 and becomes shiny, about 6-7 minutes.
5. Transfer sauce to a large bowl to let it cool and thicken while you make the chicken.
6. Chicken Instructions: Place the tapioca flour in a large Ziploc bag. Cut the chicken into cubes, season it with salt and pepper and add it into the bag, shaking until evenly coated in the flour.
7. In a medium pan, heat 1 tablespoon of the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Place half of the chicken into the pan, being careful not to crowd it, and cook until golden and browned, about 2-3 minutes. Flip and repeat.
8. Transfer the chicken to a paper-towel-lined plate, and blot off any excess oil. Repeat with the remaining chicken. If the chicken starts cooking too quickly, turn the heat down slightly.
9. While the chicken cooks, place the cauliflower in a large food processor and process until broken down and rice-like.
10. Heat the 2 teaspoons of coconut oil in a large pan over medium-high heat and add the cauliflower and coconut flakes. Cook until lightly golden, about 2-3 minutes.
11. Cover, reduce the heat to medium, and cook until the cauliflower is tender, about 2-4 minutes.
12. Transfer the chicken and mango cubes into the bowl with the sauce and toss until evenly coated.
13. Divide the chicken and cauliflower between two plates and garnish with cilantro, green onion and sesame seeds. Enjoy!

name: Creamy Barley With Mushrooms
description: Barley is one of those forgotten whole grains in the maddening dash for fast food. Simply put, some good food takes a little time to prep. This fine barley dish fits alongside a main chicken or beef entree with a side salad to make a complete meal. The pecans are a pleasant surprise and add healthy fat content to this simple side.
recipeIngredient: ['light margarine - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - ½ clove', 'barley, pearled - 1 cup', 'pecans - ¼ cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - ½ cup', 'flat-leaf parsley - ½ cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 2 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Once melted, add in the onion, garlic, barley, and pecans.
4. Continue to cook for 3-4 minutes or until barley browns.
5. Add mushrooms and parsley.
6. Continue to cook for another minute or two, and then transfer everything into a large baking dish.
7. Add chicken broth and bake for about 75 minutes, or until the broth has been absorbed.
8. Fluff with a fork and serve!

name: Deviled Eggs With Guacamole
description: Before we broke bread and let football take over the holiday, simpler times made for cleaner food. Celebrate the paleo way!
recipeIngredient: ['hard-boiled egg - 12', 'avocado - 2', 'hot sauce - 4 tsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel hardboiled eggs; once peeled, cut in half (length-wise). Remove yolks and place in a bowl.
2. Add avocado to your yolks and mash them together; add hot sauce, lemon juice, sea salt and freshly ground black pepper. Mix thoroughly.
3. Refill your egg whites halves with avocado/yolk mix.

name: Garlic and Herb Gravy
description: Before we broke bread and let football take over the holiday, simpler times made for cleaner food. Celebrate the paleo way!
recipeIngredient: ['onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 5 clove', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 4 cup', 'coconut aminos - 1 tbsp', 'butter, without salt - 2 tbsp', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, ground', 'salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place saucepan under high heat. Add broth, onions, garlic and thyme, and bring it to a boil. Once it boils, lower heat to low and let it simmer for 30 minutes (or until the onions and garlic are soft).
2. Add sea salt, pepper, and coconut aminos as it simmers.
3. Once it's simmered for about 30 minutes, pour mixture to a blender and add 2 tablespoons of butter. Blend until thoroughly mixed.
4. Serve immediately.
5. Note: You can also add full fat coconut milk if you want a creamier gravy.

name: Parsnip Mash
description: Before we broke bread and let football take over the holiday, simpler times made for cleaner food. Celebrate the paleo way!
recipeIngredient: ['parsnips, medium, peeled and sliced - 4 whole', 'onion, sliced - 1', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'water - ½ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place skillet under medium heat and add olive oil. Once olive oil is hot, add onions. Cook until onions have fried a bit.
2. Add parsnips and water to the skillet and close with lid. Cook until parsnips have softened.
3. Pour onion/parsnip mix, sea salt and pepper into a food processor. Process until the parsnips have mashed.
4. Serve immediately.

name: Kale Blueberry Smoothie
description: In the mood for a breakfast smoothie? Add some kale to it! Kale can make for a perfect addition to any fruit smoothie you might want to whip up, inconspicuously adding an extra serving of greens to your day. With the mix of other flavors, you'll drink down the benefits without it tasting like you're having a "green"—read, earthy—smoothie.
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - ½ cup', 'frozen blueberries - ½ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients (along with 1-2 ice cubes) in a blender, and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

name: Mandarin And Kale Salad
description: Sweet mandarin oranges and hearty kale mix together perfectly in this nutrient-packed salad. Add a grilled chicken breast or some grilled sirloin for protein if you want to build a complete and balanced meal!
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - 4 cup', 'almonds, slivered - 2 tbsp', 'mandarin oranges, drained - 1 can', 'dried cranberries - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix together the olive oil, vinegar, and honey.
2. Toss the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl. Drizzle dressing from the first mixture on top.
3. Serve immediately or place in the fridge, covered, until ready to serve.

name: Poached Eggs Over Kale
description: Want a low-carb breakfast option to start your day? Try poached eggs over kale. The combination of gooey egg yolk and crisp kale will be enough to make your taste buds dance, and with a healthy balance of proteins, fats, and fiber, your muscles will thank you. For a refreshing, citrus finish, serve with a slice of orange.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2 whole', 'garlic, pureed - 1 tsp', 'kale, diced - 3 cup', 'white vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add olive oil to a skillet along with garlic and heat.
2. Add kale and sauté for 2-3 minutes or until wilted. Transfer to a plate.
3. Boil a large pot of water. Reduce the heat and add 1 tablespoon of white vinegar. Slide the eggs into the water and allow them to cook for 3-4 minutes or until whites are no longer translucent.
4. Using a slotted spoon, remove the eggs from the water and set on top of the steamed kale.
5. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.

name: Green Pepper Barley Salad
description: Simplicity is important in any meal plan, but especially in a salad. People tend to throw in any green thing. Make choices that optimize flavor. This green pepper salad is a light and refreshing addition to any meal. Serve it hot or cold. Add more vegetables if you like—just remember that the calories can add up.
recipeIngredient: ['water - 2 cup', 'barley - 1 cup', 'green pepper, cut into strips - 2 whole', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'flat-leaf parsley - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'Italian dressing - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, pureed - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Boil water in a saucepan over medium heat.
2. Add the barley and then cover and let cook for 10-12 minutes.
3. Meanwhile, slice the green peppers and dice the onion. Chop up parsley and then add ingredients to the cooked barley.
4. Fluff with a fork to combine.
5. In another bowl, combine together the olive oil, Italian salad dressing, and garlic.
6. Drizzle over the mixture and then stir before serving.

name: Pesto Hummus
description: This Italian/Middle Eastern fusion will knock your socks off. The excellent flavor combination is unique, and so wonderfully palatable that even kids will like it!
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'tahini paste - 5⅓ tbsp', 'pesto - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients.
2. Serve with vegetables, pita chips, or snack of your choice.

name: Clean Ketchup
description: This recipe packs the full flavor of your favorite tabletop condiment without the ladles of sugar and chemicals ketchup usually comes with. Feel free to dress up your sauce any way you see fit: cayenne pepper for a spicy kick, fresh mustard for tang, or Worcestershire sauce for a little extra punch.
recipeIngredient: ['tomatoes, canned - 1 can', 'tomato, canned, puree - 20 g', 'apple cider vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'Himalayan rock salt - 1 pinch', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'garlic, chopped - 1 clove', 'onion, finely diced - 1', 'coconut oil - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Chop the garlic and onions. Fry gently in the coconut oil for a few minutes.
2. Add the tomato puree and cook the mixture for 30-60 seconds.
3. Add all of the remaining ingredients, and turn down the heat.
4. Allow the mixture to gently bubble for at least 10 minutes. Then remove from the heat and allow it to cool to room temperature.
5. Using a handheld blender or food processor, blend the ketchup to your desired consistency. I prefer to keep it reasonably chunky and use it more like a sauce. If you like to smoother, blend further for a more authentic ketchup texture.
6. Store your ketchup an airtight jar in the fridge. It will last for up to a week.

name: Baked Kale Chips
description: Move over, Lays. These kale chips will satisfy your craving for something crunchy, and they're the perfect alternative to potato chips. They're relatively low in calories and allow you to snack on veggies in a different way. The best part? There are no greasy fingers to hinder your grip on the bar for those sweet, post-snacking deadlifts and push presses.
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - 3 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
2. In a large Ziploc bag, combine the kale, olive oil, and salt. Shake the bag vigorously to distribute.
3. Place on a baking tray and bake for 10-15 minutes or until crisp. Serve immediately.

name: Mason Jar Chicken Taco Salad
description: This healthy taco salad recipe is the perfect stress reliever after a long day of work. Prepping bigger batches takes almost no extra time, providing delicious dinners for days to come. Even made days ahead of time, these spicy salads won't get soggy!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 8 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'avocado - 1', 'diced tomatoes - 2 cup', 'cucumber, chopped - ½', 'carrot, shredded - 2 whole', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'onion, finely diced - ½ cup', 'baby spinach - 4 cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'salsa - 1 cup', 'cilantro - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - 2 tsp', 'cumin seed - 1 tsp, whole', 'salt to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook the chicken breast until slightly browned and no longer pink on the inside. Set aside in a small bowl.
2. Add the remaining 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil into the pan and heat at medium-high heat. Cook the carrots until they begin to soften, about 3 minutes.
3. Turn the heat down to medium and add in the pepper, onion, and garlic. Cook until soft.
4. While the veggies cook, place the cumin seeds in a small, dry pan over medium-high heat and toast them, stirring frequently, until golden brown and fragrant, about two minutes. Transfer them to a cutting board and crush. I use the bottom of a glass, which works really well.
5. Add the crushed seeds into the pan with the veggies and season with salt. Mix well, and turn off the heat.
6. Scoop avocado into a small food processor, add the lime juice, and blend until smooth and creamy. You can also just mash them together in a bowl.
7. Assembly Instructions:

Place 1/2 cup of salsa in the bottom of each jar, spreading evenly. Gently spread the avocado/lime mixture on top. Then, add in the cumin and roasted veggies, followed by the chicken. You may need to lightly press everything in to get it all to fit.
8. After the chicken, add the chopped tomatoes, and then the cucumbers. Finish off by dividing the cilantro and then as much spinach as you can stuff in there!
9. Seal and refrigerate until ready to devour.

name: Chicken Vegetable Soup
description: Chicken soup is great, but add some veggies to it and it becomes even greater! This soup is rich in fiber, complex carbohydrates, lean protein, and antioxidants, so it's something you can feel good about putting into your body. Feel free to add other vegetables as desired!
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 2 stalk, small', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, pureed - 1 tsp', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 4 cup', 'chicken breast - 3⅓ oz', 'kale, diced - 4 cup', 'cannellini beans, drained and rinsed - 1 cup', 'rosemary - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a large pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
2. Brown chicken in olive oil for 5 minutes, then add garlic, onion, celery, and carrots. Sauté for another 5 minutes.
3. Add in 2 cups of chicken broth and kale. Bring the mixture to a boil, and reduce heat and simmer for about 3 minutes.
4. Add in the remaining broth along with the beans, adding salt and pepper to taste.
5. Cook for another 5 minutes. Stir in rosemary and serve.

name: Cajun Zucchini Noodle Stew With Shrimp And Sausage
description: This low-carb stew tastes like your favorite jambalaya, but with all the spicy flavor going on, you won't miss the usual accompanying rice!
recipeIngredient: ['zucchini, sliced - 2 whole', 'andouille chicken sausage - 1 link', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 4 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'diced red bell pepper - ½', 'onion, finely diced - ½ cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'diced tomatoes - 1 cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - ½ cup', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'Cajun seasoning - 2 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 tsp', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'bay leaf - 2 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spiralize zucchini using a spiralizer with a 3-millimiter blade.
2. Place your zucchini noodles in a colander (set over a large bowl) and sprinkle with a pinch of salt. Toss to coat and let stand so the noodles can release some water.
3. In a large pan, heat the olive oil on medium-high heat. Add in the Cajun seasoning and garlic and cook until garlic is golden brown and fragrant, about 1 minute.
4. Add in the sliced pepper, onion, and celery, and cook until vegetables are lightly browned and tender, about 2-3 minutes.
5. Reduce the temperature to medium, and add in the sliced chicken sausage. Cook until the sausage is slightly browned, about 2-3 minutes.
6. Add in the diced tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato paste, and bay leaves. Stir until the tomato sauce has broken down into the sauce. Raise the heat to medium-high, and bring to a boil.
7. Once boiling, reduce the heat back to medium and let simmer, uncovered, until the sauce has thickened and reduced by about half, about 10 minutes.
8. Add in the shrimp, cover the pan, and cook until the shrimp is opaque, about 2-3 minutes.
9. Squeeze out as much moisture from the zucchini noodles as you can, and then pat dry on a paper towel.
10. Divide the zucchini noodles between two bowls, then divide the stew on top of them. Garnish with fresh parsley, and devour.

name: Wild and Brown Rice Salad
description: Brown rice wins big in the great battle for health in the modern world. In a pick-up lunch game, it should never be picked last! But the salad game is a team effort. Peppers, celery, seeds, and oils add flavor to this easy-to-create dish. This salad can be served warm or cold, creating plenty of convenient options to satisfy your taste buds.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1½ tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tsp', 'wild rice, cooked - 1½ cup', 'cooked brown rice - 3 cup', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 1 whole', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - ½ cup', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'sunflower seeds - 2 tbsp', 'almonds, slivered - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine olive oil, balsamic vinegar, lemon juice, and mustard together in a small bowl to form dressing.
2. Place rice, vegetables, seeds, and nuts together in a bowl; stir until mixed.
3. Drizzle with dressing, toss to coat, and then serve immediately.

name: Kale And Peppers
description: If you're looking for a nutrient-packed side dish to accompany your main protein source, this recipe fits the bill perfectly. You'll get a solid dose of vitamin C from the peppers, along with all of kale's own considerable nutrient power. Add in some garlic and ginger and you'll also get immune-boosting and heart-protecting benefits with your meal.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - ½ tbsp', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'diced yellow bell pepper - 1 whole', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'kale, diced - 5 cup', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'low-sodium chicken broth - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add olive oil and garlic.
2. Sauté peppers and onions for 2-3 minutes. Add in kale, ginger, and chicken broth.
3. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes or until kale is tender and chicken broth has evaporated. Serve immediately.

name: Ranch-Style Hummus
description: Add some parsley, dill, and garlic salt to chickpeas and you have yourself an American taste twist. This recipe has almost no fat and fewer calories than the others recipes, so you can even enjoy it if you're on a diet.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'plain Greek yogurt - ⅓ cup', 'parsley, dried - 1 tsp', 'garlic salt - ½ tsp', 'dried dill - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients.
2. Serve with vegetables, pita chips, or snack of your choice.

name: Guacamole Hummus
description: Guacamole is tasty, and so is hummus. Combine the two and you have an epic flavor party! Pair this awesome dip with gluten-free black bean chips and salsa, and you could open up your own restaurant.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'avocado - 1', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1 whole', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 1']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients.
2. Serve with vegetables, pita chips, or snack of your choice.

name: Natalie Hodson's Frozen Spinach Cups
description: Boost the nutrient profile of your favorite protein shake with a LiveFit-approved protein spinach cup. Delicious and nutritious!
recipeIngredient: ['spinach - 1 cup', 'water - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Fill blender or food processer 2/3 full with spinach leaves.
2. Add approximately 1/2 cup of water for every 2 cups of spinach.
3. Blend until spinach is finely-blended with water. Continue adding spinach and water until bag is empty.
4. Once spinach is finely blended, pour liquid into muffin tin.
5. Fill cups 3/4 full and place tin in freezer.
6. Freeze for 3 hours.
7. Take tin out of the freezer, pop cups out, and place 4-5 in a Ziploc bag to keep in freezer.
8. Use 1-2 per protein shake.

name: Natalie Hodson's Easy Salsa Chicken
description: This easy chicken recipe is delicious, simple and versatile. It doesn't get any better!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 5 lb', 'salsa - 16 oz', 'diced tomatoes - 28 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put all ingredients in a Crock-pot.
2. Cook on high for 3-4 hours, or low for 6-7 hours.
3. Enjoy!

name: Crispy Chicken With Sweet Mustard Dip
description: If you're missing the crispy goodness of fried chicken, this recipe will fill the void. A typical serving of fried chicken has about 325 calories. This recipe has only half the calories—with just as much crunch and flavor! I listed the spices I like to use, but you could easily omit some or add your own to personalize the flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['rice cereal - 1½ cup', 'onion, finely diced - ½ cup', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - ½ tsp', 'egg whites - 2', 'water - 1 tbsp', 'chicken breast - 20 oz', 'olive oil - 1 spray', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Place cereal in a bag. Use a rolling pin or can to crush into small pieces. Be careful not to turn it into a powder.
3. Place crushed cereal in a large bowl and add onion, salt, and pepper. Mix well.
4. In a separate bowl, mix the egg whites and water, and stir well.
5. Pat the chicken dry with a paper towel.
6. Dip a piece of chicken into the egg whites and allow the excess to run off.
7. Dip chicken in the cereal mixture. Press down to help it stick. Coat thoroughly.
8. Place chicken on a baking sheet and lightly spray each piece with olive oil spray.
9. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 min. Flip the chicken and spray lightly. Bake another 8-10 min.
10. As chicken bakes, mix together Greek yogurt, mustard, and sweetener to make dipping sauce.

name: Coconut Shrimp With Sweet And Spicy Dipping Sauce
description: This recipe was a serious hit with my taste tester. With under a third of the calories found in your standard restaurant version and none of the gluten, this recipe is perfect for any fit kitchen. Because the recipe is super simple, it's doable for even the most novice cook. It's great for an appetizer, party snack, or main dish!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 3', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 6 tbsp', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 24 shrimp', 'corn starch - 3 tbsp', 'marmalade, reduced sugar - 4 tbsp', 'red chili sauce - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Whip egg whites until stiff peaks form.
3. In a separate bowl, add Stevia to unsweetened coconut flakes and mix well.
4. One at a time, coat shrimp in cornstarch, then coat in whipped egg whites. The more volume the better.
5. Coat the shrimp in coconut flakes, and place on parchment paper or a silicone baking sheet.
6. Bake at 375 degrees for 10-15 minutes, turning over after about 7 minutes. Because there is no flour on the shrimp, they will not turn golden brown like a typical breaded shrimp. When they are done, the coconut will be toasted and the tail will be pink. The egg white, if exposed, will still be white.
7. While the shrimp are in the oven, mix marmalade with Sriracha. More chili sauce will give it more heat. Add a little water to thin out the dipping sauce. The entire amount of dipping sauce is only 40 calories, so dip to your heart's content!

name: Pulled Chicken
description: This recipe has a Tex-Mex-inspired flavor. Once the chicken is prepared, you can use it in tacos, serve it over rice, or even try it in burritos. This is by far one of the easiest things in the world to cook; you can use your rice cooker or crock pot to make it. It only has a handful of ingredients and is a healthy and delicious way to eat chicken.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 piece', 'onion, finely chopped - 1', 'cilantro - 1 cup', 'salsa - 1½ cup', 'peppers, hot chili, red - ¼ cup, chopped or diced']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put all ingredients in the slow cooker, and mix by folding them over a few times.
2. Set the cooker for 4 hours or more. From my experience, you can't really overcook this recipe. I've set it for 6 hours and it turned out the same. I've even put in frozen chicken and cooked for 7 hours. It still turned out great.
3. When it's finished, stir the contents. The chicken should fall apart without much effort on your part. This is a sign it is done.
4. Serve how you like! My personal favorite is on black rice with a little avocado and lime juice.

name: Peanut Butter Hummus
description: Now, we know what you're thinking: Peanut butter hummus? Gross. It may seem strange, but it's actually a tasty treat! Give it a try and you'll be surprised.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'peanut butter - ⅓ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients.
2. Serve with vegetables, pita chips, or snack of your choice.

name: Millet-Cranberry Stuffing
description: Stuffing has been sadly typecast as a winter holiday side dish. Erroneous! Full of fiber and flavor, this recipe will draw few complaints on your table. You're sure to see those Christmas-morning smiles—in July. Any time your diet needs a complex carb boost, mix this up!
recipeIngredient: ['millet - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'stalk celery, finely diced - ½ cup', 'onion, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'sage - 1 tbsp', 'low-sodium chicken stock - ½ cup', 'dried cranberries - ½ cup', 'pecans - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook the millet according to package directions.
2. Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
3. Once bubbling, add in the celery, onions, carrots, and minced garlic.
4. Continue to cook until tender, about 3-5 minutes.
5. From there, add mushrooms and cook for another 4-5 minutes.
6. Add in the chicken stock and bring to a boil.
7. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
8. Next, add in the cranberries, pecans, and millet, heating over medium heat for 1-2 minutes to allow flavors to blend.

name: Natalie Hodson's Lime And Curry Tilapia
description: This tilapia recipe is quick and easy, but also bold and flavorful. You can even try it with chicken or other fish!
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 4 fillet', 'lime juice - 4 tbsp', 'oregano - 2 tsp, ground', 'chili powder - 2 tsp', 'black pepper - 2 tsp, ground', 'garlic powder - 2 tsp', 'curry powder - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Sprinkle tilapia filets with 1 tsp of each spice.
2. Pour lime juice in the bottom of a large skillet.
3. Put filets in skillet and cook on medium heat for 2-3 minutes.
4. Flip filets and add the remaining 1 tsp of each spice.
5. Cook for another 2-3 minutes or until fish easily flakes.

name: Traditional Hummus
description: You can't go wrong with this traditional hummus recipe. With simple ingredients that produce a fresh, light flavor, this recipe is sure to be a crowd favorite.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, canned - 1 can drained', 'tahini paste - 5⅓ tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend ingredients.
2. Serve with vegetables, pita chips, or snack of your choice.

name: Natalie Hodson's Blueberry Protein Pancakes
description: Get your egg whites in a new way! Natalie's pancake recipe is healthy, delicious and super simple.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - ½ cup', 'salt - 1 dash', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Put egg whites, oats, baking powder, almond milk (I like Almond Breeze vanilla), salt and Stevia in the blender.
2. Blend for 30 seconds on med-high speed.
3. Spray a pan with non-stick cooking spray, pour batter on pan and add half the blueberries.
4. Cook like a regular pancake.
5. For topping, add applesauce and cinnamon.
6. Recipe makes 2 pancakes.

name: Chicken Strawberry Salad With Cacao Nib Dressing
description: Meaty chicken, sweet strawberries, velvety goat cheese—teamed up with the bitter crunch of cacao nibs to deliver a festival of flavors and textures. Gently poaching the chicken in water keeps the meat deliciously moist.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 12 oz', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'salad greens - 4 1 cup', 'strawberries - 1½ cup', 'cherry tomatoes - 1½ cup', 'yellow pepper, cut into strips - 1 whole', 'green onion, chopped - 2 whole', 'goat cheese - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2½ tbsp', 'red wine vinegar - 1½ tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - ⅛ tsp, ground', 'salt - ⅛ tsp', 'cacao nibs - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place chicken and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large saucepan. Add enough water to completely cover chicken by at least 1 inch.
2. Bring water to a very slight simmer with just a few bubbles breaking the surface. Cook the chicken, partially covered, for 20 minutes, or until meat is cooked through and an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast registers 165 degrees F. Adjust heat as necessary during cooking to maintain the slight simmer.
3. As the chicken cooks, skim off any foam that forms on the surface of the water.
4. Remove chicken from pan when cool enough to handle. Slice the meat and set aside.
5. Divide salad greens, chicken, strawberries, tomatoes, bell pepper, green onion and goat cheese among serving plates.
6. For dressing: In a bowl, whisk together olive oil, vinegar, garlic, black pepper, and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Stir in cacao nibs. Drizzle dressing over salad.

name: Muscle-Gaining Shake
description: When you need to gain a pound in a pinch, look no further than this fruity combination of calories. This creamy and sweet concoction will satisfy any sweet tooth and deliver everything you need on your quest to keep the scale moving up.
recipeIngredient: ['milk, fat-free - 16 fl oz', 'heavy whipping cream - 4 oz', 'banana or vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'banana - 1 cup, mashed', 'strawberries - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in the order listed into a blender. Blend on high until desired consistency is achieved.
2. Pour into glass and drink it down!

name: Mason Jar Spinach and Feta Salad
description: Salads can be tough to transport in traditional containers because greens get soggy when pre-mixed with dressings. But by layering salad ingredients in a Mason jar, you can keep your greens separate from the dressing to preserve their crispness for lunchtime.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1 tsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1½ tbsp', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'green onion, chopped - ⅛ whole', 'Carrots, raw - 2 slice', 'avocado - ¼ cup, pureed', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1¼ cup', 'spinach - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Layer all ingredients in a 16-ounce Mason jar in the order listed above, so the dressing is on the bottom, and the spinach is on the top. Secure the Mason jar with a lid.
2. Refrigerate your salad or carry it with you in a cooler. When you're ready to eat it, shake it up to mix the ingredients and enjoy directly from the jar.

name: Cocoa Bean Veggie Tacos
description: With the stealth addition of cocoa and chipotle chili, this bean filling is so rich and smoky tasting that you won't miss the meat on taco night.
recipeIngredient: ['canola oil - 2 tsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 2 cup', 'tomato, finely diced - 2 whole', 'plantain - 1 whole', 'chipotle chili peppers in adobo sauce - 2 tsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'cumin - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'cilantro - ⅓ cup', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1½ cup', 'lime zest - 1 tsp', 'corn tortilla - 8']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion and salt and cook 5 minutes. Place bell pepper in pan and cook 2 minutes more.
2. Add black beans, tomatoes, plantain, chipotle pepper, cocoa powder, cumin, and black pepper to the skillet and cook 2 minutes. Stir in cilantro and lime juice and remove from heat.
3. Stir together yogurt and lime zest.
4. To serve, top tortillas with bean mixture and dollops of yogurt.

name: Sweet Potato, Beef, and Roasted Veggie Hash
description: Roasted vegetables and sweet potatoes are delicious and easy to make, adding a host of vitamins and minerals to your daily diet. Anytime you cook these items, make extras to use as snacks or as sides to protein-based meals. Make a little extra ground beef, too, for quick meals.
recipeIngredient: ['head cauliflower, chopped - 1 whole', 'broccoli - 1 cup', 'brussels sprouts - 3 cup', 'okra - 1 pods (3" long)', 'sweet potato - 3 whole', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'sweet potato - 1 whole', 'lean ground beef - 8 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'red onion, diced - ¼ whole', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground beef and diced red onion, cooking thoroughly. Season to taste and remove from heat.
2. Cut sweet potatoes in half and place one potato in each meal prep container. Use a fork to mash the flesh.
3. Add roasted veggies and ground beef to each container and mix with sweet potato.
4. Refrigerate container or keep in cooler until you're ready to eat. Heat in a microwave for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
5. Leftover roasted veggies can be packed separately as snacks or combined with extra ground beef or other protein to create new meals.
6. Hash Directions:

Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground beef and diced red onion, cooking thoroughly. Season to taste and remove from heat.
7. Cut sweet potatoes in half and place one potato in each meal prep container. Use a fork to mash the flesh.
8. Refrigerate container or keep in cooler until you're ready to eat. Heat in a microwave for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
9. Leftover roasted veggies can be packed separately as snacks or combined with extra ground beef or other protein to create new meals.

name: Ready-On-The-Spot Oatmeal
description: When you know you need to eat but just don't have an appetite, the last thing you feel like doing is cooking a full meal. So why not rummage through the fridge and pantry for a combination of staples you probably have on hand, then measure, mix, and enjoy?
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1 cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'BPI Sports Whey-HD, chocolate cookie - 1 scoop', 'banana - 1 cup, mashed', 'natural crunchy peanut butter - 4 tbsp', 'ground flaxseed - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine oats, Greek yogurt, and whey protein in a large bowl. Mix until incorporated. Add a drizzle of water if necessary to help moisturize all the powder.
2. Slice large banana into quarter-sized pieces.
3. Add banana and peanut butter to the oat mixture and mix.
4. Garnish with flax seeds and eat the whole darn thing!

name: Chocolate Oatmeal With Cherry Sauce
description: Chocolate infused oatmeal. Can there be any better way to start the day? Soak the oats overnight to cut down on their cooking time. You can also prepare the cherry sauce in advance and heat it up again at breakfast. If you want to bump up the protein numbers, stir some protein powder into the oats as you heat them up on the stovetop.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - 1¼ cup', 'cherries, frozen - 2 cup', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - ½ lemon yields', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'dark chocolate - 2 square', 'walnuts, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place oats and a pinch of salt in a medium saucepan. Add 3-1/2 cups water, bring to a simmer, immediately turn off heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
2. To make the cherry sauce, bring cherries, honey or maple syrup, lemon juice, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, vanilla, and a pinch of salt to a boil in a small saucepan. Reduce heat to low and simmer until cherries have softened and mixture is slightly thick, about 5 minutes.
3. In the morning, add milk and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to oats and heat over medium-low until oats are tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in chocolate until melted.
4. Place chocolate oats in serving bowls and top with cherry sauce and walnuts.

name: Banana Chocolate Chip Overnight Oats
description: Overnight oats are an easy way to prep your breakfast for a week while ensuring a good dose of fiber, protein, and whole grains. You can easily adjust the additional ingredients for a variety of flavors, like replacing the chocolate chips with a tablespoon of peanut butter per jar, or switching out the banana slices for your favorite fresh berry.
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ½ cup', 'milk, fat-free - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla, nonfat greek yogurt - ⅓ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'black chia seeds - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Layer all ingredients (base and additional) in a Mason jar with a screw-on lid. After fastening the lid, shake the jar to mix.
2. Place jar(s) in refrigerator and allow to sit overnight.
3. Enjoy cold in the morning.

name: Ground Beef Fajita Bowl
description: Fajita bowls are nice because you can switch out the protein source based on what you have on hand. If you have extra chicken, use that instead of ground beef. Add or remove ingredients based on your personal preferences. If you don't like rice, try quinoa. Or if you want more fiber, add black beans.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'wild rice, cooked - 1 cup', 'diced red bell pepper - ¼ whole', 'diced yellow bell pepper - ¼ whole', 'red onion, diced - ⅛ whole', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 1 cup', 'lean ground beef - 1 oz', 'salt to taste - 1 ', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 oz', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'avocado - 1 cup, pureed', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 1 cup', 'salsa - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil over skillet set on medium-high. Add sliced peppers and onion to skillet, season to taste, stirring often. Remove from pan and set aside when cooked through.
2. Put ground beef and additional red onion in the skillet and cook until meat is browned. Season to taste.
3. When the meat is cooked, distribute all of the ingredients among sealable containers and top with tomatoes and any desired optional ingredients.
4. Keep containers cold until it's time to eat, then heat in microwave for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes before serving.

name: Homemade Double-Stuffed Cheesy Burrito
description: Chipotle will want your recipe after you show off this easy-to-make, double-stuffed, cheesy burrito to your friends on social media. The secret is in the cheese, so don't skimp in that department!
recipeIngredient: ['diced red bell pepper - ½ whole', 'white onion - ¼ sliced', 'whole wheat soft tortillas - 2 whole', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'avocado - ½ cup, pureed', 'chicken breast - 5 oz', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray large sauce pan with non-fat cooking spray. Add diced peppers and onions and cook over medium heat for about 6 minutes, until peppers are soft and onions translucent.
2. Coat a second saucepan with non-fat cooking spray. Turn heat to medium and add one tortilla to the pan. Sprinkle the shredded cheese evenly over the tortilla.
3. Place the second tortilla over the cheese and cook until cheese begins to melt. Flip and cook until the second tortilla browns.
4. Peel and pit avocado. Mash with a fork.
5. Place the cheese-filled tortillas on a plate and spread mashed avocado on top.
6. Top avocado mash with vegetables, chicken, and beans.
7. Roll tortillas into a burrito, top with any optional ingredients, and enjoy!

name: Peanut Butter Protein Energy Balls
description: This recipe is from Nikki Metzger, a Nike Master Trainer and the owner of BODI. These energy balls make a delicious midday energy boost or post-workout snack. Whip up a batch and pack a few in your cooler each day for those moments when your stomach starts to moan and groan.
recipeIngredient: ['paleopro protein - 1 scoop', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'cacao chocolate chips - ½ cup', 'ground flaxseed - ½ cup', 'natural crunchy peanut butter - ½ cup', 'honey - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all the ingredients together.
2. Roll into small balls, about 1 tablespoon in size.
3. Place in the freezer for an hour to harden up. Transfer to the fridge or your cooler.

name: Egg and Veggie Muffins
description: These egg-and-veggie muffins are a high-protein, easily-transportable food that doubles as breakfast with a side of fruit and coffee, or as a grab-and-go snack between meals. If you use a standard muffin tin, you can make at least 12 muffins at a time, each of them a little bit different to keep your meals interesting.
recipeIngredient: ['diced red bell pepper - ½ whole', 'red onion, diced - ¼ whole', 'green pepper, chopped - ½ whole', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'bacon strips - 1 slice', 'turkey sausage - ⅛ serving', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 1 tbsp', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1⅛ cup', 'mushroom - 1 whole', 'spinach - ⅛ cup', 'chopped ham - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add onions and peppers and sauté them until cooked through and set aside. If you plan on adding meat to your muffins, you can cook it in the same unwashed skillet.
3. In a medium-sized bowl, whisk eggs together, adding salt and pepper to taste. When veggies are cooked through, add them to the eggs and mix well.
4. Grease a standard muffin tin with cooking spray, then spoon egg mixture into the tin, distributing equally. Add a tablespoon of optional ingredients to each individual muffin or row of muffins, as desired. For example, add bacon and cheddar cheese to some; feta, spinach, and mushrooms to others.
5. Cook for approximately 15-20 minutes, until the center of each muffin is cooked through. Allow to cool before removing from tin.

name: Homemade Hawaiian Pizza
description: Although Hawaii may not be your top destination in the middle of bulking season, it certainly will be when shredding season rolls around! But when that time is many months away, why not enjoy a taste of paradise while simultaneously eating for your muscle-growth goals?
recipeIngredient: ['tomato sauce, canned - 6 oz', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'mozzarella cheese - 2 cup', 'Canadian bacon - 1⅓ slices (6 per 6-oz pkg.)', 'pineapple, raw - 1 cup', 'chicken breast - 6 oz', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'Pillsbury pre-made thin pizza crust - 1 serving']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven per pizza crust package instructions.
2. Place pizza crust on lightly oiled cookie sheet
3. Spread olive oil evenly across crust.
4. Spread tomato sauce on top of olive oil.
5. Cover the crust with a thin layer of cheese.
6. Place Canadian bacon, pineapple, and chicken evenly across crust.
7. Top with spinach and remaining cheese.
8. Season as desired with garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.

name: Peanut Butter Protein Muffins
description: Beyond infusing these guilt-free muffins with protein, cottage cheese makes them extra moist without the need for extra oil. The peanut butter powder and dried cherries make the muffins taste like everyone's favorite schoolyard sandwich.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cottage cheese - 1 cup', 'milk (2% fat) - ½ cup', 'egg - 2 whole', 'coconut oil - ¼ cup', 'oat flour - 1 cup', 'powdered peanut butter - ½ tbsp', 'sugar - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'dried cherries - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Grease muffin tin or use paper liners.
3. Combine cottage cheese, milk, eggs, flour, peanut butter powder, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, and baking soda in a blender until well combined. After blending, stir in cherries.
4. Divide cottage cheese mixture among 12 muffin cups.
5. Bake muffins for 20 minutes or until set.
6. Let cool for a few minutes before serving.

name: Fruit Salad Cottage Cheese Breakfast Tacos
description: Slathered with zesty cottage cheese and piled high with fruit salad, these sweet tacos will have you jumping out of bed in the morning. Add a sprinkling of granola for some crunch. These tacos can also serve as a healthy dessert or even a post-workout treat. The cottage cheese mixture and fruit salad can be made a few days in advance and chilled.
recipeIngredient: ['fat-free cottage cheese - 1¼ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'orange zest - 2 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'blueberries - 1 cup', 'strawberries - 1 cup', 'kiwi - 2 whole', 'banana - 1 large (8" to 8-7/8" long)', 'whole wheat soft tortillas - 4 whole', 'granola - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, stir together cottage cheese, honey, orange zest, and vanilla.
2. In a separate bowl, toss together blueberries, strawberries, kiwis, and banana.
3. Spread portion of cottage cheese mixture on a tortilla.
4. Top with fruit salad and granola.

name: Berry Lemon Zinger Smoothie
description: If you're looking to add some zing to your same-old vanilla shake, look no further than this berry lemon smoothie. Antioxidant-packed fresh or frozen berries are the staple of many a healthy smoothie recipe, and with the tasty tartness of the lemon zest, this is one smoothie guaranteed to delight your palette.
recipeIngredient: ['RSP Nutrition TrueFit Lean Protein (Vanilla) - 1 scoop', 'strawberries - ½ cup', 'raspberries - ½ cup', 'skim milk - 1 cup', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients, along with a handful of ice, in a blender and blend to a smooth consistency. If the smoothie is too thick, add liquid. You can also substitute the skim milk for water or whole milk, depending on your goals and taste preferences.

name: Peanut Butter and Jelly Smoothie
description: For a little nostalgia, here is a blender drink that tastes reminiscent of everyone's favorite school-yard sandwich. The cherries and strawberries add a healthy dose of antioxidants.
recipeIngredient: ['milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'quinoa flakes - ¼ 1 cup', 'peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'cherries, frozen - ½ 1 cup', 'strawberries, frozen - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender in the order listed and blend until smooth.
2.

name: Sweet Potato Pie Smoothie
description: In addition to being one of the best carb sources on its own, sweet potato combined with navy beans makes a drink that would make a dietitian's heart jump for joy! The added sweetness of the potato—plus the perfect balance of carbs, protein, and fat—makes this smoothie a great way to recharge after a spirited workout.
recipeIngredient: ['milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'sweet potato - 1 whole', 'navy beans, canned - ¼ 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'sugar-free maple syrup - 2 tsp', 'natural almond butter - 2 tsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'pumpkin pie spice - ½ tsp', 'banana - ½ cup, mashed']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender container and blend until smooth. If the mixture is too thick, blend in additional milk.
2.

name: Salmon Salad with Cottage Cheese Dressing
description: Crunchy veggies, buttery salmon, and a creamy cottage cheese dressing make for a crave-worthy salad. This salad packs enough protein to make it extra filling and leave your muscles fueled and ready to perform later in the day.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 2 fillet', 'salad greens - 4 1 cup', 'cherry tomatoes - 1 1 cup', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - 1 cup', 'Carrots, raw - 1 cup chopped', 'pineapple, raw - 1 cup', 'green onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'fat-free cottage cheese - ⅓ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'water - 1 fl oz', 'lemon juice - 1 tsp', 'dill - 3 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil or parchment paper. Spray or grease surface.
3. Place salmon fillets skin side down on the baking sheet and season with salt and pepper.
4. Bake salmon for 12 minutes or until just barely cooked through the center.
5. When the salmon is cool enough to handle, gently break apart flesh into 1-inch chunks.
6. Divide salad greens, tomatoes, cucumber, carrot, pineapple, and green onion between serving plates.
7. Top salads with salmon.
8. Prepare dressing by whisking together cottage cheese, olive oil, water, lemon juice, dill, garlic, and black pepper.
9. Distribute cottage cheese dressing over salad and salmon. Serve.

name: Dymatize Banana Peanut Butter Protein Pancakes
description: Recreate your childhood with this classic combination of banana and peanut butter.
recipeIngredient: ['Dymatize Elite XT (Banana Nut) - 2 scoop', 'Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ¼ cup', 'milk, fat-free - 6 fl oz', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat greased skillet to medium.
2. Measure flapjack mix and protein powder into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
3. Add milk and peanut butter powder and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
4. Using a 1/4-cup measuring cup, pour pancake mixture onto skillet.
5. Cook until bubbles appear on pancakes.
6. Flip pancakes and cook 1-2 minutes or until done.
7. Serve immediately. Optional: Layer on banana slices and top with Dymatize Elite Peanut Butter protein bar chunks or You Fresh Naturals Sugar Cookie Muscle Butter.

name: Easy Thai Pumpkin Soup
description: Take a break from all the pumpkin spice with this surprisingly rich and savory soup. Use spicy curry powder instead of sweet to kick it up a notch!
recipeIngredient: ['coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 4 clove', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'pumpkin puree - 2¼ cup', 'vegetable broth - 2½ cup', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - 13½ oz', 'fresh basil leaves - 1', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Sauté the onions, garlic, and curry powder in the coconut oil over medium-high heat until the onions are translucent.
2. Whisk together the pumpkin puree, vegetable broth, coconut milk, and onion mixture in a large pot over medium heat.
3. Cook the soup, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly warmed. Season with salt and pepper.
4. When ready to serve, divide into bowls and garnish with sliced basil leaves.

name: PB Banana Split Smoothie
description: Craving peanut butter but can't seem to fit it in your macros? This shake is the solution! The natural sugars of the banana help balance out the powerful and low-fat peanut buttery taste of the PB2. Add your preferred milk or milk substitute, and you have a yummy peanut butter treat to fit any healthy diet plan!
recipeIngredient: ['RSP Nutrition TrueFit Lean Protein (Chocolate) - 1 scoop', 'powdered peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'skim milk - 1 cup', 'banana - 1']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients, along with a handful of ice, in a blender and blend to a smooth consistency. If the smoothie is too thick, add liquid. You can also substitute the PB2 for real peanut butter and the skim milk for water or whole milk, depending on your goals and taste preferences.

name: Jamie's Thai Peanut Sauce
description: Jamie's Thai Peanut Sauce
recipeIngredient: ['light soy sauce - 8 tbsp', 'white vinegar - ½ cup', 'lime juice - 4 tbsp', 'jamie eason signature whey protein isolate - 2 scoop', 'garlic, chopped - 4 clove', 'ginger, minced - 2 tsp', 'onion powder - 2 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Whisk all of the ingredients together in a medium sized bowl.

name: Coffee Breakfast Smoothie
description: By now you know there are hundreds, if not thousands, of calories hiding in those delightful Frappuccinos. If you want a creamy coffeehouse treat without the supersized waistline, try this coffee-flavored breakfast smoothie. With energy-sustaining complex carbs from the oats, not to mention a couple shots of espresso, this is one coffee indulgence you can feel good about.
recipeIngredient: ['RSP Nutrition TrueFit Lean Protein (Vanilla) - 1 scoop', 'coffee - 6 oz', 'skim milk - ¼ cup', 'raw oats - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients, along with a handful of ice,  in a blender and blend to a smooth consistency. If the smoothie is too thick, add liquid. You can also substitute water or whole milk for the skim milk, depending on your goals and taste preferences.

name: Paleo Pumpkin Pie Muffins
description: These muffins have all the convenience of individually-sized treats yet still capture the flavor and texture of pumpkin pie. Although they are wonderful plain, add coconut whipped cream for the full pumpkin-pie experience.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin puree - 1 cup', 'egg - 4 whole', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - ½ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'honey - ⅓ cup', 'coconut flour - ¾ cup', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'nutmeg - 1 tsp', 'ground ginger - ½ tsp', 'ground cloves - ¼ tsp', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - 13½ oz', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Grease or line a 12 cup muffin tin.
2. Combine the pumpkin, eggs, coconut milk, vanilla, and honey in a large bowl and whisk until smooth.
3. In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients and mix well. Then, add the dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture and stir until fully combined and smooth.
4. Fill the muffin cups about 3/4 full with the mixture.
5. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until cooked through and lightly browned on top.
6. Let cool, then top with coconut whipped cream.
7. Note: Canned full-fat coconut milk separates. Blend the coconut cream and coconut water together to create a creamy consistency before using.
8. Topping Directions:  Chill the can of coconut milk in the fridge overnight. Remove the hardened coconut cream from the can and place in a bowl. Whisk coconut cream until it is light and fluffy. If using sweetener, whisk it in now. Serve immediately. (It can be stored in the fridge for several days, but will need to be whisked again before serving.)

name: Double Chocolate Smoothie
description: To boost the chocolatey goodness in your protein shake without boosting the sugar, try adding cocoa powder and avocado. The unsweetened cocoa powder is packed with flavonoids, which act as antioxidants in the body. The healthy fats of the avocado add richness and a creamy consistency without interfering with the chocolatey taste.
recipeIngredient: ['RSP Nutrition TrueFit Lean Protein (Chocolate) - 1 scoop', 'avocado - ½', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'coconut milk - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients, along with a handful of ice, in a blender and blend to a smooth consistency. If the smoothie is too thick, add liquid. You can also substitute water or another milk for the coconut milk, depending on your goals and taste preferences.

name: Paleo Pumpkin Pancakes
description: Adding pumpkin to your pancakes is a great way to spice up your breakfast. Since they already have maple syrup in them, they taste delicious even without additional toppings. Prep them ahead of time for an easy breakfast you can grab on your way out the door.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin puree - 1 cup', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - ⅔ cup', 'egg - 3 whole', 'maple syrup - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'coconut flour - 1 tbsp', 'arrowroot flour - ¼ cup', 'pumpkin pie spice - 2 tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'baking soda - 1 tsp', 'salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, whisk together the pumpkin puree, coconut milk, eggs, maple syrup, and vanilla.
2. In a separate bowl, combine the coconut flour, arrowroot flour, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt.
3. Blend the dry mixture into the wet mixture until fully combined. The batter with be thicker than regular pancake batter.
4. Heat a frying pan to med or med-low heat and grease well. Scoop about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake. Since the batter is thick, use the back of a spoon to spread it out and create a round shape.
5. Cook until each side is deep golden brown. These take longer to cook than regular pancakes, so I recommend using a large pan or a flat grill to cook multiple pancakes at once.
6. Note: Canned full-fat coconut milk separates. Blend the coconut cream and coconut water to create a creamy consistency before using.

name: Dymatize Peanut Butter Chocolate Protein Mug Cake
description: The sponginess of this mug cake is what I like best. The Death by Chocolate drizzle complements the mug cake's texture and enhances its flavor to make this an irresistible breakfast dish.
recipeIngredient: ['Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ¼ cup', 'Dymatize Elite Whey Protein (Chocolate Peanut Butter) - 1 scoop', 'milk, fat-free - 2½ fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Measure flapjack mix and whey into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
2. Add milk and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
3. Spray coffee mug with non-stick spray.
4. Pour batter into mugs.
5. Microwave mugs for 30 seconds at a time until cooked, approximately 1-1/2 minutes.
6. Serve immediately. Optional: Top with You Fresh Naturals Death by Chocolate Muscle Frosting or serve with 1/2 Dymatize Elite Protein Bar, Peanut Butter.

name: Dymatize Vanilla Cupcake Protein Pancakes
description: I created this particular flapjack stack as an homage to my love of donuts. By using the vanilla cupcake protein powder as the base and topping it off with the You Fresh Naturals Jelly Donut Muscle Butter, I satisfied my donut craving—and got a nice serving of protein at the same time.
recipeIngredient: ['Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ½ cup', 'Dymatize Elite XT (Rich Vanilla) - 2 scoop', 'milk, fat-free - 4 fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat greased skillet to medium.
2. Measure flapjack mix and protein powder into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
3. Add milk and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
4. Using a 1/4-cup measuring cup per pancake, pour batter onto skillet.
5. Cook until bubbles appear on pancakes.
6. Flip pancakes and cook 1-2 minutes or until done.
7. Serve immediately. Optional: Top it off with a jelly donut protein peanut butter and a cookie butter Oreo cookie.

name: Dymatize Pumpkin Protein Pancakes
description: Vanilla protein powder complements the pumpkin nicely, and the pumpkin spice birthday cake topping adds another awesome layer of flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ½ cup', 'pumpkin, canned - ½ cup', 'Dymatize Elite XT (Rich Vanilla) - 2 scoop', 'milk, fat-free - 4 fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat greased skillet to medium.
2. Measure flapjack mix and protein powder into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
3. Add milk and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
4. Using a 1/4-cup measuring cup, pour pancake mixture onto skillet.
5. Cook until bubbles appear on pancakes.
6. Flip pancakes and cook 1-2 minutes or until done.
7. Serve immediately. Optional: Top with You Fresh Naturals Pumpkin Spice Birthday Cake Muscle Butter or Oreo Cadbury Chocolate Egg.

name: Dymatize Pumpkin Spice Protein Waffles
description: Waffles need love, too, so what better way to show them love than applying my "stack 'em high" technique to them. Protein waffles are just too delicious to be left off my page.
recipeIngredient: ['Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ½ cup', 'pumpkin, canned - ½ cup', 'Dymatize Elite XT (Rich Vanilla) - 2 scoop', 'milk, fat-free - 6 fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn on waffle iron, prepare with spray-on oil.
2. Measure flapjack mix and whey into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
3. Add milk and pumpkin, and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
4. Pour batter onto waffle iron.
5. Cook until done.
6. Serve immediately. Optional: Top with You Fresh Naturals Pumpkin Spice Birthday Cake Muscle Butter or Keebler's Pumpkin Spice Cookie Chunks.

name: Ghoulish Dymatize Vanilla Cupcake With Ube Protein Pancakes
description: This pancake recipe, which uses sponge cakes made with purple yam, or "ube," is something I've always wanted to try. I'm happy with how it turned out, love the color, and can't wait to try it again.
recipeIngredient: ['Dymatize Elite XT (Rich Vanilla) - 1 scoop', 'Kodiak Cakes Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix - ½ cup', 'milk, fat-free - 4 fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat greased skillet to medium.
2. Measure flapjack mix and protein powder into bowl; mix together thoroughly.
3. Add milk and 39 g of crumbled ube mamon cakes (from Red Ribon Bakery) and mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
4. Using a 1/4-cup measuring cup, pour pancake mixture onto skillet.
5. Cook until bubbles appear on pancakes.
6. Flip pancakes and cook 1-2 minutes or until done.
7. Serve immediately. Optional: Top with ube mamon crumbles or You Fresh Naturals Jelly Donut Muscle Butter, Peanut Butter .

name: Jamie's Pumped-Up Pancakes
description: Jamie's Pumped-Up Pancakes
recipeIngredient: ['oat flour - 3 cup', 'jamie eason signature whey protein isolate - 3 scoop', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - 2 tsp', 'baking soda - ¾ tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 2½ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¾ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'egg whites - 4 large']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, mix oat flour, protein powder, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
2. In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix almond milk, yogurt, applesauce, vanilla extract, and eggs.
3. Add wet ingredients to the dry and stir until combined.
4. Use a 1/4-cup measuring scoop to measure out each pancake onto a preheated skillet.
5. Cook approximately 2 minutes on each side.

name: Jamie's Turkey Salad
description: Here's a delicious Turkey Salad recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 2 lb', 'dijon mustard - 8 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¾ cup', 'apple cider vinegar - 4 tbsp', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'green onion, chopped - 5 whole', 'celery, raw - 1 cup chopped']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add turkey breast to a medium-sized pot and bring to a rapid boil. Then, immediately reduce to low heat, cover with a lid, and let simmer for 30 minutes.
2. In the meantime, chop green onions and celery, place in a small bowl and set aside. In another small bowl add the Dijon mustard, Greek yogurt, apple cider vinegar, sweetener, and salt, mixing well until thoroughly combined.
3. Next, shred or chop the turkey into bite-sized pieces and place in a large bowl. Finally, add the chopped onions and celery as well as the wet ingredients and stir until well combined.
4. Refrigerate immediately. Salad keeps for about two weeks in the refrigerator and freezes well.

name: Chocolate Fudge Smoothie
description: Avocado gives this drink its fudgy consistency and plenty of extra nutritional firepower. The duo of protein powder and egg whites delivers a boatload of protein. This smoothie tastes so sinful you could mistake it for dessert.
recipeIngredient: ['milk (2% fat) - 1 cup', 'avocado - ½ cup, pureed', 'MusclePharm Combat Powder (Chocolate) - 1 scoop', 'liquid egg whites - ⅓ cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp', 'banana - 1 cup, sliced']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender container and blend until smooth. If the mixture is too thick, blend in additional milk.

name: Mike Hildebrandt's Protein Pancakes
description: Everybody loves pancakes! Trainer Mike Hildebrandt is no exception. Today, he shares his favorite recipe. It only takes a few minutes to make, so whip them up and dig in on today's bonus workout day!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ½ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - ¾ scoop', 'egg whites - ½ cup', 'almond milk - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
2. Heat a griddle to medium heat and cook pancakes until they are golden brown on the edges.
3. Add your favorite topping and serve.

name: Kris Gethin's DTP: Peanut Butter Figs Cookies Recipe
description: These DTP-approved cookies are packed with protein, complex carbs and muscle-making nutrients.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6 large', 'figs, raw - 4 small (1-1/2" dia)', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'peanut butter - 3 tbsp', 'oat flour - ⅛ cup', 'raw oats - ⅛ cup', 'quinoa flour - ⅛ cup', 'ground flaxseed - ⅛ cup', 'cashews, crushed - 1 cup', 'walnuts, chopped - 1 cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 5 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix the wet ingredients in a small bowl.
2. Mix all dry ingredients in a bigger bowl and mix in the wet ingredients. Mix well until the dough is smooth and sticky.
3. Spray an oven tray with non-fat cooking spray and pre-heat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (175 C).
4. Use a tablespoon and scoop out cookies on the tray. Flatten them to about 1/2-inch circles.
5. Cook in oven for 12-15 minutes. Check after 10 min since the temperature can vary from oven to oven. The cookie should be a little moist in middle.

name: FreakMode Recipes: Chicken Breast And Brown Rice
description: Everybody needs an easy chicken recipe for when you just don't know what to make. When I'm out of ideas, I always turn here.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'olive oil - 4 tbsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'brown rice - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix chicken, 2 tablespoons olive oil, Montreal spice, chili flakes, pepper, and oregano in a Ziploc bag.
2. Place bag in fridge and allow to marinate overnight.
3. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil a nonstick skillet.
4. Add chicken breast to the pan and cook for 4-5 min on each side, or until done.
5. Follow directions on rice package and enjoy with chicken.

name: FreakMode Recipes: Oatmeal And Berries
description: The oatmeal breakfast is an oldie but a goodie. This is my favorite way to enjoy some carbs in the morning!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1 cup', 'milk (2% fat) - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 pinch', 'almonds, slivered - 1 tbsp', 'strawberries - ⅓ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add milk to the oats and heat in microwave for 1-2 minutes.
2. Sprinkle cinnamon, almonds, and fruit on top and enjoy!

name: FreakMode Recipes: Steak And Sweet-Potato Fries
description: I bet this steak marinade will make you wonder why you'd ever go out for a steak again!
recipeIngredient: ['sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - 16 oz', 'rosemary - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, chopped - 1 clove', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'sweet potato - 2 whole', 'rosemary - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, chopped - 1 clove']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix rosemary, garlic, pepper, salt, and olive oil in a bowl.
2. Cover steak with mixture and allow to marinade while you prepare fries.
3. When fries are almost done, cook steak on grill or in pan until desired doneness. (About 3-4 minutes on each side.)
4. Directions for sweet-potato fries:
Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
5. Place potato wedges in a bowl, add the rest of ingredients, and mix thoroughly.
6. Lay wedges flat on a nonstick baking sheet and cook for 15 minutes.
7. Flip wedges and cook for another 15 minutes, or until they develop a slight golden color.

name: Kris Gethin's DTP: Tuna Potato Melt Recipe
description: Kris Gethin's DTP tuna melt is the perfect combination of protein, carbs and flavor. Need a dense, delicious meal? Look here.
recipeIngredient: ['albacore tuna - 8 oz', 'tomato sauce, canned - 2 oz', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ½ cup', 'Red Potatoes - 1½ cup, diced', 'red chili sauce - 1 tbsp', 'Italian seasoning to taste - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut the potato in slices to panfry in non-fat cooking spray for 10-20 sec.
2. Spray a deep oven dish with non-fat cooking spray. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200C).
3. Put some of the tomato paste in the bottom of the dish and then add a layer of potato, tuna, herbs, chili flakes and fat-free cheese.
4. Repeat one more time with tomato paste, potato, tuna and finish off with the fat-free cheese.
5. Cook in the oven for 25 min until a nice color develops.

name: Kris Gethin's DTP: Indian-Spiced Yogurt Rice
description: Get the carbs your hungry muscles crave with this delicious rice recipe. Replenish muscle glycogen and please your taste buds.
recipeIngredient: ['mustard - 1 tsp', 'curry powder - 1 tsp', 'brown rice - ¾ cup', 'plain Greek yogurt - 3 tbsp', 'red chili sauce - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat and mix the spices and seeds in a pan with non-fat cooking spray.
2. Mix the rice with yogurt in a bowl and add the heated spice mix.
3. Stir and serve.

name: FreakMode Recipes: Chicken Pear And Parmesan Spinach Salad
description: If you're watching your carbs, salads are usually a big part of your nutrition plan. But salads don't have to be boring or bland! Try this unique recipe and learn how to make your salad special.
recipeIngredient: ['pear, small - ½ small', 'almonds, slivered - 1 tbsp', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1½ tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'baby spinach - 4 cup', 'chicken breast - 2 piece', 'chili powder - ½ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In bottom of large salad bowl, add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
2. Mix well
3. Pile spinach on top and add pear slices and almonds.
4. Toss when ready to serve.

name: Jamie's Turkey Breakfast Sausage
description: Enjoy this tasty turkey sausage recipe.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 2 lb', 'ground ginger - ¾ tsp', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1½ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, mix all ingredients except for ground turkey.
2. Add spice mixture to the ground turkey in a large bowl and mix by hand until well incorporated.
3. Heat a skillet coated with nonstick spray over medium-high heat. Form meat mixture into 12 patties using a 1/4-cup measuring scoop and pan-fry on both sides until brown and center is no longer pink.

name: FreakMode Recipes: Parmesan-Crusted Chicken
description: This is one of my go-to chicken recipes. It's seriously simple, but tastes like it's gourmet. With recipes like this, it's super easy to stay on your FreakMode nutrition plan!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'ground almonds - 1 tbsp', 'chickpeas, canned - ¼ can drained', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'milk (2% fat) - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all of the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
2. In a separate bowl, sprinkle milk over both chicken breasts.
3. Dredge the chicken into the dry rub mix, coating well on both sides.
4. Over medium heat in a nonstick skillet, cook breasts for 7-9 minutes on each side.

name: Kris Gethin's DTP: Apple Cinnamon Roll Muffins Recipe
description: These delicious treats are nutrient-dense and packed with muscle-making power. They're easy to make and convenient to take.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6 large', 'apple, sliced - 1½ whole', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 2 tbsp', 'peanut butter - 3 tbsp', 'raw oats - ⅛ cup', 'oat flour - ⅛ cup', 'almond flour - ⅛ tbsp', 'coconut flour - ⅛ tbsp', 'quinoa flour - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 5 scoop', 'ground flaxseed - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (175 degrees C).
2. Mix all the wet ingredients in bowl.
3. Grind the apple to chunky apple sauce and mix with wet ingredients.
4. Mix all the dry ingredients in a bigger bowl. Mix well, then add the wet ingredients and stir everything to make the mix smooth. The mix should be very sticky and run slowly off a spoon.
5. Pour mix into muffin tray.
6. Bake for 8-10 min. The temperature and time can vary from oven to oven, so I recommend checking the muffins after 6-7 min to ensure you don't over bake them.

name: Jim Stoppani's Shortcut To Shred Recipes: Green Eggs And Chicken
description: Dr. Seuss was right: green eggs are delicious. They're especially great when they're full of spinach and broccoli and paired with lean chicken. Eat up!
recipeIngredient: ['eggs, scrambled - 3 whole', 'chicken breast - 6 oz', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Coat a skillet with olive oil and cook chicken.
2. When chicken is half-way done, add broccoli to skillet.
3. After chicken is thoroughly cooked, add eggs and then spinach.
4. Stir frequently until all ingredients are mixed thoroughly and eggs are cooked to desired doneness.
5. Add salt and pepper if desired, and enjoy!

name: FreakMode Recipes: Mediterranean Tomato and Egg Wrap
description: Wake up and fuel your body with the perfect high-protein meal!
recipeIngredient: ['cherry tomatoes - 1 1 cup', 'egg - 6 whole', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'whole wheat soft tortillas - 2 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all cherry tomatoes in a blender and pulse until smooth.
2. Add tomato purée to a nonstick skillet on medium heat with olive oil.
3. Add spices and cook until all water is evaporated (around 8 minutes).
4. In a bowl, beat eggs.
5. Add eggs to tomato mixture.
6. Cook for 6-8 minutes, or until eggs have separated from the side of the pan.

name: FreakMode Recipes: Parmesan-Crusted Tilapia Fillets
description: Tilapia is a great choice for protein, especially if you're getting a little tired of chicken. The crunchy texture of the crust pairs well with the light, delicate meat of the fish.
recipeIngredient: ['4 oz tilapia fillets - 2 whole', 'milk (2% fat) - ¼ cup', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'cornmeal, whole-grain, yellow - 1 cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'steak sauce, tomato based - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place fish on a plate and drizzle with milk.
2. In a separate bowl, mix parmesan, cornmeal, salt and pepper, and Montreal spice.
3. Dredge the fish in the dry rub. Coat both sides well.
4. Over medium heat, place olive oil in nonstick pan and cook fish for 5 minutes on each side, or until a golden crust forms and fish is cooked through.

name: DTP: Mass Mush
description: Fuel your gains with this great-tasting, easy-to-prepare, muscle-building meal. Hit your macros and make more mass!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6 large', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 to taste', 'cinnamon - 1 pinch', 'plain Greek yogurt - 1 tbsp', 'pineapple, raw - 1 cup', 'walnuts, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray a pot or frying pan. Cook the egg whites with the oats and add the stevia.
2. Stir until the egg is cooked through and mixed evenly with the oats.
3. Pour the mix in a bowl and add the pineapple, walnuts on top.
4. Sprinkle with cinnamon for extra spice!

name: Jim Stoppani's Shortcut To Shred Recipes: Turkey Swiss Melt
description: Yes, going low-carb can be difficult. But it definitely doesn't mean you have to give up any flavor. Try these delicious sandwich substitutes.
recipeIngredient: ['low-fat deli turkey - 4 oz (1 serving)', 'cheese, swiss, low fat - 2 slice (1 oz)', 'avocado - ½', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pour oil in frying pan and heat on medium-low heat.
2. While oil is heating, lay turkey slices on a flat surface.
3. Slice each slice of cheese into 4 strips.
4. Slice the half avocado into 4 long pieces.
5. Place one strip of cheese in the middle of each slice of turkey breast.
6. Place one piece of avocado on top of each strip of cheese.
7. Place a second strip of cheese on top of the avocado.
8. Roll the turkey into a tube.
9. Place turkey rolls in frying pan until brown and then flip over and brown other side. Cheese should be slightly melted and the avocado soft.
10. Take rolls out of pan, add salt and pepper to taste, and enjoy!

name: FreakMode Recipes: Veal Cutlets And Roasted Squash
description: Although chicken and turkey are staples in most fit diets, you don't have to make the same meat choices over and over. Veal is delicious, and squash is a nutrient-dense vegetable that belongs in anyone's healthy nutrition plan!
recipeIngredient: ['veal - 1 lb', 'oregano - 1 tsp, leaves', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'butternut squash, baked - 1 cup', 'thyme - 1 tsp, leaves', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - 1 cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
