description: Every ingredient in this recipe will help you build muscle. Have it for breakfast or dinner and get the macronutrients you need for optimum results.
recipeIngredient: ['eggs, scrambled - 3 whole', 'lean ground beef - 4 oz', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - ⅛ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'white onion - ½']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brown ground beef in skillet.
2. As beef browns, add chopped onion to the skillet.
3. Pour scrambled eggs into the skillet.
4. As eggs harden, add spinach and mix.
5. Once the eggs are firm and the spinach is wilted, add cheese and place the mixture on a plate.
6. Top with Greek yogurt.

name: Baked French Toast
description: This recipe is delicious, yes, but it's also packed with protein. This French toast will definitely fit your muscle-building bill. It's fast to prepare and makes the perfect way to start a not-so-lazy Sunday.
recipeIngredient: ['Ezekial bread - 6 slice', 'egg - 6 whole', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'milk (1%) - 1½ cup', 'sugar - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'maple syrup - 1 tsp', 'pecans - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Lay bread slices in a shallow baking dish. Make sure they do not over lap.
3. In a bowl, whisk together eggs, Greek yogurt, milk, sugar, and extracts until well combined.
4. Pour egg mixture over the bread slices, making sure they are fully coated.
5. Top bread with pecans and then cover baking dish with foil.
6. Bake for 25 minutes and then serve with sugar-free maple syrup.

name: Iced Gingerbread Protein Doughnuts
description: You now have no excuse to blow your diet on doughnuts! These protein donuts have a rich spiced-gingerbread flavor and that classic cake-doughnut texture (great for dunking in your coffee). These also have fantastic macros. And the glaze is just perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tsp', 'coconut flour - 3 Tbsp', 'baking powder - ½ tsp', 'baking soda - ¼ tbsp', 'salt to taste - 1 ', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'ground ginger - ⅛ tsp', 'ground cloves - ¼ cup', 'butternut squash, baked - ¾ cup', 'liquid egg whites - ¼ tbsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - 2 cup', 'blackstrap molasses - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla protein powder - ½ scoop', 'cashew milk - ¼ cup', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tsp', 'ground almonds - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Whisk together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl, then mix in wet ingredients.
2. Spoon batter into a sealable baggie and cut off one corner to make a piping bag. Use piping bag to squeeze batter into doughnut wells.
3. Bake for 8-12 minutes until firm.
4. While doughnuts cool, mix up your icing. Spread icing over cooled doughnuts and enjoy!

name: Steak And Eggs Breakfast
description: It's called the "breakfast of champions" for a reason. (If it's not called that, it should be.) Chomping some steak and eggs for your morning meal is a sure-fire way to increase your protein intake. The sweet potatoes will offer some complex carbs so you have the energy to start your day strong.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'sirloin steak, about 1 inch thick - 4 oz', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'egg - 2 whole', 'garlic, pureed - ⅛ tsp', 'green onion, sliced - 1 tbsp', 'sweet potato - 1 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat.
3. While oil is heating, gently tenderize the steak, adding salt and pepper to taste.
4. Place the steak in the skillet and cook for about 5 minutes before turning over.
5. Cook for another five minutes, or slightly longer depending your preference.
6. Transfer the steak to a plate and cover with foil to keep it warm.
7. Pour 1/2 tbsp. of olive oil to the same skillet and then add both eggs.
8. Add garlic and green onion and scramble for 3-4 minutes, or until eggs are cooked.
9. While eggs are cooking, place sweet potatoes in a bowl with a small amount of water and cover.
10. Microwave potatoes for 3 minutes.
11. When eggs are done, remove from pan and place on plate with the steak, and cover.
12. Finally, add the remaining 1/2 tbsp. of olive oil to the skillet and cook sweet potatoes until they're crispy.
13. Serve potatoes alongside steak and eggs.

name: Double Chocolate Chip Zucchini Muffins
description: Although double chocolate chip muffins might not seem like the smartest breakfast choice, these muffins have a secret healthy ingredient: zucchini! This low-carb veggie adds moisture, depth of flavor, and extra nutrients to these ridiculously decadent chocolate muffins.
recipeIngredient: ['Jamie Eason Signature Series Whey Protein Isolate - 80 g', 'powdered Stevia - ⅔ cup', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'lemon zest - 3 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'black chia seeds - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350° F.
2. Whisk together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
3. In a separate mixing bowl, beat together wet ingredients.
4. Mix dry and wet ingredients until just combined, then stir in black chia seeds or poppy seeds.
5. Line cups of a muffin pan with paper, silicone, or foil liners, and lightly spray insides with cooking spray. Alternately, you can skip the liners and lightly coat the inside of each cup with cooking spray.
6. Divide batter between cups, filling almost to the top.
7. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until an inserted toothpick or knife comes out clean.
8. Cool 10-15 minutes before attempting to remove liner. Enjoy with butter if desired.
9. Note on almond flour: If subbing all-purpose or gluten-free baking blend, add 2 tbsp oil.

name: Breakfast Thai Scramble
description: If you're bored with the regular scrambled eggs, it's time to shake things up with a little bit of Thai flavor. Scrambled eggs have a great ratio of protein and healthy fats and are very nutritious. Adding ginger and a little bit of chili powder may even boost energy expenditure in the short term and ease digestion.
recipeIngredient: ['grapeseed oil - ½ tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'scallions, sliced - 1 tbsp', 'egg - 3 whole', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'cilantro - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Coat a medium skillet with the grapeseed oil (any oil or cooking spray will work) and heat over medium-high heat. Add the ginger, garlic, and scallions. Sauté for 30 seconds, and then add the eggs.
2. Cook the eggs, stirring frequently with a spatula and removing the skillet from the heat as necessary to prevent sticking, until the eggs are cooked through. Season with salt, pepper, chili, and cilantro.

name: Jamie Eason's Turkey Breakfast Sausage
description: Meat patties can be a great addition to any morning meal. Learn how to make them from scratch with all the protein and much less fat!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 2 lb', 'ground ginger - ¾ tsp', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'sage - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, mix all ingredients except for ground turkey.
2. Place the ground turkey in a large bowl. Add spice mixture and mix by hand until well incorporated.
3. Heat a skillet coated with nonstick spray over medium-high heat. Form meat mixture into 12 patties using a 1/4-cup measuring scoop. Pan-fry on both sides until they're brown and center is no longer pink.
4. Tip: Cover with lid when browning for about 2-3 minutes on each side. Be careful not to overcook.

name: High Protein Waffles
description: If homemade waffles are your favorite go-to breakfast, you need a recipe that offers the protein content traditional waffles lack. Full of muscle-making protein, rich in complex carbohydrates, and complete with a touch of healthy fat, these waffles will satisfy your nutritional needs.
recipeIngredient: ['dry oatmeal - 1½ cup', 'coconut flour - 8 Tbsp', 'vanilla protein powder - ¼ scoop', 'sugar - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - 2 tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'eggs, beaten - 2 whole', 'unsweetened applesauce - ⅓ cup', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'skim milk - 1 cup', 'dried cranberries - ¼ cup', 'blueberries - ½ cup', 'maple syrup - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together oats, coconut flour, protein powder, sugar, baking powder, and cranberries in a large bowl.
2. In another bowl, whisk together the eggs, oil, cottage cheese, and milk until smooth.
3. Slowly combine dry ingredients with wet ingredients.
4. Pour the batter into a waffle maker according to maker directions and cook.
5. Once waffles are done, top with fresh blueberries and syrup.

name: Preworkout Meal
description: When looking for a boost in energy and focus, Alicia Ziegler often pairs a quick-digesting protein source with caffeine for her pre-workout meal. The caffeine helps her get energized for the workout ahead, while the protein sets her up for muscle growth and repair.
recipeIngredient: ['stemmed and torn mustard greens - 2 cup', 'almonds, chopped - ⅛ cup', 'avocado - ¼ fruit, without skin and seed', 'rosemary - ½ tsp', 'salt to taste - 1 ', 'organic mixed greens - 2 cup', 'goji berries - 1 cup', 'sprouted-grain tortilla - ½ whole', 'strawberries - ½ cup', 'olive oil - ¼ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'Dymatize M.P.ACT raspberry - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Cut the tortilla into triangles and spray both sides of the "chips" with the cooking spray.
3. Sprinkle with salt and rosemary, and place in the oven on a perforated pan. Bake for 8-10 minutes. Be sure to watch the chips closely so they don't burn.
4. Carefully remove the chips from oven and let cool.
5. To make the vinaigrette, place berries, olive oil, lemon juice, pre-workout, and honey in a blender. Blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
6. Toss the mixed greens with 2 tablespoons of pre-workout vinaigrette, and refrigerate the remainder of the dressing. Top with the remaining ingredients and dive in. Don't forget to add a lean protein!

name: Creamy Tuna, Cucumber Canapés, And Spicy Roasted Pepitas
description: Sick of smoothies? Stark swears by his creamy tuna with cucumber recipe as a perfect bedtime snack. This protein-packed bedtime snack will provide your muscles with the overnight growing power they need and your taste buds with the flavors they desire.
recipeIngredient: ['cucumber, thinly sliced - ½ whole', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'albacore tuna - 5 oz', 'raw pepitas - ¼ cup', 'sriracha - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Toss the pepitas with the olive oil and place in a pan on medium-high heat.
2. Toast until they start to pop, turning occasionally with a spatula.
3. When they are almost browned, add the hot sauce and coat each piece completely.
4. Cook for another 3 minutes, and cool on a paper towel.
5. Mix the drained tuna with the avocado until it all holds together easily.
6. Cut the cucumber into four 2-inch-thick pieces.
7. Scoop out the seeds to create a "bowl" for the tuna.
8. Fill the cucumber pieces with the tuna, avocado mixture.
9. Top with the pepitas and a dash of hot sauce. Devour.

name: Fluffy Aquafaba Protein Pancakes
description: You know that nutrition is an essential component of hitting your health and fitness goals, whether you want to add mass or torch fat. But putting that knowledge into practice isn't always easy. Keeping track of your protein, carb, and fat intake alone can be tough, but when new and conflicting diet information seems to pop up daily, figuring out how to eat for your goals can seem nearly impossible!
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - 1 cup', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'chickpeas, cooked - 1 cups', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients (except for the aquafaba) in a blender for 3-5 minutes until completely combined. Let sit for 10 minutes.
2. To make the aquafaba, whip the chickpea liquid with a hand or stand mixer on high until a thick "meringue" forms and can hold a peak without falling. Carefully fold the aquafaba into the pancake mix. Do not overmix!
3. Cook on a greased griddle or skillet with nonstick spray for approximately 1 minute on each side, or until golden brown.

name: Pumpkin Spice Protein Pancakes
description: This is no traditional stack of flap jacks. These pumpkin-spice-infused pancakes are a delicious addition to any breakfast and really capture the joy of the season. With a bright, vibrant color, these light, flavorful cakes make canned pumpkin a welcomed addition to any meal. Top with a bit of low-calorie or no-calorie syrup, and you’ll be packing in a guilt-free 4 grams of protein per serving!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 2½ scoop', 'raw oats - 1¼ cup', 'liquid egg whites - 4 tbsp', 'almond milk - 1½ cup', 'baking soda - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'nutmeg - ¼ tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'pumpkin puree - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all the dry ingredients.
2. Add all the wet ingredients.
3. Spray griddle with non-stick butter spray.
4. Scoop batter with a 1/4 cup measuring cup onto griddle. Cook 3-5 minutes on a side.

name: Turkey Lentil Stew
description: This stew makes use of ground turkey to add extra protein, giving you well-balanced nutrition that's perfect for any post-workout meal. You'll also get a hearty dose of antioxidants thanks to the addition of mustard greens.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - ¾ lb', 'white onion - 2 sliced', 'green pepper, chopped - 2 whole', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 6 cup', 'stemmed and torn mustard greens - 4 cup', 'sweet potatoes, peeled - 2 cup', 'dried lentils - 1 cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'Carrot - 2 diced']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large pot, combine the broth, mustard greens, sweet potatoes, lentils, salt, and pepper. Put on low heat.
2. Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Add half the garlic and ground turkey, cooking until no longer pink. Be careful not to burn the garlic. Remove from skillet and set aside.
4. Heat the second tablespoon of olive oil in the same skillet, again over medium heat.
5. Add to the pot containing the broth mixture.
6. Bring stew to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
7. Add the ground turkey and garlic to the pot, cover, and cook for another 10-15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or so.
8. Serve immediately.

name: Spicy Lentil Curry
description: If you love Indian food, you'll love this spicy lentil curry. It's relatively low in fat and provides a hearty dose of complex carbohydrates. Serve it alongside a chicken breast for added protein.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1½ tsp', 'garlic, chopped - 2 clove', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'curry paste - 3 tbsp', 'green pepper, chopped - 6 whole', 'carrot, shredded - 4 whole', 'sweet potatoes, peeled - 1 whole', 'dried lentils - 1 cup', 'lime juice - 1 tsp', 'low-sodium chicken stock - 4 cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.
2. Add garlic, onion, and curry paste. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.
3. Add the carrots, ginger, garlic, sweet potatoes, lentils, broth, salt, and pepper.
4. Bring mixture to a boil, then cover and let simmer for about 15 minutes or until lentils are fully cooked.
5. Squeeze lime juice into curry, stir, and serve topped with green onions.

name: Cucumber Lentil Salad
description: This cucumber lentil salad is a terrific lunch when you're on the go and don't have time to reheat a lunch in the office. Served cold, it's a delicious way to get your carbohydrates and protein in while giving you the energy you need to get through the rest of your day.
recipeIngredient: ['dried lentils - 1 cup', 'water - 1½ cup', 'garlic, chopped - 2 clove', 'bay leaf - 1 whole', 'mustard - ½ tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 3 tbsp', 'medium cucumber, cut into 1/2-inch pieces - 1 whole', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 1 whole', 'red pepper, thinly sliced - 1 whole', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a pot, combine the lentils, garlic, bay leaf, and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 15 minutes or until lentils are soft.
2. Drain the water and remove the bay leaf. Place in the fridge until cold.
3. Toss the refrigerated lentils with the celery, cucumber, and red pepper.
4. Mix together the olive oil and the balsamic vinegar.
5. Drizzle on top of lentil mix and toss.
6. Sprinkle with feta cheese and serve.

name: Protein-Packed Lentil Energy Bars
description: Craving a granola bar but don't want the processed carbs that comes with it? These lentil bars can be an excellent substitute. Rich in protein, healthy carbohydrates, and the right fats to fuel your day, they're an excellent option for those especially busy days when you need an energy boost.
recipeIngredient: ['dried lentils - ½ cup', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 2 scoop', 'peanut butter - ½ tablespoon', 'cranberries - ¼ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - 1¼ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Rinse lentils and place in a pot along with 1 cup of water.
2. Bring water to a boil and cover.
3. Simmer lentils for 20 minutes or until the lentils are soft and all the water is absorbed.
4. Mash cooked lentils with a fork.
5. Add the remaining ingredients to the mashed lentils.
6. Mix well and press into a baking pan lined with baking paper, then refrigerate for 2 hours.
7. Remove pan from refrigerator, slice mixture into bars, and serve.
8. To save bars for later, let cool completely then wrap individually in plastic wrap. Keep refrigerated.

name: Lemon Chia Seed Protein Muffins
description: These are a classic take on the lemon poppy seed muffins, but remixed with healthy chia seeds! Chia seeds are abundant in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. They're also high in fiber and protein to help suppress any grumbling stomachs. And as a final benefit, they draw in moisture and improve the texture of any baked goods you put them in. Many vegan bakers use them as a substitute for egg yolks, and no one is the wiser!
recipeIngredient: ['Jamie Eason Signature Series Whey Protein Isolate - 80 g', 'powdered Stevia - ⅔ cup', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'liquid egg whites - ½ cup', 'unsweetened applesauce - ½ cup', 'lemon zest - 3 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'black chia seeds - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350° F.
2. Whisk together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
3. In a separate mixing bowl, beat together wet ingredients.
4. Mix dry and wet ingredients until just combined, then stir in black chia seeds or poppy seeds.
5. Line cups of a muffin pan with paper, silicone, or foil liners, and lightly spray insides with cooking spray. Alternately, you can skip the liners and lightly coat the inside of each cup with cooking spray.
6. Divide batter between cups, filling almost to the top.
7. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until an inserted toothpick or knife comes out clean.
8. Cool 10-15 minutes before attempting to remove liner. Enjoy with butter if desired.
9. Note (on almond flour): If subbing all-purpose or gluten-free baking blend, add 2 tbsp oil.

name: Slow Cooker Lentil Soup
description: This recipe is perfect for those chilly winter nights when you want a hearty meal but don't want to spend hours cooking. Simply toss all the ingredients together in a slow cooker prior to leaving in the morning. It'll be ready when you arrive home.
recipeIngredient: ['dried lentils - 1 cup', 'chicken breast - 1 piece', 'diced tomatoes - 1 can', 'onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'carrot, shredded - 1 whole', 'zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'corn - ½ cup', 'onion powder - 1 tsp', 'oregano - 1 tsp, leaves', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 2 tsp', 'salt to taste - 1 ', 'low-sodium chicken stock - 7½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Spray a crockpot with non-stick cooking spray.
2. Add in all ingredients, except for the zucchini. Mix well.
3. Set crockpot to low and cook for 7 hours.
4. After 7 hours, add the zucchini and cook for 1 more hour.
5. Ladle into bowls and serve immediately.

name: Coconut Mango Smoothie
description: If you're looking for a great-tasting smoothie to start your day, look no further than this coconut-mango beverage.
recipeIngredient: ['frozen mango pieces - 1 cup', 'light coconut milk - 1 cup', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 2 tbsp', 'xanthan gum - ¼ tsp', 'ice - 4 cubes']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients in a blender and pulse blend until the smoothie has the texture you prefer.

name: Whipped Sweet Potatoes
description: This is a relatively simple recipe that works beautifully as a side dish to your main protein source. You could even use as a replacement for regular mashed potatoes at your next big holiday meal!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potatoes, peeled - 2 lb', 'coconut milk - ½ cup', 'brown sugar - 1 tbsp', 'butter - ½ tbsp', 'cinnamon -  to taste', 'salt to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.
2. Wrap the sweet potatoes in aluminum foil and bake for 30-45 minutes, or until soft.
3. While the potatoes are baking, combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat.
4. When the sweet potatoes are done, remove and place in a bowl. Slowly add the milk mixture, beating together until the mixture is well blended and the potatoes are fluffy. Serve immediately.
5. Note: You can skip the sugar and butter if you're trying to reduce your total calorie count.

name: Creamy Strawberry Ice Cream
description: Craving ice cream but don't want to derail your diet? With this recipe, you can indulge in a smooth, icy, sweet dessert without all the guilt. The dish has some calories, due to the full-fat coconut milk, but just watch your serving size and you'll be in good shape.
recipeIngredient: ['strawberries, frozen - 1 lb', 'full-fat coconut milk - 2 cup', 'powdered Stevia -  to taste', 'lemon juice - 1½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all of the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
2. Place contents in a container, cover, and place in the freezer for 30 minutes. Remove and stir.
3. Freeze for another 30 minutes, then remove and stir again. Repeat this process until the ice cream has the desired texture. Serve immediately.
4. Note: To up the protein content, feel free to mix in a whey protein, vegetable-based protein, or even egg whites.

name: Coconut Cashew Rice
description: Brown rice is a healthier carb source than its bleached cousin, but it can get very boring, very fast. With this coconut rice recipe, you'll start looking forward to this wholesome grain once again.
recipeIngredient: ['brown rice - 1½ cup', 'light coconut milk - 2 cup', 'water - 2 cup', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 3 tbsp', 'cashews, crushed - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large pot, combine the rice, coconut milk, water, salt, and 2 tablespoons of coconut flakes.
2. Bring to a boil, then turn down to low, cover, and let simmer for about an hour or until liquid has been is absorbed.
3. Once the rice is finished, fluff it with a fork, then stir in the cashews and the remaining coconut flakes. Serve immediately.

name: Coconut Chocolate Protein Pudding
description: If you're craving pudding but don't want to let your meal plan slip, whip up a healthier, lower-calorie version of this classic that's loaded with protein and fats. If you really want to make a gourmet dessert, consider adding the optional coconut whipped topping.
recipeIngredient: ['sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - 1 box', 'chocolate protein powder - 1 scoop', 'light coconut milk - 1 cup', 'milk (1%) - 1 cup', 'full-fat coconut milk - 1 can']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, beat together the pudding powder, chocolate protein powder, coconut milk, and cow's milk until it forms a pudding-like consistency.
2. Spoon into individual dishes and serve.
3. Note: Full-fat coconut milk is an optional topping. To make the coconut topping, begin the night before by placing the can of coconut milk upside down inside the fridge. The next day, open the can and drain off the liquid. Place the remaining cream in a bowl and beat until a fluffy whipped cream forms. Serve this on top of your pudding.

name: Coconut Cauliflower And Chicken Soup
description: Struggling to get your vegetables in? By preparing your vegetables as a soup, you'll hardly notice you're eating them! This recipe gives you a strong dose of antioxidants and dietary fiber from the vegetables, protein from chicken breast, and a small portion of fats from the coconut milk and olive oil.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'white onion - 1 sliced', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'Carrot - 2 diced', 'diced red bell pepper - 1 whole', 'head cauliflower, chopped - 1 whole', 'low-sodium vegetable broth - 4 cup', 'Chicken breast - 6 oz', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'coriander - ¼ tsp', 'cumin - 1¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil and one clove of garlic over medium heat. Add diced chicken and saute until no longer pink inside. Take care not to let the garlic burn. Set aside.
2. In a large saucepan, heat the remaining oil and garlic, then add in the onions, red pepper, and carrot. Cook for 2-3 minutes or until tender, transfer to a bowl, and set aside.
3. In the same saucepan, combine broth, cauliflower, coriander, and cumin. Add salt and pepper to taste, and let simmer for 10-15 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
4. Remove and let mixture cool for 5 minutes. In batches, puree the cauliflower mixture in a blender until smooth.
5. Return puree to pot and add the coconut milk, chicken, and vegetables.
6. Cook over low heat for 5-6 minutes to let the flavors blend, then serve.

name: Matcha and Avocado Oats
description: Matcha is a good source of caffeine and the compound L-theanine, both of which have been shown to improve attention and memory, and maybe dissolve your morning brain fog. Avocado is another nutritional overachiever, full of fiber, cholesterol-busting monounsaturated fat, and a range of vitamins and minerals, including potassium, vitamin K, and vitamin C.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - ¼ cup', 'water - ⅝ cup', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'milk (2% fat) - ½ cup', 'banana - 1 medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'matcha, powdered - 2 tsp', 'ginger, powdered - 1 tsp', 'avocado - ¼ fruit, without skin and seed', 'mango - ½ cup', 'cashews, chopped - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place steel-cut oats, a pinch of salt, and water in a medium saucepan.
2. Bring to a slight simmer, turn off the heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
3. To reheat leftovers, place cooked oatmeal in a saucepan, with a splash or two of water or milk, over medium-low heat until warm.
4. In the morning, heat prepared oats with milk, banana, matcha powder, and ginger.
5. Top bowls of oatmeal with avocado, mango, and cashews.

name: Ricotta And Raspberries Oatmeal
description: This dynamic duo supplies oatmeal with a creamy sweetness that's sure to release an early-morning dopamine surge. Ricotta cheese adds additional calcium and protein to your morning routine, and is one of the best dairy sources of whey protein, a nutrient that helps build muscle.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - ¼ cup', 'water - ⅝ cup', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'milk (2% fat) - ½ cup', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tbsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'honey - 2 tsp', 'ricotta cheese (skim-milk) - ¼ cup', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'raspberries - ½ cup', 'almonds, chopped - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place steel-cut oats, a pinch of salt, and water in a medium saucepan.
2. Bring to a slight simmer, turn off the heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
3. In the morning, heat prepared oats with milk, lemon zest, and cinnamon.
4. Mix ricotta with honey and vanilla extract.
5. Top bowls of oatmeal with ricotta mixture, fresh or frozen (thawed) raspberries, and almonds.

name: Carrot and Walnut Oats
description: Many people struggle to eat enough vegetables, so why not use oatmeal to sneak in a little more? Shredded carrot adds earthy sweetness and beta-carotene, which your body converts into immune-boosting vitamin A. A Journal of Nutrition study found that higher consumption of beta-carotene helps maintain healthy cholesterol levels.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - ¼ cup', 'water - ⅝ cup', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'milk (2% fat) - ½ cup', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'raisins - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'walnuts, chopped - 2 tbsp', 'dried unsweetened coconut flakes - 2 tbsp', 'maple syrup - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place steel-cut oats, a pinch of salt, and water in a medium saucepan.
2. Bring to a slight simmer, turn off the heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
3. In the morning, heat prepared oats with milk, carrot, raisins, vanilla extract, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
4. Top oatmeal with chopped walnuts and coconut flakes. Finish it off with a drizzle of pure maple syrup.

name: Egg And Baby Spinach Oats
description: Most people think of oatmeal as a sweet dish, but it can also become a savory porridge. So get cracking and top off your bowl with a poached egg! A recent study published in the American Journal of Clinical Nutrition found that people following a high-egg diet (an average of 2 eggs each day) had about the same blood cholesterol numbers as people on a low-egg diet (eating less than 2 eggs a week).
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - ¼ cup', 'water - ⅝ cup', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'low-sodium vegetable broth - ½ cup', 'baby spinach - 3 cup', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ⅓ cup', 'sun-dried tomatoes - ⅓ cup', 'thyme - 1 tsp, leaves', 'vinegar - ¼ tsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'pepper to taste - ', 'hot sauce - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place steel-cut oats, a pinch of salt, and water in a medium saucepan.
2. Bring to a slight simmer, turn off the heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
3. To reheat leftovers, place cooked oatmeal in a saucepan, with a splash or two of water or milk, over medium-low heat until warm.
4. In the morning, heat prepared oats with water or vegetable broth, spinach, Parmesan cheese, tomatoes, and thyme.
5. Place 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon vinegar in a small microwave safe bowl. To poach the egg, carefully crack it into water, cover with paper towel, and microwave on high for 1 minute, or until whites are set and opaque but yolk is still runny. If needed, continue microwaving in 10 second spurts.
6. Remove egg with slotted spoon and place on top of the bowl of oats.
7. Add hot sauce and fresh cracked black pepper.

name: Steel-Cut Oats Foundation Recipe
description: Skip the rolled oats or sugar-laden instant oats and buy the heartier, steel-cut version. For a fast getaway in the morning, use this overnight-soaking trick.
recipeIngredient: ['steel-cut oats - 1 cup', 'water - 2½ cup', 'salt - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place 1 cup steel-cut oats, a pinch of salt, and 2-1/2 cups water in a medium saucepan.
2. Bring to a slight simmer, turn off the heat, and let oats soak covered overnight.
3. This recipe makes enough oats for about 4 servings. To reheat leftovers, place cooked oatmeal in a saucepan, with a splash or two of water or milk, over medium-low heat until warm.

name: Blueberry Spinach Smoothie
description: Another creative way to get spinach into your day is to add it to your smoothie. With the combination of your favorite protein powder and fresh fruit, you'll hardly notice the spinach—except for the lovely green color it imparts. This smoothie provides a great mix of proteins, carbohydrates, and dietary fats, and makes an excellent, well-balanced addition to your daily diet plan.
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'frozen blueberries - 1 cup', 'frozen peaches - ½ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1 cup', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'natural almond butter - 1 tbsp', 'ice - 3 cubes']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients in a blender and pulse blend until desired consistency is reached.

name: Sweet Turkey Burger
description: If it's a sweet burger you crave, this turkey burger recipe is sure to fit the bill. Apples bring in a refreshing change of pace, while giving you an added dose of fiber your body is sure to love. The ground turkey supplies the protein, while the avocado on top provides plenty of healthy fats. Serve this any day of the week for a quick and delicious meal that's ready in under 20 minutes.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'red onion, diced - ½', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'gala apples, sliced - 2 whole', 'thyme - 1 tbsp, leaves', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'dijon mustard - 4 tbsp', 'avocado - ¼ cup, pureed', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'red pepper, thinly sliced - ½']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the ground turkey breast, red onion, oats, apples, thyme leaves, salt, and pepper. Once well mixed, form into four patties.
2. In another bowl, mix together the avocado, honey, Dijon mustard, and diced red pepper. Set aside.
3. Place the burgers on the grill and cook for about 5-6 minutes per side. You can also pan-fry these in a little olive oil if you prefer.
4. Once the burgers are golden, remove and serve with some of the Dijon mustard sauce on top.

name: Thai Chicken Burger
description: If you love the taste of Thai, this burger recipe will become a staple in your kitchen. Filled with lean ground chicken breast for protein and healthy fats from natural peanut butter, it's a great lower-carb option for those who still want to enjoy a juicy and flavorful burger.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken breast - 1 lb', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'egg - 1 whole', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'natural peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tsp', 'lime juice - ½ tbsp', 'water - 1½ fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, mix together the ginger, garlic, peanut butter, soy sauce, stevia, lime juice, and water. Divide into halves and set one half aside.
2. In another bowl, combine the ground chicken breast, onion, cilantro, oats, and egg. Stir in half the peanut sauce. Mix well and shape into four patties.
3. Place on grill and cook for about 5-6 minutes per side.
4. Serve with remaining sauce drizzled on top, along with your favorite side dish.

name: Vegetarian Hummus Wrap
description: Going meat free every now and then is a great way to lower your risk of heart disease, thanks to the lowered saturated fat content. With delicious meat-free recipes like this, you'll hardly know it's gone. These wraps make for a great afternoon snack any time hunger strikes. They're also the perfect finger food for a gathering.
recipeIngredient: ['whole wheat soft tortillas - 2', 'hummus - ½ cup', 'red pepper, thinly sliced - 1', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - ½', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'fat-free cream cheese - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Smear the cream cheese over the soft tortillas, then carefully spread the hummus on top of the cream cheese.
2. Top with the red pepper, cucumber, and baby spinach leaves.
3. Roll up and slice into bite-sized serving pieces.

name: Simple Ground Turkey Burger
description: If you want an unbelievably delicious yet simple burger that takes no time at all, this recipe is for you. Low in fat and carbs and packed with protein, this simple ground turkey burger is perfect for even the strictest of diet plans.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'plain instant oats - ¼ cup', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'low-sugar barbecue sauce - 2 tbsp', 'low-sugar ketchup - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'onion soup mix powder - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Combine all ingredients together in a bowl until well mixed.
2. Form four patties of even size and thickness, and place on a nonstick baking sheet.
3. Bake turkey burgers for 30-35 minutes or until completely cooked through.
4. Serve immediately wrapped in a lettuce leaf or on its own with your favorite side dish.

name: Tangy Chickpea Burger
description: Another great vegetarian option, this chickpea burger has it all. You'll get some complex carbohydrates from the chickpeas, coupled with protein and enough healthy fats from the added seeds to balance out your macros. These burgers can easily be eaten on their own for long-lasting energy or served with your favorite side dish for a complete meal.
recipeIngredient: ['chickpeas, cooked - 2 cups', 'wild rice, cooked - 1 cup', 'sunflower seeds - 3 tbsp', 'walnut, pieces - 2 tbsp', 'ground flaxseed - 2 tbsp', 'plain instant oats - 3 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'diced red bell pepper - ½', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1 whole', 'carrot, shredded - 1 whole', 'plain Greek yogurt - 3 tbsp', 'dijon mustard - 1 tbsp', 'low-sugar barbecue sauce - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by preheating your oven to 300 degrees F. Toast the sunflower seeds and walnuts for about 10 minutes.
2. Mash together the chickpeas and hot rice using a masher until a thick paste is formed.
3. Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
4. Form into four patties. Grill for about 4-5 minutes per side, or until slightly browned and firm.
5. Brush with a little extra barbecue sauce for added flavor partway through cooking. Serve immediately.

name: Sautéed Spinach
description: Sautéed spinach is fast and easy and goes well with just about any protein source.
recipeIngredient: ['baby spinach - 5 cup', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tbsp', 'sesame seeds - 2 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'lemon juice - ½ fl oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
2. Add the garlic and cook for about one minute, or until garlic is fragrant.
3. Add the baby spinach leaves and salt and pepper to taste. Stir, cover, and sauté over low heat for about 4 minutes.
4. Once the spinach looks soft, remove from heat and add the lemon juice and sesame seeds. Toss and serve.

name: Cheesy Spinach Omelet
description: A classic way to start your day, the egg omelet provides the perfect opportunity to get your leafy greens in early. Most people don't typically have vegetables with their breakfast meal, but this spinach-infused omelet is a fantastic way to start your day off right. Feel free to add other diced vegetables to the spinach. Just sauté them lightly in a little olive oil prior to adding them along with the spinach to the center of the omelet.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1 whole', 'liquid egg whites - 1 cup', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ⅛ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'paprika - 1 pinch', 'salsa - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Whisk together the egg, egg whites, and Parmesan cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste along with a pinch of paprika.
2. Spray a skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Pour egg mixture into skillet and cook for 1-2 minutes.
3. Add the spinach leaves and cheddar cheese to the center of the omelet. Using a spatula, fold the omelet in half.
4. Cook for another minute, then flip over. Cook on that side until eggs are fully done. Serve topped with salsa.

name: Shrimp Pesto
description: Shrimp is an excellent and often overlooked protein source. It's low in fat, rich in quality protein, provides a small dose of zinc, and helps regulate your testosterone levels. This pesto recipe is relatively easy to cook and contains a nice balance of the three main macronutrients.
recipeIngredient: ['baby spinach - 1 cup', 'fresh basil leaves - 1 cup', 'flat-leaf parsley - ¼ cup', 'tomato, finely diced - ½', 'cashews, chopped - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ⅛ cup', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'brown rice - 1 cup', 'asparagus spears - 15', 'small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1 lb', 'sesame seed oil - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place a pot with 3 cups of water on high heat to boil. Once water boils, add rice, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or according to package directions.
2. Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add enough water to cover the bottom of the skillet 1/2-inch deep. Add spinach and parsley leaves. Cook for about 2 minutes.
3. Drain and transfer leaves along with the basil, tomato, cashews, lime juice, salt and pepper, Parmesan cheese, one clove of garlic, and olive oil to a food processor.
4. Blend until well mixed. Set aside.
5. Slice asparagus spears into bite-sized pieces. Place them in skillet filled with 1/2 inch of boiling water. Cook for 4-5 minutes or until tender.
6. Next, heat sesame oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add second clove of garlic and shrimp, adding salt and pepper to taste.
7. Cook for 3-4 minutes or until shrimp is no longer pink. Remove from stove and mix in a bowl with the cooked rice.
8. Drain the asparagus and add to the bowl, topping with pesto. Stir gently and serve.

name: Black Bean Burger
description: If your diet plan allows a higher carb intake but you don't want the gluten that comes with a normal burger bun, a black bean burger is a great alternative. This burger tastes great over a bowl of rice and diced vegetables and topped with salsa or melted cheese—or both! The black beans provide a nice blend of protein, complex carbohydrates, and dietary fiber, giving you plenty of nutrients and energy while keeping you lean and ready for your next adventure.
recipeIngredient: ['black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 16 oz can', 'red pepper, thinly sliced - ½', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'egg - 1 whole', 'chili powder - 1 tbsp', 'hot sauce - 1 tsp', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'avocado - ¼ cup, pureed']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mash the beans to break apart.
2. Blend the red pepper, onion, and garlic in a food processor until tiny chunks are formed. Stir this into the bean mixture.
3. Next, add in the egg, spices, and avocado. Stir together well, then mix in the oats.
4. Form into four large patties. Place on a preheated grill, brushed with a little olive oil, then grill for about 8 minutes per side.
5. Serve with a little added avocado on top, if desired.

name: Tuna Melt Patties
description: Here's a special edition of an American classic that clocks in at a preparation speed of five minutes or less!
recipeIngredient: ['tuna, canned in water - 6 oz', 'egg whites - 1', 'rolled oats - 2 tbsp', 'onion powder - 2 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ¼ tsp', 'salt to taste - ', 'mozzarella cheese - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients except cheese together in a small bowl.
2. Heat a small nonstick frying pan over medium heat and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
3. Make two small patties by spooning 1/2 of tuna mixture into each side of the pan and lightly pressing with fork to flatten into a patty.
4. Cook until both sides are brown.
5. Top with 1 tbsp cheese and serve alone, on top of light bread, or with sides of choice.

name: Quick Recipe: Strawberry Savior Shake
description: This delicious powerhouse of protein, carbs, and healthy fats is the perfect post-workout body booster. Further proof that as long as you own a blender, good nutrition and delicious treats will never forsake you!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 4 scoop', 'creatine powder - 1 scoop', 'flaxseed oil - 1 tbsp', 'water - 1 cup', 'strawberry nonfat Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'strawberries, frozen - 3 whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the water, flaxseed oil, yogurt, and strawberries in a blender until the strawberries are well blended.
2. Blend in the protein powder and creatine.
3. Pour into a frozen glass with a strawberry garnish.

name: Garlic Greens
description: Green vegetables are a must-have for any diet. They're low in calories, rich in vitamins, and loaded with antioxidants. With this delicious recipe, you'll look forward to eating them all. Serve these greens as a side dish for your main meal.
recipeIngredient: ['kale, diced - 1½ cup', 'spinach - 4 cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 6 clove', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring a pot of water to a boil. Add greens and cook for 2 minutes or until just softened.
2. Drain the water, then fill pot with ice water to stop greens from cooking. Remove greens and pat dry.
3. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until golden. Remove garlic and set aside.
4. Place blanched greens in skillet and cook for 3 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 1 minute.
5. Add cooked garlic back to the skillet and heat for another minute to blend flavors. Serve immediately.

name: Quick Recipe: Almond Butter Protein Pancakes
description: Finally, a protein pancake with almost no carbs or fat. Get your flapjack freak on with this quick-as-you-please treat!
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 3 large', 'vanilla protein powder - 1 scoop', 'water - ¼ cup', 'natural almond butter - ¼ tsp', 'Splenda - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine the whey protein and Splenda in a bowl, then add the egg whites, water, and almond butter. If your almond butter is thick, you can microwave it for a few seconds to make it easier to blend.
2. Heat a greased skillet over medium heat. Pour batter out to form one pancake, and cook on each side for 90 seconds.
3. Throw it in your mouth naked, or top with more almond butter.

name: Foil Baked Garlic and Dill Tilapia
description: Baking in foil is an excellent way to prepare fish because the foil traps the delicate flavors. While grilling can also be a great option, foil-prepared dishes tend to pack in more overall flavor. This low-calorie tilapia recipe is also a good source of lean protein. Serve this fish with vegetables and a side of carbohydrates.
recipeIngredient: ['4 oz tilapia fillets - 2', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'lemon - 1', 'dried dill - 1 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.
2. Set tilapia on a square of heavy-duty foil. Rub fish with olive oil and top with dill, garlic, salt, and pepper. Squeeze half the lemon over top and lay asparagus over the fish.
3. Slice other half of the lemon and lay slices on top of asparagus.
4. Fold up sides of the foil and twist closed, creating an envelope around the fish.
5. Place in the oven and bake for about 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve immediately.

name: Lemon Garlic Shrimp
description: Shrimp is one of the best protein sources you can include in your diet for fat loss; it's low in calories and nearly fat-free. Couple that with brown rice and you have a perfect post-workout meal to support speedy recovery.
recipeIngredient: ['small shrimp, peeled and deveined - 1 lb', 'sesame seed oil - 2 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'paprika - ¼ tsp', 'diced red bell pepper - 1', 'yellow pepper, cut into strips - 1', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'lemon, cut into wedges - ½ whole', 'salt to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
2. Add half the garlic, half the sesame seed oil, and all of the peppers. Sauté until almost tender.
3. Add the remaining oil and garlic, then add the shrimp. Sprinkle in the remaining spices. Sauté for 2 minutes or until shrimp are thoroughly heated.
4. Drizzle lemon juice on top and serve on a bed of rice.

name: Supercharged Garlic Guacamole
description: Guacamole is an excellent side dish for any meal. It's loaded with healthy fats, rich in fiber, and doesn't contain any preservatives or processed ingredients—as long as you make it yourself, that is.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 2 fruit, without skin and seed', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'garlic, chopped - 2 clove', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1 whole', 'plum tomato, finely chopped - 1 whole', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cut the avocado in half and remove the pit.
2. Place avocado meat in a bowl, squeeze the lemon juice over top, and mash together.
3. Add the remaining ingredients. Keep mashing until well mixed. If you prefer no chunks in your guacamole, feel free to puree the mixture.
4. Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate for up to two days.

name: Garlic Cauliflower and Red Pepper Soup
description: This cauliflower soup is delicious and loaded with nutrition. Prepare a big batch and serve before your main course. People who start their meal with soups tend to consume fewer calories overall, which might help you shed a few pounds.
recipeIngredient: ['garlic, chopped - 1 clove', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'head cauliflower, chopped - 1', 'red pepper, cut into strips - 1', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 4 cup', 'low-fat Parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'salt and pepper to taste - 1 ', 'paprika - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
2. Add the garlic and red pepper and cook for 2-3 minutes or until garlic is slightly golden. Remove red pepper pieces, set aside, and dice when cool.
3. Add the cauliflower, chicken broth, salt, pepper, and paprika to the skillet. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
4. Allow mixture to cool, then puree in a blender until smooth. Note: Scalding-hot liquids can expand and explode in a blender. Always cool liquid until it's comfortable to the touch before blending it.
5. Return to skillet and add diced red pepper. Stir in Parmesan cheese and cook for 2-3 minutes. Serve immediately.

name: Egg White And Vegetable Scramble
description: he Paleolithic diet is inspired by what our ancestors ate before the agricultural age. Along with being low-carb, the foods included on Paleo diet lists are usually natural and organic. The point of eating Paleo is to give your body the nutrients it needs without the processed additives and extra calories of a contemporary diet.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 4 large', 'zucchini, finely shredded - ¼ whole', 'avocado - ¼', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'coconut oil spray - 1 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place skilled over medium heat and spray coconut oil.
2. Once skillet is hot, add zucchini and cook until edges are golden brown.
3. Reduce heat to low and pour in egg whites.
4. Cook slowly (about two minutes).
5. Once eggs are scrambled, add sea salt, pepper, and top with avocado.

name: Quick Recipe: Nada Colada Shake
description: Celebrate summer with this guilt-free twist on the classic piña colada!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla protein powder - 2 scoop', 'water - ½ cup', 'pineapple-orange juice - ½ cup', 'rum extract - ¼ tsp', 'coconut extract - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ingredients in a blender until ice is crushed.
2. Serve in a chilled glass with a wedge of orange for garnish.

name: Natalie Hodson's Death By Garlic Roasted Asparagus
description: Like asparagus? Like garlic? You'll love this healthy, LiveFit-approved recipe! Add it as a side dish to your next dinner.
recipeIngredient: ['asparagus spears - 20 whole', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 6 clove', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - 1 tbsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
3. Trim bottom 1/2 inch of asparagus spears.
4. Place trimmed spears on cookie sheet.
5. Drizzle olive oil over asparagus.
6. Sprinkle minced garlic, garlic powder and black pepper over asparagus.
7. Bake for 15-20 minutes, flip asparagus at 10 minutes.
8. Bake until asparagus and garlic are lightly browned.

name: Bean and Sweet Potato Salad
description: You don't have to be a vegan or vegetarian to understand and appreciate the power of beans. They're full of fiber, iron, and thiamin, and they're also a great protein source. That's why this recipe is an all-out win for your health and your taste buds!
recipeIngredient: ['kidney beans, canned - 1 14 oz can', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 16 oz can', 'corn - 1 15 oz can', 'cilantro - 1 tbsp', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 1 whole', 'garlic salt - 1 tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pan fry sweet potato in olive oil and set aside to cool.
2. Drain and rinse kidney beans, black beans, and corn and add to a large bowl.
3. Add garlic salt, cilantro, and cooled sweet potato to the bowl of beans and stir.
4. Enjoy as is or use as a side dish.

name: Tuna Guacamole With Baked Sweet Potato Chips
description: The Paleolithic diet is inspired by what our ancestors ate before the agricultural age. Along with being low-carb, the foods included on Paleo diet lists are usually natural and organic. The point of eating Paleo is to give your body the nutrients it needs without the processed additives and extra calories of a contemporary diet.
recipeIngredient: ['tuna, white, canned in oil - 1 can', 'avocado - 1½', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - ½', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'tomatoes - ¼ medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'cilantro - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place one avocado in mortar and pestle (or molcajete) and add walnut oil and lemon juice.
2. Crush avocados and then add salt and pepper to taste.
3. Add tuna and the rest of the ingredients to avocado paste and mix well.
4. Enjoy with sweet potato or vegetable chips.

name: Tuna Apple Salad
description: Oh, I know what you're thinking: tuna and apple, you're crazy! I promise you, the texture and taste combo of apple and tuna is great. The best part about this salad is its versatility. Eat it as it is, on a sandwich, or make a lettuce wrap. Whichever option you go for, it'll be a good decision.
recipeIngredient: ['stalk celery, finely diced - 2 tbsp', 'tuna, canned in water - 2 can', 'relish, sweet - 1 tbsp', 'apple, sliced - ½', 'garlic powder - ¼ tsp', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Drain water from cans and place tuna in a bowl.
2. Finely chop celery and apple and add to tuna.
3. Stir in sweet relish, garlic powder, and mayo.

name: Lemon Quinoa Mint Salad
description: I love quinoa. It's full of protein, has an interesting taste, and it pretty much goes with everything. That's why I eat this recipe as a meal. It also works great as a side dish. Bring it to your next barbecue or potluck and I guarantee you won't have any leftovers!
recipeIngredient: ['quinoa, cooked - 3 cup', 'pine nuts - ½ cup', 'mint leaves - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 lemon yields', 'salt - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix mint leaves into cooled quinoa.
2. Add lemon juice.
3. Stir in pine nuts, salt, and basil oil (optional).
4. Devour by yourself or share with friends!

name: Arugula Chicken Salad
description: Arugula isn't just fancy lettuce—it's a flavorful, nutritious vegetable that has a long list of health benefits. It's low in calories, high in folic acid, vitamins A, C, and K, and minerals like iron and copper. Its peppery flavor also provides a unique twist. Here's my favorite way to make arugula even yummier!
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'baby carrots, chopped - 10', 'red cabbage - ½ cup, chopped', 'arugula, raw - 1 cup', 'chicken breast, cut into cubes - 8 oz', 'sunflower seeds - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pan fry cubed chicken in a non-stick pan with olive oil. Set aside and allow it to cool.
2. Chop red cabbage and baby carrots.
3. Add arugula, carrots, and cabbage to a large salad bowl.
4. Top salad with sunflower seeds and cooled chicken.
5. Add your favorite dressing and enjoy.

name: Spinach Almond Salad
description: Spinach and almonds make a wonderful combination. It's a tasty treat, and a healthy one at that, but I wanted to up the ante a little. So, I added broccoli, a great source of vitamin A, protein-packed eggs, and basil leaves for some extra flavor.
recipeIngredient: ['baby spinach - 1½ cup', 'broccoli - ½ cup', 'tomato, diced - 1', 'hard-boiled egg - 3', 'almonds, slivered - 1 tbsp', 'fresh basil leaves -  cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add spinach to a large salad bowl.
2. Chop broccoli, tomatoes, and hard-boiled eggs and add to salad bowl.
3. Sprinkle with slivered almonds and fresh basil leaves.
4. Top with your favorite dressing or try half a squeezed lemon and olive oil.

name: Ginger Garlic Tilapia with Summer Squash Wedges
description: The Paleolithic diet is inspired by what our ancestors ate before the agricultural age. Along with being low-carb, the foods included on Paleo diet lists are usually natural and organic. The point of eating Paleo is to give your body the nutrients it needs without the processed additives and extra calories of a contemporary diet.
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 5 fillet', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'ginger, minced - 8 tbsp', 'green onion, chopped - 8 whole', 'coconut, shredded - ⅛ cup, shredded', 'liquid aminos - 2 tbsp', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'summer squash - ½ medium', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 pinch', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat 1 tbsp of coconut oil in skillet over medium heat.
2. Once oil has melted, add 2 or 3 tilapia fillets to skillet and cook for 2 minutes.
3. Flip tilapia and add ginger, garlic, and shredded coconut to the top of each fillet and let cook for 1 minute.
4. Spread 1 tbsp liquid aminos on the fillets and cook for another minute.
5. Flip fillets one more time, add green onions and cook for another minute.
6. Turn oven to broil. Arrange rack so baking pan is close to heat.
7. Cover baking pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
8. Cut squash into thick wedges about one inch thick.
9. Place wedges in a Ziploc bag and add the rest of the ingredients.
10. Close bag and shake it thoroughly.
11. Place wedges in a single row in the center of the baking dish and broil for 5 minutes or until golden.
12. Carefully flip each wedge and broil for another two minutes.

name: Gluten-Free Apple Pie Protein Bars
description: You can have your pie and eat it too with this fruit-inspired protein creation.
recipeIngredient: ['coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla protein powder - ½ cup', 'coconut sugar - 4 tbsp', 'natural almond butter - 4 tbsp', 'almond milk - 4 tbsp', 'coconut flour - 4 tbsp', 'cinnamon - 2 tbsp', 'apple, sliced - 1']
recipeInstructions:
1. Steam your apple slices until they get soft. You can peel the apple before steaming it or you can leave the skin on—it's up to you.
2. Make your bar my mixing the rest of the ingredients together in a food processor until you get a soft dough.
3. Press the dough onto a small silicone brownie pan. Add your apple slices on top, and sprinkle the whole thing with some extra cinnamon or allspice.
4. Bake at 340 F (170 C) for about 15-20 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean. Or if you want your bars really soft inside, just take them out while they're still a bit sticky in the middle! That's what I did when I made these bars, and they were delish.
5. Let the bars cool down completely before slicing and eating.
6. Note: You can substitute sunflower seed butter for the almond butter. You can use coconut or regular milk in place of almond milk.

name: Cilantro Beef Burgers & Ecuadorian Style Patacones
description: The Paleolithic diet is inspired by what our ancestors ate before the agricultural age. Along with being low-carb, the foods included on Paleo diet lists are usually natural and organic. The point of eating Paleo is to give your body the nutrients it needs without the processed additives and extra calories of a contemporary diet.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1¼ lb', 'egg - 2 whole', 'onion, finely diced - ¼', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'cilantro - 3 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'plantain - 2 whole', 'coconut oil - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn oven to broil. Arrange rack so baking pan is close to heat.
2. Cover backing pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
3. Cover backing pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
4. Place patties on the center of the baking pan and broil for 6-8 minutes. Flip and broil for another 6-8 minutes.
5. When both sides are golden brown, remove from oven.
6. Cut plantain into thick slices (each slice about one inch long).
7. Place oil in skillet and turn stove to medium heat. Oil should cover skillet's surface and over 1/4 inch of plantains.
8. Place plantains in oil and fry for two minutes. Should be crisp, but not burnt at the bottom.
9. Turn plantains over and fry another two minutes.
10. Remove plantains from oil and use paper towel to remove excess oil.
11. Smash plantains with bottom of a glass and then sprinkle each with a little salt.
12. Fry both sides of plantains again for 1-2 minutes.
13. Remove from oil, pat dry with a paper towel and serve.

name: Grilled Chicken Salad
description: The Paleolithic diet is inspired by what our ancestors ate before the agricultural age. Along with being low-carb, the foods included on Paleo diet lists are usually natural and organic. The point of eating Paleo is to give your body the nutrients it needs without the processed additives and extra calories of a contemporary diet.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 piece', 'lemon pepper to taste - ', 'salt to taste - ', 'salad greens - 1 cup', 'cherry tomatoes - 1 cup', 'avocado - ¼', 'green pepper, chopped - ¼ whole', 'almonds, slivered - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set oven to broil and arrange rack so baking pan is close to heat.
2. Cover baking pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
3. Season both sides of chicken breasts with a bit of sea salt and generous amounts of lemon pepper.
4. Place chicken breasts in the middle of the baking pan and broils for 12-13 minutes on each side.
5. Remove from oven and cut into slices or chunks.
6. Place cup of greens in a salad bowl and top with the rest of the vegetables.
7. Add slivered almonds, and 1/2 sliced chicken breast to salad.
8. Top with olive oil, vinegar, sea salt, and pepper.

name: Vegan Oatmeal Raisin Protein Cookies
description: Looking for a tasty cookie that travels well whether you're enjoying it on a picnic, during a hike, or simply while sitting down at the dinner table? Give this sweet treat a try.
recipeIngredient: ['natural almond butter - 3 tbsp', 'vanilla protein powder - ⅜ cup', 'agave syrup - ⅛ cup', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'raisins - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor, mix all ingredients together except for the raisins, chocolate chips, or chopped nuts. Once you have dough you can mold with your hands, mix in your toppings.
2. Divide your mix into five balls. Place them on a tray lined with baking paper and press them down into cookies.
3. Bake the cookies at 325 degress F (160 C) for 8-12 minutes. Just be sure to keep an eye on them and do not overbake. If you do, they will come out very dry! Remove them as soon as they've browned on top.
4. Allow your cookies to cool down completely before eating. It might be hard, but try. Expect them to be a bit mushy at first—they'll settle to a perfect consistency as they cool.

name: Greek Turkey (Or Chicken) Burgers
description: Looking for a flavorful, easy meal-prep option? These healthy Greek burgers are delicious and can be made with either lean ground turkey or ground chicken. I just love how the flavors of mint, oregano, lemon, and feta come together in a symphony of deliciousness!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 2 lb', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1 cup', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'mint leaves - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'oregano - 1½ tsp, ground', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
2. Mix until feta, oats, mint, and spices are evenly distributed, but don't over mix or your burgers may be dense.
3. Grill (or pan-fry) 4-6 minutes per side until browned, or until internal temperature reaches 165 degrees F. Enjoy!
4. Store in the fridge up to one week, or in the freezer up to one month.

name: Greek Turkey (Or Chicken) Burgers
description: Looking for a flavorful, easy meal-prep option? These healthy Greek burgers are delicious and can be made with either lean ground turkey or ground chicken. I just love how the flavors of mint, oregano, lemon, and feta come together in a symphony of deliciousness!
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 2 lb', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1 cup', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'mint leaves - ½ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'oregano - 1½ tsp, ground', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'salt - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
2. Mix until feta, oats, mint, and spices are evenly distributed, but don't over mix or your burgers may be dense.
3. Grill (or pan-fry) 4-6 minutes per side until browned, or until internal temperature reaches 165 degrees F. Enjoy!
4. Store in the fridge up to one week, or in the freezer up to one month.

name: Lean Beef Enchiladas
description: I don't know about you, but I love Mexican food! These healthy enchiladas are filled with spiced ground beef, peppers, onion, and melty cheese. Yum! They're easy to make, low in fat, and gluten-free! I divided my enchiladas into airtight containers for a week's worth of meal prep. Convenient and delicious!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 2 lb', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'green bell pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 tsp, ground', 'enchilada sauce - 15 oz', 'corn tortilla - 16 whole', 'reduced-fat Mexican cheese - 1½ cup', 'cilantro - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Lightly grease a 9x13 casserole dish or baking pan.
3. In a large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat, breaking up with a spatula.
4. Drain fat and add onion, garlic, and peppers. Sauté until onion is translucent and garlic is fragrant.
5. Season beef with cumin, smoked paprika, and black pepper. Remove from heat.
6. Wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel, then heat in microwave for 20-30 seconds.
7. Pour enchilada sauce into one medium bowl and shredded cheese into another.
8. Dip a warm tortilla in enchilada sauce, and set in casserole dish.
9. Fill tortilla with 3 tablespoons of beef mixture and 1 tablespoon of cheese.
10. Roll up and arrange in corner of dish, seam side down. Repeat with all tortillas and beef.
11. Pour remaining sauce over the enchiladas in pan. Sprinkle the tops evenly with remaining cheese.
12. Bake 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
13. Remove from oven and let cool 5-10 minutes before serving.
14. Serve with desired toppings and enjoy!

name: Lean Beef Enchiladas
description: I don't know about you, but I love Mexican food! These healthy enchiladas are filled with spiced ground beef, peppers, onion, and melty cheese. Yum! They're easy to make, low in fat, and gluten-free! I divided my enchiladas into airtight containers for a week's worth of meal prep. Convenient and delicious!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 2 lb', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'green bell pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'red enchilada sauce - 15 oz', 'corn tortilla - 16', 'reduced-fat Mexican cheese - 1½ cup', 'cilantro - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Lightly grease a 9x13 casserole dish or baking pan.
3. In a large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat, breaking up with a spatula.
4. Drain fat and add onion, garlic, and peppers. Sauté until onion is translucent and garlic is fragrant.
5. Season beef with cumin, smoked paprika, and black pepper. Remove from heat.
6. Wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel, then heat in microwave for 20-30 seconds.
7. Pour enchilada sauce into one medium bowl and shredded cheese into another.
8. Dip a warm tortilla in enchilada sauce, and set in casserole dish.
9. Fill tortilla with 3 tablespoons of beef mixture and 1 tablespoon of cheese.
10. Roll up and arrange in corner of dish, seam side down. Repeat with all tortillas and beef.
11. Pour remaining sauce over the enchiladas in pan. Sprinkle the tops evenly with remaining cheese.
12. Bake 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
13. Remove from oven and let cool 5-10 minutes before serving.
14. Serve with desired toppings and enjoy!

name: Thai Chicken And Vegetable Coconut Curry
description: Here's a meal prep idea for all you Thai fans! Thai cuisine happens to be one of my favorites, so I was quite happy with how authentic this simplified version of Thai chicken coconut curry came out.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'canola oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - ½ cup', 'ginger, minced - 1 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'red bell pepper, sliced - 1', 'yellow pepper, sliced - 1', 'kale - 1 cup 1" pieces, loosely packed', 'light coconut milk - 1½ cup', 'water - ½ cup', 'Thai red curry paste - 2 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'lime juice - 2 tsp', 'curry powder - 1½ tsp', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - 1 tsp', 'fish sauce - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice chicken breasts into 1/4-inch strips (very thin).
2. Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat and add chicken. Cook until meat is white or lightly browned and just barely cooked through.
3. Set chicken aside on a plate.
4. In the same skillet, add diced onion, ginger, and garlic. Cook and stir until fragrant and onion is translucent.
5. Add carrots and bell peppers, cooking about 3 minutes until tender.
6. Add back chicken, plus kale, coconut milk, and remaining ingredients.
7. Simmer over medium heat for 5-10 minutes to allow flavors to blend. Adjust seasoning to taste.
8. For meal prep, weigh out the entire batch and divide by six to find the exact weight per serving. Serve over cooked basmati rice or riced cauliflower and enjoy!

name: Hamburger Lentil Soup
description: This is my new winter favorite! I adapted the recipe from Food.com's Country Hamburger Lentil Soup, making it higher in protein and slightly lower in carbs. I also tweaked the seasonings a little to suit my taste.
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 16 oz', 'diced tomatoes - 2 can', 'dried lentils - ¾ cup', 'water - 4 cup', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 3', 'carrots, sliced - 3', 'onion, finely diced - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'Better Than Boullion (Organic Beef Base) - 1 tbsp', 'oregano - 2 tsp, ground', 'basil, dried - 1 tsp, ground', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'bay leaf - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Stove Top:
In a large saucepan, cook ground beef over medium-high heat until no longer pink. Drain fat.
2. Stir in diced tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
3. Cover saucepan, reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 40-60 minutes until vegetables are tender. Adjust seasoning to taste.
4. Discard bay leaves before serving or dividing into meal prep containers.
5. Slow Cooker:
In a skillet, cook ground beef over medium-high heat until no longer pink. Drain fat.
6. Add ground beef to slow cooker along with remaining ingredients. Stir once to combine.
7. Cover and cook on LOW setting for 12 hours or HIGH setting for 6 hours.
8. Discard bay leaves before serving or dividing into meal prep containers.

name: Chocolate Banana "Ice Cream"
description:
There's nothing like concluding a steamy summer day with a bowl of frosty ice cream. With frozen bananas for your creamy base and protein-packed Greek yogurt, this near-instant version won't blow up your physique, but it will deliver plenty of texture and taste!

To freeze bananas for "ice cream" or smoothies, peel the fruit, slice it into chunks, and spread it out on a baking sheet. Place the bananas in the freezer until they're frozen solid, then transfer them to an airtight bag until you're ready to use them.
recipeIngredient: ['banana - 1', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - ¼ cup', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place the frozen bananas in a food processor. Process until the bananas are reduced to the size of small pebbles. At first, the bananas will bounce around and make a lot of noise before taking on a smooth consistency.
2. Scrape down the sides of the bowl, then add yogurt, cocoa powder, honey, vanilla and cinnamon. Blend until creamy.
3. Serve this immediately like soft-serve ice cream, or freeze it for later use. If frozen, the mixture will need to sit at room temperature for a few minutes to soften up.

name: Moroccan Chicken Salad
description: Rustle up this salad in advance, and you'll be set up for a few cook-free dinners throughout the week. Supermarket rotisserie chicken lets someone else do all the cooking, while you get to benefit from a bounty of juicy protein.
recipeIngredient: ['couscous, whole-grain - 1 cup', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'chicken, rotisserie, chopped - 4 cup', 'carrots, sliced - 2', 'cherry tomatoes - 2 cup', 'cucumber, chopped - 1', 'scallions, sliced - 2', 'mint leaves - ⅓ cup', 'dried apricots - ½ cup, halves', 'almonds, dry roasted, unsalted, sliced - ⅓ cup', 'olive oil - ¼ cup', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring 1 cup water to a boil using a kettle or microwave. In a large heat-proof bowl, stir boiling water with couscous and salt. Cover and let stand until the water has absorbed, about 5 minutes. Fluff the couscous with a fork and let cool.
2. Toss together the couscous, chicken, carrots, tomatoes, cucumber, scallions, mint, apricot and almonds. Whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, and smoked paprika. Toss the dressing with the salad.

name: Zucchini Smoked Fish Rolls
description: Here's proof that no-cook snacks can be so much more than just a bowl of yogurt or handful of nuts. Strips of zucchini are a fancy delivery method for ready-to-go smoked fish. Beyond being a top-notch protein provider, smoked swimmers like mackerel are a source of ultra-healthy omega-3 fatty acids. These bundles of great nutrition are also an inspired appetizer for summer backyard parties.
recipeIngredient: ['zucchini, sliced - 1 whole', 'flat-leaf parsley - ½ cup', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'salmon, smoked - 2 oz', 'red pepper, roasted, thinly sliced - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Chop the ends off the zucchini. Use a vegetable peeler or mandolin slicer to peel the zucchini into long, wide, thin strips.
2. In a small bowl, stir together parsley, olive oil, lemon juice, and black pepper. Spread about 1/2 teaspoon of the parsley mixture on one of the zucchini strips, and place two slices of the fish and two slices of the red pepper at one end.
3. Tightly roll up the zucchini strip, and stab a toothpick through the middle to keep the roll together.

name: Chilled Avocado Coconut Soup With Shrimp
description: A steamy bowl of soup is not something you probably crave when temperatures are soaring. This chilled version will help you keep your cool and load up on the heart-healthy fats found in avocado. Ready to thaw at a moment's notice, bags of previously cooked frozen shrimp are a quick way to add a healthy dose of muscle-building protein in a flash.
recipeIngredient: ['light coconut milk - 1½ cup', 'water - 1½ cup', 'avocado - 2', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - ½ cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - ¼ tsp, ground', 'shrimp, precooked and diced - 16 oz', 'lime zest - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place coconut milk, water, avocado flesh, basil, lime juice, jalapeno, salt and black pepper in a blender and blend until smooth. If the resulting mixture is too thick, blend in more liquid. Pour the mixture into a container, and chill for at least 2 hours.
2. To serve, pour the soup in serving bowls and top with shrimp and lime zest.

name: Cantaloupe Bowls
description: With this refreshing recipe in your back pocket, there's no need to settle for boxed cereal when you don't want to make a hot breakfast. Cottage cheese is a fuss-free way to kick-start your day with high-quality protein. And since they're made up of almost 90 percent water, edible cantaloupe bowls are a stealthy way to bolster your summer-hydration efforts.
recipeIngredient: ['cantaloupe - 1', 'fat-free cottage cheese - 1½ cup', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp', 'granola - ⅓ cup', 'pistachio nuts, chopped - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice a cantaloupe in half, and then slice roughly a half inch off the bottoms so both halves sit flat. Scoop out the seeds.
2. Stir together cottage cheese, honey, vanilla extract, and lemon zest. Stuff half of the cottage cheese mixture into each of the cantaloupe halves. Sprinkle on granola and pistachios.

name: Teriyaki Tangelo Chicken Skewers
description: These excellent skewers are made with an Asian twist. The tangelos and teriyaki go perfectly with protein-packed chicken. It's a yummy, healthy, fun dish that's secretly easy but looks gourmet.
recipeIngredient: ['tangelo orange - 2', 'chicken breast, oven-roasted, sliced - 6 serving 2 slices', 'teriyaki sauce, fat-free - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel and divide tangelos into triangular wedges.
2. Roll the chicken slices and then cut into halves.
3. Alternate tangelos and chicken slices on the skewers (8 skewers).
4. Plate and drizzle with teriyaki sauce.

name: Cucumber Crab Wraps
description: The tuna and crackers snack is good, sure, but sometimes you need to add a little "fancy" to your nutrition. Instead of crackers, use fresh cucumber, and eat crab instead of tuna. It's a wonderfully refreshing low-cal play on an old favorite.
recipeIngredient: ['crab meat - 3 oz', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 2 tbsp', 'cucumber, thinly sliced - 1 whole', 'scallions, sliced - ½ tbsp', 'dill pickle relish - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel cucumber and cut lengthwise into thin strips.
2. Combine mayo, relish, and scallions in a bowl and stir.
3. Place mayo mixture and crab pieces on a strip of cucumber, roll the cucumber, and fasten with a toothpick.

name: Red Pear And Prosciutto Skewers
description: Putting together sweet pears with salty prosciutto is a seriously tasty treat. The combination of textures just makes it even better. Bring this dish to a get-together and I bet you won't even get to eat one.
recipeIngredient: ['red pears - 2 medium', 'prosciutto - 1 package', 'Walden Farms Balsamic - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Chop the pears into triangular wedges.
2. Roll slices of prosciutto and then cut into halves.
3. Alternate pears and prosciutto on the skewers (4 skewers).
4. Plate and drizzle with balsamic vinegar.

name: Caprese Salad
description: This Italian specialty is probably one of the most delicious combinations of flavors ever created. Layer fresh tomato, mozzarella, and basil, and you have a beautiful dish that is impossible not to like!
recipeIngredient: ['tomatoes - 2 small whole (2-2/5" dia)', 'mozzarella cheese - 8 oz', 'fresh basil leaves -  cup']
recipeInstructions:
