1. Cut the mozzarella and tomatoes in quarter-inch slices.
2. Layer them on a plate with the basil leaves.
3. Optional: Drizzle balsamic vinegar or try a little sea salt and olive oil combination.

name: Protein Pow No-Bake Buckeyes
description: Do you really want to live without decadent dark chocolate and creamy peanut butter? By adding a protein punch to this classic combo, you'll never have to go hungry again!
recipeIngredient: ['Peanut butter - ¼ cup', 'Vanilla whey protein powder - ⅓ cup', 'Ground almonds - ⅛ cup', 'Almond milk - 2 tsp', 'Dark chocolate chips - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl until you get a thick doughy consistency that can be rolled into balls. If your dough is too wet or sticky, add more of the ground almonds. If it's too dry and crumbly, add more milk one tablespoon at a time.
2. Using your hands, roll your dough into 8-10 balls, or truffles.
3. Melt dark chocolate and dunk your truffles using a small spoon or a toothpick. Leave a bit of the ball uncoated; that's the "eye" of the buck.
4. Allow buckeyes to set in the fridge for 30 minutes or in the freezer for 10 minutes.

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Oatmeal
description: A fan of Reese's peanut butter cups? This chocolate peanut butter protein-style oatmeal tastes just like it—heck, it even incorporates some of it into the recipe!—and is just the ticket to send your taste buds into ecstasy.
recipeIngredient: ['raw oats - ¾ cup', 'milk (1%) - ¾ cup', 'MusclePharm Combat Powder (Chocolate) - 1 scoop', 'liquid egg whites - 2', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon -  to taste', 'Musclepharm Combat Crunch Bar - ½ bar', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 tsp', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Microwave oats and water or milk in a microwave-safe bowl for about 2-1/2 minutes.
2. Add 2 egg whites and whisk until completely mixed in. Microwave for another 45 seconds.
3. Add protein powder and cocoa powder and mix. Add Stevia and cinnamon if desired.
4. Chop protein bar (chocolate peanut butter flavor) into small squares. Top with protein bar pieces, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, and natural peanut butter.

name: Greek Chicken
description: Turning up the flavor on chicken breast can make your meal sing. A palm-sized portion of grilled chicken provides roughly 25 grams of protein, while the addition of thyme and rosemary add flavor, sans salt. Rosemary, rich in folic acid and vitamins A and C, has been shown to ease muscle pain and indigestion.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'black olives, sliced - ½ cup', 'tomatoes, sliced - 4', 'reduced-fat feta cheese - 1 cup', 'olive oil - ⅓ cup', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'rosemary - 1 tsp', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'lemon juice - 2 lemon yields', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix the olive oil, garlic, rosemary, thyme, oregano, pepper, and lemon juice.
2. Cut the chicken into strips. Place the chicken strips, olives, and diced tomatoes in the olive oil mixture. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight.
3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
4. Place chicken mixture in aluminum foil and, creating a pocket, add some of the marinade to keep it moist.
5. Cook for about 30 minutes.
6. Sprinkle with feta cheese before serving.

name: Red-Eye Chocolate And Peanut Butter Protein Parfait With Blueberries And Dark Chocolate Chips
description: This parfait packs a punch; and not just because it's made with Gaspari Nutrition ISOFusion. The shot of coffee gives you the jolt you need to jumpstart your day.
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 1 scoop', 'instant coffee - 1 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 1 tbsp', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'powdered peanut butter - 2 tbsp', 'granola - ⅓ cup', 'blueberries - 6 berries', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add granola to a jar, glass, cup or bowl.
2. Add 1/3 cup yogurt on top of the granola.
3. Mix 1/3 cup yogurt with powdered peanut butter. Add to the jar.
4. Mix 1/3 cup yogurt with protein powder, coffee, and cocoa powder. Add to the jar.
5. Top parfait with granola, 1 tbsp of chocolate chips, and blueberries.

name: Protein French Toast With Sautéed Apples
description: There are just some foods that nearly every gym rat or gym bunny loves. French toast is one of them. Carb it up for a long day or a monster leg workout.
recipeIngredient: ['Dymatize ISO-100 - 1 scoop', 'Ezekial bread - 2 slice', 'almond milk - ¼ cup', 'egg - 1', 'egg whites - 1', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix eggs, almond milk, cinnamon, and protein.
2. Soak each piece of bread in the mixture until it is all used.
3. Lightly spray a pan or skillet with olive oil or coconut oil and heat pan. Cook each piece of bread until each side has browned.
4. Top toast with your favorite syrup, sugar-free syrup, or honey.
5. Optional: Top toast with 1 sauteed sliced apple in 1 tsp coconut oil.

name: Rosemary Marinated Salmon
description: When it comes to eating fish, you can't go wrong with salmon. It is rich in omega-3 fats and high in EPA and DHA content?just four ounces contain more healthy fat than the average adult consumes in days. Salmon helps prevent chronic inflammation, promote cognitive function, and improve vision. Perhaps owing to the high levels of vitamin D and selenium, salmon also lowers cancer risks.
recipeIngredient: ['salmon fillet - 24 oz', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'rosemary - ½ tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine all ingredients, except salmon, in a bowl. Add pepper to taste.
3. Pour the mixture into the bottom of a small baking dish.
4. Add salmon steaks and turn to coat. Marinate 15 minutes.
5. Wrap each steak in aluminum foil, and bake for about 20 minutes at 350 degrees F.

name: Alaskan Omelet
description: Are you looking for the perfect breakfast recipe to kickstart your metabolism and burn some fat? Consider amplifying your morning eggs with a hint of basil. Revered as the "holy herb," basil's antibacterial properties have been used to treat everything from the common cold and fever to respiratory disorders, kidney stones, and bronchitis and sinus infections. Its high magnesium content also makes basil key to improved blood flow.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1', 'egg whites - 4', 'reduced-fat sour cream - 1 tbsp', 'canned salmon - 2 oz', 'fresh basil leaves, chopped - 1 tbsp', 'scallions, sliced - 1 tbsp', 'parsley, dried - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash']
recipeInstructions:
1. Beat eggs and pour them in a heated skillet.
2. When the omelet hardens, place salmon on top.
3. Top salmon with sour cream and sprinkle with basil, scallion, parsley, and pepper.
4. Fold in half and cook until done.

name: Peppers With "Fit Grits," Egg Whites And Pico De Gallo
description: This meal is great for breakfast or, if you work out in the evening, a post-workout dinner. Regardless of when you have it, your body and taste buds will thank you.
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 2 whole', 'egg whites - 2', 'spinach - 1 cup', 'brown rice - ¼ cup', 'green bell pepper - ½', 'pico de gallo - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook egg whites and farina separately. Mix together and add spinach. Cook until spinach is wilted.
2. Cut bell peppers horizontally to create 2 thick rings.
3. Lightly spray another skillet with coconut oil or olive oil and set on medium heat.
4. Place bell peppers rings in the skillet and crack the eggs inside the bell pepper.
5. Push down on the bell pepper sides to prevent spillage. Let it cook until the egg turns white.
6. Place cooked pepper rings and egg/farina mixture on a plate. Top whatever you'd like with pico de gallo.

name: Dark Chocolate Gluten-Free Protein Waffles
description: These waffles are powered by Gaspari Nutrition MyoFusion. The "rite of passage" for any FMC/ FWC is making protein waffles and pancakes. And these waffles prove that feeding muscles is pretty delicious!
recipeIngredient: ['Gaspari Nutrition Myofusion Advanced Protein - 1 scoop', 'egg - 1', 'egg whites - 1', 'sorghum flour - ¼ cup', 'almond flour - ⅛ cup', 'almond milk - ⅓ cup', 'powdered Stevia - 1 g']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a bowl, mix protein powder, sorghum flour, almond flour, cocoa powder, Stevia or sugar.
2. Add eggs and almond milk and mix or blend.
3. Spray waffle iron with coconut or olive oil.
4. Pour batter onto the waffle iron and cook.
5. When waffles are done, drizzle with fruit, your favorite sugar-free syrup, or both.

name: Provencal Chicken Strips
description: Are you searching for a high-protein recipe that's skimpy on carbs and fats? Try these simple, easy-to-make, downright delicious chicken strips flavored with a dash of parsley and rosemary. Parsley has strong anti-inflammatory properties and serves up more vitamin K than any other herb?just two tablespoons provide half of your recommended daily value. The kick of rosemary acts as an antioxidant.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 24 oz', 'olive oil - 2 tsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'tomato, diced - 6', 'shallots - 1', 'parsley, dried - 1 tbsp', 'capers, canned - 1 tbsp, drained', 'red wine vinegar - 1 tsp', 'rosemary - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Saute chicken strips and 2 tbsp of olive oil in a large skillet at medium-high heat for 4 minutes.
2. Add shallot and garlic and cook for another 3 minutes. Stir frequently.
3. Stir in tomatoes, capers, parsley, vinegar, and rosemary.
4. Reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes, or until the liquid evaporates.

name: Buffalo Chicken Dip
description: Enjoy with your favorite keto-friendly veggie for a delicious low-carb appetizer!
recipeIngredient: ['canned chunk chicken breast, drained - 10 oz', 'fat-free cream cheese - 8 oz', 'red hot sauce - ½ cup', 'monterey jack cheese, shredded - ⅓ cup, diced', 'ranch dressing, reduced-fat - ⅓ cup', 'blue cheese - ⅓ cup, crumbled, not packed']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine cream cheese, ranch dressing, and hot sauce in a medium-sized bowl. You can use a fork or whisk, but if you have a hand-held beater it will make the job go by a lot faster.
2. Fold in chicken.
3. Spread mixture into a pie plate sprayed with a nonstick cooking oil.
4. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes.
5. Add Monterey jack cheese and blue cheese to the top. Bake for an additional 10-15 minutes.

name: Anabolic Muscle Bowl
description: You want to start the day building muscle? This breakfast will get you there. I dare you to try this and not feel your "muscles feeding"—certified muscle food and energy.
recipeIngredient: ['egg whites - 6 large', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'banana - ½ medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'walnuts, chopped - ⅛ cup', 'raspberries - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 1 dash', 'organic honey - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook egg whites in a skillet on low heat.
2. If you want to cook your banana, spray another skillet with coconut oil or virgin olive oil and set on low-medium heat. Chop half of the banana into pieces and add to the skillet. Use a spatula and be careful not to let the banana pieces stick to the skillet.
3. Combine oatmeal and egg whites in a bowl and mix.
4. Add cinnamon and Stevia (or raw honey) and mix.
5. Top with banana, raspberries, and walnuts.

name: Lebanese Beef Kebabs
description: Nothing says protein-packed finger food like meat on a skewer. And nothing's better than tender beef marinated with herbs and spices. Enter: Lebanese beef kebabs. Along with the usual favorites of thyme and parsley, which are high in potassium, iron, calcium, and manganese, this recipe also calls for two other great herbs: the bay leaf and mint.
recipeIngredient: ['beef tenderloin - 16 oz', 'olive oil - 4 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp', 'lemon zest - 1 tsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'mint leaves - 1 tsp', 'paprika - ½ tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'thyme - 1 tsp, ground', 'bay leaf - 1', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp', 'flat-leaf parsley - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a food processor or blender, puree onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and zest, mint, paprika, cumin, thyme, bay leaf, and cayenne.
2. In a big Ziploc bag, combine beef cubes with the mixture, coating the beef completely. Marinate in the fridge overnight.
3. Drain the marinade in a saucepan, and bring to a boil.
4. Skewer beef cubes and place on hot grill. While turning the beef, brush with boiled marinade.
5. Serve in a bowl with the remaining marinade.

name: Deviled Eggs
description: No barbecue menu would be complete without this quick and easy low-carb favorite!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 12 whole', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 1 cup', 'dijon mustard - 2½ tbsp', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'paprika - 1 pinch']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place eggs in a single layer in a sauce pan and cover with enough water so there's about an inch of water above the eggs. Heat on high until water begins to boil, then cover and turn the heat to low. Cook for 1 minute.
2. Remove from heat and leave covered for 14 minutes, then rinse under cold water for 1 minute.
3. Crack egg shells and peel under cool running water. Pat dry with a paper towel.
4. Slice the eggs in half lengthwise. Remove the yolks and place them in a bowl.
5. Mash the yolks into a fine crumble with a fork. Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt, and pepper. Mix well.
6. Scoop the yolk mixture into the egg whites, sprinkle with paprika, and enjoy!

name: Summer Slaw
description: A little crunchy, a little creamy, and 100 percent refreshing! Enjoy this summertime side dish at your next outdoor gathering.
recipeIngredient: ['coleslaw mix (cabbage salad) - 16 oz', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 1 cup', 'heavy whipping cream - ½ cup, fluid (yields 2 cups whipped)', 'white vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, heavy cream, vinegar, and lemon juice. Mix well.
2. Pour over the cabbage mixture and toss to coat well.
3. Cover and chill for at least one hour or until ready to serve.

name: Bacon Caesar Salad
description: Swap out the croutons for bacon in this traditional Caesar salad recipe for extra flavor and crunch!
recipeIngredient: ['romaine lettuce - 8 cup shredded', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 4 oz', 'bacon - 5 oz, chopped', 'caesar dressing, fat-free - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Cook bacon in a skillet over medium-high heat until crisp, about 7-8 minutes. Remove from heat and place on a plate to cool.
2. Once the bacon is cooled, crumble into small pieces.
3. Combine chopped lettuce, cheese, and bacon in a large bowl, drizzle with dressing, and toss to coat. Serve immediately.

name: Post Cardio Protein Banana Split
description: Banana split for breakfast? Yep, you read that right. For all you who prefer to perform fasted cardio in the morning, here is an easy, customizable recipe to replenish those glycogen stores.
recipeIngredient: ['banana - 1 medium (7" to 7-7/8" long)', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ¾ cup', 'Dymatize ISO-100 - ½ scoop', 'strawberries, sliced - 1 whole', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'granola - 1 tbsp', 'dark chocolate chips - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Slice banana in half lengthwise and lay both sides in a bowl or on a plate.
2. Mix together protein and Greek yogurt and spoon on top of the banana slices.
3. Top bananas and protein mixture with berries, granola, and chocolate chips.

name: Cheddar-Stuffed Burgers
description: Forget the bun! You won't be disappointed by these juicy burgers with a surprise filling of cheddar cheese!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 2 lb', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 8 oz', 'olive oil - ½ cup', 'iceberg lettuce - 8 leaf, large', 'tomatoes - 1 medium whole (2-3/5" dia)', 'Worcestershire sauce - 2½ tbsp', 'avocado - 1', 'pickles - 8 slice', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and pepper to taste in a medium bowl. Blend well.
2. Divide meat into 8 equal portions and shape each into a ball.
3. Poke a deep hole in each ball and fill with 1 ounce of cheese. Mold meat around cheese to enclose, and flatten each burger to a 3/4-inch-thick patty.
4. Cook each burger in olive oil to desired doneness, about 5 minutes per side for medium.
5. Top each burger with avocado, a slice of tomato, and a pickle spear, and wrap in a lettuce leaf.

name: Caesar Chicken Meatballs
description: This creamy Caesar chicken meatball recipe is just plain yummy. Even your kids will like it! With almost 20 grams of protein per meatball, you can enjoy the taste without having to feel guilty about it.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken breast - 1½ lb', 'egg whites - 3', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'caesar dressing, fat-free - 2 tbsp (1 nlea serving)', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven 425 degrees F.
2. Combine all ingredients together in a large bowl.
3. Roll chicken mixture into about 20 meatballs.
4. Place each meatball in a muffin cup and bake for 25-28 minutes, or until golden brown.
5. Once out of the oven, remove from muffin tin.
6. Before serving, squeeze lemon juice over top.

name: Beef With Root Vegetables
description: Lower-cost cuts of beef are well suited to slow cookers, since they require longer cooking times at low temperatures, which also allows the flavors to blend better. As for nutrition, root vegetables contain beta-carotene and other carotenoids, which are the nutrients that give orange produce its bright hue and serve as the raw materials for the body's production of vitamin A. (If you're watching your carbs, you can omit the veggies).
recipeIngredient: ['onion, finely diced - 1 whole', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 2', 'carrot, shredded - 2', 'turnips, peeled and chopped - 2', 'beef, bottom-round - 3 lb', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'flour - 3 tbsp', 'tomato sauce, canned - 15 oz', 'brown sugar - ⅔ cup', 'chili powder - 2 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'ground mustard - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Arrange onion, potatoes, carrots, and turnips in bottom of slow cooker.
2. Season beef with salt and black pepper. Rub flour on the beef. Place the beef on top of the vegetables.
3. In a medium bowl, combine the tomato sauce, brown sugar, chili powder, cumin, and mustard powder, stirring well. Pour the mixture over the beef.
4. Cover and cook on low for 12 hours or on high for 8 hours.

name: Spicy Turkey Meatballs
description: If you like it spicy, this recipe is right up your alley. Chili peppers, jalapenos, and salsa turn ground turkey into a zesty meal. Throw the meatballs in some tomato sauce, or plate them with vegetables and a complex carb. They're also perfect to pack as a lunch.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1½ lb', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2 large', 'raw oats - ¾ cup', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 2 tbsp', 'chili powder - ½ tsp', 'salsa - ¼ cup', 'green pepper, chopped - ½ whole', 'red bell pepper, chopped - ½']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.
2. Using your hands, combine all ingredients together in a large bowl.
3. Form mixture into medium-sized meatballs.
4. Set meatballs in a baking dish.
5. Place dish in oven and cook for 12-15 minutes, or until golden brown.
6. Top with added salsa.

name: Quinoa And Bean Chili
description: This cholesterol-free vegetarian chili is high in fiber and low in saturated fat, a dynamic duo that keeps your blood flowing to your muscles and organs. Plus, one serving packs about one-third of your daily potassium need, which keeps blood pressure in check and your heart and muscles in working order.
recipeIngredient: ['red quinoa - 1 cup', 'kidney beans, canned - 2 14 oz can', 'diced tomatoes - 2 can', 'water - 2½ cup', 'onion, finely diced - 1', 'green pepper, chopped - 1', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 1', 'bay leaf - 1', 'sun-dried tomatoes - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'tomato paste - 1 tbsp', 'vegetable bouillon - 1 tbsp', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'cumin - 2 tsp', 'oregano - 1 tsp, ground', 'garlic powder - 1 tsp', 'ground chipotle powder - 1 tsp', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'salt - ½ tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground']
recipeInstructions:
1. Add all ingredients to the slow cooker.
2. Cover and cook 8-10 hours on low (or 4-5 hours on high).
3. Remove bay leaf and stir well before serving.

name: Italian Chicken Meatballs
description: Bring some delicious Italian flavor into your clean diet with these meatballs. The oregano and basil provide extra flair and the ground chicken will definitely help you make and maintain those lean gains. If you want a complete meal, serve with some steamed vegetables.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken breast - 2½ lb', 'egg whites - 3', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'green pepper, chopped - 1', 'red bell pepper, chopped - 1', 'red onion, diced - 1', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'onion flakes - 1 tbsp', 'basil, dried - 1 tbsp, ground', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, ground', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
2. Using your hands, combine all ingredients together in a large bowl.
3. Form about 12 meatballs from the chicken mixture.
4. Spray a muffin tin with non-stick spray.
5. Place a meatball in each muffin cup.
6. Bake for about 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

name: Salmon Meatball Wrap
description: If you need a power-packed meal to get you through a busy afternoon or evening, here's your recipe. These salmon meatball wraps are full of fats, protein, and complex carbohydrates. If you have specific flavors in mind, add your own spices—it's easy to make this recipe your own!
recipeIngredient: ['canned salmon - 1 can drained solids (total)', 'onion, finely diced - 1', 'egg whites - 2', 'raw oats - ½ cup', 'garlic, minced - ½ clove', 'Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - 3 pita, large (6-1/2" dia)', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine salmon, onion, egg whites, oats, and minced garlic.
2. Form into meatballs and set on a plate.
3. In a skillet over medium heat, heat olive oil.
4. Place salmon meatballs in skillet and cook 4-5 minutes, or until browned.
5. Remove from skillet and place in pitas along with spinach leaves.

name: Cheesy Chicken Meatballs
description: Cheese doesn't make the cut in everybody's macros, but if it fits in yours, you'll love this recipe. The meatballs are creamy, tasty and full of muscle-building protein. If you're not into mozzarella or Parmesan, feel free to use low-fat cheddar cheese.
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken breast - 1½ lb', 'mozzarella cheese - ½ cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - ½ cup', 'oregano - 1 tbsp, ground', 'egg whites - 3', 'raw oats - 1 cup', 'onion, finely diced - ½ whole']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.
2. Using your hands, combine all ingredients.
3. Roll chicken mixture into bite-sized meatballs.
4. Place meatballs on a greased baking sheet.
5. Bake for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown.

name: Thai Peanut Chicken
description: Chicken contains choline, an essential nutrient that supports your heart, liver, and brain, and helps prevent neural-tube defects in early pregnancy; a serving of Thai Peanut Chicken supplies nearly 25 percent of your daily needs. You can substitute boneless chicken breast as well.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken thigh - 8 piece', 'black pepper - 1 dash', 'salsa - ¾ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - ⅓ cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 2 tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Season chicken with fresh ground black pepper and place in slow cooker.
2. In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients except cilantro.
3. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
4. Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken and place on serving platter. Pour sauce over chicken.
5. Garnish with cilantro and lime wedges.

name: Orange Pecan Chicken Salad
description: This fresh, delicious salad is so good you don't even need dressing! The bright taste of blackberries and oranges balances perfectly with the salty crunch of the sunflower seeds and the savory chicken. Eat up!
recipeIngredient: ['blackberries - 7 whole', 'pecans - ¼ cup', 'sunflower seeds - 1 tbsp', 'orange - ¼', 'mixed salad greens - 1 cup', 'chicken breast - 4 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place greens in a large bowl.
2. Cut 1/4 orange into small bite-sized pieces and add to greens.
3. Top salad with the remaining ingredients and enjoy.
4. Tip: I think the juicy fruit and salty sunflower seeds provide enough flavor that this salad doesn't need dressing, but you could add a little olive oil and balsamic vinegar if that's more to your liking.

name: Coconut Almond Cookies
description: I was really happy with the way these turned out! The texture is amazing and the flavor is even better. Have one or two with your evening cuppa and you'll wonder how you ever got along without them.
recipeIngredient: ['coconut butter - ¼ cup', 'natural almond butter - 1 cup', 'coconut, shredded - 1 cup, shredded', 'almond flour - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'egg - 1', 'honey - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. In a large bowl, stir together almond flour, coconut, and baking powder.
3. Add coconut butter, almond butter, vanilla, egg, and honey. Stir.
4. Place dough in round, golf-ball-sized pieces on a baking sheet, and flatten slightly.
5. Bake cookies for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown around the edges.
6. Let cool and enjoy!
7. Note: Feel free to add chocolate chips!

name: "Double Cluck" Portabella Burger
description: Sandwich your meats between some veggies and, voila! You've got the lunch of champions. The chicken breast and Portabella mushroom combination is a tasty, protein-packed bite. You'll also get a fantastic helping of potassium and selenium.
recipeIngredient: ['portabella mushroom caps - 2 piece whole', 'coconut oil - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'chicken breast - 1 piece', 'tomatoes, sliced - 2 slice, thin/small', 'lettuce - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat broiler to high.
2. Pat dry chicken breast with a paper towel and season with salt and pepper.
3. Place on top rack of the broiler, uncovered, and cook each side for approximately 10 minutes or until cooked through. There should be no appearance of pink in the meat.
4. Heat coconut oil in a skillet and sauté mushrooms for 3-5 minutes on each side or until the mushrooms turn golden brown on the top and become tender. Remove and set aside.
5. Fry the egg in the skillet over medium-high heat.
6. Arrange the burger with fresh lettuce, tomato slices, chicken breast and fried egg.

name: Easy Pulled Pork
description: Pork tenderloin has no bone and very little fat to trim. It's also a zinc powerhouse, and one serving provides 20 percent of the suggested daily intake for zinc, which regulates blood sugar levels. Pork contains thiamin, too, which insures your muscles and nervous system work properly.
recipeIngredient: ['onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'brown sugar - 2 tbsp', 'paprika - 1 tbsp', 'salt - 1 tsp', 'black pepper - ½ tsp, ground', 'pork tenderloin - 3 lb', 'apple cider vinegar - 6 tbsp', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 1 cup', 'Worcestershire sauce - 1 tablespoon', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tsp', 'sugar - 1 tsp', 'ground mustard - 1 tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place onion in a slow cooker.
2. In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, paprika, salt, and pepper, mixing thoroughly.
3. Rub the mixture on the meat, coating evenly. Place the pork in the slow cooker.
4. In a medium bowl, combine the vinegar, chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper flakes, sugar, mustard, and cayenne pepper, mixing thoroughly.
5. Add to the slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours.
6. Remove the meat. Using two forks, shred the meat and onions coarsely and discard the fat.

name: Crock Pot Paprika Pot Roast
description: I love crock pot recipes. They're just so convenient! This recipe is also super easy because it's made of ingredients you probably already have in your cabinets and fridge. If you're not a paprika fan, feel free to substitute other spices.
recipeIngredient: ['pot roast - 2⅓ lb', 'red onion, sliced - 1 whole', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ cup', 'tomato sauce, canned - 8 oz', 'coconut oil - 1 tbsp', 'paprika - 1¼ tbsp', 'garlic powder - 1 tbsp', 'onion powder - 1 tbsp', 'Italian seasoning - 1¼ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat coconut oil in a large pan.
2. In a bowl, mix paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, Italian spice, and cayenne pepper.
3. Rub pot roast with mixed spices until well-covered.
4. Place pot roast in pan and brown on all sides.
5. While meat is browning, cut onion into small slivers.
6. Place half of the onion slivers into bottom of crock pot.
7. Add just enough water to crock pot to partially cover onions, then place browned pot roast on top of the onions.
8. Add remaining onion slivers around the pot roast in crock pot.
9. In a small bowl, stir together tomato sauce and balsamic vinegar.
10. Carefully pour mixture over pot roast.
11. Turn crock pot to high and cook for approximately 4-1/2 hours.
12. Tip: All slow cookers are a bit different, so reference your manual and a cook-time chart if you're unsure or if your pot roast is bigger or smaller than 2-1/3 pounds.

name: Double Beef Chili
description: A good chili recipe should be a staple in everyone's kitchen. This one is particularly awesome because it's rich, flavorful, and has lots of muscle-building protein. Make a whole batch and you'll have healthy meals for an entire week!
recipeIngredient: ['ground chicken breast - 1 lb', 'lean ground beef - 2 lb', 'pinto beans - 15 oz', 'black beans, drained and rinsed - 1 16 oz can', 'kidney beans, canned - 1 14 oz can', 'diced tomatoes - 2 can', 'tomato sauce, canned - 1 28 oz can', 'water - 1 cup', 'red wine vinegar - 1 cup', 'carrot, shredded - 2', 'stalk celery, finely diced - 3 stalk, medium', 'onion, finely chopped - 1', 'Italian seasoning - 2 tbsp', 'garlic, minced - 1 tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brown sausage and beef, then add to a large pot.
2. Sauté onion and add to pot.
3. Add canned tomatoes and beans to pot.
4. Add carrots and celery to pot.
5. Add wine, water, and spices to the pot.
6. Heat and let simmer for at least two hours.
7. Eat up!
8. Tip(s):
When choosing your tomatoes and beans, check the label for added sugar or corn syrup.
Get creative! Add more veggies, curry spice, or anything else you might like.
Leftovers taste even better the day after!

name: Vanilla Butter Coffee
description: I know, I know, butter in a cup of joe might seem really strange. I was doubtful myself—until I tried it! The butter takes some of the bitter bite out of the coffee, and the vanilla adds a little warmth and sweetness. This coffee has a thicker, more robust mouthfeel, which may take a little getting used to.
recipeIngredient: ['coffee - 1 cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'butter, without salt (melted) - ½ tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Brew a cup of black coffee to your desired strength.
2. Add 1 tsp of vanilla.
3. Add butter, stir and enjoy.

name: Fried-Egg-Topped Veggie Burger with Iced Coffee
description: Move over, Egg McMuffin. Choose this healthier option and have a transportable breakfast perfect for on-the-go morning meals. It's also a great source of B-12, containing 1.5 micrograms of the recommended daily dosage of 2.4 micrograms.
recipeIngredient: ['coffee - 1 cup', 'nonfat milk - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'Sara Lee whole-wheat thin-style bun - 1 bun', 'garden veggie burger - 1 patty']
recipeInstructions: 1. Heat veggie patty and egg separately and place on whole wheat bun. Pour yourself a cup of coffee over ice and enjoy!

name: Kale and Tofu Omelet
description: To help meet the recommended intake for calcium, consider adding calcium-fortified soy and cereals, as well as calcium-rich milk, yogurt, and green vegetables like broccoli, bok choy, and kale. This omelet contains tofu, which has 16 grams of calcium per quarter block.
recipeIngredient: ['tofu, firm - ¼ block', 'egg - 1 whole', 'egg whites - 2', 'kale, diced - 1 cup', 'reduced fat cheddar cheese, shredded - 30 g', 'skim milk - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat eggs and mix in kale and tofu to create omelet.
2. Top omelet with cheese.
3. Pour yourself a glass of milk and enjoy!

name: Turkey Avocado Skewers
description: If you're watching your carb intake, these skewers are a great choice. The healthy fats from the avocado and the lean protein from the turkey are a perfect way to meet your nutritional goals without any extra or empty calories.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 2', 'low-fat deli turkey - 10 oz (1 serving)', 'Walden Farms Raspberry Vinaigrette - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Peel and chop avocados into triangular wedges.
2. Roll turkey slices and cut into halves.
3. Alternate avocado and turkey pieces on the skewers (8 skewers).
4. Plate and drizzle with raspberry vinaigrette.

name: Cornflakes with Strawberries
description: This bowl of goodness contains 181 IU of vitamin D, about 20 percent of the recommended daily value. Following calcium, vitamin D is the next most important micronutrient for bone health.
recipeIngredient: ['corn flakes - 1½ cup (1 nlea serving)', 'skim milk - ½ cup', 'strawberries, sliced - 100 g']
recipeInstructions: 1. Pour yourself a bowl of cereal and enjoy!

name: Paleo Bread
description: Grab your spear and fur cape—it's time to head back to your caveman roots. Try this easy, delicious Paleo-inspired bread recipe. It's so good you might just be inspired to hunt a mammoth!
recipeIngredient: ['ground almonds - ¼ cup', 'cashews, crushed - ¼ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - ¼ cup', 'macadamia nuts - ¼ cup', 'black chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'pumpkin seeds - 2 tbsp', 'zucchini, sliced - ½', 'carrot, shredded - 1', 'psyllium husk powder - 1½ tbsp', 'olive oil - 1½ tbsp', 'egg - 4', 'honey - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - 2 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
2. Blend almonds, cashews, walnuts, and macadamia nuts into a coarse mixture.
3. Mix nut mixture and the rest of the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
4. Line a loaf pan with olive oil or coconut oil spray.
5. Pour batter evenly into the loaf pan.
6. Bake bread for 40 minutes.
7. Remove bread from loaf pan and enjoy!
8. Fun toppings: I top the bread with almond butter and 88% cacao bar pieces (OMG), eggs and avocado, bacon and kale—the combinations are endless! For a sweeter option, you can add a mashed banana, natural unsweetened apple sauce, or any sort of fruit.

name: Sausage and Egg Sandwich with OJ
description: Nothing says homestyle goodness like the combination of eggs, sausage, and toast. Vegetarians don't have to miss out on this classic meal; a little creative adaptation is all it takes! In addition to being a protein powerhouse, this take on an open-faced breakfast sandwich of vegan sausage, eggs, and toast provides 26 milligrams of iron—a hefty percentage of the 30 milligrams recommended for women, and almost twice the 14 milligrams suggested for men.
recipeIngredient: ['vegan sausage patties - 2 patty', 'egg - 1 whole', 'multi-grain bread - 1 slice regular', 'orange juice, fresh squeezed - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Heat sausage patties and eggs to make sandwich. Pour yourself a glass of OJ and enjoy!

name: Yogurt Parfait with Wheat Germ and Berries
description: All those weights lifted and miles logged can increase zinc loss, putting vegetarian athletes at even higher risk for zinc deficiency. This meal can help! Add some wheat germ and fruit to your protein-rich yogurt, and you've got a meal that hits the spot—not to mention one that contains 3.9 milligrams of the 15 milligrams of zinc needed for men and 13 milligrams needed for women.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'wheat germ - 2 tbsp', 'blackberries - 50 g', 'raspberries - 50 g']
recipeInstructions: 1. Assemble and enjoy!

name: Pumpkin Protein Oat Bars
description: These yummy bars are perfect for a post-workout treat. Pack a couple in your gym bag so you have easy access after you're done training. Seriously, these bars are so good you'll make them a permanent part of your Sunday food preparation.
recipeIngredient: ['pumpkin, canned - 1 cup', 'raw oats - 1½ cup', 'vanilla protein powder - 2 scoop(s)', 'powdered Stevia - ½ cup', 'smooth peanut butter - ½ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'cinnamon - 1 tsp', 'carob chips - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine oats, protein powder, Splenda, cinnamon, and carob chips.
3. Add pumpkin, vanilla, and peanut butter, and thoroughly stir until the mixture has a cookie-batter consistency.
4. Pour batter on a greased or foiled cake pan. Distribute evenly.
5. Bake for 20-25 minutes and enjoy!

name: Chocolate Pudding Pie
description: This is one of the simplest recipes imaginable. All you need is five ingredients and a mixing bowl. Easy as it is, this recipe tastes so good. It's cool and creamy, but the best part is that it's full of muscle-building protein!
recipeIngredient: ['milk, fat-free - 1 cup', 'sugar-free fat-free chocolate pudding powder - 1 box', 'fat-free whipped cream - 4 oz', 'casein protein powder - 2 scoop(s)']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine pudding powder and casein (chocolate flavor).
2. Stir in milk and Cool Whip until mixture is thick.
3. Pour mixture into chocolate pie crust and let it cool in fridge for 30 minutes before serving.
4. Note: Try adding sprinkles, a spoonful of Cool Whip, or mini chocolate chips as a delicious garnish. Or, if you have a tight rein on your carbs, do away with the pie crust and make an epic chocolate pudding.

name: Protein Pumpkin Pecan Pie
description: The holidays don't live up to their name without some pumpkin pie. This year, bring this healthier recipe to your family celebration. No one will be able to tell the difference between this amazing pie and the sugar-laden one they're used to having.
recipeIngredient: ['cinnamon - 1½ tsp', 'ground cloves - 1 tsp', 'allspice, ground - ½ tsp', 'ground ginger - ½ tsp', 'salt - 1 pinch', 'pumpkin, canned - 2 cup', 'egg whites - ½ cup', 'milk, fat-free - ½ cup', 'Splenda, brown sugar blend - ¼ cup', 'vanilla whey protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'pecans - 1 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Combine cinnamon, cloves, allspice, ginger, salt, Splenda, and protein powder (vanilla, cinnamon, or pumpkin flavor) in a bowl.
3. Add eggs, pumpkin, and milk to the bowl and stir.
4. Pour pumpkin mixture into the pie crust and spread evenly. Arrange pecans on top.
5. Bake for 45-55 minutes and enjoy.

name: Protein Chai Latte
description: Chilly winter evenings often call for a cozy blanket and a hot, tasty beverage. No need to waste carbs and calories on a sugary drink. Try this smooth, protein-packed tea latte that will make any regular evening special.
recipeIngredient: ['casein protein powder - 1 scoop(s)', 'decaf chai spice mix - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Boil water.
2. Pour water into mug and add casein (cinnamon flavor) and chai spice mix.
3. Stir until well-combined.
4. Sip and enjoy!
5. Note: Some types of protein do not respond well to hot water. I have found casein works the best, and even creates a frothy latte layer on top. Mmmmmmm!

name: Homemade Seed Cereal
description: This seed combo makes for a great hearty breakfast cereal, works as a crunchy topping for your yogurt, and can add a bit of texture to your morning smoothie. Add dried fruit for that extra pop of sweet or tart, or add a few walnuts for an even greater healthy fat boost.
recipeIngredient: ['black chia seeds - 1 tbsp', 'hemp seeds - 1 tbsp', 'buckwheat - 1 tbsp', 'dried cranberries - 1 tbsp', 'skim milk - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix ingredients together and enjoy!
2. Alternate milk options: almond, soy, coconut, or cashew milk

name: Apple Pie Protein Waffles
description: Embrace the taste of the season with these fruit-filled, protein-packed waffles!
recipeIngredient: ['vanilla whey protein powder - ½ cup(s)', 'rolled oats - ½ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'milk, fat-free - 2 tbsp', 'ground almonds - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon - 2 tsp', 'banana - 1', 'apples - 1', 'egg - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all of the ingredients in a food processor until they create a thick batter.
2. Preheat your waffle iron, and add some low-cal cooking spray to it.
3. Cook your batter in your waffle iron. Done!
4. Note: substitute 4 egg whites if you'd like lower fat.

name: Acai Boost Smoothie
description: What's all of this talk about acai? Although acai berries have been around for a long time, they've recently gained popularity due to their powerful health benefits. Acai berries, which are found primarily in the Amazon, are extremely high in anthocyanins, antioxidants that lower cholesterol levels in the blood.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 1', 'frozen blueberries - 1½ cup', 'fresh coconut meat - ½ cup, shredded', 'organic acai juice - 1½ cup']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients in blender. Blend on high until smooth.

name: Sunflower Chocolate Smoothie
description: Sunflower seed butter is a fabulous substitute for any butter spread. It's nut- and gluten-free, making it a great solution for people with allergies and dietary restrictions. It's a great nutritional source of fiber, zinc, iron, magnesium, and vitamin E, all of which may help lower blood pressure and protect your body against damaging free radicals which cause chronic diseases.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 2', 'raw cacao powder - 1 tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1½ cup', 'medjool dates - 4 date, pitted', 'sunflower seed butter - 2 tbsp']
recipeInstructions: 1. Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high until smooth.

name: Never Beet Smoothie
description: Even though beets are low-calorie foods, they are packed with fiber, vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. This delicious root is a key source of glycine betaine, which helps lower homo-cysteine levels in the blood to keep it from clotting and developing problems such as coronary heart disease, stroke, and vascular diseases.
recipeIngredient: ['beets - ⅓ cup', 'banana, frozen - 1', 'frozen mixed berries - 1 cup', 'baby spinach - 1 cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1½ cup', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'black chia seeds - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Bring a small pot of water to a boil. Boil beets for 5 minutes.
2. Remove from heat, rinse with cold water, and let cool. Remove skin.
3. Place all ingredients in blender. Blend on high until smooth.

name: Pumpkin Pie Smoothie
description: Pumpkin pie is a seasonal favorite in many homes. The only problem with traditional pumpkin pie is that it tends to have a high amount of added sugars and fats. This smoothie recipe skips the bad-for-you additives and sticks with natural sweeteners like maple syrup and fruit to keep things clean and give your body what it craves without sacrificing taste.
recipeIngredient: ['banana, frozen - 1', 'pumpkin puree - ½ cup', 'unsweetened almond milk - 1½ cup', 'maple syrup - 1 tsp', 'vanilla extract - ¼ tsp', 'ground ginger - ⅛ tsp', 'nutmeg - ⅛ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place all ingredients in blender, except for the cinnamon (reserved for garnish). Blend on high until smooth.
2. Pour smoothie in a glass and garnish with the reserved cinnamon. Enjoy!

name: Chicken With White Wine Tomato Sauce
description: This works perfectly as a quick meal, but it's so good it doubles as homemade gourmet when you have guests. Serve with a baked potato or side of your choice.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 12 oz', 'pesto - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - ⅛ cup', 'red bell pepper - 1', 'onion, sliced - ½', 'garlic, minced - 1 clove', 'White wine - ½ cup', 'tomatoes - 1', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - ¼ cup', 'mozzarella cheese - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by brushing the chicken breasts with pesto.
2. Next, heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Add red peppers and onions along with garlic and continue to cook until slightly tender.
4. Place chicken into the pan and cook until browned and no longer pink inside.
5. Add in the tomatoes and white wine, turn down to low heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
6. Finally, sprinkle with Parmesan and mozzarella cheese, cooking for 30-60 longer or until cheese is slightly melted.
7. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken and Chickpea Stew
description: This recipe is high in fiber as well as high-quality protein. It's easy to make and packed with micronutrients, so it's great to regularly incorporate into your diet. People often overlook chickpeas when planning a nutrition plan, but they're nutrient dense and go well in myriad recipes.
recipeIngredient: ['stalk celery, finely diced - 1 cup', 'carrot, shredded - ¾ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - ½ cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 5 whole', 'sweet potato, cut into cubes - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'low-sodium chicken stock - 4 cup', 'low-sodium tomato sauce - 3 cup', 'wild rice, cooked - 1½ cup', 'chicken breast - 16 oz']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat a large casserole dish or pot over medium heat.
2. Spray dish lightly with cooking spray and add carrot, onion, sweet potatoes, and mushrooms.
3. Cook for about 10 minutes, or until tender.
4. Add in garlic and cook for 30 more seconds, stirring constantly.
5. Add the broth, tomato sauce, and chickpeas.
6. Reduce to low heat and cook for 10 minutes.
7. Add in the chicken, and cook for 5-10 minutes or until no longer pink inside.
8. Serve immediately.

name: Creamy Parmesan Chicken
description: This creamy chicken dish provides the great cheesy taste you crave without mounds of extra, unhealthful fats.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 12 oz', 'low-sodium chicken stock - ¼ cup', 'garlic, minced - ½ tsp', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'low-fat parmesan cheese - ⅛ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by heating the chicken broth in a pan over medium heat.
2. Add in garlic along with chicken breasts, cooking until no longer pink inside, 8-10 minutes, flipping a few times throughout the cooking process.
3. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise with parmesan cheese.
4. Once chicken is finished, remove and place on a baking sheet and smother with sauce.
5. Place under the broiler for 1-2 minutes or until cheese is melted and chicken is slightly browned.
6. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken Stew with Vegetables
description: This chicken stew is loaded with antioxidants and micronutrients. It makes a great meal choice any night of the week. You can also make a massive batch and freeze some to eat later!
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'chicken breast - 12 oz', 'zucchini, sliced - 2 cup', 'carrot, shredded - 1 cup', 'red bell pepper - 1 cup, chopped', 'diced yellow bell pepper - 1 cup', 'green pepper, chopped - 1 cup', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'oregano - ¾ tsp, ground', 'garlic, minced - 2 clove', 'white beans - 2 cup', 'low-sodium chicken broth - 2 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat the oil in a large pan.
2. Once bubbling, add in onions, carrots, mushrooms, and peppers along with garlic; saute for 3-5 minutes.
3. Next, add in chicken and continue to cook for 4-5 minutes.
4. Add remaining ingredients to the pan and reduce to low heat, covering and simmering for 30 minutes.
5. Serve immediately.

name: Creamy Chicken Pitas
description: Ditch the brown bag and try this more adventurous lunch! The tangy, sweet tastes of the add-ins make these pitas completely different from what you tried in the past.
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'white vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'Splenda - 1 tbsp', 'stalk celery, finely diced - ¼ cup', 'dried cranberries - 2 tbsp', 'walnut, pieces - 2 tbsp', 'spinach - 2 cup', 'Whole-Wheat Pita Bread - 2']
recipeInstructions:
1. Begin by combining together the white vinegar, Splenda, and mayonnaise.
2. Add the chicken (pre-cooked) and celery in and stir until coated.
3. Sprinkle with dried cranberries and walnuts, stirring until mixed and then spoon into whole wheat pitas.
4. Top with spinach leaves and then serve.

name: Cashew Chicken with Baby Corn
description: This dish is filled with healthful fats and muscle-building protein but relatively low in carbs. This recipe will help you combat hunger and provide a dose of long-lasting energy.
recipeIngredient: ['low-sodium chicken broth - ½ cup', 'oyster sauce - 2 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'Splenda - 1 tbsp', 'corn starch - 1 tbsp', 'white vinegar - 1 tbsp', 'olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'chicken breast, cut into cubes - 12 oz', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'red bell pepper - 1 medium (approx 2-3/4" long, 2-1/2 dia.)', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'baby corn - ½ cup', 'green onion, sliced - 2', 'cashews, chopped - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine together the chicken broth, oyster sauce, soy sauce, Splenda, cornstarch, and white vinegar and set aside.
2. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Add in chicken breast chunks, stir-frying for 6-8 minutes.
4. Add peppers, mushrooms, and baby corn, cooking for 2-3 minutes longer.
5. Add combined mixture from step 1 to the skillet, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 10-12 minutes.
6. Sprinkle with cashews and green onions, toss, and then serve.

name: Chicken and Chickpea Stew
description: This recipe is high in fiber as well as high-quality protein. It's easy to make and packed with micronutrients, so it's great to regularly incorporate into your diet. People often overlook chickpeas when planning a nutrition plan, but they're nutrient dense and go well in myriad recipes.

name: Chicken Pad Thai
description: This chicken pad Thai recipe offers a creamy flavor that will please any peanut butter lover's taste buds. It is higher in carbohydrates and calories than the other recipes here, so it's best for those who don't mind the extra calories. Use it to build muscle in a hustle!
recipeIngredient: ['whole-wheat pasta - 2 cup spaghetti', 'chicken breast, cut into cubes - 9 oz', 'mushrooms, sliced - 1 cup', 'diced yellow bell pepper - ½ cup', 'fish sauce - 1 tbsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'Splenda - 1 tbsp', 'crushed red pepper flakes - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Prepare the pasta according to package directions.
2. Next, heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Add the chicken and cook for 2-3 minutes.
4. Mix together the fish sauce, peanut butter, Splenda, and chili flakes.
5. Pour over chicken, cover, and simmer for 3-4 minutes.
6. Top with cilantro before serving.

name: Tangy Pineapple Chicken
description: This tangy pineapple chicken is a great way to satisfy your sweet cravings, hit your protein goals, and stick to your diet. Serve over a bed of brown or wild rice if you want the extra carbs for more performance fuel.
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'diced yellow bell pepper - 1', 'chicken breast - 12 oz', 'low-sugar ketchup - 3 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'Splenda - 3 tbsp', 'pineapple, raw - ½ cup', 'pineapple juice - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a pan on medium heat.
2. Add in onions and peppers; saute until golden brown.
3. Add chicken and continue to stir-fry until no longer pink inside.
4. Combine together the ketchup, soy sauce, Splenda, and pineapple juice and add to the pan.
5. Lower heat and cover, simmering for 20 minutes.
6. Before serving, top with pineapple.

name: Chicken Pad Thai

recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 2 tbsp', 'onion, finely chopped - 1 cup', 'diced yellow bell pepper - 1 whole', 'chicken breast - 12 oz', 'low-sugar ketchup - 3 tbsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tbsp', 'Splenda - 3 tbsp', 'pineapple, raw - ½ cup', 'pineapple juice - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:

4. Combine together the ketchup, soy sauce, Splenda, and pineapple juice and add to the pan.
5. Lower heat and cover, simmering for 20 minutes.

name: Chocolate Avocado Protein Brownies
description: What's better than a decadently rich chocolate brownie? A decadently rich chocolate protein brownie! This recipe uses good ol' fashioned baking ingredients such as sugar, flour, and vanilla extract, but supercharges the brownies with the addition of protein powder. The avocado adds an extra creaminess as well as a dose of heart-healthy omega-3s.
recipeIngredient: ['flour - 1½ cup', 'sugar - 1 cup', 'Dymatize Elite 100% Whey Protein, Chocolate Cake Batter - ¾ cup', 'baking powder - 1 tsp', 'table salt - 1 tsp', 'avocado - 1 cup, pureed', 'soy milk, light - ½ cup', 'water - ⅓ cup', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly grease a 9x13 baking dish. Set aside.
2. In a medium-sized mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, protein powder, baking powder, and salt until well combined. Set aside.
3. In a large mixing bowl, beat together avocado, soy milk, water, and vanilla extract.
4. Add the dry ingredients, mixing until well combined.
5. Pour into baking dish and bake for 30-35 minutes, or until the top is no longer shiny and a toothpick inserted into the center emerges with only a few crumbs.
6. Allow brownies to cool completely in the pan, then cut into squares and serve.

name: Snickerdoodle Protein Flan
description: Flan is one of those frequently overlooked desserts that doesn't get made at home often enough. Not only is flan one of the creamiest little dishes of caramel heaven you can imagine, it's also incredibly easy to make. Of course, your guests will be really impressed by your mad baking skills, so you don't need to tell them there are only three steps in this whole recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['flan, caramel custard mix - 1 package (3 oz)', 'milk (2% fat) - 2 cup', 'Dymatize Elite 100% Whey Protein, Snickerdoodle - 1 scoop']
recipeInstructions:
1. Open caramel sauce packet included in the Jell-O flan. Pour evenly into 4 small cups or 1 small bowl.
2. Stir flan mix into 2 cups milk in small saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Pull pot off heat and mix in protein powder.
3. Pour slowly over caramel. Refrigerate 1 hour or until set (2 hours if preparing in bowl). To unmold, run small metal spatula around edge of each custard, invert onto plate, and shake slightly to loosen. Store leftovers in refrigerator.
4. Note: For best results, use 2% or whole milk.

name: No-Churn Vanilla Protein Ice Cream
description: You don't need an ice-cream machine to make this old-fashioned treat at home! This recipe channels the rich vanilla flavor of a cupcake and transforms it into a frozen scoop of creamy deliciousness. Top your favorite dessert with a scoop, or enjoy this by itself with some berries on top. Just beware of ice-cream headaches!
recipeIngredient: ['sweetened condensed milk - 14 fl oz', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'Dymatize Elite 100% Whey Protein, Vanilla Cupcake - 1 scoop', 'heavy whipping cream - 2 cup, whipped']
recipeInstructions:
1. Pour sweetened condensed milk into a large bowl, and mix in the vanilla extract.
2. Using a mixer, whip the heavy cream and protein powder together until the mixture holds stiff, billowy peaks, about 3 minutes.
3. In a separate bowl, gently mix a scoop of the whipped cream into the condensed milk. This "lightens" the condensed milk and makes it easier to fold into the rest of the whipped cream.
4. Gently fold the rest of the whipped cream into the condensed milk. At first, it will look very lumpy. As you continue to fold, the mixture will smooth out and become soft and silky. Stop when you see just a few small lumps here and there; overmixing will cause it to deflate.
5. Place the mixture into a freezer container. Smooth the top with a spatula, then press a piece of wax paper against the surface to prevent ice crystals from forming.
6. Freeze for at least six hours, or up to 2 weeks: The ice cream will become more firm the longer you let it freeze. For best texture and flavor, eat within two weeks.

name: Chocolate Protein Yogurt With Berries
description: If you're looking for a creative way to kick your morning yogurt up a notch, this protein yogurt is just the thing you start your day off right. The Chocolate Cake Batter protein powder adds a sweeter element, while the granola gives the entire recipe a satisfying crunch.
recipeIngredient: ['nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1½ cup', 'Dymatize Elite 100% Whey Protein, Chocolate Cake Batter - 1 scoop', 'mixed berries - ¼ cup', 'water - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a mixing bowl, mix protein powder and water thoroughly with a whisk or blender, then add yogurt and blend.
2. Place yogurt in a cup and top with berries and granola (optional).

name: Shredded Chicken Enchiladas
description: Usually, I leave enchiladas off the menu. They're smothered in cheese and full of grease—not what I would choose as a healthy option. However, I know that many people love enchiladas, so I took my crack at a healthier version. After this successful experiment, I came out an enchilada believer!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 2 piece', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - 1 cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'green chilies, diced - 4½ oz', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'diced tomatoes - 1 can', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'garlic, minced - 4 clove', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'balsamic vinegar - ¼ tsp', 'powdered Stevia - ½ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'corn tortilla - 6 whole', 'reduced-fat Mexican cheese - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
2. In a large pan, heat olive oil for one minute on medium heat.
3. Add garlic, onion, and spices and sauté for 5 minutes.
4. Add tomatoes, Stevia, vinegar, and cilantro.
5. Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes.
6. In a mixing bowl mix together cooked and shredded chicken, Greek yogurt, lime juice, green chills, cumin, salt, and pepper.
7. Spray 9x9 baking dish with non-stick spray.
8. Spread a thin layer of enchilada sauce on the bottom of the dish.
9. Spoon chicken mixture into tortillas, roll each one, and place in dish seam-side down.
10. Pour remaining sauce over the top of rolled tortillas, sprinkle with cheese, and then garnish with cilantro.
11. Bake for 20 minutes.

name: Steak Tacos
description: With just a few adjustments, you can have some delicious and satisfying steak tacos without the side dish of guilt!
recipeIngredient: ['flank steak - 8 oz', 'lime juice - 1 tbsp', 'garlic powder - ½ tbsp', 'paprika - ½ tbsp', 'black pepper - ½ tbsp, ground', 'onion powder - ½ tbsp', 'cumin - ½ tbsp', 'cayenne pepper - ½ tbsp', 'corn tortilla - 4 whole', 'cotija cheese - 4 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Marinate the steak with lime juice, garlic powder, paprika, black pepper, onion powder, cumin, and cayenne pepper. Allow to marinate for at least 30 minutes.
2. Grill steak to desired temperature.
3. Let steak rest for 3 minutes and slice thinly against the grain.
4. Assemble tacos with thinly sliced steak, 1 tbsp light guacamole, and 1 tsp cotija cheese.

name: Guacamole Lite
description: The standard homemade guacamole is not unhealthy by any means. It provides a healthy dose of unsaturated fats, vitamin C, and vitamin E. However, it packs hefty a calorie punch. Because this version is a little lighter, you don't have to be limited to a measly portion size. One avocado can go a long way! Serve as a dip with whole-grain homemade pita chips, as a meal topper, or with cucumber and sliced bell pepper for a sodium-free option.
recipeIngredient: ['avocado - 1', 'cucumber, chopped - ½', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'tomatoes - 1', 'cilantro - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, add all ingredients.
2. Mix together until all ingredients are well-combined.

name: Smoky Snapper with Avocado Verde Sauce
description: Serve this when you need some healthy fats and protein, want to impress your dinner guests, or need to add a spicy Mexican kick to your regular dinner fare.
recipeIngredient: ['snapper - 2 fillet', 'paprika - 1 tsp', 'cumin - 1 tsp', 'chili powder - 1 tsp', 'avocado - ½', 'verde sauce - ¼ cup', 'lime juice - 2 tbsp', 'tomatoes - ½', 'cilantro - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Set broiler to high.
2. Sprinkle both sides of fish with paprika, cumin, and chili powder.
3. Broil each side for 5 minutes, or until cooked through.
4. In a food processor, blend avocado, verde sauce, and half of lime juice.
5. In a small bowl, combine chopped tomatoes, cilantro, and the rest of the lime juice.
6. Top cooked snapper with avocado sauce and tomato relish.

name: Coffee and Pecan Protein Bread
description: Looking for a new way to add some protein to your morning meal? Add a dunk-friendly treat to your cup of joe with this protein-rich recipe!
recipeIngredient: ['ground almonds - ½ cup', 'natural almond butter - 2 tbsp', 'egg - 1 whole', 'vanilla whey protein powder - ¼ cup(s)', 'powdered Stevia - 2 tbsp', 'freshly brewed espresso - 2 tbsp', 'unsweetened applesauce - 1 tbsp', 'pecans, chopped - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Blend all ingredients except for the pecans in a food processor. Add pecans after blending in order to retain the crunchy texture.
2. Bake at 320 F (160 C) for 10-15 minutes, being careful not to exceed the 15-minute mark. Check on the baked good after 8 minutes, especially if you bake the batter in muffin cups! As soon as a knife comes out clean, remove your treat from the oven.
3. Enjoy with almond butter on top, or if you're a fan of icing, with some protein frosting. Just be sure to let the bread cool before you add the topping.
4. Note: You can also use brown rice syrup in place of Stevia or sweetener of choice.

name: Crab Burgers
description: Any meat can be pounded into a patty! Crab is a quality source of lean protein, and it offers a nice change of pace from the usual chicken or beef. This recipe pairs crab with avocado for a creamy burger bursting in flavor and stuffed with healthy fat.
recipeIngredient: ['crab meat - 3 cup', 'green onion, chopped - 4', 'garlic, pureed - ½ tsp', 'ginger, pureed - ½ tsp', 'light soy sauce - 2 tsp', 'avocado - 1', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 3', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 3 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a large bowl, combine the lump crab meat, green onions, pureed garlic and ginger, light soy sauce, avocado, lemon juice, and oats.
2. Once well mixed, heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
3. Place the burgers in the skillet and cook for 4-5 minutes per side or until golden and slightly crispy.
4. Serve on top of the buns with some mayonnaise, lettuce, tomato, along with a cucumber if desired.

name: Pineapple Turkey Burgers
description: Fruit is unnecessarily ignored at many barbecues and burger bonanzas. Let's right that wrong! This unique pineapple turkey burger finally brings fruit and meat together. The pineapple adds sweet juice to the turkey and will engage your taste buds in a whirl of flavor. Pineapple contains beneficial digestive enzymes, as well.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'raw oats - 3 tbsp', 'pineapple juice - 2 tbsp', 'pineapple, raw - ½ cup', 'onion, finely chopped - 2 tbsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 2 oz', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 4', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 4 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ground turkey, oats, pineapple juice, pineapple chunks, with diced onion.
2. Heat olive oil in a skillet (or on a grill) on medium heat and once bubbling, lay the burgers in the skillet.
3. Cook for 5-7 minutes per side or until cooked.
4. Once there's about one minute left on the second side, layer the cheese on top and cook until melted.
5. Serve on top of the buns with mayonnaise, lettuce, tomato, and onion slices if desired.

name: Tomato Turkey Burgers
description: This turkey burger delivers a pleasing combination of fresh flavors. The cheese pairs with tomatoes to create an experience you won't forget. This recipe is high in protein and low in fat, a great option for people on a cutting diet.
recipeIngredient: ['ground 99% fat-free turkey breast - 1 lb', 'fat-free mozzarella cheese - 3 oz', 'tomato, diced - 1', 'garlic, minced - 1 tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'cucumber, chopped - 1 cup slices', 'fat-free mayonnaise - 4 tbsp', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 4']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ground turkey, shredded cheese, tomato, with salsa and garlic.
2. Once ingredients are well combined, form into patties.
3. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
4. Cook patties for 4-5 minutes per side or until done.
5. Remove from skillet and lay on top of whole wheat bun, smeared with fat-free mayonnaise and layered with the cucumber.

name: Homemade Beef Burgers
description: If a beef burger is the only burger in your mind, this recipe will bring your belly inner peace. The recipe calls for extra-lean ground beef, and grilling on a barbecue will further reduce the fat content. This burger packs a protein punch!
recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1 lb', 'egg whites - 2', 'onion, finely diced - ½', 'green onion, chopped - 2', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'Worcestershire sauce - 2 tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'low-sugar barbecue sauce - 1 tbsp', 'whole-wheat bun - 4']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ground beef, egg whites, onion, green onions, dry oats, with Worcestershire sauce, and soy sauce.
2. Form into four patties and place on a heated grill.
3. Brush patties with barbecue sauce as they cook. Flip patties every few minutes until cooked to desired specs.
4. Serve on top of the bun with lettuce, tomato, and mustard if desired.

name: Sesame Salmon Burgers
description: This burger is loaded with heart-healthy fats that support lean body composition and offer a bevy of additional benefits to your skin, circulation, and overall health. Many people reach for canned tuna for fish-based burgers, but canned salmon can work even better.
recipeIngredient: ['canned salmon - 1', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'lemon juice - 1 tbsp', 'ginger, minced - 1 tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'sesame seeds - ¼ cup', 'fat-free mayonnaise - ¼ cup', 'olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'whole-wheat bun - 3 serving', 'spinach - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Remove bones and skin from salmon.
2. Combine the salmon, oats, lemon juice, ginger, soy sauce, and mayonnaise in a bowl.
3. Form into patties and then press sesame seeds into them.
4. Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat and cook patties, 2-3 minutes per side.
5. Serve on the whole wheat bun with spinach leaves and mustard if desired.

recipeIngredient: ['lean ground beef - 1 lb', 'egg whites - 2', 'onion, finely diced - ½ whole', 'green onion, chopped - 2', 'raw oats - ¼ cup', 'Worcestershire sauce - 2 tsp', 'light soy sauce - 1 tbsp', 'low-sugar barbecue sauce - 1 tbsp', 'whole-wheat hamburger buns - 4']
recipeInstructions:
1. Combine ground beef, egg whites, onion, green onions, dry oats, with Worcestershire sauce, and soy sauce.
2. Form into four patties and place on a heated grill.
3. Brush patties with barbecue sauce as they cook. Flip patties every few minutes until cooked to desired specs.
4. Serve on top of the bun with lettuce, tomato, and mustard if desired.

name: Chocolate Pumpkin Bark
description: Move over, peppermint bark! This season, swap that stuff for some squash—or pumpkin, to be exact. This is another guilt-free dessert to help you cheat your cheat and stay committed to your goals. It may be low in calories, fat, and sugar, but it's high in protein and big on taste!
recipeIngredient: ['olive oil - 1 tbsp', 'Gaspari Nutrition MyoFusion Advanced Protein, Milk Chocolate - ½ scoop', 'pumpkin, canned - 1 tsp', 'Walden Farms Syrup - 1 tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a small bowl, mix the extra virgin coconut oil and Myofusion Elite Protein.
2. Spread the mixture thinly on a plate covered in plastic wrap. Don't worry about being neat and tidy.
3. In another small dish, mix the pumpkin and syrup. Layer this on top of the chocolate base. Add swirls for decoration.
4. Place in the freezer for 10-20 minutes. It sets quickly.
5. Once it's set, break the bark into pieces. Eat immediately before it melts, or store the rest in the freezer for later!

name: Almond-Coconut Waffle
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['almond flour - 1½ cup', 'coconut - ¼ cup, shredded', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'egg - 2 whole', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'honey - 1 tbsp', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn on waffle maker.
2. Mix all ingredients.
3. Pour mixture into waffle maker and cook until machine beeps.
4. Top with coconut flakes and fresh raspberries. For additional sweetness, add a bit of honey.

name: Healthy Ice Cream
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potatoes, peeled - 1', 'coconut milk, canned, full-fat - 12 oz', 'maple syrup - 1 tbsp', 'egg yolks - 2', 'cinnamon - 2 tbsp', 'vanilla extract - 1 tsp', 'nutmeg - ⅛ tsp', 'salt - ⅛ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place ice cream attachment in your freezer and leave over night.
2. Place sweet potato and coconut milk in food processor. Process to a puréed consistency.
3. Add vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, sea salt, and egg yolks. Process until all ingredients are well-combined.
4. Pour mixture in a mixing bowl and refrigerate for at least two hours.
5. Once mixture is cold, add it to your ice cream maker and follow instructions.
6. Let churn for 25-30 minutes.

name: Hearty Paleo Juice
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['Carrots, raw - 2', 'beets, raw - 2', 'apples, red - 1 medium']
recipeInstructions:
1. Scrub beets with vegetable brush to remove any dirt.
2. Place beets in a large pot with enough water to cover them.
3. Bring water to a boil and simmer for 25 minutes.
4. Drain hot water and rinse beets with cold water.
5. While beets are in cold water, peel their skins.
6. Trim ends off beets and cut into slices.
7. Peel carrots and apple.
8. Slice apple and cut each carrot in half.
9. Place all ingredients into juicer. Enjoy!

name: Tilapia and Sweet Potatoes
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['tilapia - 6 fillet', 'pesto - 7 tbsp', 'almond flour - 7 tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ', 'sweet potato - 1 whole', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Spray baking dish with coconut oil.
3. Place tilapia in dish and top with pesto. Sprinkle with almond flour, sea salt, and pepper.
4. Bake for about 10 minutes.
5. For sweet potato: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
6. Wash, dry, and poke holes in the sweet potato.
7. Place sweet potato in an aluminum-foil-covered baking pan and bake for 45 minutes to one hour.
8. Once potato is done, cut in half and store 1/2 for later.
9. Slice sweet potato and sprinkle with cinnamon, sea salt, and black pepper.

name: Artichoke with Dipping Sauce
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['artichokes - 2', 'hard-boiled egg - 3', 'green onion, sliced - 2 tbsp', 'white vinegar - 2 tbsp', 'mustard - 1 tsp', 'olive oil - 1 tsp', 'water - 3 tbsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Place artichoke in a large, water-filled pot and place over medium heat.
2. Bring water to a boil and let it cook for 45 minutes.
3. While artichokes are cooking, separate yolks from egg whites, smash yolks with fork and finely chop the whites.
4. Place in a bowl and combine with the rest of the ingredients.
5. Mix well, add purified water, and mix again.
6. Once artichokes are done, let them cool and serve with dipping sauce.

name: Bison and Greens
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['bison, ground - 1 lb', 'shallots - 1', 'jalapeno pepper, diced - 2 whole', 'egg - 1 whole', 'garlic, minced - 3 clove', 'salt and pepper to taste -  ', 'salad greens - 1 cup', 'cherry tomatoes - ½ cup', 'walnuts, chopped - ½ cup', 'avocado - ¼', 'walnut oil - 1 tbsp', 'balsamic vinegar - 1 tbsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn oven to broil. Arrange rack so baking pan is close to heat.
2. Cover baking pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
3. Combine all ingredients and form into patties.
4. Place patties on the center of the baking pan and broil for 6-8 minutes. Flip and broil for another 6-8 minutes.
5. When both sides are golden brown, remove from oven.
6. For salad: Place all vegetables in a plate or salad bowl and mix. Top salad with walnuts, walnut oil, and balsamic vinegar.

name: Sweet Potato Hash With Egg
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['egg - 1 whole', 'sweet potato, shredded - ¼', 'onion powder - ⅛ tsp', 'garlic powder - ⅛ tsp', 'cayenne pepper - ⅛ tsp', 'salt and pepper to taste - ']
recipeInstructions:
1. Grease skillet with coconut spray and place on medium heat.
2. Add shredded sweet potato and cook for one minute.
3. Add spices and cook for another minute or two.
4. Once sweet potatoes start getting golden on the edges, add egg and cover with lid.
5. Let egg cook for about 3 minutes.
6. Serve!

name: Chicken and Broccoli
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
recipeIngredient: ['chicken breast - 6 piece', 'lemon pepper to taste - ', 'salt to taste - ', 'broccoli - 1 cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Turn oven to "broil" and arrange rack so baking pan is close to heat.
2. Cover baking pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
3. Season both sides of chicken breasts with sea salt and a generous amount of lemon pepper.
4. Place chicken breasts in the middle of the baking pan and broil for 12-13 minutes (or until bottom side is golden).
5. Flip and broil for another 12 minutes.
6. When both sides are golden, remove from oven and serve.
7. For broccoli: Bring 1/4 inch of water to boil in a large pan.
8. Add salt and broccoli florets.
9. Cover and steam until desired tenderness.
10. For added spice, add Sriracha hot sauce on the side for chicken and broccoli.

name: Chicken and Broccoli
description: The Paleo principles are simple: if you can grow it or kill it, eat it. If it's been processed, don't. Here are six meals for one full day of Paleo perfection!
