name: Killa Vanilla Cookies
description: Nothing says "happy holidays" quite like a batch of freshly baked cookies. There's a reason they're Santa's favorite, after all! Bring the holiday cheer without packing on the pounds, and leave Santa questioning his choice of chocolate chip.
recipeIngredient: ['butter, without salt - ⅓ cup', 'brown sugar - ¼ cup', 'egg - 2 whole', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'flour - ½ cup', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'Grenade Hydra 6, Killa Vanilla - 6 scoop', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'raw oats - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, combine butter and brown sugar.
2. Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla.
3. In a separate bowl, combine flour, protein powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Stir into the first mixture.
4. Mix in oats. (Optional: Add a splash of milk or almond milk if the batter is too dry.) Cover and chill dough for at least one hour.
5. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
6. Grease a cookie sheet with coconut oil, and roll dough balls to place on the sheet. Flatten each cookie with a large fork.
7. Bake 8-10 minutes in preheated oven. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring them onto a wire rack to cool completely.

name: Chocolate Banana Bread
description: There's not much that tops the pairing of chocolate and vanilla. Kiss your usual buttery poundcake goodbye and reach for this fruit-filled loaf instead!
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra Charge, Chocolate Charge - 3 scoop', 'banana - 1½', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'egg whites - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'raisins - 1 tbsp', 'strawberries, sliced - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together all of the ingredients.
2. Mix all ingredients together. (Depending on consistency, add in more egg whites for a thinner batter or more protein powder for added thickness).
3. Spray loaf pan with PAM. Pour in the mixture.
4. Bake 30-40 minutes, or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

name: Blueberry Oat Muffins
description: Not all muffins will leave you with an unflattering muffin top. These blueberry morsels will satisfy your sweet tooth without spiking your blood sugar levels and setting you up for a midday crash.
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra 6, Killa Vanilla - 2 scoop', 'blueberries - 2 oz', 'raw oats - 1 oz', 'coconut oil - 1¼ tsp', 'unsweetened almond milk - ¼ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix ingredients together and pour the mixture into a muffin tin.
2. Cook 10-12 minutes at 375 F.
3. Ta-da. They're ready! Eat them warm or, if you can resist temptation, let them cool down a bit.
4. Optional: Top with a mix of Greek yogurt and sugar-free pancake syrup drizzle. Amazing!

name: Chocolate Banana Bread
description: There's not much that tops the pairing of chocolate and vanilla. Kiss your usual buttery poundcake goodbye and reach for this fruit-filled loaf instead!
recipeIngredient: ['Grenade Hydra 6, Chocolate Charge - 3 scoop', 'banana - 1½', 'nonfat plain Greek yogurt - ½ cup', 'egg whites - ½ cup', 'blueberries - ¼ cup', 'raisins - 1 tbsp', 'strawberries, sliced - ¼ cup', 'natural peanut butter - 1 tbsp', 'rolled oats - ¼ cup', 'cinnamon -  to taste']
recipeInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 F.
2. Mix all ingredients together. (Depending on consistency, add in more egg whites for a thinner batter or more protein powder for added thickness).
3. Spray loaf pan with PAM. Pour in the mixture.
4. Bake 30-40 minutes, or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

name: Killa Vanilla Cookies
description: Nothing says "happy holidays" quite like a batch of freshly baked cookies. There's a reason they're Santa's favorite, after all! Bring the holiday cheer without packing on the pounds, and leave Santa questioning his choice of chocolate chip.
recipeIngredient: ['butter, without salt - ⅓ cup', 'brown sugar - ¼ cup', 'egg - 2 whole', 'vanilla extract - ½ tsp', 'flour - ½ cup', 'salt - ¼ tsp', 'cinnamon - ½ tsp', 'nutmeg - ½ tsp', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Killa Vanilla - 6 scoop', 'baking soda - ½ tsp', 'raw oats - ¾ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. In a medium bowl, combine butter and brown sugar.
2. Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla.
3. In a separate bowl, combine flour, protein powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Stir into the first mixture.
4. Mix in oats. (Optional: Add a splash of milk or almond milk if the batter is too dry.) Cover and chill dough for at least one hour.
5. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
6. Grease a cookie sheet with coconut oil, and roll dough balls to place on the sheet. Flatten each cookie with a large fork.
7. Bake 8-10 minutes in preheated oven. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring them onto a wire rack to cool completely.

name: Chocolate Protein Waffles
description: Oatmeal and eggs don't have to be your only healthy breakfast options. Get a protein punch—along with a healthy dose of carbs—with this tasty breakfast dish!
recipeIngredient: ['waffle mix - ⅓ cup', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Chocolate Charge - 1 scoop', 'egg - 1 whole', 'skim milk - ½ cup']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix together all of the ingredients.
2. Spray the waffle maker and add the batter.
3. Optional: Top with mixed berry cream cheese for a sweet addition!

name: Chocolate Charged Brownies
description: What's better than a piping hot plate of fresh-from-the-oven brownies? Make the gooey, delicious dessert fit into your meal plan with this recipe that cuts out the butter and brings the moisture with vitamin-rich sweet potatoes.
recipeIngredient: ['sweet potato - 2', 'Grenade Hydra Charge, Chocolate Charge - 5 scoop', 'egg - 3 whole', 'coconut oil - 2 oz', 'dark chocolate - 11 g', 'coconut flour - 3 tbsp', 'cocoa powder, unsweetened - 2 tbsp', 'baking powder - ¼ tsp', 'cinnamon - ¼ tsp']
recipeInstructions:
1. Microwave the sweet potatoes until they're cooked. Peel and mash.
2. Set the oven to 350 F.
3. Melt coconut oil with half of the chopped-up chocolate.
4. Add the coconut oil, melted chocolate, and whisked eggs to the mashed sweet potatoes. Mix together.
5. Add in the coconut flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and cinnamon. Use a blender or food processor to prevent lumps in the mixture.
6. Break up the rest of the chocolate and mix into the batter.
7. Pour the mixture into a baking dish and bake for 20 minutes on the middle rack. Leave to cool slightly, and then dig in!

name: Triple Berry Custard
description: For so many reasons soy is a great addition to every woman's diet. Soy can increase heart health, lower cancer risk, increase bone health, and alleviate countless menopausal symptoms. Soy protein contains less fat, no cholesterol and ten times as much fiber as animal protein. It is also much easier on your stomach making it a fantastic alternative to animal proteins and dairy products. All in all it seems soy is pure joy!
recipeIngredient: ['Soy protein isolate - 8 oz', 'Fage Nonfat Greek Yogurt - 1 cup', 'Blueberries, raw - ⅛ cup', 'strawberries - ⅛ cup', 'raspberries - ⅛ cup', 'mint leaves - 1']
recipeInstructions:
1. Mix yogurt and multi-purpose soy protein in a bowl.
2. Once all of the protein powder is mixed in and you've created a custard, add in the berries and mix.
3. Pour into a glass dessert dish and garnish with a mint leaf. Chill for 20 minutes and serve!
